{"_id":"07ByXWPoykuejm9e","name":"The Green Knight","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"OK3cqMatnCypt0tz","name":"The Green Knight - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the spirit of a knight sworn to protect the \nancient cults. My armor is old now, but the plants and flowers that have grown on it protect me. With my big ax, I can \nchop off a head with ease.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 192.","positive":"I am the spirit of a knight sworn to protect the \nancient cults. My armor is old now, but the plants and flowers that have grown on it protect me. With my big ax, I can \nchop off a head with ease.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644146,"modifiedTime":1781557644146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bOqrdY4uPIMVpk3D","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the spirit of a knight sworn to protect the \nancient cults. My armor is old now, but the plants and flowers that have grown on it protect me. With my big ax, I can \nchop off a head with ease. \nAgenda: Protect the altar and allow those who worship the \nold gods to have a place to worship. \nGift - The Just Punishment: The Green Knight starts \neach Scene with 3 Retaliation Tokens, each time he suffers \n1 Wound he can spend 1 Token to inflict 1 Wound on whoever hit him.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 192."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644146,"modifiedTime":1781557644146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-the-green-knight-192","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":192,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the spirit of a knight sworn to protect the \nancient cults. My armor is old now, but the plants and flowers that have grown on it protect me. With my big ax, I can \nchop off a head with ease. \nAgenda: Protect the altar and allow those who worship the \nold gods to have a place to worship. \nGift - The Just Punishment: The Green Knight starts \neach Scene with 3 Retaliation Tokens, each time he suffers \n1 Wound he can spend 1 Token to inflict 1 Wound on whoever hit him.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Protect the altar and allow those who worship the \nold gods to have a place to worship.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644146,"modifiedTime":1781557644146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"0aaWFM10EH7UzuWC","name":"Genevieve the Chemist","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"L5qlHU8eyb6MxDTl","name":"Genevieve the Chemist - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I escaped from a past full of witchcraft and deceit. \nI know how to summon spirits and talk with them.\n4 Marcel the Time-Waster</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","positive":"I escaped from a past full of witchcraft and deceit. \nI know how to summon spirits and talk with them.\n4 Marcel the Time-Waster","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"umfABiKbbWIEUP8X","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I escaped from a past full of witchcraft and deceit. \nI know how to summon spirits and talk with them.\n4 Marcel the Time-Waster</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-genevieve-the-chemist-123","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":123,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I escaped from a past full of witchcraft and deceit. \nI know how to summon spirits and talk with them.\n4 Marcel the Time-Waster</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"0dwdpRZI9Me3Wljl","name":"The Canine Tigers","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"5SUVPP90FXXlg7gs","name":"The Canine Tigers - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the village dogs, turned into monsters \nby the desire of one of the children. Once the tiger’s ferocity \ntakes over, we can no longer be controlled.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242.","positive":"We are the village dogs, turned into monsters \nby the desire of one of the children. Once the tiger’s ferocity \ntakes over, we can no longer be controlled.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"cQjORsQ2uA651AsW","name":"Gift - Fierce as a Tiger","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>When a Canine Tiger suffers \na Wound, it goes mad with rage and its Opposition Level \nrises to Hard 7. At the mercy of anger, the Tiger will attack \nthe closest target without distinguishing between allies and \nenemies.\nNorman Henkle \nThe Powerful Wizard Who \nMakes Wishes Come True</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"AkGap2Ft8NdfwTSs","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are the village dogs, turned into monsters \nby the desire of one of the children. Once the tiger’s ferocity \ntakes over, we can no longer be controlled.\nGift - Fierce as a Tiger: When a Canine Tiger suffers \na Wound, it goes mad with rage and its Opposition Level \nrises to Hard 7. At the mercy of anger, the Tiger will attack \nthe closest target without distinguishing between allies and \nenemies.\nNorman Henkle \nThe Powerful Wizard Who \nMakes Wishes Come True</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-the-canine-tigers-242","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":242,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are the village dogs, turned into monsters \nby the desire of one of the children. Once the tiger’s ferocity \ntakes over, we can no longer be controlled.\nGift - Fierce as a Tiger: When a Canine Tiger suffers \na Wound, it goes mad with rage and its Opposition Level \nrises to Hard 7. At the mercy of anger, the Tiger will attack \nthe closest target without distinguishing between allies and \nenemies.\nNorman Henkle \nThe Powerful Wizard Who \nMakes Wishes Come True</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"0sRUBUKdIfuEapLk","name":"Hanse","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"5Zrq5DSeaUWZGMkj","name":"Hanse - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 101.","positive":"I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1781557626419,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vxRdfKKXaT668tCt","name":"Gift - Mutant Maw","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>As long as they maintain their original appearance, a \nmutant Maw appears in every way as a common child. When they unleash their \npower, the body shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a \nlong line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a higher OL category \nfor every physical action they perform involving speed, strength, or ferocity. \nA mutant perceives the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, \nand for this reason, every attempt to hide from their sense of smell receives \n1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour flesh (human or animal), they \ncannot stop until they have finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw \ninflicts 1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound they suffered.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 101.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1781557626419,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9KT4vRJeIJaboTv6","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable. \nAgenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future for the Maw’s offspring. \nUnlike my sister Gréte, I have no regard for humans and, now that I spared my \nfather to make my sister happy, I just want to protect the stone that came from \nthe sky.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their original appearance, a \nmutant Maw appears in every way as a common child. When they unleash their \npower, the body shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a \nlong line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a higher OL category \nfor every physical action they perform involving speed, strength, or ferocity. \nA mutant perceives the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, \nand for this reason, every attempt to hide from their sense of smell receives \n1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour flesh (human or animal), they \ncannot stop until they have finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw \ninflicts 1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound they suffered.\nGift – First Maw: As the firstborn among the Maws, Hanse has learned \nto manipulate the power that he harbors in his body. During a Scene, \nHanse may self-inflict 1 Wound to benefit from one of the following effects: \n1. Superhuman Strength , if he inflicts 1 Wound with an action and \ndoes not devour the target, Hanse can throw it 15 feet away. The target \nwill fall to the ground and suffer 1 additional Wound if they impact an \nobstacle. Hanse can use his strength to throw one enemy into another, in \nwhich case the target can try to dodge the attack with a Defense Check. \n2. Superhuman Speed , Hanse can make an incredible leap of over 30 \nfeet. He does not need any preparation, and he can take another subject with \nhim while moving. 3. Power of the Stone that Came from the Sky , \nHanse can tap into the latent power in his body. Once per Scene, all human \nsubjects in his presence lose 2 Soma or alternatively can resist by taking 1 \nWound. Suffering the last Wound for this effect does not cause death, but a \nloss of consciousness.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 101."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1781557626419,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-hanse-101","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":101,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable. \nAgenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future for the Maw’s offspring. \nUnlike my sister Gréte, I have no regard for humans and, now that I spared my \nfather to make my sister happy, I just want to protect the stone that came from \nthe sky.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their original appearance, a \nmutant Maw appears in every way as a common child. When they unleash their \npower, the body shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a \nlong line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a higher OL category \nfor every physical action they perform involving speed, strength, or ferocity. \nA mutant perceives the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, \nand for this reason, every attempt to hide from their sense of smell receives \n1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour flesh (human or animal), they \ncannot stop until they have finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw \ninflicts 1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound they suffered.\nGift – First Maw: As the firstborn among the Maws, Hanse has learned \nto manipulate the power that he harbors in his body. During a Scene, \nHanse may self-inflict 1 Wound to benefit from one of the following effects: \n1. Superhuman Strength , if he inflicts 1 Wound with an action and \ndoes not devour the target, Hanse can throw it 15 feet away. The target \nwill fall to the ground and suffer 1 additional Wound if they impact an \nobstacle. Hanse can use his strength to throw one enemy into another, in \nwhich case the target can try to dodge the attack with a Defense Check. \n2. Superhuman Speed , Hanse can make an incredible leap of over 30 \nfeet. He does not need any preparation, and he can take another subject with \nhim while moving. 3. Power of the Stone that Came from the Sky , \nHanse can tap into the latent power in his body. Once per Scene, all human \nsubjects in his presence lose 2 Soma or alternatively can resist by taking 1 \nWound. Suffering the last Wound for this effect does not cause death, but a \nloss of consciousness.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future for the Maw’s offspring. \nUnlike my sister Gréte, I have no regard for humans and, now that I spared my \nfather to make my sister happy, I just want to protect the stone that came from \nthe sky.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626419,"modifiedTime":1781557626419,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1Aw1B8926eTW8q99","name":"Robbers","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"1Lfx2JClg7Kv6amF","name":"Robbers - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are veteran soldiers and have seen the horrors of war. We do not shy away from danger and have no \nqualms about committing acts of cruelty. \nThe Golden Plate Tavern\nDescriptor: The finest and most famous tavern in Heidelberg: Brigit’s cuisine is of the highest standard, but only the \nvery rich can afford it.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 140.","positive":"We are veteran soldiers and have seen the horrors of war. We do not shy away from danger and have no \nqualms about committing acts of cruelty. \nThe Golden Plate Tavern\nDescriptor: The finest and most famous tavern in Heidelberg: Brigit’s cuisine is of the highest standard, but only the \nvery rich can afford it.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641635,"modifiedTime":1781557641635,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sbMXEQLWPL5QlCQG","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are veteran soldiers and have seen the horrors of war. We do not shy away from danger and have no \nqualms about committing acts of cruelty. \nThe Golden Plate Tavern\nDescriptor: The finest and most famous tavern in Heidelberg: Brigit’s cuisine is of the highest standard, but only the \nvery rich can afford it.\nInformation: There are no rooms to sleep in at the Tavern, which is best known for the haute cuisine of Chef Brigit. Nobles and rich men come from all over Europe to taste \nthe food of the Golden Plate. Brigit became accustomed to \nBastian’s presence, always showering her with compliments on her cooking. At first, Bastian was a good customer, \nbut soon he had no money to pay for the meals, and Brigit \ngave him credit until she realized that the soldier was a lost \ncause. If asked about Bastian, Brigit will say that he is a good-tempered man who tries to live far beyond his means. \nWhen he is not eating at the Golden Plate, Bastian is often \nat the Drunken Hussar’s Gambling House, where he gambles and tries to accumulate some money.\nIf Bastian is present: He will sit at the table and beg \nBrigit to serve him one of her fantastic dishes. As soon as \nhe sees the Hunters, he will try to escape by sneaking into \nthe kitchens.\nIf the Black Cat is present: The Hunters will see her \nthrough the half-open door into the kitchen as she tries to \nknock down an old ladle hanging on the wall with her paw. \nThe Cat is unsuccessful, as someone always intervenes to \nchase it away. Brigit will complain that the animal seems \nto be obsessed with the old ladle given to her by the elderly \nBritta. \nFirst Reset: If this is the first time he encounters the \nHunters in this Place, Bastian will try to escape. However, \nif the Hunters have already met him here, Bastian will not \nappear again.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 140."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641635,"modifiedTime":1781557641635,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-robbers-140","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":140,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are veteran soldiers and have seen the horrors of war. We do not shy away from danger and have no \nqualms about committing acts of cruelty. \nThe Golden Plate Tavern\nDescriptor: The finest and most famous tavern in Heidelberg: Brigit’s cuisine is of the highest standard, but only the \nvery rich can afford it.\nInformation: There are no rooms to sleep in at the Tavern, which is best known for the haute cuisine of Chef Brigit. Nobles and rich men come from all over Europe to taste \nthe food of the Golden Plate. Brigit became accustomed to \nBastian’s presence, always showering her with compliments on her cooking. At first, Bastian was a good customer, \nbut soon he had no money to pay for the meals, and Brigit \ngave him credit until she realized that the soldier was a lost \ncause. If asked about Bastian, Brigit will say that he is a good-tempered man who tries to live far beyond his means. \nWhen he is not eating at the Golden Plate, Bastian is often \nat the Drunken Hussar’s Gambling House, where he gambles and tries to accumulate some money.\nIf Bastian is present: He will sit at the table and beg \nBrigit to serve him one of her fantastic dishes. As soon as \nhe sees the Hunters, he will try to escape by sneaking into \nthe kitchens.\nIf the Black Cat is present: The Hunters will see her \nthrough the half-open door into the kitchen as she tries to \nknock down an old ladle hanging on the wall with her paw. \nThe Cat is unsuccessful, as someone always intervenes to \nchase it away. Brigit will complain that the animal seems \nto be obsessed with the old ladle given to her by the elderly \nBritta. \nFirst Reset: If this is the first time he encounters the \nHunters in this Place, Bastian will try to escape. However, \nif the Hunters have already met him here, Bastian will not \nappear again.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641635,"modifiedTime":1781557641635,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1LU78xZ9wRJAgnvb","name":"Crazed Maws","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"uZrSfy4LZCljC0sS","name":"Crazed Maws - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A mad abomination whose form constantly \nshifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 102.","positive":"A mad abomination whose form constantly \nshifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626450,"modifiedTime":1781557626450,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9ExnJm3hevBKySYl","name":"Gift - Mutant Abomination","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A Crazed Maw does not \nfeel any pain. For this reason the Wounds it suffers have \nno narrative effect but are only a counter to understand \nwhen the abomination will crumble into a thousand pieces. \nTentacles and arms are constantly born from the body of \na Crazed Maw, and as a result it can act 2 times during \nan Exchange. With one of its actions, a Crazed Maw can \nslam its huge mass to the ground to create a strong tremor. \nAll targets in the immediate vicinity must pass a Defense \nCheck to avoid falling to the ground.\nThreat – The Stone that Came from \nthe Sky</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 102.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626450,"modifiedTime":1781557626450,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YWPKluzEQTADJDV7","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: A mad abomination whose form constantly \nshifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour. \nAgenda: Eat every living thing, except other Maws.\nGift – Mutant Abomination: A Crazed Maw does not \nfeel any pain. For this reason the Wounds it suffers have \nno narrative effect but are only a counter to understand \nwhen the abomination will crumble into a thousand pieces. \nTentacles and arms are constantly born from the body of \na Crazed Maw, and as a result it can act 2 times during \nan Exchange. With one of its actions, a Crazed Maw can \nslam its huge mass to the ground to create a strong tremor. \nAll targets in the immediate vicinity must pass a Defense \nCheck to avoid falling to the ground.\nThreat – The Stone that Came from \nthe Sky\nDescriptor: An alien stone, the size of a fist, that thrums \nwith energy. \nGift – Alien Stone: All the powers of the Maws derive \nfrom the stone. With its destruction, the mutations will \ndeteriorate, causing the death of all mutants except Hanse \nand Gréte. The stone has 6 Wounds and has no OL, because \nit cannot interact directly or defend itself. For each Wound \nsuffered, a spark of the power comes out, affecting the one \nwho inflicted the blow. Whoever suffers this effect can \ndecide between losing 2 Soma or suffering 1 Wound. If the \nstone is destroyed or stolen, Hanse will be able to unleash \nall the latent power in him and, by joining with Gréte, give \nlife to the Great Maw.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 102."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626450,"modifiedTime":1781557626450,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-crazed-maws-102","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":102,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: A mad abomination whose form constantly \nshifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour. \nAgenda: Eat every living thing, except other Maws.\nGift – Mutant Abomination: A Crazed Maw does not \nfeel any pain. For this reason the Wounds it suffers have \nno narrative effect but are only a counter to understand \nwhen the abomination will crumble into a thousand pieces. \nTentacles and arms are constantly born from the body of \na Crazed Maw, and as a result it can act 2 times during \nan Exchange. With one of its actions, a Crazed Maw can \nslam its huge mass to the ground to create a strong tremor. \nAll targets in the immediate vicinity must pass a Defense \nCheck to avoid falling to the ground.\nThreat – The Stone that Came from \nthe Sky\nDescriptor: An alien stone, the size of a fist, that thrums \nwith energy. \nGift – Alien Stone: All the powers of the Maws derive \nfrom the stone. With its destruction, the mutations will \ndeteriorate, causing the death of all mutants except Hanse \nand Gréte. The stone has 6 Wounds and has no OL, because \nit cannot interact directly or defend itself. For each Wound \nsuffered, a spark of the power comes out, affecting the one \nwho inflicted the blow. Whoever suffers this effect can \ndecide between losing 2 Soma or suffering 1 Wound. If the \nstone is destroyed or stolen, Hanse will be able to unleash \nall the latent power in him and, by joining with Gréte, give \nlife to the Great Maw.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Eat every living thing, except other Maws.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626450,"modifiedTime":1781557626450,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1fO3397r07ryycl9","name":"The Magic Lake Portal","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"hCBX236xjFaC5HOj","name":"The Magic Lake Portal - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A magical portal leading close to Lady Storm’s \ncastle. Only those who know the magic formula can plunge \ninto the lake’s waters and pass through.\nEpilogue\nOnce they plunge into the waters of the lake, the Hunters \nare transported to the home of Sinikka the Finland Woman, a few miles from Lady Storm’s castle. \nStoryteller’s Note: The Hunters’ journey continues with \nPART THREE - The Winter Castle. \nScenario Events\nThere are 3 Events in this Scenario, though the Storyteller \nshould feel free to create new ones in response to the Hunter’s actions.\nIf one of the Black Feathers or Reinsdyr can still \nact after a fight: they will have anticipated the Hunters \nand alerted Pernille to the danger. \nIf no one has warned Pernille of the arrival of the \nHunters: the witch will act as usual and tell the Hunters that to get to Gerda and Kay’s castle, they must pass \nthrough a secret passage that only she knows. However, this \npassage is very expensive, and Pernille will ask the Hunters \nfor a large sum of money.\nIf Miss Snow and Lady Storm are among the \nHunters: Pernille will take refuge in the house and try to \nintimidate the Hunters into leaving. The old witch is afraid \nthat Lady Storm will punish her for helping Gerda and Kay.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 218.","positive":"A magical portal leading close to Lady Storm’s \ncastle. Only those who know the magic formula can plunge \ninto the lake’s waters and pass through.\nEpilogue\nOnce they plunge into the waters of the lake, the Hunters \nare transported to the home of Sinikka the Finland Woman, a few miles from Lady Storm’s castle. \nStoryteller’s Note: The Hunters’ journey continues with \nPART THREE - The Winter Castle. \nScenario Events\nThere are 3 Events in this Scenario, though the Storyteller \nshould feel free to create new ones in response to the Hunter’s actions.\nIf one of the Black Feathers or Reinsdyr can still \nact after a fight: they will have anticipated the Hunters \nand alerted Pernille to the danger. \nIf no one has warned Pernille of the arrival of the \nHunters: the witch will act as usual and tell the Hunters that to get to Gerda and Kay’s castle, they must pass \nthrough a secret passage that only she knows. However, this \npassage is very expensive, and Pernille will ask the Hunters \nfor a large sum of money.\nIf Miss Snow and Lady Storm are among the \nHunters: Pernille will take refuge in the house and try to \nintimidate the Hunters into leaving. The old witch is afraid \nthat Lady Storm will punish her for helping Gerda and Kay.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645699,"modifiedTime":1781557645699,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"P4eY9hMSgLkfxR6N","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A magical portal leading close to Lady Storm’s \ncastle. Only those who know the magic formula can plunge \ninto the lake’s waters and pass through.\nEpilogue\nOnce they plunge into the waters of the lake, the Hunters \nare transported to the home of Sinikka the Finland Woman, a few miles from Lady Storm’s castle. \nStoryteller’s Note: The Hunters’ journey continues with \nPART THREE - The Winter Castle. \nScenario Events\nThere are 3 Events in this Scenario, though the Storyteller \nshould feel free to create new ones in response to the Hunter’s actions.\nIf one of the Black Feathers or Reinsdyr can still \nact after a fight: they will have anticipated the Hunters \nand alerted Pernille to the danger. \nIf no one has warned Pernille of the arrival of the \nHunters: the witch will act as usual and tell the Hunters that to get to Gerda and Kay’s castle, they must pass \nthrough a secret passage that only she knows. However, this \npassage is very expensive, and Pernille will ask the Hunters \nfor a large sum of money.\nIf Miss Snow and Lady Storm are among the \nHunters: Pernille will take refuge in the house and try to \nintimidate the Hunters into leaving. The old witch is afraid \nthat Lady Storm will punish her for helping Gerda and Kay.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 218."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645699,"modifiedTime":1781557645699,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-the-magic-lake-portal-218","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":218,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A magical portal leading close to Lady Storm’s \ncastle. Only those who know the magic formula can plunge \ninto the lake’s waters and pass through.\nEpilogue\nOnce they plunge into the waters of the lake, the Hunters \nare transported to the home of Sinikka the Finland Woman, a few miles from Lady Storm’s castle. \nStoryteller’s Note: The Hunters’ journey continues with \nPART THREE - The Winter Castle. \nScenario Events\nThere are 3 Events in this Scenario, though the Storyteller \nshould feel free to create new ones in response to the Hunter’s actions.\nIf one of the Black Feathers or Reinsdyr can still \nact after a fight: they will have anticipated the Hunters \nand alerted Pernille to the danger. \nIf no one has warned Pernille of the arrival of the \nHunters: the witch will act as usual and tell the Hunters that to get to Gerda and Kay’s castle, they must pass \nthrough a secret passage that only she knows. However, this \npassage is very expensive, and Pernille will ask the Hunters \nfor a large sum of money.\nIf Miss Snow and Lady Storm are among the \nHunters: Pernille will take refuge in the house and try to \nintimidate the Hunters into leaving. The old witch is afraid \nthat Lady Storm will punish her for helping Gerda and Kay.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645699,"modifiedTime":1781557645699,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1tB1Rszsp13XIDSK","name":"Alizée the Fugitive","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Rp27krF7r8o0P5jM","name":"Alizée the Fugitive - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out \nof love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability \nsometimes scares me.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 152.","positive":"I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out \nof love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability \nsometimes scares me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1KScU5RI2aTItaeI","name":"Gift - Spiritualist","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Alizée can see and communicate with \nspirits. If anyone has been in contact with spirits in the past \ntwenty-four hours, Alizée will sense the remaining spirit \nenergy. With each use of this Gift, the young woman can \nobtain a single piece of information about the spirit aura she \nhas perceived. The Spiritualist Gift can also be used to remove \na Grudge Token from the Gift Mass of Restless Spirits.\nThe Underground Pit</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 152.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XSTtKBX9CZCplzjz","name":"Gift - Mass of Restless Spirits","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The pit accumulates \nspiritual energy thanks to the passage of the comet Morituris. \nAt the beginning of each Scene, there are 2 Grudge Tokens \nin the pit. An NPC with the Gift Spirit, Alizée with the Gift \nSpiritualist, or a Hunter with a Descriptor associated with \nmagic or spirits, can use their action to add or remove 1 \nToken from the mass. If at midnight on December 31st there \nare 3 Tokens in the pit, all the accumulated energy will cause \na powerful explosion capable of wiping out half of Paris. \nThe passage of the comet will add 1 Token at the stroke of \nmidnight. There can never be more than 4 Grudge Tokens on \nthis Gift.\nThreat - Grudge of the Dead</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 152.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YZpCxl2kj1exRH5e","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out \nof love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability \nsometimes scares me.\nAgenda: Escape with Lorenzo to a place where we don’t need \nto fear the Church’s punishment.\nGift - Spiritualist: Alizée can see and communicate with \nspirits. If anyone has been in contact with spirits in the past \ntwenty-four hours, Alizée will sense the remaining spirit \nenergy. With each use of this Gift, the young woman can \nobtain a single piece of information about the spirit aura she \nhas perceived. The Spiritualist Gift can also be used to remove \na Grudge Token from the Gift Mass of Restless Spirits.\nThe Underground Pit\nDescriptor: A huge pit where the corpses of all those who \ncannot afford a burial are thrown. Crowds of restless spirits \nthrong among the inert bodies, invisible to mundane eyes.\nGift - Mass of Restless Spirits: The pit accumulates \nspiritual energy thanks to the passage of the comet Morituris. \nAt the beginning of each Scene, there are 2 Grudge Tokens \nin the pit. An NPC with the Gift Spirit, Alizée with the Gift \nSpiritualist, or a Hunter with a Descriptor associated with \nmagic or spirits, can use their action to add or remove 1 \nToken from the mass. If at midnight on December 31st there \nare 3 Tokens in the pit, all the accumulated energy will cause \na powerful explosion capable of wiping out half of Paris. \nThe passage of the comet will add 1 Token at the stroke of \nmidnight. There can never be more than 4 Grudge Tokens on \nthis Gift.\nThreat - Grudge of the Dead\nDescriptor: We are the spirits of those who are dead and \nforgotten by all. We hate the living and their life energy, and we \nattack anyone who dares to approach the underground pit.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 152."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-aliz-e-the-fugitive-152","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":152,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out \nof love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability \nsometimes scares me.\nAgenda: Escape with Lorenzo to a place where we don’t need \nto fear the Church’s punishment.\nGift - Spiritualist: Alizée can see and communicate with \nspirits. If anyone has been in contact with spirits in the past \ntwenty-four hours, Alizée will sense the remaining spirit \nenergy. With each use of this Gift, the young woman can \nobtain a single piece of information about the spirit aura she \nhas perceived. The Spiritualist Gift can also be used to remove \na Grudge Token from the Gift Mass of Restless Spirits.\nThe Underground Pit\nDescriptor: A huge pit where the corpses of all those who \ncannot afford a burial are thrown. Crowds of restless spirits \nthrong among the inert bodies, invisible to mundane eyes.\nGift - Mass of Restless Spirits: The pit accumulates \nspiritual energy thanks to the passage of the comet Morituris. \nAt the beginning of each Scene, there are 2 Grudge Tokens \nin the pit. An NPC with the Gift Spirit, Alizée with the Gift \nSpiritualist, or a Hunter with a Descriptor associated with \nmagic or spirits, can use their action to add or remove 1 \nToken from the mass. If at midnight on December 31st there \nare 3 Tokens in the pit, all the accumulated energy will cause \na powerful explosion capable of wiping out half of Paris. \nThe passage of the comet will add 1 Token at the stroke of \nmidnight. There can never be more than 4 Grudge Tokens on \nthis Gift.\nThreat - Grudge of the Dead\nDescriptor: We are the spirits of those who are dead and \nforgotten by all. We hate the living and their life energy, and we \nattack anyone who dares to approach the underground pit.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Escape with Lorenzo to a place where we don’t need \nto fear the Church’s punishment.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"2AObYqf2o4217R19","name":"The White Rabbit","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"CC4WlZOwSYiHnSes","name":"The White Rabbit - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I’m a little white rabbit wandering around the \nCure Rooms and I have a message holder tied around my neck. \nI fear those I do not know.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 173.","positive":"I’m a little white rabbit wandering around the \nCure Rooms and I have a message holder tied around my neck. \nI fear those I do not know.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622907,"modifiedTime":1781557622907,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wiQcshOaXKV3qrGw","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: I’m a little white rabbit wandering around the \nCure Rooms and I have a message holder tied around my neck. \nI fear those I do not know.\nGift - Messenger: By capturing a White Rabbit it is \npossible to take the message it carries. Roll a die.\n1-2: It’s not always convenient to knock on a door with your \nhand. \n3-4: Knocking on a door is the bare minimum to be \nexpected of a respectable person. \n5-6: When you arrive at a door, it is polite to ask if anyone \nis home.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 173."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622907,"modifiedTime":1781557622907,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-the-white-rabbit-173","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":173,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: I’m a little white rabbit wandering around the \nCure Rooms and I have a message holder tied around my neck. \nI fear those I do not know.\nGift - Messenger: By capturing a White Rabbit it is \npossible to take the message it carries. Roll a die.\n1-2: It’s not always convenient to knock on a door with your \nhand. \n3-4: Knocking on a door is the bare minimum to be \nexpected of a respectable person. \n5-6: When you arrive at a door, it is polite to ask if anyone \nis home.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622907,"modifiedTime":1781557622907,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"2OpJ1kDZBZGhmUnT","name":"Christian","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"qCkDaU4aW3wdJzCz","name":"Christian - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a former soldier, called the Relentless \nby all because of my cold determination. I act without any \nqualms when it comes to executing an order.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","positive":"I am a former soldier, called the Relentless \nby all because of my cold determination. I act without any \nqualms when it comes to executing an order.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bi5GTIJgKP32HkgS","name":"Gift - The Relentless","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>When he is carrying out an order, \nChristian is immune to any effect that affects his behavior, \nsuch as fear or charm. The soldier increases his Opposition \nLevel by 1 when he tries to eliminate an obstacle that stands \nbetween him and the subject of an order he must carry out.\nEnar</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PVoxrgSMaAt3I78v","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a former soldier, called the Relentless \nby all because of my cold determination. I act without any \nqualms when it comes to executing an order.\nAgenda: Help Andersen in memory of the old days and a \nmilitary life I can’t forget / Eliminate Enar to prove I am the \nbetter man.\nGift - The Relentless: When he is carrying out an order, \nChristian is immune to any effect that affects his behavior, \nsuch as fear or charm. The soldier increases his Opposition \nLevel by 1 when he tries to eliminate an obstacle that stands \nbetween him and the subject of an order he must carry out.\nEnar</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-christian-162","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":162,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a former soldier, called the Relentless \nby all because of my cold determination. I act without any \nqualms when it comes to executing an order.\nAgenda: Help Andersen in memory of the old days and a \nmilitary life I can’t forget / Eliminate Enar to prove I am the \nbetter man.\nGift - The Relentless: When he is carrying out an order, \nChristian is immune to any effect that affects his behavior, \nsuch as fear or charm. The soldier increases his Opposition \nLevel by 1 when he tries to eliminate an obstacle that stands \nbetween him and the subject of an order he must carry out.\nEnar</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Help Andersen in memory of the old days and a \nmilitary life I can’t forget / Eliminate Enar to prove I am the \nbetter man.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"2QCyVC62tCz7fvT5","name":"Ivory Seeking Pirates","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"jSRHT04V3sVhJnyM","name":"Ivory Seeking Pirates - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are ruthless pirates who win every battle \nwith our sabers and guns.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 158.","positive":"We are ruthless pirates who win every battle \nwith our sabers and guns.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642442,"modifiedTime":1781557642442,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TQXMB9Fk3Xf2jJbb","name":"Gift - Pirate Crew","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A Pirate increases their OL by 1 when \nthe Captain is present. \nCaptain of the Ivory Seeking \nPirates</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 158.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642442,"modifiedTime":1781557642442,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bD5CvMOeWobnjgsu","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are ruthless pirates who win every battle \nwith our sabers and guns. \nAgenda: Obey the captain’s orders. \nGift - Pirate Crew: A Pirate increases their OL by 1 when \nthe Captain is present. \nCaptain of the Ivory Seeking \nPirates</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 158."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642442,"modifiedTime":1781557642442,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-ivory-seeking-pirates-158","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":158,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are ruthless pirates who win every battle \nwith our sabers and guns. \nAgenda: Obey the captain’s orders. \nGift - Pirate Crew: A Pirate increases their OL by 1 when \nthe Captain is present. \nCaptain of the Ivory Seeking \nPirates</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Obey the captain’s orders.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642458,"modifiedTime":1781557642458,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"2Yvmk1D5MZwrxQSu","name":"Lorenzo Scannapecore the Plague Doctor","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"zcrAPBmOi0RKAwTB","name":"Lorenzo Scannapecore the Plague Doctor - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to \ndetail is obsessive.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 152.","positive":"I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to \ndetail is obsessive.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dwcKQFxklR0Ay3t6","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to \ndetail is obsessive.\nAgenda: Pretend to work in the cemetery to protect Alizée \nfrom prying eyes.\nAlizée the Fugitive</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 152."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-lorenzo-scannapecore-the-plague-doctor-152","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":152,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to \ndetail is obsessive.\nAgenda: Pretend to work in the cemetery to protect Alizée \nfrom prying eyes.\nAlizée the Fugitive</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Pretend to work in the cemetery to protect Alizée \nfrom prying eyes.\nAlizée the Fugitive","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622342,"modifiedTime":1781557622342,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"2z7dF091hEgGkk6r","name":"Hedge Labyrinth","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"y0YerOpefrmKzxrI","name":"Hedge Labyrinth - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that \nextends throughout the estate garden.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 129.","positive":"A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that \nextends throughout the estate garden.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632122,"modifiedTime":1781557632122,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"r9OL5faa5reaFer6","name":"Gift - Secret Passage","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Bellina and Dionysus know a \nseries of secret passages to avoid wasting time in the maze. \nAnyone else might need several hours to negotiate it. \nBellina Cantalupo known as Bella</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 129.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632122,"modifiedTime":1781557632122,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"b2fWt81kExPFvjVD","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that \nextends throughout the estate garden. \nGift – Secret Passage: Bellina and Dionysus know a \nseries of secret passages to avoid wasting time in the maze. \nAnyone else might need several hours to negotiate it. \nBellina Cantalupo known as Bella</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 129."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632122,"modifiedTime":1781557632122,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-hedge-labyrinth-129","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":129,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that \nextends throughout the estate garden. \nGift – Secret Passage: Bellina and Dionysus know a \nseries of secret passages to avoid wasting time in the maze. \nAnyone else might need several hours to negotiate it. \nBellina Cantalupo known as Bella</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632122,"modifiedTime":1781557632122,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"30GSHeK0NSJ2q03y","name":"Sea Fairy","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"FCvFlvtH96ICKgxs","name":"Sea Fairy - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a fairy of the sea and my magic allows me to \nperform true miracles. My entire existence is tied to the sea and \nleaving it would destroy me.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164.","positive":"I am a fairy of the sea and my magic allows me to \nperform true miracles. My entire existence is tied to the sea and \nleaving it would destroy me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PvlBAOQFdDSH9pNx","name":"Gift - Sea Magic","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The Sea Fairy can always use one of \nthe following effects. 1. Water of Life: A target recovers 1 \nWound and, if they have been dead for no more than a day, \nthey can even come back to life. 2. The Fury of the Sea: \nThe water of the sea engulfs everything, sweeping away all \nthreats. Those who are within 30 feet must pass a Defense</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"kURlJmi9ZuaU9mo7","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fairy of the sea and my magic allows me to \nperform true miracles. My entire existence is tied to the sea and \nleaving it would destroy me.\nAgenda: I am sad because Enar has forsaken the love that kept \nhim alive in favor of blind hatred. I would like to do something \nfor him, but I cannot go to the mainland to stop his fury or find \nhis beloved.\nSpecial Agenda (Marina the Sea Explorer): I have \nheard of Marina and know her reputation. She uses her powers \nonly to enrich herself at the expense of others. I will never agree \nto help her unless she first shows me that she is also capable of \ngood deeds.\nGift – Sea Magic: The Sea Fairy can always use one of \nthe following effects. 1. Water of Life: A target recovers 1 \nWound and, if they have been dead for no more than a day, \nthey can even come back to life. 2. The Fury of the Sea: \nThe water of the sea engulfs everything, sweeping away all \nthreats. Those who are within 30 feet must pass a Defense</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-sea-fairy-164","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":164,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fairy of the sea and my magic allows me to \nperform true miracles. My entire existence is tied to the sea and \nleaving it would destroy me.\nAgenda: I am sad because Enar has forsaken the love that kept \nhim alive in favor of blind hatred. I would like to do something \nfor him, but I cannot go to the mainland to stop his fury or find \nhis beloved.\nSpecial Agenda (Marina the Sea Explorer): I have \nheard of Marina and know her reputation. She uses her powers \nonly to enrich herself at the expense of others. I will never agree \nto help her unless she first shows me that she is also capable of \ngood deeds.\nGift – Sea Magic: The Sea Fairy can always use one of \nthe following effects. 1. Water of Life: A target recovers 1 \nWound and, if they have been dead for no more than a day, \nthey can even come back to life. 2. The Fury of the Sea: \nThe water of the sea engulfs everything, sweeping away all \nthreats. Those who are within 30 feet must pass a Defense</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I am sad because Enar has forsaken the love that kept \nhim alive in favor of blind hatred. I would like to do something \nfor him, but I cannot go to the mainland to stop his fury or find \nhis beloved.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"36Z1BHsZ8LEnDMgf","name":"Bruna the Poor Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"t9w3bXeo9QFInlnx","name":"Bruna the Poor Witch - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a poor old woman to whom life has \noffered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, \nbut I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending \nup at the stake.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","positive":"I am a poor old woman to whom life has \noffered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, \nbut I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending \nup at the stake.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7E5eYV8sCaqOXzYE","name":"Gift - Latent Witch","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Bruna has magic abilities, but \nshe never studied and uses her powers unconsciously. If \nthreatened, Bruna will activate her power and the objects \nin the immediate vicinity will begin to move and then fall \nupon everyone. Acting in the area affected by this power \nconfers 2 Penalties on each Check due to the uncontrolled \nmagic manifestations. If Bruna is killed, she will curse her \nkiller who, for the rest of the Scenario, will receive 1 Penalty \nat each Defense Check. A practitioner of magic or someone \nwho can communicate with spirits can soothe Bruna’s soul \nto undo the curse, but a Position Check will be required</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PcrTASuBExNdGFVp","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a poor old woman to whom life has \noffered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, \nbut I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending \nup at the stake.\nAgenda: To live in peace, seeking acceptance from the \ninhabitants of Lohr.\nGift – Latent Witch: Bruna has magic abilities, but \nshe never studied and uses her powers unconsciously. If \nthreatened, Bruna will activate her power and the objects \nin the immediate vicinity will begin to move and then fall \nupon everyone. Acting in the area affected by this power \nconfers 2 Penalties on each Check due to the uncontrolled \nmagic manifestations. If Bruna is killed, she will curse her \nkiller who, for the rest of the Scenario, will receive 1 Penalty \nat each Defense Check. A practitioner of magic or someone \nwho can communicate with spirits can soothe Bruna’s soul \nto undo the curse, but a Position Check will be required</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-bruna-the-poor-witch-113","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":113,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a poor old woman to whom life has \noffered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, \nbut I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending \nup at the stake.\nAgenda: To live in peace, seeking acceptance from the \ninhabitants of Lohr.\nGift – Latent Witch: Bruna has magic abilities, but \nshe never studied and uses her powers unconsciously. If \nthreatened, Bruna will activate her power and the objects \nin the immediate vicinity will begin to move and then fall \nupon everyone. Acting in the area affected by this power \nconfers 2 Penalties on each Check due to the uncontrolled \nmagic manifestations. If Bruna is killed, she will curse her \nkiller who, for the rest of the Scenario, will receive 1 Penalty \nat each Defense Check. A practitioner of magic or someone \nwho can communicate with spirits can soothe Bruna’s soul \nto undo the curse, but a Position Check will be required</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To live in peace, seeking acceptance from the \ninhabitants of Lohr.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"3SLSu4vZsbehoJ9o","name":"3: Mikko","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"I24ejMCYjQbZ9WvA","name":"3: Mikko - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an accountant who is in \ncharge of the gold trade between the village \nand the merchants.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 119.","positive":"I am an accountant who is in \ncharge of the gold trade between the village \nand the merchants.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640550,"modifiedTime":1781557640550,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jHfoaf12lgfifrkx","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 \nWound)\nDescriptor: I am an accountant who is in \ncharge of the gold trade between the village \nand the merchants. \nAgenda: Make the village prosperous and \nearn good money. \nInformation: Mikko is the newest addition \nto the group of elders and was not present during the first \nnight of the pledge. He does not believe in rumors and sees \nthe “kidnapped” people simply as workers who choose to \nstay in the comfort of Nikola’s warm and cozy mansion. \nHowever, Mikko noticed that some of the traders missed \nthe appointment to load the gold and he has not heard \nfrom them. The old man has noted everything in his records, where it can be seen that the missed appointments \nand disappearances of the merchants occur on a regular basis. However, the old accountant is extremely jealous of his \nwork and will not share the records with anyone. \n4: Katri</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 119."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640550,"modifiedTime":1781557640550,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-3-mikko-119","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":119,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 \nWound)\nDescriptor: I am an accountant who is in \ncharge of the gold trade between the village \nand the merchants. \nAgenda: Make the village prosperous and \nearn good money. \nInformation: Mikko is the newest addition \nto the group of elders and was not present during the first \nnight of the pledge. He does not believe in rumors and sees \nthe “kidnapped” people simply as workers who choose to \nstay in the comfort of Nikola’s warm and cozy mansion. \nHowever, Mikko noticed that some of the traders missed \nthe appointment to load the gold and he has not heard \nfrom them. The old man has noted everything in his records, where it can be seen that the missed appointments \nand disappearances of the merchants occur on a regular basis. However, the old accountant is extremely jealous of his \nwork and will not share the records with anyone. \n4: Katri</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Make the village prosperous and \nearn good money.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640550,"modifiedTime":1781557640550,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"3XANKF9oPVfgjyqp","name":"Bella’s Servants","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"qQkr7ufeWttJa745","name":"Bella’s Servants - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are young people in the service of Bella \nand we are trained to defend the House \nof Roses.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 127.","positive":"We are young people in the service of Bella \nand we are trained to defend the House \nof Roses.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Z3zdJYr4H7gsub4l","name":"Gift - For Our Lady","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The Servants are brainwashed \nand totally dependent on Bella. Every attempt to scare or \nmentally manipulate them receives 2 Penalties. If Bella \nis targeted by a threat, once per Exchange, a Servant can \nsacrifice themselves to take the hit in her place. \nThe White Beach</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 127.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bVq8bOiq0Uudm4QC","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young people in the service of Bella \nand we are trained to defend the House \nof Roses. \nAgenda: Follow all of Bella’s \norders to the letter. \nGift – For Our Lady: The Servants are brainwashed \nand totally dependent on Bella. Every attempt to scare or \nmentally manipulate them receives 2 Penalties. If Bella \nis targeted by a threat, once per Exchange, a Servant can \nsacrifice themselves to take the hit in her place. \nThe White Beach\nDescriptor: A small beach of pebbles and earth hidden \namong the dense vegetation.\nInformation: Docking at the beach without the \nnecessary precautions will attract 1d6+2 Mastiffs.\nThe Forest\nDescriptor: A large wooded area that almost entirely \ncovers Martana Island.\nInformation: The forest is overrun by mastiffs loyal to \nDionysus. Avoiding them requires overcoming the Pack of \nMastiffs Threat. In case of a Failure, 8 Mastiffs will appear \nand surround the intruders. At the center of the forest is \na mass grave where the bodies of Dionysus’ victims are \ndumped. Francesca hides in the pit to escape the hungry \ndogs.\nThreat – Pack of Mastiffs</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 127."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-bella-s-servants-127","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":127,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young people in the service of Bella \nand we are trained to defend the House \nof Roses. \nAgenda: Follow all of Bella’s \norders to the letter. \nGift – For Our Lady: The Servants are brainwashed \nand totally dependent on Bella. Every attempt to scare or \nmentally manipulate them receives 2 Penalties. If Bella \nis targeted by a threat, once per Exchange, a Servant can \nsacrifice themselves to take the hit in her place. \nThe White Beach\nDescriptor: A small beach of pebbles and earth hidden \namong the dense vegetation.\nInformation: Docking at the beach without the \nnecessary precautions will attract 1d6+2 Mastiffs.\nThe Forest\nDescriptor: A large wooded area that almost entirely \ncovers Martana Island.\nInformation: The forest is overrun by mastiffs loyal to \nDionysus. Avoiding them requires overcoming the Pack of \nMastiffs Threat. In case of a Failure, 8 Mastiffs will appear \nand surround the intruders. At the center of the forest is \na mass grave where the bodies of Dionysus’ victims are \ndumped. Francesca hides in the pit to escape the hungry \ndogs.\nThreat – Pack of Mastiffs</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Follow all of Bella’s \norders to the letter.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629804,"modifiedTime":1781557629804,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"3pl4aKy7zqZsNrCD","name":"The Imposter","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"gcMqtPDWQyQg50sr","name":"The Imposter - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a poor beggar who pretends to be Hazir. I \nam good at adapting to any situation.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163.","positive":"I am a poor beggar who pretends to be Hazir. I \nam good at adapting to any situation.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YIJsiEfpcSAUjuXB","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a poor beggar who pretends to be Hazir. I \nam good at adapting to any situation.\nAgenda: To keep the life that was gifted to me. I am not evil \nand therefore I can play the role of the good Hazir well. \nThe Four Daughters of Hazir</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-the-imposter-163","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":163,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a poor beggar who pretends to be Hazir. I \nam good at adapting to any situation.\nAgenda: To keep the life that was gifted to me. I am not evil \nand therefore I can play the role of the good Hazir well. \nThe Four Daughters of Hazir</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To keep the life that was gifted to me. I am not evil \nand therefore I can play the role of the good Hazir well. \nThe Four Daughters of Hazir","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"49YOUFn3ZbhgPFIU","name":"Hans","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"2pryG4yGoya7phtG","name":"Hans - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a former soldier, once one \nof the company’s best marksmen. I never miss \nmy mark and always have a loaded weapon \nhidden under my heavy overcoat.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164.","positive":"I am a former soldier, once one \nof the company’s best marksmen. I never miss \nmy mark and always have a loaded weapon \nhidden under my heavy overcoat.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"GP69kOroC8imLhep","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a former soldier, once one \nof the company’s best marksmen. I never miss \nmy mark and always have a loaded weapon \nhidden under my heavy overcoat.\nAgenda: Convince Nils to keep our \nsecret or remove him.\nGift - Gunslinger: Hans owns a \npair of prized experimental pistols, \nwhich he bought from an inventor</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-hans-164","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":164,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a former soldier, once one \nof the company’s best marksmen. I never miss \nmy mark and always have a loaded weapon \nhidden under my heavy overcoat.\nAgenda: Convince Nils to keep our \nsecret or remove him.\nGift - Gunslinger: Hans owns a \npair of prized experimental pistols, \nwhich he bought from an inventor</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Convince Nils to keep our \nsecret or remove him.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"4AE8YZgLqPxd02Uc","name":"Angry Little Girl","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"e9pcksd7ENXMe3V3","name":"Angry Little Girl - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I survived the adults’ madness and now I \nstruggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this \ncruel world.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 188.","positive":"I survived the adults’ madness and now I \nstruggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this \ncruel world.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"t824E7rPGaQYhETR","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I survived the adults’ madness and now I \nstruggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this \ncruel world.\nAgenda: Find a safe place to stay or a group of people \nready to accept and protect me.\nEnd of Scene: after one or more encounters (at the \ndiscretion of the Storyteller) the Hunters come across \nthe crown of the Fairies (THIRD SCENE OPTION A - \nThe Crown of the Fairies) or the Hulder (THIRD SCENE \nOPTION B - The Hulder and the white dress).\nTHIRD SCENE OPTION A – \nThe Crown of the Fairies\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Sherazade smiles at a young \nnobleman among her audience who has risen from his chair \nto get a better look at her. She winks at him and says: “Sit \ndown my little guest, now the best is coming. ” \n“The swamps are shrouded in thin veils of a ghostly mist. All \nis silent. The moon appears to crack and bleed into the sky, \nand the faint stars die out one by one as you travel deeper \ninto this nocturnal realm. There is a light in the distance, a \nglow that is reflected in the swamps and still water. This light \ncomes from a small golden crown, and all around, many \nsilhouettes dance as if enthralled by its light. Fairies look like \npale women with long hair. They glide, dance, and writhe in \nthe air as if adrift in an invisible current. They are dreamlike, \nethereal, but their bodies meet, touch and brush against each \nother or, sometimes, through each other. Their eyes are shut</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 188."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-angry-little-girl-188","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":188,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I survived the adults’ madness and now I \nstruggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this \ncruel world.\nAgenda: Find a safe place to stay or a group of people \nready to accept and protect me.\nEnd of Scene: after one or more encounters (at the \ndiscretion of the Storyteller) the Hunters come across \nthe crown of the Fairies (THIRD SCENE OPTION A - \nThe Crown of the Fairies) or the Hulder (THIRD SCENE \nOPTION B - The Hulder and the white dress).\nTHIRD SCENE OPTION A – \nThe Crown of the Fairies\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Sherazade smiles at a young \nnobleman among her audience who has risen from his chair \nto get a better look at her. She winks at him and says: “Sit \ndown my little guest, now the best is coming. ” \n“The swamps are shrouded in thin veils of a ghostly mist. All \nis silent. The moon appears to crack and bleed into the sky, \nand the faint stars die out one by one as you travel deeper \ninto this nocturnal realm. There is a light in the distance, a \nglow that is reflected in the swamps and still water. This light \ncomes from a small golden crown, and all around, many \nsilhouettes dance as if enthralled by its light. Fairies look like \npale women with long hair. They glide, dance, and writhe in \nthe air as if adrift in an invisible current. They are dreamlike, \nethereal, but their bodies meet, touch and brush against each \nother or, sometimes, through each other. Their eyes are shut</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Find a safe place to stay or a group of people \nready to accept and protect me.\nEnd of Scene: after one or more encounters (at the \ndiscretion of the Storyteller) the Hunters come across \nthe crown of the Fairies (THIRD SCENE OPTION A - \nThe Crown of the Fairies) or the Hulder (THIRD SCENE \nOPTION B - The Hulder and the white dress).\nTHIRD SCENE OPTION A – \nThe Crown of the Fairies\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Sherazade smiles at a young \nnobleman among her audience who has risen from his chair \nto get a better look at her. She winks at him and says: “Sit \ndown my little guest, now the best is coming. ” \n“The swamps are shrouded in thin veils of a ghostly mist. All \nis silent. The moon appears to crack and bleed into the sky, \nand the faint stars die out one by one as you travel deeper \ninto this nocturnal realm. There is a light in the distance, a \nglow that is reflected in the swamps and still water. This light \ncomes from a small golden crown, and all around, many \nsilhouettes dance as if enthralled by its light. Fairies look like \npale women with long hair. They glide, dance, and writhe in \nthe air as if adrift in an invisible current. They are dreamlike, \nethereal, but their bodies meet, touch and brush against each \nother or, sometimes, through each other. Their eyes are shut","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"52lW9h1hsjKzdHHO","name":"Dose the Giant in Love","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"H58zx0AwEyBMmiX4","name":"Dose the Giant in Love - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>My body has become pure metal and only the \npower of love can bring me back to flesh and blood. I fight \nand destroy anything that can threaten my sweet OZena.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242.","positive":"My body has become pure metal and only the \npower of love can bring me back to flesh and blood. I fight \nand destroy anything that can threaten my sweet OZena.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"cSKrRR9wqPxQ3uqr","name":"Gift - Of Steel and Love","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Dose is made of pure metal and \ncannot suffer any kind of physical Wound. The only way to \nget him to return to flesh and blood for a few moments is \nto make his heart beat with love. Seeing OZena in danger \nor well disposed towards him will change him back for \none Exchange. Seeing OZena, Dose can’t help but declare \nhis love as he fights, making his infatuation for the young \nassassin clear.\nThe Canine Tigers</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wkyDDfZzhXyKrQrH","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: My body has become pure metal and only the \npower of love can bring me back to flesh and blood. I fight \nand destroy anything that can threaten my sweet OZena.\nAgenda: I am in love with OZena and I want her to loyally \nserve Henkle once more. I know that imprisonment in the \nhands of the enemy may have made her reluctant to trust us. \nI have to save her, whether she wants it or not.\nGift - Of Steel and Love: Dose is made of pure metal and \ncannot suffer any kind of physical Wound. The only way to \nget him to return to flesh and blood for a few moments is \nto make his heart beat with love. Seeing OZena in danger \nor well disposed towards him will change him back for \none Exchange. Seeing OZena, Dose can’t help but declare \nhis love as he fights, making his infatuation for the young \nassassin clear.\nThe Canine Tigers</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-dose-the-giant-in-love-242","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":242,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: My body has become pure metal and only the \npower of love can bring me back to flesh and blood. I fight \nand destroy anything that can threaten my sweet OZena.\nAgenda: I am in love with OZena and I want her to loyally \nserve Henkle once more. I know that imprisonment in the \nhands of the enemy may have made her reluctant to trust us. \nI have to save her, whether she wants it or not.\nGift - Of Steel and Love: Dose is made of pure metal and \ncannot suffer any kind of physical Wound. The only way to \nget him to return to flesh and blood for a few moments is \nto make his heart beat with love. Seeing OZena in danger \nor well disposed towards him will change him back for \none Exchange. Seeing OZena, Dose can’t help but declare \nhis love as he fights, making his infatuation for the young \nassassin clear.\nThe Canine Tigers</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I am in love with OZena and I want her to loyally \nserve Henkle once more. I know that imprisonment in the \nhands of the enemy may have made her reluctant to trust us. \nI have to save her, whether she wants it or not.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5F14HmdVW60IAO1q","name":"The Patients of Wonder","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"TlpInPt87Ew45nlN","name":"The Patients of Wonder - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are mad and desperate, driven to Wonder \nin the hope of curing our ailments. Madness guides our \nactions and we no longer understand that there is a world \noutside the bedlam.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 174.","positive":"We are mad and desperate, driven to Wonder \nin the hope of curing our ailments. Madness guides our \nactions and we no longer understand that there is a world \noutside the bedlam.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622931,"modifiedTime":1781557622931,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MsbPeOoEe7uAwCvO","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are mad and desperate, driven to Wonder \nin the hope of curing our ailments. Madness guides our \nactions and we no longer understand that there is a world \noutside the bedlam.\nGift - Why I Am Here: Roll a die to see what problem led \nthem to Wonder.\n1 Violence: The Patient struggles to contain their anger. \nWhen they act violently increase their OL by 1. \n2 Kleptomania: The Patient yearns for any object they \ndeem interesting and will do everything to have it. Once \nper Scene, they can act 2 times consecutively, though the \nadditional Action must be used to attempt to escape and \nhide with the stolen goods.\n3 Abandoned: The Patient was interned at Wonder to \nbe forgotten. Hardened by loneliness, they gain 1 extra \nWound.\n4 Split personality: The Patient changes personality in \nthe face of a specific event, such as a threat. When the new \npersonality acts, its OL becomes Hard 7.\n5 Dementia: The Patient is not fully aware of what is \nhappening around them. They are immune to all attempts \nat intimidation. Increase their OL by 1 when defending \nagainst a violent action.\n6 Illness: The Patient is ill or horribly disfigured. Each \naction against them receives 1 Penalty.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 174."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622931,"modifiedTime":1781557622931,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-the-patients-of-wonder-174","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":174,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are mad and desperate, driven to Wonder \nin the hope of curing our ailments. Madness guides our \nactions and we no longer understand that there is a world \noutside the bedlam.\nGift - Why I Am Here: Roll a die to see what problem led \nthem to Wonder.\n1 Violence: The Patient struggles to contain their anger. \nWhen they act violently increase their OL by 1. \n2 Kleptomania: The Patient yearns for any object they \ndeem interesting and will do everything to have it. Once \nper Scene, they can act 2 times consecutively, though the \nadditional Action must be used to attempt to escape and \nhide with the stolen goods.\n3 Abandoned: The Patient was interned at Wonder to \nbe forgotten. Hardened by loneliness, they gain 1 extra \nWound.\n4 Split personality: The Patient changes personality in \nthe face of a specific event, such as a threat. When the new \npersonality acts, its OL becomes Hard 7.\n5 Dementia: The Patient is not fully aware of what is \nhappening around them. They are immune to all attempts \nat intimidation. Increase their OL by 1 when defending \nagainst a violent action.\n6 Illness: The Patient is ill or horribly disfigured. Each \naction against them receives 1 Penalty.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622931,"modifiedTime":1781557622931,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5KQLljG0uteZFQDV","name":"Henrich the Father","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"O2COw8xKCBB15YSK","name":"Henrich the Father - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am one of the many people Margareta \nsaved from the miserable life of an outcast. My son Klaus is \neverything to me, which is why I don’t want the village of \nGelb to be suspected of witchcraft.\nKlaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 226.","positive":"I am one of the many people Margareta \nsaved from the miserable life of an outcast. My son Klaus is \neverything to me, which is why I don’t want the village of \nGelb to be suspected of witchcraft.\nKlaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LmKd9khrFxspLJJh","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am one of the many people Margareta \nsaved from the miserable life of an outcast. My son Klaus is \neverything to me, which is why I don’t want the village of \nGelb to be suspected of witchcraft.\nKlaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 226."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-henrich-the-father-226","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":226,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am one of the many people Margareta \nsaved from the miserable life of an outcast. My son Klaus is \neverything to me, which is why I don’t want the village of \nGelb to be suspected of witchcraft.\nKlaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5XEyVW05EwvDvOm5","name":"Aleksandr Pták","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"5dvUDtB0MRrBgfY2","name":"Aleksandr Pták - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am divided between who I was before and \nthe spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to \nkill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.\nSwallow’s</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","positive":"I am divided between who I was before and \nthe spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to \nkill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.\nSwallow’s","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yD6xEWnvFzBP8SxN","name":"Gift - Swallow’s Flight","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Aleksandr can easily climb \nanywhere and perform inhuman leaps. As he does, his OL \nincreases by 1. If he hits someone plunging down from \nabove, he can automatically escape the enemy’s threat range \nwith a long jump.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ruzn4nprCzdQv4w5","name":"Gift - What is Yours is Mine","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>As an additional action, \nAleksandr can steal any object in the hands of another \ncharacter with extreme ease. A Hunter can avoid the theft \nby succeeding in a Defense Check. \n \nCernobog Potmešil The Child</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vExBfULSPvsPz14d","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am divided between who I was before and \nthe spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to \nkill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.\nSwallow’s Agenda: Finding an ally in the people I helped \nin my previous life / Restoring the Prince, my only true love / \nAvenging wrongs suffered. \nAlexandr’s Agenda: Finding peace and freeing myself \nfrom the spirit that possesses me. \nGift – Swallow’s Flight: Aleksandr can easily climb \nanywhere and perform inhuman leaps. As he does, his OL \nincreases by 1. If he hits someone plunging down from \nabove, he can automatically escape the enemy’s threat range \nwith a long jump. \nGift – What is Yours is Mine: As an additional action, \nAleksandr can steal any object in the hands of another \ncharacter with extreme ease. A Hunter can avoid the theft \nby succeeding in a Defense Check. \n \nCernobog Potmešil The Child</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-aleksandr-pt-k-173","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":173,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am divided between who I was before and \nthe spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to \nkill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.\nSwallow’s Agenda: Finding an ally in the people I helped \nin my previous life / Restoring the Prince, my only true love / \nAvenging wrongs suffered. \nAlexandr’s Agenda: Finding peace and freeing myself \nfrom the spirit that possesses me. \nGift – Swallow’s Flight: Aleksandr can easily climb \nanywhere and perform inhuman leaps. As he does, his OL \nincreases by 1. If he hits someone plunging down from \nabove, he can automatically escape the enemy’s threat range \nwith a long jump. \nGift – What is Yours is Mine: As an additional action, \nAleksandr can steal any object in the hands of another \ncharacter with extreme ease. A Hunter can avoid the theft \nby succeeding in a Defense Check. \n \nCernobog Potmešil The Child</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Finding an ally in the people I helped \nin my previous life / Restoring the Prince, my only true love / \nAvenging wrongs suffered. \nAlexandr’s Agenda: Finding peace and freeing myself \nfrom the spirit that possesses me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637920,"modifiedTime":1781557637920,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5sf2sa1BL6TPhjQc","name":"Arne the Captain","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"0eTc8DjRFLTptLxG","name":"Arne the Captain - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I once was a military man and I’ve earned the \ncrown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and \nboast about my crew.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 95.","positive":"I once was a military man and I’ve earned the \ncrown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and \nboast about my crew.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"kSIlUR1DSiZL1pYd","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I once was a military man and I’ve earned the \ncrown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and \nboast about my crew. \nAgenda: Do my best to carry out the mission I was entrusted \nwith. However, I won’t put the people under my command at \nrisk.\nSailors</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 95."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-arne-the-captain-95","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":95,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I once was a military man and I’ve earned the \ncrown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and \nboast about my crew. \nAgenda: Do my best to carry out the mission I was entrusted \nwith. However, I won’t put the people under my command at \nrisk.\nSailors</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Do my best to carry out the mission I was entrusted \nwith. However, I won’t put the people under my command at \nrisk.\nSailors","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"63Pd9STT91uPaJNk","name":"Lizard Automaton","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Eaq3QZ0PyRLhNg9a","name":"Lizard Automaton - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions \nat the same time.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177.","positive":"I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions \nat the same time.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OsLD6H2jyOpWLrHA","name":"Gift - Tail","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The Automaton always acts twice, once with its \nfront legs and once with its long tail, but cannot focus both \nits actions on the same target.\nHall of the Mind</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vaqSto8H8BA8zAI1","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions \nat the same time.\nGift - Tail: The Automaton always acts twice, once with its \nfront legs and once with its long tail, but cannot focus both \nits actions on the same target.\nHall of the Mind\nDescriptor: A series of rooms painted entirely in white. The \ndoors themselves do not have handles and it takes a careful \nlook to distinguish them from the walls. A large central hall \ngathers all the Patients, lying on rows of beds, asleep in a state \nof trance. The distant ticking of a clock breaks an otherwise \nunnatural silence, creating a hypnotic echo.\nInformation: In the Hall of the Mind, it is possible to \nfind several Patients in a catatonic state, including Alissa \nof Norfolk. Alice Liddell will not seek a confrontation with \nany intruders but will be friendly and willing to listen to the \nunexpected guests. Alice will offer a good tea in which \na powerful sleep drug is mixed.\nThreat - Alice’s special tea</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-lizard-automaton-177","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":177,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions \nat the same time.\nGift - Tail: The Automaton always acts twice, once with its \nfront legs and once with its long tail, but cannot focus both \nits actions on the same target.\nHall of the Mind\nDescriptor: A series of rooms painted entirely in white. The \ndoors themselves do not have handles and it takes a careful \nlook to distinguish them from the walls. A large central hall \ngathers all the Patients, lying on rows of beds, asleep in a state \nof trance. The distant ticking of a clock breaks an otherwise \nunnatural silence, creating a hypnotic echo.\nInformation: In the Hall of the Mind, it is possible to \nfind several Patients in a catatonic state, including Alissa \nof Norfolk. Alice Liddell will not seek a confrontation with \nany intruders but will be friendly and willing to listen to the \nunexpected guests. Alice will offer a good tea in which \na powerful sleep drug is mixed.\nThreat - Alice’s special tea</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"69fMuRE1MWgFizKt","name":"Haunted House","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"Sw9VvrH7OYYyxO3c","name":"Haunted House - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A house that emits an aura of ignorant \nwell-being, relaxing intruders into sleep.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 206.","positive":"A house that emits an aura of ignorant \nwell-being, relaxing intruders into sleep.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645071,"modifiedTime":1781557645071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"pxIis2ZzKokk89wT","name":"Gift - Induced Fatigue","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>For each room visited in the \nHouse, roll one die for each intruder:\n1-3: Nothing happens.\n4-6: They lose 1 Soma. \nOn the second point of Soma lost to this Gift, a Hunter \nmust pass a Defense Check to avoid falling into an eighthour deep sleep from which they cannot be awakened. For \nan NPC, the effect is triggered when they lose Soma equal \nto the category of their OL: 1 for Easy, 2 for Medium, and \n3 for Hard.\nFlora’s Bedroom</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 206.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645071,"modifiedTime":1781557645071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LX0TYO5vIec48WR8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A house that emits an aura of ignorant \nwell-being, relaxing intruders into sleep. \nGift - Induced Fatigue: For each room visited in the \nHouse, roll one die for each intruder:\n1-3: Nothing happens.\n4-6: They lose 1 Soma. \nOn the second point of Soma lost to this Gift, a Hunter \nmust pass a Defense Check to avoid falling into an eighthour deep sleep from which they cannot be awakened. For \nan NPC, the effect is triggered when they lose Soma equal \nto the category of their OL: 1 for Easy, 2 for Medium, and \n3 for Hard.\nFlora’s Bedroom\nDescriptor: A richly decorated room with a large canopy \nbed. Flowers and plants of all kinds grow on the walls, giving \nthe impression of being in a small greenhouse. \nInformation: The Hunters will quickly notice a small box \non the wardrobe next to the bed. Inside is Flora’s diary, but \nas you might guess, a witch’s box can’t be opened by just \nanyone.\n2a</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 206."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645071,"modifiedTime":1781557645071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-haunted-house-206","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":206,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A house that emits an aura of ignorant \nwell-being, relaxing intruders into sleep. \nGift - Induced Fatigue: For each room visited in the \nHouse, roll one die for each intruder:\n1-3: Nothing happens.\n4-6: They lose 1 Soma. \nOn the second point of Soma lost to this Gift, a Hunter \nmust pass a Defense Check to avoid falling into an eighthour deep sleep from which they cannot be awakened. For \nan NPC, the effect is triggered when they lose Soma equal \nto the category of their OL: 1 for Easy, 2 for Medium, and \n3 for Hard.\nFlora’s Bedroom\nDescriptor: A richly decorated room with a large canopy \nbed. Flowers and plants of all kinds grow on the walls, giving \nthe impression of being in a small greenhouse. \nInformation: The Hunters will quickly notice a small box \non the wardrobe next to the bed. Inside is Flora’s diary, but \nas you might guess, a witch’s box can’t be opened by just \nanyone.\n2a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645071,"modifiedTime":1781557645071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6AHALfZiYzV7veOp","name":"Princess Tuvstarr","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"fvYqVm0zntDey9fW","name":"Princess Tuvstarr - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a pure and innocent soul, who just \nwants a world without suffering.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 193.","positive":"I am a pure and innocent soul, who just \nwants a world without suffering.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623498,"modifiedTime":1781557623498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wj343Oz4WvWaQbWp","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a pure and innocent soul, who just \nwants a world without suffering.\nAgenda: I want to stay forever in my perfect world. I \nhave been here for so long that I have forgotten what my \nlife was like before.\nGift – Creative Will: Tuvstarr has the power to create \nanything she wants in the Dream World. She can make a</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 193."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623498,"modifiedTime":1781557623498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-princess-tuvstarr-193","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":193,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a pure and innocent soul, who just \nwants a world without suffering.\nAgenda: I want to stay forever in my perfect world. I \nhave been here for so long that I have forgotten what my \nlife was like before.\nGift – Creative Will: Tuvstarr has the power to create \nanything she wants in the Dream World. She can make a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I want to stay forever in my perfect world. I \nhave been here for so long that I have forgotten what my \nlife was like before.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623498,"modifiedTime":1781557623498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6AgLmnl8Lczmtx8m","name":"Helpers","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"xAFHLOPyHrBC0y0t","name":"Helpers - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We live and work only to serve our master Nikola. Our bodies are made stronger by the power that has \nbeen infused into them.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 125.","positive":"We live and work only to serve our master Nikola. Our bodies are made stronger by the power that has \nbeen infused into them.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640759,"modifiedTime":1781557640759,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"H38dhLcwikSemqT2","name":"Gift - Servants of the Mansion","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Each Helper can avail themselves of a different effect based on their role.\nJori the Cook: Can inflict 1 additional Wound with his \ncleaver. Injuries inflicted by Jori count as a mark for Nikola’s Reindeer.\nPete the Butler: When moving inside the mansion, Pete \nignores any movement penalty and no one can block him.\nVerna the Accountant: Increases her OL to Hard 7 \nwhen defending against an attack inside the mansion.\nNikola Lupei</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 125.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640759,"modifiedTime":1781557640759,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"n3x9skXcgKKYFq0D","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We live and work only to serve our master Nikola. Our bodies are made stronger by the power that has \nbeen infused into them. \nAgenda: Defend Nikola from all threats.\nGift - Servants of the Mansion: Each Helper can avail themselves of a different effect based on their role.\nJori the Cook: Can inflict 1 additional Wound with his \ncleaver. Injuries inflicted by Jori count as a mark for Nikola’s Reindeer.\nPete the Butler: When moving inside the mansion, Pete \nignores any movement penalty and no one can block him.\nVerna the Accountant: Increases her OL to Hard 7 \nwhen defending against an attack inside the mansion.\nNikola Lupei</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 125."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640759,"modifiedTime":1781557640759,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-helpers-125","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":125,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We live and work only to serve our master Nikola. Our bodies are made stronger by the power that has \nbeen infused into them. \nAgenda: Defend Nikola from all threats.\nGift - Servants of the Mansion: Each Helper can avail themselves of a different effect based on their role.\nJori the Cook: Can inflict 1 additional Wound with his \ncleaver. Injuries inflicted by Jori count as a mark for Nikola’s Reindeer.\nPete the Butler: When moving inside the mansion, Pete \nignores any movement penalty and no one can block him.\nVerna the Accountant: Increases her OL to Hard 7 \nwhen defending against an attack inside the mansion.\nNikola Lupei</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Defend Nikola from all threats.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640759,"modifiedTime":1781557640759,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6YwAcsjsqkuM5V9y","name":"Fury and Wrath, the Two Deadly Twins","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"SMoTjBAyD8S5Lcmr","name":"Fury and Wrath, the Two Deadly Twins - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two Djinn fighters who watch each other’s back. There is no match for our pair fighting technique.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 164.","positive":"We are two Djinn fighters who watch each other’s back. There is no match for our pair fighting technique.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642733,"modifiedTime":1781557642733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CT3R7dkranlCPpox","name":"Gift - Invincible Duo","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>While fighting as a pair, Fury \nand Wrath cannot take Wounds. Any attack or method of \nwounding them will be blocked by one of the two Djinn. \nTo avoid this Gift, it is necessary to use an effect that affects \nboth Djinn at the same time or to separate them so that \nthey cannot support each other. \n6B The Djinn King\nThe story that led us here...\nThe Hunters are summoned to the deck of the ship, where \nthey will find a mysterious old man smoking a water pipe. \nThe old man will ask them to run errands for him, and if they \ndo a good job, he will reward them with a golden Tarì. The \nold man exudes a strong aura of power, and the Hunters understand that the strange figure is hiding his true nature. The \nship lands on a large island and the old man claps his hands \nin satisfaction: it is time to begin. The Hunters must find nine \ngolden columns scattered throughout the city and bring them \nback to him so he can furnish his palace.\nPlace: A large port city filled with temples and merchant \ndistricts.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 164.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642733,"modifiedTime":1781557642733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bHSUDnIGt5KrhL8g","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are two Djinn fighters who watch each other’s back. There is no match for our pair fighting technique. \nAgenda: Carry out every order of Hazir. \nGift - Invincible Duo: While fighting as a pair, Fury \nand Wrath cannot take Wounds. Any attack or method of \nwounding them will be blocked by one of the two Djinn. \nTo avoid this Gift, it is necessary to use an effect that affects \nboth Djinn at the same time or to separate them so that \nthey cannot support each other. \n6B The Djinn King\nThe story that led us here...\nThe Hunters are summoned to the deck of the ship, where \nthey will find a mysterious old man smoking a water pipe. \nThe old man will ask them to run errands for him, and if they \ndo a good job, he will reward them with a golden Tarì. The \nold man exudes a strong aura of power, and the Hunters understand that the strange figure is hiding his true nature. The \nship lands on a large island and the old man claps his hands \nin satisfaction: it is time to begin. The Hunters must find nine \ngolden columns scattered throughout the city and bring them \nback to him so he can furnish his palace.\nPlace: A large port city filled with temples and merchant \ndistricts.\nInformation: Finding the columns is only a matter of \ntime for the Hunters, but they will encounter several people \nwho need help. Even if they don’t know it, spending time \nwith others will earn the Hunters a positive rating from the \nDjinn King. \nChallenges: Each column requires 1 hour of time and at \nleast one Position Check. The list below shows where they \ncan be found. Using Gifts and Descriptors for additional information can speed up the search. For every two columns \nfound, roll 1 die to see who needs help, up to a maximum \nof 3 requests. \nThe Columns\nFirst: On the pier in the harbor, covered with seaweed and \nshells. / Second: In a dung-covered square used as a hitching post for horses and camels. / Third: In the inner courtyard of a merchant’s mansion. / Fourth: In the middle of \nan olive grove, not far from the city walls. / Fifth: In the art \ncollection of a wealthy Vizier. / Sixth: In the middle of a \nnotorious tavern, as a pillar supporting the roof. / Seventh: \nIn the wall of a watchtower. / Eighth: In the bedroom of the \nfirst daughter of the Sultan. / Ninth: In the hold of Sinbad’s \nship, stolen and then forgotten by the old sailor years ago.\nThe Needy\n1: A poor farmer has no money to buy seeds for the coming \nseason. Without the precious seeds, he will not be able to \nfeed his family. \n2: A child just five years old is lost and has wandered clear \nacross the city from where he lives. He struggles to speak \nand is frightened, but no one seems to care about him. \n3: A poor sailor was poisoned by some villains because he \nwon too much at dice. If he does not get an antidote he will \ndie. \n4: A merchant was robbed of a precious gold crown he \nhad bought for his daughter’s wedding. Without the crown,</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 164."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642733,"modifiedTime":1781557642733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-fury-and-wrath-the-two-deadly-twins-164","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":164,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are two Djinn fighters who watch each other’s back. There is no match for our pair fighting technique. \nAgenda: Carry out every order of Hazir. \nGift - Invincible Duo: While fighting as a pair, Fury \nand Wrath cannot take Wounds. Any attack or method of \nwounding them will be blocked by one of the two Djinn. \nTo avoid this Gift, it is necessary to use an effect that affects \nboth Djinn at the same time or to separate them so that \nthey cannot support each other. \n6B The Djinn King\nThe story that led us here...\nThe Hunters are summoned to the deck of the ship, where \nthey will find a mysterious old man smoking a water pipe. \nThe old man will ask them to run errands for him, and if they \ndo a good job, he will reward them with a golden Tarì. The \nold man exudes a strong aura of power, and the Hunters understand that the strange figure is hiding his true nature. The \nship lands on a large island and the old man claps his hands \nin satisfaction: it is time to begin. The Hunters must find nine \ngolden columns scattered throughout the city and bring them \nback to him so he can furnish his palace.\nPlace: A large port city filled with temples and merchant \ndistricts.\nInformation: Finding the columns is only a matter of \ntime for the Hunters, but they will encounter several people \nwho need help. Even if they don’t know it, spending time \nwith others will earn the Hunters a positive rating from the \nDjinn King. \nChallenges: Each column requires 1 hour of time and at \nleast one Position Check. The list below shows where they \ncan be found. Using Gifts and Descriptors for additional information can speed up the search. For every two columns \nfound, roll 1 die to see who needs help, up to a maximum \nof 3 requests. \nThe Columns\nFirst: On the pier in the harbor, covered with seaweed and \nshells. / Second: In a dung-covered square used as a hitching post for horses and camels. / Third: In the inner courtyard of a merchant’s mansion. / Fourth: In the middle of \nan olive grove, not far from the city walls. / Fifth: In the art \ncollection of a wealthy Vizier. / Sixth: In the middle of a \nnotorious tavern, as a pillar supporting the roof. / Seventh: \nIn the wall of a watchtower. / Eighth: In the bedroom of the \nfirst daughter of the Sultan. / Ninth: In the hold of Sinbad’s \nship, stolen and then forgotten by the old sailor years ago.\nThe Needy\n1: A poor farmer has no money to buy seeds for the coming \nseason. Without the precious seeds, he will not be able to \nfeed his family. \n2: A child just five years old is lost and has wandered clear \nacross the city from where he lives. He struggles to speak \nand is frightened, but no one seems to care about him. \n3: A poor sailor was poisoned by some villains because he \nwon too much at dice. If he does not get an antidote he will \ndie. \n4: A merchant was robbed of a precious gold crown he \nhad bought for his daughter’s wedding. Without the crown,</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Carry out every order of Hazir.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642733,"modifiedTime":1781557642733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6eSrOciqJXg5hX0t","name":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"c3fZ840sW9P4XzrA","name":"Spawn of The God Under the Mine - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>An abomination of flesh and tentacles, obeying \nArthur’s will.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","positive":"An abomination of flesh and tentacles, obeying \nArthur’s will.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KFhkwNLxb2tpFJDy","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: An abomination of flesh and tentacles, obeying \nArthur’s will.\nGift – Flesh Abomination: A Spawn can perform its \naction with a flesh tentacle up to a range of 6 feet, and at the \nend of each Exchange it will grow as indicated in the table. \nIf not engaged in a conflict, the Spawn will grow 1 step per</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-spawn-of-the-god-under-the-mine-212","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":212,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: An abomination of flesh and tentacles, obeying \nArthur’s will.\nGift – Flesh Abomination: A Spawn can perform its \naction with a flesh tentacle up to a range of 6 feet, and at the \nend of each Exchange it will grow as indicated in the table. \nIf not engaged in a conflict, the Spawn will grow 1 step per</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7FGUoXqISwEI3R41","name":"Fredrika Okland","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"dmrCAwwwUs9Yts3L","name":"Fredrika Okland - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the young scion of the Okland family, I believe in justice and honesty as my father taught me.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 205.","positive":"I am the young scion of the Okland family, I believe in justice and honesty as my father taught me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645007,"modifiedTime":1781557645007,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"oUrf4tvSnU3S3VA9","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young scion of the Okland family, I believe in justice and honesty as my father taught me. \nAgenda: To heal my father and make him the good man who raised me.\nAleksander Okland</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 205."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645007,"modifiedTime":1781557645007,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-fredrika-okland-205","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":205,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young scion of the Okland family, I believe in justice and honesty as my father taught me. \nAgenda: To heal my father and make him the good man who raised me.\nAleksander Okland</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To heal my father and make him the good man who raised me.\nAleksander Okland","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645007,"modifiedTime":1781557645007,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7bA6AM8NIgVcDWM0","name":"The Four Daughters of Hazir","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"JtS4J7rKW7rr6nJ4","name":"The Four Daughters of Hazir - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the Daughters of Hazir and we love our \nfather because he taught us kindness and humility. \nHazir’s Guards</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163.","positive":"We are the Daughters of Hazir and we love our \nfather because he taught us kindness and humility. \nHazir’s Guards","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YEaKXjMpqT64aZ89","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the Daughters of Hazir and we love our \nfather because he taught us kindness and humility. \nHazir’s Guards</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-the-four-daughters-of-hazir-163","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":163,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the Daughters of Hazir and we love our \nfather because he taught us kindness and humility. \nHazir’s Guards</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7jgelMet4eBmMlNL","name":"Ice Golem","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"L3gCXDtficWW04k7","name":"Ice Golem - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a mighty creature of pure ice and live only \nto serve my creator.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 218.","positive":"I am a mighty creature of pure ice and live only \nto serve my creator.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645699,"modifiedTime":1781557645699,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"SaG01fRW4z4f5ebV","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a mighty creature of pure ice and live only \nto serve my creator. \nInformation: Pernille is the only one who knows the \nmagic formula that opens the portal located in the small \nlake, leading to the house of Sinikka, the Finland Woman. A Hunter who understands magic can also activate the \nportal by studying the passage. If both of these options are \nimpractical, Hunters can ask Iselin for help.\nThreat – The Magic Lake Portal</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 218."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645699,"modifiedTime":1781557645699,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-ice-golem-218","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":218,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a mighty creature of pure ice and live only \nto serve my creator. \nInformation: Pernille is the only one who knows the \nmagic formula that opens the portal located in the small \nlake, leading to the house of Sinikka, the Finland Woman. A Hunter who understands magic can also activate the \nportal by studying the passage. If both of these options are \nimpractical, Hunters can ask Iselin for help.\nThreat – The Magic Lake Portal</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645699,"modifiedTime":1781557645699,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7moweb3lakst027s","name":"Mercenary and Researcher of Renowned Fame","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"0NnYYBPAk5H6v41D","name":"Mercenary and Researcher of Renowned Fame - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, \nand I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what \nI want.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 139.","positive":"I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, \nand I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what \nI want.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636228,"modifiedTime":1781557636228,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sKpjXaf9YwmwXRyQ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, \nand I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what \nI want. \nAgenda: Escape from Stegeborg while keeping the secret of \nwhat I have done, as well as keeping the treasure I have found \n/ Take advantage of the arrival of the Hunters in Stegeborg to \nappease the fury of Talia. \nGift – Good at Escaping: Accursio is skilled at making \nhimself scarce when things get bad. Increase his OL by 1 \nfor all actions involving fleeing or avoiding a menace. Once \nper Scene, Accursio can move away from a place without \nanyone being able to stop or see him. To do this, however, \nit is necessary that something happens that can attract the</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 139."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636228,"modifiedTime":1781557636228,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-mercenary-and-researcher-of-renowned-fame-139","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":139,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, \nand I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what \nI want. \nAgenda: Escape from Stegeborg while keeping the secret of \nwhat I have done, as well as keeping the treasure I have found \n/ Take advantage of the arrival of the Hunters in Stegeborg to \nappease the fury of Talia. \nGift – Good at Escaping: Accursio is skilled at making \nhimself scarce when things get bad. Increase his OL by 1 \nfor all actions involving fleeing or avoiding a menace. Once \nper Scene, Accursio can move away from a place without \nanyone being able to stop or see him. To do this, however, \nit is necessary that something happens that can attract the</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Escape from Stegeborg while keeping the secret of \nwhat I have done, as well as keeping the treasure I have found \n/ Take advantage of the arrival of the Hunters in Stegeborg to \nappease the fury of Talia.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636228,"modifiedTime":1781557636228,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"82MyIbsuhvcs8Cgg","name":"Red-Hood Iskra","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"FEzxY9Q69WAvuH59","name":"Red-Hood Iskra - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I possess the strength and agility of a wolf. I \nhide my face with a rudimentary wooden mask that I made \nwith my own hands. I wear a threadbare red cape, the \nlast gift from my mother.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126.","positive":"I possess the strength and agility of a wolf. I \nhide my face with a rudimentary wooden mask that I made \nwith my own hands. I wear a threadbare red cape, the \nlast gift from my mother.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Bp7eOIjTrQhZcQLp","name":"Gift - Wolf’s Blood","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Iskra is \nmoved by an animalistic fury \nthat allows her to act twice in \nthe course of an Exchange.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ncRf52CnXWtSLjAH","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I possess the strength and agility of a wolf. I \nhide my face with a rudimentary wooden mask that I made \nwith my own hands. I wear a threadbare red cape, the \nlast gift from my mother.\nAgenda: To unleash her animalistic fury \non Elizaveta and anyone who defends \nher. Taking revenge on my mother has \nbecome an obsession for me.\nGift - Wolf’s Blood: Iskra is \nmoved by an animalistic fury \nthat allows her to act twice in \nthe course of an Exchange.\nGift - The Senses of a \nWolf: Iskra’s sense of smell \nhas become infallible. The \nlittle girl will always be able to \nidentify someone if she knows \ntheir scent, ignoring all kinds \nof disguises and even magic.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RmpsD4VKzuhoZabe","name":"Gift - The Senses of a Wolf","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"legacySource":"E:/respaldos","importSlug":"red-hood-iskra-Gift - The Senses of a Wolf"}},"system":{"description":"<p>Iskra's sense of smell has become infallible. The little girl will always be able to identify someone if she knows their scent, ignoring all kinds of disguise and even magic.</p>","notes":"Red-Hood Iskra scenario actor gift.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783931098622,"modifiedTime":1783931098622,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-red-hood-iskra-126","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":126,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>I possess the strength and agility of a wolf. I hide my face with a rudimentary wooden mask that I made with my own hands. I wear a threadbare red cape, the last gift of my mother.</p><p>Agenda: To unleash her animalistic fury on Elizaveta and anyone who defends her. Taking revenge on my mother has become an obsession for me.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To unleash her animalistic fury on Elizaveta and anyone who defends her. Taking revenge on my mother has become an obsession for me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"8Sis9tPhtp1ad32h","name":"Seal of the Cauldron Fae","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"5stJ5deOucBcjIpM","name":"Seal of the Cauldron Fae - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic \nof the Cauldron Fae.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","positive":"A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic \nof the Cauldron Fae.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UAVWcUxmwrzuV8do","name":"Gift - Seals Everywhere","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>At least one Seal of the \nCauldron Fae is present in all the Places of the Scenario. \nWhoever possesses the Gang Seal or Personal Seal Gift \ncan activate the effect of the Seal of the Cauldron Fae as an \nadditional action; this allows them to teleport to another \nplace featuring a Seal. The Seals are invisible to the human \neye and can be used only by those who have a tattooed eye \non their hand, placing said tattoo in front of the right eye. \nThose who use magic can detect the presence of a Seal, but \nthe Seal of Disbelief Scenario Gift is necessary to activate it. \nNote: Some Places feature more than one Seal to grant \nthe Lost Boys more narrative options in case the Hunters \nmanage to impede access to a Seal or negate the Gift. \nGeorge Carnarvon</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LqWk519l7dKB1wcr","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic \nof the Cauldron Fae.\nGift – Seals Everywhere: At least one Seal of the \nCauldron Fae is present in all the Places of the Scenario. \nWhoever possesses the Gang Seal or Personal Seal Gift \ncan activate the effect of the Seal of the Cauldron Fae as an \nadditional action; this allows them to teleport to another \nplace featuring a Seal. The Seals are invisible to the human \neye and can be used only by those who have a tattooed eye \non their hand, placing said tattoo in front of the right eye. \nThose who use magic can detect the presence of a Seal, but \nthe Seal of Disbelief Scenario Gift is necessary to activate it. \nNote: Some Places feature more than one Seal to grant \nthe Lost Boys more narrative options in case the Hunters \nmanage to impede access to a Seal or negate the Gift. \nGeorge Carnarvon</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-seal-of-the-cauldron-fae-84","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":84,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic \nof the Cauldron Fae.\nGift – Seals Everywhere: At least one Seal of the \nCauldron Fae is present in all the Places of the Scenario. \nWhoever possesses the Gang Seal or Personal Seal Gift \ncan activate the effect of the Seal of the Cauldron Fae as an \nadditional action; this allows them to teleport to another \nplace featuring a Seal. The Seals are invisible to the human \neye and can be used only by those who have a tattooed eye \non their hand, placing said tattoo in front of the right eye. \nThose who use magic can detect the presence of a Seal, but \nthe Seal of Disbelief Scenario Gift is necessary to activate it. \nNote: Some Places feature more than one Seal to grant \nthe Lost Boys more narrative options in case the Hunters \nmanage to impede access to a Seal or negate the Gift. \nGeorge Carnarvon</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"8VA68S0ThBGzvLLq","name":"Hazir the Poor Merchant","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"rtbZ2wlotRJqBKGQ","name":"Hazir the Poor Merchant - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an honest merchant who has always \nshown respect for others. My wealth is as great as my good \nheart.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163.","positive":"I am an honest merchant who has always \nshown respect for others. My wealth is as great as my good \nheart.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Eage07NrdS0HqEHU","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am an honest merchant who has always \nshown respect for others. My wealth is as great as my good \nheart. \nAgenda: Return to my old life, perhaps without punishing \nthe beggar, for I understand the reasons for his selfishness. \nThe Imposter</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-hazir-the-poor-merchant-163","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":163,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am an honest merchant who has always \nshown respect for others. My wealth is as great as my good \nheart. \nAgenda: Return to my old life, perhaps without punishing \nthe beggar, for I understand the reasons for his selfishness. \nThe Imposter</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Return to my old life, perhaps without punishing \nthe beggar, for I understand the reasons for his selfishness. \nThe Imposter","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"8et2DnGrdSN8XT3C","name":"Nils the Poor Devil","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"3UFYk3zJ3wdBvsKu","name":"Nils the Poor Devil - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an old soldier who lost his legs \nin the war.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164.","positive":"I am an old soldier who lost his legs \nin the war.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TxGGhULdCaQV8qxx","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old soldier who lost his legs \nin the war.\nAgenda: The guilt for what we did to Enar \nhaunts me, I want to find a way to bring him \npeace.\nHans</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 164."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-nils-the-poor-devil-164","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":164,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old soldier who lost his legs \nin the war.\nAgenda: The guilt for what we did to Enar \nhaunts me, I want to find a way to bring him \npeace.\nHans</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"The guilt for what we did to Enar \nhaunts me, I want to find a way to bring him \npeace.\nHans","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622688,"modifiedTime":1781557622688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"8iYfFojQvO0TpvNj","name":"Dark Waters","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"5WfrddevDIfCkK2x","name":"Dark Waters - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Frigid waters, animated by Blanca’s resentment of all living things, form a barrier to keep the Mother’s \nHeart safe.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 108.","positive":"Frigid waters, animated by Blanca’s resentment of all living things, form a barrier to keep the Mother’s \nHeart safe.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640070,"modifiedTime":1781557640070,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"aExVvpK8unR04NE1","name":"Gift - The Frigid Embrace of Death","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>When a subject \nplunges into the Dark Waters, they are attacked by the \nwater, which will try to enter their nose and mouth. If the \nsubject fails the Defense Check, they suffer 1 Wound from \nthe cold and lack of oxygen and become stuck in the water, \nunable to move. A successful Defense Check is required to \nget free and return to the surface or to descend into the \nDungeon. Singing the lullaby that Pepe knows causes the \nwaters to recede for one hour, allowing safe access. \nThe Dungeon</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 108.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640070,"modifiedTime":1781557640070,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qBkw4D5RYmdN13wP","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: Frigid waters, animated by Blanca’s resentment of all living things, form a barrier to keep the Mother’s \nHeart safe.\nGift - The Frigid Embrace of Death: When a subject \nplunges into the Dark Waters, they are attacked by the \nwater, which will try to enter their nose and mouth. If the \nsubject fails the Defense Check, they suffer 1 Wound from \nthe cold and lack of oxygen and become stuck in the water, \nunable to move. A successful Defense Check is required to \nget free and return to the surface or to descend into the \nDungeon. Singing the lullaby that Pepe knows causes the \nwaters to recede for one hour, allowing safe access. \nThe Dungeon\nDescriptor: A bare dungeon where the remains of six small \nbodies are huddled together. In the center of the room, a mass \nof plants, seabed debris, and animal bodies are formed into a \nheart that pulsates with malevolent energy.\nMorning, Afternoon, and Evening: The Mother’s \nHeart is the fulcrum that gives life to Blanca’s spirit and to \ndestroy it is to put an end to Mother Blanca de las Lágrimas.\nThe Mother’s Heart</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 108."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640070,"modifiedTime":1781557640070,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-dark-waters-108","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":108,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: Frigid waters, animated by Blanca’s resentment of all living things, form a barrier to keep the Mother’s \nHeart safe.\nGift - The Frigid Embrace of Death: When a subject \nplunges into the Dark Waters, they are attacked by the \nwater, which will try to enter their nose and mouth. If the \nsubject fails the Defense Check, they suffer 1 Wound from \nthe cold and lack of oxygen and become stuck in the water, \nunable to move. A successful Defense Check is required to \nget free and return to the surface or to descend into the \nDungeon. Singing the lullaby that Pepe knows causes the \nwaters to recede for one hour, allowing safe access. \nThe Dungeon\nDescriptor: A bare dungeon where the remains of six small \nbodies are huddled together. In the center of the room, a mass \nof plants, seabed debris, and animal bodies are formed into a \nheart that pulsates with malevolent energy.\nMorning, Afternoon, and Evening: The Mother’s \nHeart is the fulcrum that gives life to Blanca’s spirit and to \ndestroy it is to put an end to Mother Blanca de las Lágrimas.\nThe Mother’s Heart</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640070,"modifiedTime":1781557640070,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"8q8TLsIN8LcLgiu7","name":"Rotten Wreck","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"NKjueY9hC7c0EmMl","name":"Rotten Wreck - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Rotten wood can give way even under light \nweight.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 189.","positive":"Rotten wood can give way even under light \nweight.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644069,"modifiedTime":1781557644069,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ioE4r54V94sGo9kz","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: Rotten wood can give way even under light \nweight. \nGift - Splinters and Scrap: If a Defense Check fails, the \ntarget falls overboard and suffers 1 Wound, and the Storyteller gets 1 Wreck Token. When the number of Wreck \nTokens reaches 3, the ship collapses in on itself, burying \neverything inside.\nHidden among diary pages filled with uninteresting travel \nnotes are entries about the island.\nNote 1: Boyce followed the creature that destroyed his ship \nand discovered that its lair was east of the beach. \nNote 2: With a group of trusted sailors, Boyce headed to the \ncastle that towers in the center of the island in search of help. \nNote 3: The only survivor of the journey to the castle, Boyce \nwrites in shaky handwriting, asking God’s forgiveness for his \nsins and for the companions he had to leave behind to escape.\nNote 4: A knight in strange red armor roams the beach. Now \nlonely and desperate, Boyce decides to try his best to get his \nattention.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 189."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644069,"modifiedTime":1781557644069,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-rotten-wreck-189","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":189,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: Rotten wood can give way even under light \nweight. \nGift - Splinters and Scrap: If a Defense Check fails, the \ntarget falls overboard and suffers 1 Wound, and the Storyteller gets 1 Wreck Token. When the number of Wreck \nTokens reaches 3, the ship collapses in on itself, burying \neverything inside.\nHidden among diary pages filled with uninteresting travel \nnotes are entries about the island.\nNote 1: Boyce followed the creature that destroyed his ship \nand discovered that its lair was east of the beach. \nNote 2: With a group of trusted sailors, Boyce headed to the \ncastle that towers in the center of the island in search of help. \nNote 3: The only survivor of the journey to the castle, Boyce \nwrites in shaky handwriting, asking God’s forgiveness for his \nsins and for the companions he had to leave behind to escape.\nNote 4: A knight in strange red armor roams the beach. Now \nlonely and desperate, Boyce decides to try his best to get his \nattention.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644069,"modifiedTime":1781557644069,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"943mStPd9WOMvYcE","name":"The Hulder","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"5DJePHkaIA5kVZU6","name":"The Hulder - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an ancient forest spirit. I have eaten so many \nliving things that I have become fat and swollen, and the pieces \nof the animals and people I have devoured are dripping from my \nslobbering lips.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 190.","positive":"I am an ancient forest spirit. I have eaten so many \nliving things that I have become fat and swollen, and the pieces \nof the animals and people I have devoured are dripping from my \nslobbering lips.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623404,"modifiedTime":1781557623404,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"v0gskAe9U5i63cGu","name":"Gift - Corrupted Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The Hulder has a feminine form, \nbut her skin is spongy and slimy. Her breath smells of rot. She \ndoesn’t realize what a grotesque monster she has become, as in \nher mind she is still beautiful and seductive. When she suffers \n1 Wound, the Hulder vomits a cloud of foul vapor that reeks \nof rot. All the subjects hit by the cloud suffer 1 Wound in turn. \nThe effect of this Gift can be avoided with a Defense Check.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 190.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623404,"modifiedTime":1781557623404,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"M4tsHOMgubkhRhxY","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an ancient forest spirit. I have eaten so many \nliving things that I have become fat and swollen, and the pieces \nof the animals and people I have devoured are dripping from my \nslobbering lips.\nAgenda: Devour everything I meet.\nGift – Corrupted Spirit: The Hulder has a feminine form, \nbut her skin is spongy and slimy. Her breath smells of rot. She \ndoesn’t realize what a grotesque monster she has become, as in \nher mind she is still beautiful and seductive. When she suffers \n1 Wound, the Hulder vomits a cloud of foul vapor that reeks \nof rot. All the subjects hit by the cloud suffer 1 Wound in turn. \nThe effect of this Gift can be avoided with a Defense Check. \nGift – Swollen with Flesh and Blood: If killed, the Hulder \nwill emit a long, heart-breaking cry that will echo in the \nwoods, and all the dead she has eaten will scream in agony in a</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 190."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623404,"modifiedTime":1781557623404,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-the-hulder-190","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":190,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an ancient forest spirit. I have eaten so many \nliving things that I have become fat and swollen, and the pieces \nof the animals and people I have devoured are dripping from my \nslobbering lips.\nAgenda: Devour everything I meet.\nGift – Corrupted Spirit: The Hulder has a feminine form, \nbut her skin is spongy and slimy. Her breath smells of rot. She \ndoesn’t realize what a grotesque monster she has become, as in \nher mind she is still beautiful and seductive. When she suffers \n1 Wound, the Hulder vomits a cloud of foul vapor that reeks \nof rot. All the subjects hit by the cloud suffer 1 Wound in turn. \nThe effect of this Gift can be avoided with a Defense Check. \nGift – Swollen with Flesh and Blood: If killed, the Hulder \nwill emit a long, heart-breaking cry that will echo in the \nwoods, and all the dead she has eaten will scream in agony in a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Devour everything I meet.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623404,"modifiedTime":1781557623404,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"9itcPUuDWXmC5Zdo","name":"Anselm Wagner","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"v80LFw5LRl5wZ90i","name":"Anselm Wagner - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the most important person in the city, \ninvolved in politics and with many investments in various \nactivities. Everyone admires my efforts to make Heidelberg \nprosperous.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136.","positive":"I am the most important person in the city, \ninvolved in politics and with many investments in various \nactivities. Everyone admires my efforts to make Heidelberg \nprosperous.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mJQnH7EeA6smKpOm","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the most important person in the city, \ninvolved in politics and with many investments in various \nactivities. Everyone admires my efforts to make Heidelberg \nprosperous. \nAgenda: Keep an eye out for potential problems for the city \nand maintain a clean appearance. \n•\nArmsmen of the City</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-anselm-wagner-136","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":136,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the most important person in the city, \ninvolved in politics and with many investments in various \nactivities. Everyone admires my efforts to make Heidelberg \nprosperous. \nAgenda: Keep an eye out for potential problems for the city \nand maintain a clean appearance. \n•\nArmsmen of the City</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Keep an eye out for potential problems for the city \nand maintain a clean appearance. \n•\nArmsmen of the City","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"A9ctUKJhYEILk7NE","name":"Baba the Poor Conman","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ENRkaAj87EniKVZ6","name":"Baba the Poor Conman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a cunning, poor man who struggles to get \nby. My greed is matched only by my nerve.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 161.","positive":"I am a cunning, poor man who struggles to get \nby. My greed is matched only by my nerve.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642536,"modifiedTime":1781557642536,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WAHwE7TwejNsdXVQ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a cunning, poor man who struggles to get \nby. My greed is matched only by my nerve.\nAgenda: Use others to eliminate the remaining thieves and \nkeep the treasure all to myself.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 161."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642536,"modifiedTime":1781557642536,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-baba-the-poor-conman-161","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":161,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a cunning, poor man who struggles to get \nby. My greed is matched only by my nerve.\nAgenda: Use others to eliminate the remaining thieves and \nkeep the treasure all to myself.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Use others to eliminate the remaining thieves and \nkeep the treasure all to myself.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642536,"modifiedTime":1781557642536,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"AXQ4KJucw2vLFoCG","name":"The Alchemical Door","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"XB0otUapXecZos8j","name":"The Alchemical Door - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A precious ancient door that connects Rome to \nBorgo Maleanime. The One Who Plots in the Shadows is the \nonly one who knows the exact words to open the door.</p>","notes":"Rome, City of the Order - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 66.","positive":"A precious ancient door that connects Rome to \nBorgo Maleanime. The One Who Plots in the Shadows is the \nonly one who knows the exact words to open the door.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638382,"modifiedTime":1781557638382,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WqM7lIKDah1AcmPY","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A precious ancient door that connects Rome to \nBorgo Maleanime. The One Who Plots in the Shadows is the \nonly one who knows the exact words to open the door. \nGift - Magic Door: No Gift, magic, or effect can open the \ndoor, for the engraved seal draws its power directly from \nthe soul of the One Who Plots in the Shadows. The only \nway to open the door is to say the magical words A Fairytale Turned Upside Down . It is possible, however, to pass \npapers and envelopes under the doorframe, and this is how \nSilvan keeps his master informed of his discoveries. \nIf Silvan is present: The guide will tell you that the \nprevious owner of the villa was an eccentric Baron who \ndecided to live in a tree. Many say that the Baron’s ghost \nstill roams the streets of Rome, appearing some nights to \nfrighten passersby. The villa was bought for little money \nby a strange figure whose name no one remembers. The \nstranger came from the north, but after the purchase, he \ndid not spend a single night in the house.</p>","notes":"Rome, City of the Order - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 66."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638382,"modifiedTime":1781557638382,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-rome-city-of-the-order-the-alchemical-door-66","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"rome-city-of-the-order","adventureTitle":"Rome, City of the Order","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":66,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Rome, City of the Order","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A precious ancient door that connects Rome to \nBorgo Maleanime. The One Who Plots in the Shadows is the \nonly one who knows the exact words to open the door. \nGift - Magic Door: No Gift, magic, or effect can open the \ndoor, for the engraved seal draws its power directly from \nthe soul of the One Who Plots in the Shadows. The only \nway to open the door is to say the magical words A Fairytale Turned Upside Down . It is possible, however, to pass \npapers and envelopes under the doorframe, and this is how \nSilvan keeps his master informed of his discoveries. \nIf Silvan is present: The guide will tell you that the \nprevious owner of the villa was an eccentric Baron who \ndecided to live in a tree. Many say that the Baron’s ghost \nstill roams the streets of Rome, appearing some nights to \nfrighten passersby. The villa was bought for little money \nby a strange figure whose name no one remembers. The \nstranger came from the north, but after the purchase, he \ndid not spend a single night in the house.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638382,"modifiedTime":1781557638382,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Axj5S4ZXdBNtMwqW","name":"Althea the Agent of the Order","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"pL6kMfOGjgmCpXRg","name":"Althea the Agent of the Order - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a nun in the service of the Order and, \ndespite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and \na fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because \nit has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 99.","positive":"I am a nun in the service of the Order and, \ndespite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and \na fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because \nit has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626372,"modifiedTime":1781557626372,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"07CVUpiT6lpSeQc1","name":"Gift - Agent of the Order","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Althea is talented and trained to support the Hunters. Althea can spend her action to \nsupport a Hunter’s action and give them 1 Additional \nSuccess in any Check.\nThe Mist Roads</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 99.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626372,"modifiedTime":1781557626372,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PuGh6ZUoD7IritPw","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a nun in the service of the Order and, \ndespite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and \na fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because \nit has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.\nAgenda: Solve the mystery of the Maws and provide support \nto the Hunters of the Order.\nGift – Agent of the Order: Althea is talented and trained to support the Hunters. Althea can spend her action to \nsupport a Hunter’s action and give them 1 Additional \nSuccess in any Check.\nThe Mist Roads\nDescriptor: All the communication routes between Vík í \nMýrdal and the nearby villages are surrounded by a dense, \ndark fog that does not allow you to see more than a few feet \nahead.\nFor each trip on the Mist Roads, you can choose or roll for \na Threat/encounter with an NPC.\n1-2: A crevasse created by the eruption of Laki has \nopened up, barring the way.\nThreat – Crevasse in the Mist \nDescriptor: A crevasse eighteen feet deep, hidden by the \ndense mist.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 99."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626372,"modifiedTime":1781557626372,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-althea-the-agent-of-the-order-99","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":99,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a nun in the service of the Order and, \ndespite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and \na fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because \nit has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.\nAgenda: Solve the mystery of the Maws and provide support \nto the Hunters of the Order.\nGift – Agent of the Order: Althea is talented and trained to support the Hunters. Althea can spend her action to \nsupport a Hunter’s action and give them 1 Additional \nSuccess in any Check.\nThe Mist Roads\nDescriptor: All the communication routes between Vík í \nMýrdal and the nearby villages are surrounded by a dense, \ndark fog that does not allow you to see more than a few feet \nahead.\nFor each trip on the Mist Roads, you can choose or roll for \na Threat/encounter with an NPC.\n1-2: A crevasse created by the eruption of Laki has \nopened up, barring the way.\nThreat – Crevasse in the Mist \nDescriptor: A crevasse eighteen feet deep, hidden by the \ndense mist.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Solve the mystery of the Maws and provide support \nto the Hunters of the Order.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626372,"modifiedTime":1781557626372,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"BFkM7b0G1BkFToEC","name":"Enar","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"p4YtlbppoEbRaC1P","name":"Enar - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an immortal being, the result of all the \nhatred I harbored in my exile into the abyss. I have the \nstrength of five men and my body feels no pain.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","positive":"I am an immortal being, the result of all the \nhatred I harbored in my exile into the abyss. I have the \nstrength of five men and my body feels no pain.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fNvsqvaDqGYrXerL","name":"Gift - The Eternal Soldier","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Enar’s body is the result of \npowerful magic tainted by hatred. When Enar suffers his \nfinal Wound, his body becomes seawater and soaks into \nthe ground. The following day, Enar completely regenerates \nhimself at the bottom of the sea, where his heart is, the very \nfocus of his existence. Only by recovering the heart and \ndestroying it can Enar be permanently eliminated.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"poLwfRSaxSNBJ325","name":"Gift - Rage of the Sea","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to the magic granted by \nthe Sea Fairy, Enar has gained powers. When he acts, he \ncan always choose an additional effect. 1. Algae Whip: A \nstring of algae stretches from Enar’s body and can perform \na second independent action. 2. Wave: Enar’s body \nbecomes seawater for a few moments, allowing him to slip \naway and cover a distance of 30 feet before regrouping. \n3. Shells: 3 large seashells are shot from Enar’s body in \ndifferent directions, which should be considered 3 attacks</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4I2r81jISUb8XfrK","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an immortal being, the result of all the \nhatred I harbored in my exile into the abyss. I have the \nstrength of five men and my body feels no pain.\nAgenda: Take revenge on Andersen, but not before I have \neliminated all my former companions / After eliminating \nAndersen and his people, I want to meld with Satu so that \nour bodies and souls are united for eternity.\nGift - The Eternal Soldier: Enar’s body is the result of \npowerful magic tainted by hatred. When Enar suffers his \nfinal Wound, his body becomes seawater and soaks into \nthe ground. The following day, Enar completely regenerates \nhimself at the bottom of the sea, where his heart is, the very \nfocus of his existence. Only by recovering the heart and \ndestroying it can Enar be permanently eliminated. \nGift - Rage of the Sea: Thanks to the magic granted by \nthe Sea Fairy, Enar has gained powers. When he acts, he \ncan always choose an additional effect. 1. Algae Whip: A \nstring of algae stretches from Enar’s body and can perform \na second independent action. 2. Wave: Enar’s body \nbecomes seawater for a few moments, allowing him to slip \naway and cover a distance of 30 feet before regrouping. \n3. Shells: 3 large seashells are shot from Enar’s body in \ndifferent directions, which should be considered 3 attacks</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-enar-162","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":162,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an immortal being, the result of all the \nhatred I harbored in my exile into the abyss. I have the \nstrength of five men and my body feels no pain.\nAgenda: Take revenge on Andersen, but not before I have \neliminated all my former companions / After eliminating \nAndersen and his people, I want to meld with Satu so that \nour bodies and souls are united for eternity.\nGift - The Eternal Soldier: Enar’s body is the result of \npowerful magic tainted by hatred. When Enar suffers his \nfinal Wound, his body becomes seawater and soaks into \nthe ground. The following day, Enar completely regenerates \nhimself at the bottom of the sea, where his heart is, the very \nfocus of his existence. Only by recovering the heart and \ndestroying it can Enar be permanently eliminated. \nGift - Rage of the Sea: Thanks to the magic granted by \nthe Sea Fairy, Enar has gained powers. When he acts, he \ncan always choose an additional effect. 1. Algae Whip: A \nstring of algae stretches from Enar’s body and can perform \na second independent action. 2. Wave: Enar’s body \nbecomes seawater for a few moments, allowing him to slip \naway and cover a distance of 30 feet before regrouping. \n3. Shells: 3 large seashells are shot from Enar’s body in \ndifferent directions, which should be considered 3 attacks</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Take revenge on Andersen, but not before I have \neliminated all my former companions / After eliminating \nAndersen and his people, I want to meld with Satu so that \nour bodies and souls are united for eternity.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"BhqIT5i6j4eEMU4N","name":"Talia the Sleeper","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"OTY9HDlIiuOJdzWZ","name":"Talia the Sleeper - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the \nmagic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, \nthanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143.","positive":"I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the \nmagic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, \nthanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Lxg22KcLMcAKSRAE","name":"Gift - Sleeping Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Talia can literally manipulate the \nentire castle as she pleases. During each Exchange, she can \nperform up to 3 of the following actions. 1. Manipulate: \nMove or reshape an object of the castle into something else; \n2. Attack: Throw and move objects to inflict 1 Wound; \n3. Reject: Prevent people from moving, entering, or \nleaving by manipulating objects, or even the castle itself. \nTalia cannot speak, but she can use Manipulate to write or \ncompose rudimentary messages through objects. Talia can \nconcentrate all 3 actions into one with devastating effects. It \ncan collapse an entire wing of the castle or open a deep well \nin the ground. The effects of this action are wide-ranging and, \nat the discretion of the Storyteller, may remove one or more \nHunters who fail a Defense Check from the Scene.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UyCa5tnOggHju3kZ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the \nmagic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, \nthanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.\nAgenda: Revenge myself on Accursio, who betrayed my trust \nthe way so many others have / Finding peace through death, or \nassimilating everything I can with my power.\nGift – Sleeping Spirit: Talia can literally manipulate the \nentire castle as she pleases. During each Exchange, she can \nperform up to 3 of the following actions. 1. Manipulate: \nMove or reshape an object of the castle into something else; \n2. Attack: Throw and move objects to inflict 1 Wound; \n3. Reject: Prevent people from moving, entering, or \nleaving by manipulating objects, or even the castle itself. \nTalia cannot speak, but she can use Manipulate to write or \ncompose rudimentary messages through objects. Talia can \nconcentrate all 3 actions into one with devastating effects. It \ncan collapse an entire wing of the castle or open a deep well \nin the ground. The effects of this action are wide-ranging and, \nat the discretion of the Storyteller, may remove one or more \nHunters who fail a Defense Check from the Scene.\nInformation: Next to Talia’s sleeping body, one can find her \ndiary, written with a pen manipulated by her hair. It tells the \nSleeper’s whole sad story.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-talia-the-sleeper-143","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":143,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the \nmagic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, \nthanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.\nAgenda: Revenge myself on Accursio, who betrayed my trust \nthe way so many others have / Finding peace through death, or \nassimilating everything I can with my power.\nGift – Sleeping Spirit: Talia can literally manipulate the \nentire castle as she pleases. During each Exchange, she can \nperform up to 3 of the following actions. 1. Manipulate: \nMove or reshape an object of the castle into something else; \n2. Attack: Throw and move objects to inflict 1 Wound; \n3. Reject: Prevent people from moving, entering, or \nleaving by manipulating objects, or even the castle itself. \nTalia cannot speak, but she can use Manipulate to write or \ncompose rudimentary messages through objects. Talia can \nconcentrate all 3 actions into one with devastating effects. It \ncan collapse an entire wing of the castle or open a deep well \nin the ground. The effects of this action are wide-ranging and, \nat the discretion of the Storyteller, may remove one or more \nHunters who fail a Defense Check from the Scene.\nInformation: Next to Talia’s sleeping body, one can find her \ndiary, written with a pen manipulated by her hair. It tells the \nSleeper’s whole sad story.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Revenge myself on Accursio, who betrayed my trust \nthe way so many others have / Finding peace through death, or \nassimilating everything I can with my power.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"BliQMnFyozVnGJIS","name":"The Merchant","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"rjNNbXXEFgYlWa8T","name":"The Merchant - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a cunning old Merchant, I am a good \nmimic and I love to disguise myself.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 152.","positive":"I am a cunning old Merchant, I am a good \nmimic and I love to disguise myself.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642142,"modifiedTime":1781557642142,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"c5i9oJsf9TQbnBcB","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a cunning old Merchant, I am a good \nmimic and I love to disguise myself. \nAgenda: Escape the island by secretly boarding a ship, or \nfind a way to appease the Djinn’s wrath.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 152."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642143,"modifiedTime":1781557642143,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-the-merchant-152","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":152,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a cunning old Merchant, I am a good \nmimic and I love to disguise myself. \nAgenda: Escape the island by secretly boarding a ship, or \nfind a way to appease the Djinn’s wrath.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Escape the island by secretly boarding a ship, or \nfind a way to appease the Djinn’s wrath.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642143,"modifiedTime":1781557642143,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Btz7XLc4f1jmofVA","name":"Margareta the Good Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"wGpakceWbe7aioZb","name":"Margareta the Good Witch - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a capable witch who has devoted her life to \ncaring for the unfortunate. My body is wracked with disease, \nbut that doesn’t make me any less fearsome.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 227.","positive":"I am a capable witch who has devoted her life to \ncaring for the unfortunate. My body is wracked with disease, \nbut that doesn’t make me any less fearsome.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624294,"modifiedTime":1781557624294,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"IShv8JH6N23hdf7x","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a capable witch who has devoted her life to \ncaring for the unfortunate. My body is wracked with disease, \nbut that doesn’t make me any less fearsome.\nAgenda: Keep Gelb and everyone who lives there safe.\nGift - Witch: Margareta can draw on her witch power \nto create a Descriptor to represent the effect of her magic. \nHer abilities are related to manipulating emotions, such as \ninstilling fear or bestowing calm. The Descriptor thus created \nremains for the entire duration of a Scene. Alternatively, \nMargareta can move objects with the power of thought. These \nabilities can be used to hit someone from a distance, knock \nobjects out of someone’s hand, and generally manipulate the \nenvironment.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 227."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624294,"modifiedTime":1781557624294,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-margareta-the-good-witch-227","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":227,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a capable witch who has devoted her life to \ncaring for the unfortunate. My body is wracked with disease, \nbut that doesn’t make me any less fearsome.\nAgenda: Keep Gelb and everyone who lives there safe.\nGift - Witch: Margareta can draw on her witch power \nto create a Descriptor to represent the effect of her magic. \nHer abilities are related to manipulating emotions, such as \ninstilling fear or bestowing calm. The Descriptor thus created \nremains for the entire duration of a Scene. Alternatively, \nMargareta can move objects with the power of thought. These \nabilities can be used to hit someone from a distance, knock \nobjects out of someone’s hand, and generally manipulate the \nenvironment.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Keep Gelb and everyone who lives there safe.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624294,"modifiedTime":1781557624294,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CQxQ77TVe0URL7Xc","name":"Ice Layer","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"uwwQ6oynwf9OQUPJ","name":"Ice Layer - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A thick layer of steel-hard ice. \nEnd of Scene: The Hunters can head to Lady Storm’s castle, go to SECOND SCENE - Lady Storm’s Castle.\nSECOND SCENE – Lady Storm’s \nCastle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: In front of you is an ancient \ncastle that appears to be made entirely of ice. The large entrance door is open, and there seems to be no guard at all. As \nyou walk across the bridge, which is also frozen, a shiver runs \ndown your spine, and you know that the cold is not to blame. \nIt may sound crazy, but you feel a gaze directed at you, as if \nthe whole structure has a malevolent will of its own. \nPlace: Lady Storm’s Castle.\nTime: Early morning of a clear-sky day. \nInitial Situation: The castle is open, so it will be easy for \nthe Hunters to enter. Each room is completely covered in \nice, and moving around the structure takes time, considering there are over two hundred rooms.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 220.","positive":"A thick layer of steel-hard ice. \nEnd of Scene: The Hunters can head to Lady Storm’s castle, go to SECOND SCENE - Lady Storm’s Castle.\nSECOND SCENE – Lady Storm’s \nCastle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: In front of you is an ancient \ncastle that appears to be made entirely of ice. The large entrance door is open, and there seems to be no guard at all. As \nyou walk across the bridge, which is also frozen, a shiver runs \ndown your spine, and you know that the cold is not to blame. \nIt may sound crazy, but you feel a gaze directed at you, as if \nthe whole structure has a malevolent will of its own. \nPlace: Lady Storm’s Castle.\nTime: Early morning of a clear-sky day. \nInitial Situation: The castle is open, so it will be easy for \nthe Hunters to enter. Each room is completely covered in \nice, and moving around the structure takes time, considering there are over two hundred rooms.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645745,"modifiedTime":1781557645745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"h8CnjJ6t6swVnah3","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A thick layer of steel-hard ice. \nEnd of Scene: The Hunters can head to Lady Storm’s castle, go to SECOND SCENE - Lady Storm’s Castle.\nSECOND SCENE – Lady Storm’s \nCastle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: In front of you is an ancient \ncastle that appears to be made entirely of ice. The large entrance door is open, and there seems to be no guard at all. As \nyou walk across the bridge, which is also frozen, a shiver runs \ndown your spine, and you know that the cold is not to blame. \nIt may sound crazy, but you feel a gaze directed at you, as if \nthe whole structure has a malevolent will of its own. \nPlace: Lady Storm’s Castle.\nTime: Early morning of a clear-sky day. \nInitial Situation: The castle is open, so it will be easy for \nthe Hunters to enter. Each room is completely covered in \nice, and moving around the structure takes time, considering there are over two hundred rooms. \nInformation: Exploration of the castle is handled by \nEncounter Rooms, each with a different challenge for the \nHunters. These places represent the will of the Ice Heart \nto eliminate unwanted guests. After each Encounter Room, \nthe Hunters will wander through other neutral rooms, \nwhere they will find information about Lady Storm, the \ntrue owner of the castle. These rooms are important because they provide vital clues as to what kind of heat can \nscratch the Ice Heart, as explained on page 224.\n1\n2</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 220."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645745,"modifiedTime":1781557645745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-ice-layer-220","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":220,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A thick layer of steel-hard ice. \nEnd of Scene: The Hunters can head to Lady Storm’s castle, go to SECOND SCENE - Lady Storm’s Castle.\nSECOND SCENE – Lady Storm’s \nCastle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: In front of you is an ancient \ncastle that appears to be made entirely of ice. The large entrance door is open, and there seems to be no guard at all. As \nyou walk across the bridge, which is also frozen, a shiver runs \ndown your spine, and you know that the cold is not to blame. \nIt may sound crazy, but you feel a gaze directed at you, as if \nthe whole structure has a malevolent will of its own. \nPlace: Lady Storm’s Castle.\nTime: Early morning of a clear-sky day. \nInitial Situation: The castle is open, so it will be easy for \nthe Hunters to enter. Each room is completely covered in \nice, and moving around the structure takes time, considering there are over two hundred rooms. \nInformation: Exploration of the castle is handled by \nEncounter Rooms, each with a different challenge for the \nHunters. These places represent the will of the Ice Heart \nto eliminate unwanted guests. After each Encounter Room, \nthe Hunters will wander through other neutral rooms, \nwhere they will find information about Lady Storm, the \ntrue owner of the castle. These rooms are important because they provide vital clues as to what kind of heat can \nscratch the Ice Heart, as explained on page 224.\n1\n2</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645745,"modifiedTime":1781557645745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CSi3PSgrooXAP9l5","name":"Demonic Dogs","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"h2cafWw1SeG4rvrS","name":"Demonic Dogs - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are ancient demons and take the form of \ndogs to mingle with humans. We can fly and with our fangs, \nwe tear at the soft flesh of our prey.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 143.","positive":"We are ancient demons and take the form of \ndogs to mingle with humans. We can fly and with our fangs, \nwe tear at the soft flesh of our prey.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641729,"modifiedTime":1781557641729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jHHdK39wJomzekUu","name":"Gift - Demonic Powers","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>These creatures can fly, with \nall the narrative benefits that brings. As supernatural creatures, Demonic Dogs are immune to all effects of fear and \nmind manipulation. Those who use magic against them \ntake 1 Penalty to all related Checks and must pay 1 additional Soma if it is required to activate magic. A Demonic Dog \ncan spend 1 Reset Token to increase its OL to Hard 7 for a \nsingle action, but not to defend itself.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 143.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641729,"modifiedTime":1781557641729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"DK7xDqSNN3D5Xu9B","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC \n(2 Wounds - 3 Dogs)\nDescriptor: We are ancient demons and take the form of \ndogs to mingle with humans. We can fly and with our fangs, \nwe tear at the soft flesh of our prey. \nAgenda: To kill as many humans as possible and thereby \nincrease our power. \nGift - Demonic Powers: These creatures can fly, with \nall the narrative benefits that brings. As supernatural creatures, Demonic Dogs are immune to all effects of fear and \nmind manipulation. Those who use magic against them \ntake 1 Penalty to all related Checks and must pay 1 additional Soma if it is required to activate magic. A Demonic Dog \ncan spend 1 Reset Token to increase its OL to Hard 7 for a \nsingle action, but not to defend itself. \nInformation: When the Demonic Dogs are defeated, \nBritta or a witch who has read her diary can place a magical seal on the Magic Tinderbox: \nthe object will lose some of \nits power and become the \nTreasure of the Order, \nThe Tinderbox of Second Chances (see page \n28). \nScenario Gifts\nThese Gifts represent special abilities related to The Last \nWish Scenario and can be acquired once conditions are \nmet. A Hunter can acquire one Scenario Gift. If they acquire a new one during an Interlude, they will have to forgo \nthe previous one.\nDéjà vu \nRequirement: Witness the effect of one or more Resets.\nBy experiencing temporal shifts, you are able to notice the \nsmall differences in the fabric of reality. Once per Scene, \nyou can spend 1 Soma to activate each of the following effects:\n1. I’ve Already Got It: Y ou already have an item that belongs to the Place you are in, and if it is a unique item, no \none has noticed that it is missing.\n2. I Was Already Here: Y ou can move to any Place you \ncan see from where you are without anyone being able to \nstop you; to the eyes of anyone present, it will look as if you \nhave always been where you are now.\n3. I’ve Seen It Before: The Storyteller will reveal the \neffect of a particular Gift or equipment from an NPC in \nfront of you that you must have known or met before.\nNote: This Gift can only be used when the use of a \nspell that affects the normal flow of time is manifested, like a Reset. Outside of this Scenario, it is up \nto the Storyteller to determine if the Hunter can use \nthis Gift again.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 143."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641729,"modifiedTime":1781557641729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-demonic-dogs-143","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":143,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC \n(2 Wounds - 3 Dogs)\nDescriptor: We are ancient demons and take the form of \ndogs to mingle with humans. We can fly and with our fangs, \nwe tear at the soft flesh of our prey. \nAgenda: To kill as many humans as possible and thereby \nincrease our power. \nGift - Demonic Powers: These creatures can fly, with \nall the narrative benefits that brings. As supernatural creatures, Demonic Dogs are immune to all effects of fear and \nmind manipulation. Those who use magic against them \ntake 1 Penalty to all related Checks and must pay 1 additional Soma if it is required to activate magic. A Demonic Dog \ncan spend 1 Reset Token to increase its OL to Hard 7 for a \nsingle action, but not to defend itself. \nInformation: When the Demonic Dogs are defeated, \nBritta or a witch who has read her diary can place a magical seal on the Magic Tinderbox: \nthe object will lose some of \nits power and become the \nTreasure of the Order, \nThe Tinderbox of Second Chances (see page \n28). \nScenario Gifts\nThese Gifts represent special abilities related to The Last \nWish Scenario and can be acquired once conditions are \nmet. A Hunter can acquire one Scenario Gift. If they acquire a new one during an Interlude, they will have to forgo \nthe previous one.\nDéjà vu \nRequirement: Witness the effect of one or more Resets.\nBy experiencing temporal shifts, you are able to notice the \nsmall differences in the fabric of reality. Once per Scene, \nyou can spend 1 Soma to activate each of the following effects:\n1. I’ve Already Got It: Y ou already have an item that belongs to the Place you are in, and if it is a unique item, no \none has noticed that it is missing.\n2. I Was Already Here: Y ou can move to any Place you \ncan see from where you are without anyone being able to \nstop you; to the eyes of anyone present, it will look as if you \nhave always been where you are now.\n3. I’ve Seen It Before: The Storyteller will reveal the \neffect of a particular Gift or equipment from an NPC in \nfront of you that you must have known or met before.\nNote: This Gift can only be used when the use of a \nspell that affects the normal flow of time is manifested, like a Reset. Outside of this Scenario, it is up \nto the Storyteller to determine if the Hunter can use \nthis Gift again.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To kill as many humans as possible and thereby \nincrease our power.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641729,"modifiedTime":1781557641729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CUdwz0SJFHONcmNS","name":"Father Neron Lobo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"GPJdvt68Ejxe9LEX","name":"Father Neron Lobo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an exorcist priest who fights evil with the \npower of faith. Because of my rough and wild appearance, I \noften inspire fear, but I am a gentle and good-hearted person.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 102.","positive":"I am an exorcist priest who fights evil with the \npower of faith. Because of my rough and wild appearance, I \noften inspire fear, but I am a gentle and good-hearted person.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639852,"modifiedTime":1781557639852,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fcYFuMdE0rpiZuOV","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an exorcist priest who fights evil with the \npower of faith. Because of my rough and wild appearance, I \noften inspire fear, but I am a gentle and good-hearted person. \nAgenda: Save the children of Murcia from the threat of the \nMadre Blanca de las Lágrimas. \nGift - Exorcist Priest: Father Neron has the ability to \nperceive damned souls, which allows him to see and inter-act with all spiritual creatures. He can perform an exorcism \nand inflict 1 Wound on a target with the word Spirit in its \nprofile. No Defense Check can be made against this attack.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 102."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639852,"modifiedTime":1781557639852,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-father-neron-lobo-102","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":102,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an exorcist priest who fights evil with the \npower of faith. Because of my rough and wild appearance, I \noften inspire fear, but I am a gentle and good-hearted person. \nAgenda: Save the children of Murcia from the threat of the \nMadre Blanca de las Lágrimas. \nGift - Exorcist Priest: Father Neron has the ability to \nperceive damned souls, which allows him to see and inter-act with all spiritual creatures. He can perform an exorcism \nand inflict 1 Wound on a target with the word Spirit in its \nprofile. No Defense Check can be made against this attack.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Save the children of Murcia from the threat of the \nMadre Blanca de las Lágrimas.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639852,"modifiedTime":1781557639852,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Cfak53LI1UqEmQJH","name":"Amabile Burromo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"7ajV7A1ga746hMwX","name":"Amabile Burromo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled business owner \nand I manage my inn without delegating \nanything to anyone. I trust myself only.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137.","positive":"I am a skilled business owner \nand I manage my inn without delegating \nanything to anyone. I trust myself only.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"cwE3pteHfw4PR8LS","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled business owner \nand I manage my inn without delegating \nanything to anyone. I trust myself only.\nAgenda: To make profitable deals, \nwithout worrying about scruples.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-amabile-burromo-137","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":137,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled business owner \nand I manage my inn without delegating \nanything to anyone. I trust myself only.\nAgenda: To make profitable deals, \nwithout worrying about scruples.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To make profitable deals, \nwithout worrying about scruples.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"D3HmPhY5jdaqUYvt","name":"(Opponent Dark Presence)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"DWnIPJzaFxnRNcOA","name":"(Opponent Dark Presence) - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>That of the original NPC.</p>","notes":"One Thousand and One Nightmares - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 198.","positive":"That of the original NPC.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623612,"modifiedTime":1781557623612,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2bHSngfzxoGu139F","name":"Gift - Variable","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The Shadow has all the Gifts of the \noriginal NPC.</p>","notes":"One Thousand and One Nightmares - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 198.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623612,"modifiedTime":1781557623612,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HWVcBdogIIJiQcNC","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: That of the original NPC.\nAgenda: Interfering with and impeding the path of the \nHunters of the Order, preventing them from achieving their \nmission.\nGift - Variable: The Shadow has all the Gifts of the \noriginal NPC. \nGift - Shadow Body: A Shadow is a darker, sadder \nversion of the original. They can speak and behave like \nthe character they are modelled after, but on a careful \ninspection they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per \nScene, a Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness \nby moving through walls and other solid obstacles. When \nit spawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element</p>","notes":"One Thousand and One Nightmares - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 198."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623612,"modifiedTime":1781557623612,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-one-thousand-and-one-nightmares-opponent-dark-presence-198","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","adventureTitle":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":198,"role":"Scenario Actor"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","origin":"Core Book","role":"Scenario Actor","notes":"<p>– (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: That of the original NPC.\nAgenda: Interfering with and impeding the path of the \nHunters of the Order, preventing them from achieving their \nmission.\nGift - Variable: The Shadow has all the Gifts of the \noriginal NPC. \nGift - Shadow Body: A Shadow is a darker, sadder \nversion of the original. They can speak and behave like \nthe character they are modelled after, but on a careful \ninspection they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per \nScene, a Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness \nby moving through walls and other solid obstacles. When \nit spawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Interfering with and impeding the path of the \nHunters of the Order, preventing them from achieving their \nmission.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623612,"modifiedTime":1781557623612,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"DN0U23LnG3Wj9k9M","name":"City Chaos","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"1zdqs6gs3rDBLpUS","name":"City Chaos - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Murcia is a big city, full of narrow streets and \nalways full of busy people.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 99.","positive":"Murcia is a big city, full of narrow streets and \nalways full of busy people.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639711,"modifiedTime":1781557639711,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"iHxeNYqVmn02HYyA","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: Murcia is a big city, full of narrow streets and \nalways full of busy people. \nGift - Time Waste: By Failing a Check against this \nThreat, the Hunters fall victim to the city’s confusion and \ntheir trip takes longer than planned, so they arrive at a later time slot. A Positive Outcome means the Hunters arrive \nat their goal destination one time slot after their departure \n(e.g., leave in the Morning and arrive in the Afternoon). A \nFailed Check delays the Hunter’s arrival by one time slot, so \nthat their journey takes two periods of the day (e.g., leave \nin the Morning, arrive in the Evening). Failing the Check, \nhowever, allows the Hunters to learn one of the rumors circulating in the city. The Storyteller rolls a die or can choose \nwhich rumor reaches the Hunters’ ears:\n1: The Bats are a gang of street urchins who regularly steal \nfrom the city’s merchants. The seven brats who make up \nthe gang live in the old Clock Tower, and though many residents turn a blind eye to their misdeeds, it seems that some \nnobles are planning to raid the Tower and put an \nend to the gang. \n2: A new priest has recently arrived in the \ncity, but he does not seem to have taken up his \nministry in any of the churches open to the \nfaithful. The stranger is a burly, rude-looking \nfellow who lives in an old Monastery that no \none has used in decades.\n3: A dark rumor describes a ghost that \nhaunts Murcia during November. Parents \nmust be very careful with their children \nbecause the Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas \nwanders among the living in the guise of a</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 99."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639711,"modifiedTime":1781557639711,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-city-chaos-99","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":99,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: Murcia is a big city, full of narrow streets and \nalways full of busy people. \nGift - Time Waste: By Failing a Check against this \nThreat, the Hunters fall victim to the city’s confusion and \ntheir trip takes longer than planned, so they arrive at a later time slot. A Positive Outcome means the Hunters arrive \nat their goal destination one time slot after their departure \n(e.g., leave in the Morning and arrive in the Afternoon). A \nFailed Check delays the Hunter’s arrival by one time slot, so \nthat their journey takes two periods of the day (e.g., leave \nin the Morning, arrive in the Evening). Failing the Check, \nhowever, allows the Hunters to learn one of the rumors circulating in the city. The Storyteller rolls a die or can choose \nwhich rumor reaches the Hunters’ ears:\n1: The Bats are a gang of street urchins who regularly steal \nfrom the city’s merchants. The seven brats who make up \nthe gang live in the old Clock Tower, and though many residents turn a blind eye to their misdeeds, it seems that some \nnobles are planning to raid the Tower and put an \nend to the gang. \n2: A new priest has recently arrived in the \ncity, but he does not seem to have taken up his \nministry in any of the churches open to the \nfaithful. The stranger is a burly, rude-looking \nfellow who lives in an old Monastery that no \none has used in decades.\n3: A dark rumor describes a ghost that \nhaunts Murcia during November. Parents \nmust be very careful with their children \nbecause the Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas \nwanders among the living in the guise of a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639711,"modifiedTime":1781557639711,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"DWsYtsKilMiq8I2d","name":"Helga the Red Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"iSy9ZLS9bPI3YnKJ","name":"Helga the Red Witch - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a powerful witch and I use blood to \nperform my spells. Drinking one drop of my blood is enough \nto become my slave.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 236.","positive":"I am a powerful witch and I use blood to \nperform my spells. Drinking one drop of my blood is enough \nto become my slave.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624545,"modifiedTime":1781557624545,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"d5ci0tvR0DF44rTQ","name":"Gift - Blood Magic","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Helga can unleash her powers to \naffect the blood of one or more subjects, inflicting 1 Wound \nor commanding their movements. Whoever has swallowed \nHelga’s blood is totally subject to her will. It is possible to \nresist the effects of Blood Magic with a Defense Check, \nbut this does not eliminate Helga’s magic. Drinking the \nInfusion of Purity renders anyone immune to Blood Magic \nfor the course of a Scene and cancels the crowd control. \nThose under the influence of the Blood Magic have a slight \ncrimson tinge to their eyes.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 236.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624545,"modifiedTime":1781557624545,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mMLFY0AsWIpsTaHk","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful witch and I use blood to \nperform my spells. Drinking one drop of my blood is enough \nto become my slave.\nAgenda: Accumulating power and collecting the four pieces \nof the Compass Rose thanks to the information obtained \nfrom OZena’s sacrifice / I am always willing to make an \nadvantageous deal, even if this leads me to revise my plans. I \nwould do anything to live forever.\nGift - Blood Magic: Helga can unleash her powers to \naffect the blood of one or more subjects, inflicting 1 Wound \nor commanding their movements. Whoever has swallowed \nHelga’s blood is totally subject to her will. It is possible to \nresist the effects of Blood Magic with a Defense Check, \nbut this does not eliminate Helga’s magic. Drinking the \nInfusion of Purity renders anyone immune to Blood Magic \nfor the course of a Scene and cancels the crowd control. \nThose under the influence of the Blood Magic have a slight \ncrimson tinge to their eyes.\nGift - Blood Witch: Helga is made young and immortal \nby blood magic. At the end of each of her actions and if hurt,</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 236."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624545,"modifiedTime":1781557624545,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-helga-the-red-witch-236","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":236,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful witch and I use blood to \nperform my spells. Drinking one drop of my blood is enough \nto become my slave.\nAgenda: Accumulating power and collecting the four pieces \nof the Compass Rose thanks to the information obtained \nfrom OZena’s sacrifice / I am always willing to make an \nadvantageous deal, even if this leads me to revise my plans. I \nwould do anything to live forever.\nGift - Blood Magic: Helga can unleash her powers to \naffect the blood of one or more subjects, inflicting 1 Wound \nor commanding their movements. Whoever has swallowed \nHelga’s blood is totally subject to her will. It is possible to \nresist the effects of Blood Magic with a Defense Check, \nbut this does not eliminate Helga’s magic. Drinking the \nInfusion of Purity renders anyone immune to Blood Magic \nfor the course of a Scene and cancels the crowd control. \nThose under the influence of the Blood Magic have a slight \ncrimson tinge to their eyes.\nGift - Blood Witch: Helga is made young and immortal \nby blood magic. At the end of each of her actions and if hurt,</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Accumulating power and collecting the four pieces \nof the Compass Rose thanks to the information obtained \nfrom OZena’s sacrifice / I am always willing to make an \nadvantageous deal, even if this leads me to revise my plans. I \nwould do anything to live forever.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624545,"modifiedTime":1781557624545,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Detkbj4ut9gjHrSo","name":"Manycorpses","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"BQbR52xfvrQW6BDl","name":"Manycorpses - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an abomination created by Helga’s \nexperiments, in which she has united all her lovers into one. \nI hate anyone who still has a normal body and I use my \nincredible power to destroy them.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 234.","positive":"I am an abomination created by Helga’s \nexperiments, in which she has united all her lovers into one. \nI hate anyone who still has a normal body and I use my \nincredible power to destroy them.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624482,"modifiedTime":1781557624482,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7yDSmKI9gW884NdW","name":"Gift - Aberration","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Manycorpses can act twice during an \nExchange. Thanks to its multiple arms it can move on any \nsurface.\nEnd of Scene: After being freed, the greenhouse workers \nreveal that Helga is able to control people’s bodies with her \nblood magic. Something called the Infusion of Purity, a \npotion, can lift the curse. Helga is producing the Infusion \nbecause she plans to sell the antidote to rich and powerful \nnobles after poisoning them with her magical blood. To \ncomplete the Infusion, however, Elderberry is required, \nthough the ingredient does not grow in this area. A strange \ngirl in a green cape has stolen the small stash Helga had \nbrought back from her last trip.\nGo to the THIRD SCENE - The Dolls’ Court.\nTHIRD SCENE – The Dolls’ \nCourt\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You come to a bleak, \ndilapidated village made up of small, ruined houses and \nbrightly colored tents. Men and women in an evident state of \ndistress lie sprawled along the streets. From their tired eyes, \nyou understand that they are exhausted by the incessant work \nHelga magically forces them to do. Suddenly, figures wearing \ngrotesque doll masks appear and head in your direction, \ndrawing their weapons.\nPlace: The dilapidated village of Rot.\nTime: The sun is setting, but time seems to have stopped \nin the small village.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 234.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624482,"modifiedTime":1781557624482,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ALMYJuMP1hRIfDY8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an abomination created by Helga’s \nexperiments, in which she has united all her lovers into one. \nI hate anyone who still has a normal body and I use my \nincredible power to destroy them.\nAgenda: Kill and dismember any human that comes within \nrange.\nGift - Aberration: Manycorpses can act twice during an \nExchange. Thanks to its multiple arms it can move on any \nsurface.\nEnd of Scene: After being freed, the greenhouse workers \nreveal that Helga is able to control people’s bodies with her \nblood magic. Something called the Infusion of Purity, a \npotion, can lift the curse. Helga is producing the Infusion \nbecause she plans to sell the antidote to rich and powerful \nnobles after poisoning them with her magical blood. To \ncomplete the Infusion, however, Elderberry is required, \nthough the ingredient does not grow in this area. A strange \ngirl in a green cape has stolen the small stash Helga had \nbrought back from her last trip.\nGo to the THIRD SCENE - The Dolls’ Court.\nTHIRD SCENE – The Dolls’ \nCourt\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You come to a bleak, \ndilapidated village made up of small, ruined houses and \nbrightly colored tents. Men and women in an evident state of \ndistress lie sprawled along the streets. From their tired eyes, \nyou understand that they are exhausted by the incessant work \nHelga magically forces them to do. Suddenly, figures wearing \ngrotesque doll masks appear and head in your direction, \ndrawing their weapons.\nPlace: The dilapidated village of Rot.\nTime: The sun is setting, but time seems to have stopped \nin the small village.\nInformation:\n ◆ The Porcelain Dolls are the only individuals worth \ntalking to. They will initially have their guard up, but if \nthe Hunters are convincing, they will be brought to the \nPorcelain Princess.\n ◆ The village is just an old, dilapidated logging settlement. \nNot far away, it is possible to see a noble’s mansion \nwhere Helga now resides.\n ◆ No one can come before Helga without the approval of \nthe Porcelain Princess, her favorite.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 234."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624482,"modifiedTime":1781557624482,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-manycorpses-234","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":234,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an abomination created by Helga’s \nexperiments, in which she has united all her lovers into one. \nI hate anyone who still has a normal body and I use my \nincredible power to destroy them.\nAgenda: Kill and dismember any human that comes within \nrange.\nGift - Aberration: Manycorpses can act twice during an \nExchange. Thanks to its multiple arms it can move on any \nsurface.\nEnd of Scene: After being freed, the greenhouse workers \nreveal that Helga is able to control people’s bodies with her \nblood magic. Something called the Infusion of Purity, a \npotion, can lift the curse. Helga is producing the Infusion \nbecause she plans to sell the antidote to rich and powerful \nnobles after poisoning them with her magical blood. To \ncomplete the Infusion, however, Elderberry is required, \nthough the ingredient does not grow in this area. A strange \ngirl in a green cape has stolen the small stash Helga had \nbrought back from her last trip.\nGo to the THIRD SCENE - The Dolls’ Court.\nTHIRD SCENE – The Dolls’ \nCourt\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You come to a bleak, \ndilapidated village made up of small, ruined houses and \nbrightly colored tents. Men and women in an evident state of \ndistress lie sprawled along the streets. From their tired eyes, \nyou understand that they are exhausted by the incessant work \nHelga magically forces them to do. Suddenly, figures wearing \ngrotesque doll masks appear and head in your direction, \ndrawing their weapons.\nPlace: The dilapidated village of Rot.\nTime: The sun is setting, but time seems to have stopped \nin the small village.\nInformation:\n ◆ The Porcelain Dolls are the only individuals worth \ntalking to. They will initially have their guard up, but if \nthe Hunters are convincing, they will be brought to the \nPorcelain Princess.\n ◆ The village is just an old, dilapidated logging settlement. \nNot far away, it is possible to see a noble’s mansion \nwhere Helga now resides.\n ◆ No one can come before Helga without the approval of \nthe Porcelain Princess, her favorite.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Kill and dismember any human that comes within \nrange.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624482,"modifiedTime":1781557624482,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"DmOmEJScBxcNf3Ba","name":"Nikola’s Bats","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Y1IrHBDYFqk3NfYt","name":"Nikola’s Bats - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are a swarm of bats ready to devour any intruder.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 126.","positive":"We are a swarm of bats ready to devour any intruder.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640775,"modifiedTime":1781557640775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QJI7HkLIPvBQrCem","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (5 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are a swarm of bats ready to devour any intruder. \nAgenda: Protect Nikola while he sleeps.\nGift - Swarm: Bats are considered a single unit with 5 Wounds. \nAny damage dealt reduces the total by 1, and attacks that hit an \narea inflict 1 additional Wound. As a swarm, Nikola’s Bats can \nbite up to 3 different targets in a single action. The flapping \nof the Bats’ wings causes discomfort to living creatures: \nas the swarm rises, each Hunter present loses 2 Soma, \nwhile NPCs suffer 1 Wound from fatigue.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 126."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640775,"modifiedTime":1781557640775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-nikola-s-bats-126","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":126,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (5 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are a swarm of bats ready to devour any intruder. \nAgenda: Protect Nikola while he sleeps.\nGift - Swarm: Bats are considered a single unit with 5 Wounds. \nAny damage dealt reduces the total by 1, and attacks that hit an \narea inflict 1 additional Wound. As a swarm, Nikola’s Bats can \nbite up to 3 different targets in a single action. The flapping \nof the Bats’ wings causes discomfort to living creatures: \nas the swarm rises, each Hunter present loses 2 Soma, \nwhile NPCs suffer 1 Wound from fatigue.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":5},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Protect Nikola while he sleeps.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640775,"modifiedTime":1781557640775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"DpAvVdabWtuttDlW","name":"The God Under the Mine","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"T1fDQhyfDe2jRqiV","name":"The God Under the Mine - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a creature as old as the world, trapped \nbeneath the bedrock. Millennia of inactivity have made me \ncatatonic and there is nothing that can really wake me up. \nOnly pain can stir me even slightly.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","positive":"I am a creature as old as the world, trapped \nbeneath the bedrock. Millennia of inactivity have made me \ncatatonic and there is nothing that can really wake me up. \nOnly pain can stir me even slightly.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"NRcWzz44W5k7lex4","name":"Gift - The Head of the God","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Only the enormous head of \nthe God emerges from the rock, and pieces of meat can be \nobtained from it. When he suffers 1 Wound, the God emits \na loud grunt that sends everyone flying (a Defense Check \ncan avoid this). As an additional effect of the grunt, the \nGod’s fetid breath taints the air, granting 1 Penalty to the \nnext action of all affected subjects, excluding Arthur. When \nreduced to 0 Wounds, the God falls into a deep sleep to \nfully regenerate in the following Scene.\nSpawn of The God Under the \nMine</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WrILwwQwACeD1Qzp","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a creature as old as the world, trapped \nbeneath the bedrock. Millennia of inactivity have made me \ncatatonic and there is nothing that can really wake me up. \nOnly pain can stir me even slightly.\nGift - The Head of the God: Only the enormous head of \nthe God emerges from the rock, and pieces of meat can be \nobtained from it. When he suffers 1 Wound, the God emits \na loud grunt that sends everyone flying (a Defense Check \ncan avoid this). As an additional effect of the grunt, the \nGod’s fetid breath taints the air, granting 1 Penalty to the \nnext action of all affected subjects, excluding Arthur. When \nreduced to 0 Wounds, the God falls into a deep sleep to \nfully regenerate in the following Scene.\nSpawn of The God Under the \nMine</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-the-god-under-the-mine-212","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":212,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a creature as old as the world, trapped \nbeneath the bedrock. Millennia of inactivity have made me \ncatatonic and there is nothing that can really wake me up. \nOnly pain can stir me even slightly.\nGift - The Head of the God: Only the enormous head of \nthe God emerges from the rock, and pieces of meat can be \nobtained from it. When he suffers 1 Wound, the God emits \na loud grunt that sends everyone flying (a Defense Check \ncan avoid this). As an additional effect of the grunt, the \nGod’s fetid breath taints the air, granting 1 Penalty to the \nnext action of all affected subjects, excluding Arthur. When \nreduced to 0 Wounds, the God falls into a deep sleep to \nfully regenerate in the following Scene.\nSpawn of The God Under the \nMine</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"E0CCV33Xx42RXLZj","name":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"a1ukQAzwrX61MYWD","name":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a restless spirit, bound to the memory of \nmy granddaughter. My condition as a spirit does not allow \nme to communicate with the living except through dreams, \nwhispers, and visions.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 125.","positive":"I am a restless spirit, bound to the memory of \nmy granddaughter. My condition as a spirit does not allow \nme to communicate with the living except through dreams, \nwhispers, and visions.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621392,"modifiedTime":1781557621392,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8sOWyUG4gYVgCtI3","name":"Gift - Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Anastazia is a spirit and can only be damaged \nby magic. She may appear in a dream to a target, who may \nresist with a Defense Check or accept contact voluntarily. \nThe target suffers 1 Wound from stress but will receive from \nAnastazia a vision of a present or past event with a barely \nwhispered phrase.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 125.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621392,"modifiedTime":1781557621392,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jXH4WZxHDJbfkm6x","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a restless spirit, bound to the memory of \nmy granddaughter. My condition as a spirit does not allow \nme to communicate with the living except through dreams, \nwhispers, and visions.\nAgenda: Preventing further harm to Iskra and find a way to \nsave my granddaughter’s soul.\nGift - Spirit: Anastazia is a spirit and can only be damaged \nby magic. She may appear in a dream to a target, who may \nresist with a Defense Check or accept contact voluntarily. \nThe target suffers 1 Wound from stress but will receive from \nAnastazia a vision of a present or past event with a barely \nwhispered phrase.\nGift - Loving Grandmother: Anastazia always follows \nIskra and protects her from danger. Thanks to her strong \nwill, she can interact with the material world by moving \nobjects and manipulating the environment, even inflicting \na Wound on a target. If a subject is likely to help save her \ngranddaughter, Anastazia will simply fill their mind with \nmemories of her.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 125."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621392,"modifiedTime":1781557621392,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-anastazia-the-sorrowful-spirit-125","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":125,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a restless spirit, bound to the memory of \nmy granddaughter. My condition as a spirit does not allow \nme to communicate with the living except through dreams, \nwhispers, and visions.\nAgenda: Preventing further harm to Iskra and find a way to \nsave my granddaughter’s soul.\nGift - Spirit: Anastazia is a spirit and can only be damaged \nby magic. She may appear in a dream to a target, who may \nresist with a Defense Check or accept contact voluntarily. \nThe target suffers 1 Wound from stress but will receive from \nAnastazia a vision of a present or past event with a barely \nwhispered phrase.\nGift - Loving Grandmother: Anastazia always follows \nIskra and protects her from danger. Thanks to her strong \nwill, she can interact with the material world by moving \nobjects and manipulating the environment, even inflicting \na Wound on a target. If a subject is likely to help save her \ngranddaughter, Anastazia will simply fill their mind with \nmemories of her.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Preventing further harm to Iskra and find a way to \nsave my granddaughter’s soul.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621392,"modifiedTime":1781557621392,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"E4thHxU24DMKBcjx","name":"The Count Azul of Vigo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Q1DzS1sL8qI1CnKr","name":"The Count Azul of Vigo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a rich and bored nobleman who \ncares only about social position.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 154.","positive":"I am a rich and bored nobleman who \ncares only about social position.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"smQSNiZvsGwpWh9T","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and bored nobleman who \ncares only about social position. \nAgenda: To waste time between parties and \npleasures, leaving the burden of leadership to my wife \nPrincesca.\nCinder Known to all as \nPrincesca of Vigo</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 154."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-the-count-azul-of-vigo-154","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":154,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and bored nobleman who \ncares only about social position. \nAgenda: To waste time between parties and \npleasures, leaving the burden of leadership to my wife \nPrincesca.\nCinder Known to all as \nPrincesca of Vigo</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To waste time between parties and \npleasures, leaving the burden of leadership to my wife \nPrincesca.\nCinder Known to all as \nPrincesca of Vigo","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"EOhiwVbwk3tBSATI","name":"Ostromir Malý","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ePo5hRRBbPhlrnKt","name":"Ostromir Malý - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria \nTheresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the \npalm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my \nlife, though so far the noble families support my authority.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 166.","positive":"I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria \nTheresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the \npalm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my \nlife, though so far the noble families support my authority.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"I4qCtyJFoBBeYaMR","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria \nTheresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the \npalm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my \nlife, though so far the noble families support my authority.\nAgenda: Capture the assassin who is causing panic among \nthe nobles / Avoid a popular uprising.\nBeáta Czernin the Noblewoman</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 166."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-ostromir-mal-166","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":166,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria \nTheresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the \npalm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my \nlife, though so far the noble families support my authority.\nAgenda: Capture the assassin who is causing panic among \nthe nobles / Avoid a popular uprising.\nBeáta Czernin the Noblewoman</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Capture the assassin who is causing panic among \nthe nobles / Avoid a popular uprising.\nBeáta Czernin the Noblewoman","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ElolsV3Y4uWwYuCU","name":"Azzurra The Spirit of the Witch who Spurns Death","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"SrRcobNcHPZfkxyv","name":"Azzurra The Spirit of the Witch who Spurns Death - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the spirit of an old and powerful witch. My powers allow \nme to summon the souls of the dead and bind them to my will.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 139.","positive":"I am the spirit of an old and powerful witch. My powers allow \nme to summon the souls of the dead and bind them to my will.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621905,"modifiedTime":1781557621905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XDnhwPucDqNLPHmJ","name":"Gift - Ancient Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Azzurra’s body is immaterial and can only be \ndamaged by magic. Azzurra can interact with the world by evoking the souls \nof the dead, choosing between various effects. 1. Poltergeist: Throw up to \n3 objects at once. The force with which the objects are thrown is such that \nthey can cause a Wound. 2. Cacophony of the Dead: Frighten everyone \nwith the agonized voices of the damned. Anyone who hears the cacophony \nmust pass a Defense Check or lose 2 Soma points. 3. Possession: Take \npossession of a target’s body and cause them to perform a single action, \nalbeit not a self-destructive one. Azzurra must change the spirits’ effect with \neach action and must use all three before she can use an effect again.\nThe Secret Laboratory</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 139.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621905,"modifiedTime":1781557621905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dYHYrz7fLsEe8AYQ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the spirit of an old and powerful witch. My powers allow \nme to summon the souls of the dead and bind them to my will. \nAgenda: To come back to life thanks to Carlo’s power.\nGift - Ancient Spirit: Azzurra’s body is immaterial and can only be \ndamaged by magic. Azzurra can interact with the world by evoking the souls \nof the dead, choosing between various effects. 1. Poltergeist: Throw up to \n3 objects at once. The force with which the objects are thrown is such that \nthey can cause a Wound. 2. Cacophony of the Dead: Frighten everyone \nwith the agonized voices of the damned. Anyone who hears the cacophony \nmust pass a Defense Check or lose 2 Soma points. 3. Possession: Take \npossession of a target’s body and cause them to perform a single action, \nalbeit not a self-destructive one. Azzurra must change the spirits’ effect with \neach action and must use all three before she can use an effect again.\nThe Secret Laboratory\nDescriptor: The cellar of Villa Cilesterino, converted into an alchemical \nlaboratory by Antonio. The smell of wine and mold is unbearable.\nInformation: \n ◆ Antonio continues his research under Azzurra’s guidance. This led him \nto create a magical brazier in which Carlo is to be burned.\n ◆ Nino, the carpenter’s apprentice, is tied to a table, alive but with his legs \nnow ruined by Antonio’s slow flaying. Azzurra wants him kept alive, as \nshe needs innocent blood for the rite.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 139."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621905,"modifiedTime":1781557621905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-azzurra-the-spirit-of-the-witch-who-spurns-death-139","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":139,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the spirit of an old and powerful witch. My powers allow \nme to summon the souls of the dead and bind them to my will. \nAgenda: To come back to life thanks to Carlo’s power.\nGift - Ancient Spirit: Azzurra’s body is immaterial and can only be \ndamaged by magic. Azzurra can interact with the world by evoking the souls \nof the dead, choosing between various effects. 1. Poltergeist: Throw up to \n3 objects at once. The force with which the objects are thrown is such that \nthey can cause a Wound. 2. Cacophony of the Dead: Frighten everyone \nwith the agonized voices of the damned. Anyone who hears the cacophony \nmust pass a Defense Check or lose 2 Soma points. 3. Possession: Take \npossession of a target’s body and cause them to perform a single action, \nalbeit not a self-destructive one. Azzurra must change the spirits’ effect with \neach action and must use all three before she can use an effect again.\nThe Secret Laboratory\nDescriptor: The cellar of Villa Cilesterino, converted into an alchemical \nlaboratory by Antonio. The smell of wine and mold is unbearable.\nInformation: \n ◆ Antonio continues his research under Azzurra’s guidance. This led him \nto create a magical brazier in which Carlo is to be burned.\n ◆ Nino, the carpenter’s apprentice, is tied to a table, alive but with his legs \nnow ruined by Antonio’s slow flaying. Azzurra wants him kept alive, as \nshe needs innocent blood for the rite.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"To come back to life thanks to Carlo’s power.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621905,"modifiedTime":1781557621905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"EqmrHgu42Me1etMj","name":"Uther Pendragon","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"8SDPdxLDataQTT8x","name":"Uther Pendragon - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an experienced knight and a great strategist. I am too old for war now, but that will not stop me from \nsaving my kingdom.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 194.","positive":"I am an experienced knight and a great strategist. I am too old for war now, but that will not stop me from \nsaving my kingdom.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644240,"modifiedTime":1781557644240,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HO4Hw799LElPFXtX","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (0 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an experienced knight and a great strategist. I am too old for war now, but that will not stop me from \nsaving my kingdom.\nAgenda: Protect Camelot and bring Arthur to his senses so \nthat he can once again be a worthy ruler of these lands. \nInformation: Uther is dying, and even if he is saved, it \nwill be clear that his injuries are fatal. Before he breathes \nhis last, however, the old man will reveal important details \nto the Hunters.\n ◆ Arthur was always a good ruler, as long as Merlin remained at his side as an advisor. Uther, however, could \nalways see envy in the Sorcerer’s eyes, envy for the \nyoung king that was his protégé. When Merlin suddenly disappeared, Arthur went mad and lost all the traits \nthat made him a righteous and benevolent man.\n ◆ In the southeast, past the great Lake, lies an old Abandoned House. Arthur spent his childhood there, and \nUther is convinced that the spirit of all that is good in \nhis son’s heart dwells there.\n ◆ There is a secret passage to enter the Camelot Castle. It \nis located inside a large oak tree that has been struck by \nlightning. From there, an underground tunnel leads to \nthe hall of the Round Table. \nZone 8 – Camelot Castle\nDescription: Camelot Castle appears to be an ancient \nabandoned ruin, with only the cackling of soldiers preparing for war revealing that it is still inhabited. Knights and \nvillagers alike are busy crafting weapons and war machines. \nInformation: Arthur is in the hall of the Round Table, \nwhere he sits with his most trusted Knights. There are thirteen seats in total, one is occupied by Arthur, and one is \nempty as it belongs to Merlin. There are then eleven more \nKnights (page 181), but for every Empty Seat Token that \nthe Hunters have collected, the number is reduced by one. \nWithout his Virtues, Arthur is an invading madman whose \ngoal is the conquest of Europe, second only to finding his \nbeloved Guinevere. Arthur’s behavior is greatly influenced \nby finding the Virtue of Wisdom (page 194).</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 194."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644240,"modifiedTime":1781557644240,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-uther-pendragon-194","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":194,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (0 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an experienced knight and a great strategist. I am too old for war now, but that will not stop me from \nsaving my kingdom.\nAgenda: Protect Camelot and bring Arthur to his senses so \nthat he can once again be a worthy ruler of these lands. \nInformation: Uther is dying, and even if he is saved, it \nwill be clear that his injuries are fatal. Before he breathes \nhis last, however, the old man will reveal important details \nto the Hunters.\n ◆ Arthur was always a good ruler, as long as Merlin remained at his side as an advisor. Uther, however, could \nalways see envy in the Sorcerer’s eyes, envy for the \nyoung king that was his protégé. When Merlin suddenly disappeared, Arthur went mad and lost all the traits \nthat made him a righteous and benevolent man.\n ◆ In the southeast, past the great Lake, lies an old Abandoned House. Arthur spent his childhood there, and \nUther is convinced that the spirit of all that is good in \nhis son’s heart dwells there.\n ◆ There is a secret passage to enter the Camelot Castle. It \nis located inside a large oak tree that has been struck by \nlightning. From there, an underground tunnel leads to \nthe hall of the Round Table. \nZone 8 – Camelot Castle\nDescription: Camelot Castle appears to be an ancient \nabandoned ruin, with only the cackling of soldiers preparing for war revealing that it is still inhabited. Knights and \nvillagers alike are busy crafting weapons and war machines. \nInformation: Arthur is in the hall of the Round Table, \nwhere he sits with his most trusted Knights. There are thirteen seats in total, one is occupied by Arthur, and one is \nempty as it belongs to Merlin. There are then eleven more \nKnights (page 181), but for every Empty Seat Token that \nthe Hunters have collected, the number is reduced by one. \nWithout his Virtues, Arthur is an invading madman whose \ngoal is the conquest of Europe, second only to finding his \nbeloved Guinevere. Arthur’s behavior is greatly influenced \nby finding the Virtue of Wisdom (page 194).</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":0},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Protect Camelot and bring Arthur to his senses so \nthat he can once again be a worthy ruler of these lands.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644240,"modifiedTime":1781557644240,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FQS2dO9SA5cYIOWc","name":"Vincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"v95tXvsxGrY3uyZI","name":"Vincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms \nabout doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life \nwithout working so hard.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122.","positive":"I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms \nabout doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life \nwithout working so hard.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RrMHx8oa7VIHM70J","name":"Gift - Veteran","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Vincent is skilled in taking advantage \nof any situation. When he has the support of at least two \nof his men, every action against him receives 1 Penalty \nand Vincent can inflict 1 additional Wound.\nThe Guards of Gerard Dubois</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PMpGXwATE0dUsgGb","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms \nabout doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life \nwithout working so hard.\nAgenda: I understand how the world works and who \nreally runs the Dubois household. Pleasing Elizaveta is the \nbest way to maintain my status.\nGift - Veteran: Vincent is skilled in taking advantage \nof any situation. When he has the support of at least two \nof his men, every action against him receives 1 Penalty \nand Vincent can inflict 1 additional Wound.\nThe Guards of Gerard Dubois</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-vincent-arn-former-huntsman-and-chief-of-the-guards-122","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":122,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms \nabout doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life \nwithout working so hard.\nAgenda: I understand how the world works and who \nreally runs the Dubois household. Pleasing Elizaveta is the \nbest way to maintain my status.\nGift - Veteran: Vincent is skilled in taking advantage \nof any situation. When he has the support of at least two \nof his men, every action against him receives 1 Penalty \nand Vincent can inflict 1 additional Wound.\nThe Guards of Gerard Dubois</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I understand how the world works and who \nreally runs the Dubois household. Pleasing Elizaveta is the \nbest way to maintain my status.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FaMGvGQBVQr3gyS9","name":"Nature Rises Up","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"v7gpNO9TWLz7EYan","name":"Nature Rises Up - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae \nexposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to \nblock those who walk without their lady’s approval.\nMtyrya the Fairy also called the \nCauldron Fae</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 85.","positive":"Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae \nexposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to \nblock those who walk without their lady’s approval.\nMtyrya the Fairy also called the \nCauldron Fae","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"nWKNO1L19tKkpH2u","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae \nexposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to \nblock those who walk without their lady’s approval.\nMtyrya the Fairy also called the \nCauldron Fae</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 85."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-nature-rises-up-85","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":85,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae \nexposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to \nblock those who walk without their lady’s approval.\nMtyrya the Fairy also called the \nCauldron Fae</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FaUuRuYnM40gvpT8","name":"Francisca and Marta the Vengeful Sisters","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"xnsQsB5RLk0eom5r","name":"Francisca and Marta the Vengeful Sisters - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two poor sisters sewn together in one \nbody. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate \neffortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 157.","positive":"We are two poor sisters sewn together in one \nbody. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate \neffortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637117,"modifiedTime":1781557637117,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"V4dZzI201IN4xNQD","name":"Gift - The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to \nthe magical slippers the Kind Mother gave them, at every \nstep Francisca and Marta can click the glass heels and create \na resonance that generates a state of confusion in subjects \nwithin forty feet. When a Hunter acts under the influence \nof the Slippers, they must perform a Defense Check against</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 157.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637117,"modifiedTime":1781557637117,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RafpHmj6TC7QMIc8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are two poor sisters sewn together in one \nbody. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate \neffortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger. \nAgenda: Discredit Princesca and reveal to everyone that \nshe is Cinder, our despised sister.\nGift – The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers: Thanks to \nthe magical slippers the Kind Mother gave them, at every \nstep Francisca and Marta can click the glass heels and create \na resonance that generates a state of confusion in subjects \nwithin forty feet. When a Hunter acts under the influence \nof the Slippers, they must perform a Defense Check against</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 157."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637117,"modifiedTime":1781557637117,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-francisca-and-marta-the-vengeful-sisters-157","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":157,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are two poor sisters sewn together in one \nbody. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate \neffortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger. \nAgenda: Discredit Princesca and reveal to everyone that \nshe is Cinder, our despised sister.\nGift – The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers: Thanks to \nthe magical slippers the Kind Mother gave them, at every \nstep Francisca and Marta can click the glass heels and create \na resonance that generates a state of confusion in subjects \nwithin forty feet. When a Hunter acts under the influence \nof the Slippers, they must perform a Defense Check against</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Discredit Princesca and reveal to everyone that \nshe is Cinder, our despised sister.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637117,"modifiedTime":1781557637117,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FdPWtUCbcwUe2XWL","name":"Ice Soldier","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"6twiKN1X9kVn9TUC","name":"Ice Soldier - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a soldier made entirely of ice and I defend \nLady Storm’s castle. My priority is to always focus on the targets that make the most noise.\nENCOUNTER ROOM – Col-umns Walk\nDescriptor: A very long corridor leads into the heart of \nLady Storm’s castle. A series of ice pillars divides the corridor, \nand in them, you can see the silhouettes of trapped people.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 222.","positive":"I am a soldier made entirely of ice and I defend \nLady Storm’s castle. My priority is to always focus on the targets that make the most noise.\nENCOUNTER ROOM – Col-umns Walk\nDescriptor: A very long corridor leads into the heart of \nLady Storm’s castle. A series of ice pillars divides the corridor, \nand in them, you can see the silhouettes of trapped people.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645979,"modifiedTime":1781557645979,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"zFMjlZvTK9zqqxzL","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a soldier made entirely of ice and I defend \nLady Storm’s castle. My priority is to always focus on the targets that make the most noise.\nENCOUNTER ROOM – Col-umns Walk\nDescriptor: A very long corridor leads into the heart of \nLady Storm’s castle. A series of ice pillars divides the corridor, \nand in them, you can see the silhouettes of trapped people. \nInformation: The trapped people are mostly treasure \nseekers, but if you look closely, you can see some of the \nBergen nobles. It will be clear to the Hunters that the sick \npeople who made it to the castle are trapped inside the columns. The columns are difficult to melt, and the people \ninside them are dead. Approaching a column without an \noccupant will activate Threat - Columns of Eternal Sleep.\n Threat – Columns of Eternal Sleep</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 222."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645979,"modifiedTime":1781557645979,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-ice-soldier-222","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":222,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a soldier made entirely of ice and I defend \nLady Storm’s castle. My priority is to always focus on the targets that make the most noise.\nENCOUNTER ROOM – Col-umns Walk\nDescriptor: A very long corridor leads into the heart of \nLady Storm’s castle. A series of ice pillars divides the corridor, \nand in them, you can see the silhouettes of trapped people. \nInformation: The trapped people are mostly treasure \nseekers, but if you look closely, you can see some of the \nBergen nobles. It will be clear to the Hunters that the sick \npeople who made it to the castle are trapped inside the columns. The columns are difficult to melt, and the people \ninside them are dead. Approaching a column without an \noccupant will activate Threat - Columns of Eternal Sleep.\n Threat – Columns of Eternal Sleep</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645979,"modifiedTime":1781557645979,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FhyUF3wGPgFm5zf9","name":"Britta the Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ytqyiadAK6OkGYZz","name":"Britta the Witch - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled witch who wishes only to live a \nquiet life, using my powers only to help others.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 142.","positive":"I am a skilled witch who wishes only to live a \nquiet life, using my powers only to help others.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641698,"modifiedTime":1781557641698,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2igh5qdNbHeFzfBu","name":"Gift - Britta’s Witchcraft","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Britta can perform various \nrituals to achieve different effects: she can find someone or \nsomething, she can change the weather in the area, or she \ncan communicate with and take control of an animal. All of \nthese rituals take about ten minutes to complete. Britta can \nalso dispel magic, a practice in which she is a true master. \nIn a single action, Britta can end a spell or block the power \nof a Treasure of the Order until the end of the Scene.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 142.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641698,"modifiedTime":1781557641698,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8xmKR6NcCYFV4Sw3","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled witch who wishes only to live a \nquiet life, using my powers only to help others.\nAgenda: Stop the power of the Magic Tinderbox before the \nDemonic Dogs inside it become too powerful. \nGift - Britta’s Witchcraft: Britta can perform various \nrituals to achieve different effects: she can find someone or \nsomething, she can change the weather in the area, or she \ncan communicate with and take control of an animal. All of \nthese rituals take about ten minutes to complete. Britta can \nalso dispel magic, a practice in which she is a true master. \nIn a single action, Britta can end a spell or block the power \nof a Treasure of the Order until the end of the Scene. \nInformation: Britta will tell the Hunters the secret of the \nMagic Tinderbox and that she can use her magic to stop the \ndisasters Bastian is causing, but there is a catch. Once the \nMagic Tinderbox’s power is blocked, the three Demonic \nDogs inside will be released and must be defeated to send \nthem back into the magical object.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 142."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641698,"modifiedTime":1781557641698,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-britta-the-witch-142","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":142,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled witch who wishes only to live a \nquiet life, using my powers only to help others.\nAgenda: Stop the power of the Magic Tinderbox before the \nDemonic Dogs inside it become too powerful. \nGift - Britta’s Witchcraft: Britta can perform various \nrituals to achieve different effects: she can find someone or \nsomething, she can change the weather in the area, or she \ncan communicate with and take control of an animal. All of \nthese rituals take about ten minutes to complete. Britta can \nalso dispel magic, a practice in which she is a true master. \nIn a single action, Britta can end a spell or block the power \nof a Treasure of the Order until the end of the Scene. \nInformation: Britta will tell the Hunters the secret of the \nMagic Tinderbox and that she can use her magic to stop the \ndisasters Bastian is causing, but there is a catch. Once the \nMagic Tinderbox’s power is blocked, the three Demonic \nDogs inside will be released and must be defeated to send \nthem back into the magical object.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Stop the power of the Magic Tinderbox before the \nDemonic Dogs inside it become too powerful.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641698,"modifiedTime":1781557641698,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FmCI0DPoPWEDpot9","name":"Ravn","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"rJPjmL0QhT3DnXv0","name":"Ravn - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled assassin, and my throwing \nknives can hit a target even in total darkness.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 210.","positive":"I am a skilled assassin, and my throwing \nknives can hit a target even in total darkness.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645318,"modifiedTime":1781557645318,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4AD4D3qKoKTgQx3P","name":"Gift - The Raven","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, Ravn can transform \ninto a raven and escape by flying away. If he makes a sur -\nprise attack, Ravn inflicts 1 Additional Wound.\nKråke</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 210.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645318,"modifiedTime":1781557645318,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xGPy1eZd7s9PZHlX","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled assassin, and my throwing \nknives can hit a target even in total darkness. \nAgenda: Escort those who have paid the correct amount to \nthe White Hospital / Eliminate any potential threat to Gerda \nand Kay’s business. \nGift - The Raven: Once per Scene, Ravn can transform \ninto a raven and escape by flying away. If he makes a sur -\nprise attack, Ravn inflicts 1 Additional Wound.\nKråke</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 210."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645318,"modifiedTime":1781557645318,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-ravn-210","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":210,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled assassin, and my throwing \nknives can hit a target even in total darkness. \nAgenda: Escort those who have paid the correct amount to \nthe White Hospital / Eliminate any potential threat to Gerda \nand Kay’s business. \nGift - The Raven: Once per Scene, Ravn can transform \ninto a raven and escape by flying away. If he makes a sur -\nprise attack, Ravn inflicts 1 Additional Wound.\nKråke</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Escort those who have paid the correct amount to \nthe White Hospital / Eliminate any potential threat to Gerda \nand Kay’s business.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645318,"modifiedTime":1781557645318,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FmoeOJTuXpMjnwHN","name":"Sister Esperanza","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"J0Iv9GU3ErLBKhC4","name":"Sister Esperanza - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young nun who has dedicated her life \nto helping others. I follow Father Neron in his crusade against \nevil and am willing to give my life to save the innocent.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 107.","positive":"I am a young nun who has dedicated her life \nto helping others. I follow Father Neron in his crusade against \nevil and am willing to give my life to save the innocent.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640056,"modifiedTime":1781557640056,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Cm1oSaFsYsVAeq9V","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young nun who has dedicated her life \nto helping others. I follow Father Neron in his crusade against \nevil and am willing to give my life to save the innocent. \nAgenda: Helping Father Neron and taking care of the children in the Monastery.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 107."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640056,"modifiedTime":1781557640056,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-sister-esperanza-107","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":107,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young nun who has dedicated her life \nto helping others. I follow Father Neron in his crusade against \nevil and am willing to give my life to save the innocent. \nAgenda: Helping Father Neron and taking care of the children in the Monastery.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Helping Father Neron and taking care of the children in the Monastery.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640056,"modifiedTime":1781557640056,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"FxfgNMMiWALQdDwe","name":"Pietro Gonsalva Regent of Capodimonte","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"kUxdiLNGAGDAIHCW","name":"Pietro Gonsalva Regent of Capodimonte - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have \nmanaged to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being \nin charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more \nexperienced than I am.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 125.","positive":"I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have \nmanaged to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being \nin charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more \nexperienced than I am.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629741,"modifiedTime":1781557629741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1s0t1KveqH0bavht","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have \nmanaged to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being \nin charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more \nexperienced than I am.\nAgenda: Preserve the House of Roses because it is the first \nplace where Dionysus appears to be restrained / Not to lose the \nadvantageous agreements made with the Church.\nInformation from the conversation with Pietro: \nThe Regent of Capodimonte will welcome the Hunters with \nall honors, praising their importance to the Church and for \nhumanity’ salvation. Pietro is sincerely respectful of the work \nof the Order. \n ◆ Pietro will say that the island was once a monastery and \nthat, thanks to the efforts of his son Dionysus, it has now \nreturned to a renewed splendor.\n ◆ Martana Island has become a place of worship, where \npeople can take refuge and contemplate God.\n ◆ Pietro cares a lot about the House of Roses because \nhis son Dionysus is suffering from a rare disease that \ncovers his whole body with hair and, unfortunately, his \nmonstrous aspect is not accepted by society. To Pietro, it</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 125."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629741,"modifiedTime":1781557629741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-pietro-gonsalva-regent-of-capodimonte-125","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":125,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have \nmanaged to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being \nin charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more \nexperienced than I am.\nAgenda: Preserve the House of Roses because it is the first \nplace where Dionysus appears to be restrained / Not to lose the \nadvantageous agreements made with the Church.\nInformation from the conversation with Pietro: \nThe Regent of Capodimonte will welcome the Hunters with \nall honors, praising their importance to the Church and for \nhumanity’ salvation. Pietro is sincerely respectful of the work \nof the Order. \n ◆ Pietro will say that the island was once a monastery and \nthat, thanks to the efforts of his son Dionysus, it has now \nreturned to a renewed splendor.\n ◆ Martana Island has become a place of worship, where \npeople can take refuge and contemplate God.\n ◆ Pietro cares a lot about the House of Roses because \nhis son Dionysus is suffering from a rare disease that \ncovers his whole body with hair and, unfortunately, his \nmonstrous aspect is not accepted by society. To Pietro, it</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Preserve the House of Roses because it is the first \nplace where Dionysus appears to be restrained / Not to lose the \nadvantageous agreements made with the Church.\nInformation from the conversation with Pietro: \nThe Regent of Capodimonte will welcome the Hunters with \nall honors, praising their importance to the Church and for \nhumanity’ salvation. Pietro is sincerely respectful of the work \nof the Order. \n ◆ Pietro will say that the island was once a monastery and \nthat, thanks to the efforts of his son Dionysus, it has now \nreturned to a renewed splendor.\n ◆ Martana Island has become a place of worship, where \npeople can take refuge and contemplate God.\n ◆ Pietro cares a lot about the House of Roses because \nhis son Dionysus is suffering from a rare disease that \ncovers his whole body with hair and, unfortunately, his \nmonstrous aspect is not accepted by society. To Pietro, it","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629741,"modifiedTime":1781557629741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"GDn0zbg4p4WkoayP","name":"Miss Snow","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"vuGZ06Efp04frOJi","name":"Miss Snow - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an apprentice ice mage, although I often cause disasters with \nmy powers. I am naive and always kind to others.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 227.","positive":"I am an apprentice ice mage, although I often cause disasters with \nmy powers. I am naive and always kind to others.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646296,"modifiedTime":1781557646296,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"JE0zqoTVrJstiuAh","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an apprentice ice mage, although I often cause disasters with \nmy powers. I am naive and always kind to others. \n \nGift – Snow Sorceress Apprentice: Miss Snow can use the Gifts of the \nSnow Sorceress and Winter’s Kiss, but when she does, she rolls a die, and \nif she rolls a 4 or higher, a magical disaster (determined by the Storyteller) \noccurs, complicating the situation.\nDescriptors and Gifts\nI am a powerful ice sorceress and can manipulate the weather. I want \nSnow to learn to be a Hunter, so I limit the use of my powers to solving \nproblems for her. \n• Snow Sorceress: Y ou can use magic to create and manipulate the cold. \nDescribe the effects of a spell that has one of the following Keywords as a condition: Ice, Snow, or Frost. Y ou could, for example, Create an Ice Bridge \nto cross a crevasse or Freeze an Enemy to immobilize it. Pay a cost of 1 to 2 \nSoma, decided by the Storyteller, to activate the spell. The effects you describe \nlast until the end of the Scene. The Soma cost is increased by 1 when environmental conditions are not compatible with cold.\nI am impassive and know how to assert my authority, nothing can \nshake my heart. I have a weakness for those who show true love or \nfriendship, and it comes naturally to me to help these people, although \nI do not want anyone to notice this weakness of mine. \n• Winter’s Kiss: In you lies the power of winter. When you give someone \na chaste kiss, you can choose one of the following effects:\n1. Erase one of their memories. It must be the memory of an event in the Scene \nin which you use this effect. Particularly capable Hunters and NPCs may require a Position Check for the effect to succeed.\n2. Make the subject immune to cold for the rest of the Scene. This will prevent \nthem from suffering Wounds from frost and make them immune to the effects \nof the Snow Sorceress Gift. \n3. Make an object extremely fragile. \nY ou can spend 1 Soma when you use this Gift to blow a kiss to the target, thus \navoiding physical contact.\nI have a special insight into understanding people and their intentions, \nand with my magic, I can quickly create help for the weak. I dislike people who talk too much and social events. \n• Dark Ego - Deus Ex Machina: When all seems lost, use your magic \nto make truth triumph. Reduce by 1 the Soma cost of spells you cast with \nthe Gift of the Snow Sorceress when your goal is to help someone. Once per \nExchange, you can spend 1 Soma to prevent one of your allies from taking \n1 Wound by protecting them with a wall of icy frost. Y ou can use the Gift of \nWinter’s Kiss as a free action once per Exchange.\nActivator: Step in and show your power to save a good-hearted person from the \ndanger that threatens them.\nEquipment\nA brooch in the shape of a sleigh / A small knife with an ice blade that never \nmelts / A scarf handmade by Miss Snow / Books of magic / A mirror fragment \nwith a strange magical aura.\nSoma\n 5\nPX\nLady Storm and \nMiss Snow\nIam a powerful witch who rules over winter and frost. Because of a betrayal, I was robbed of my \nbody for a long time and a new personality was created in me: Miss Snow. As much as I hate to admit \nit, it is thanks to Miss Snow that I have regained my full strength, and I intend to help her find her way. Thanks to my magic, I have given her a body, and now we are like twins: identical in appearance, \nbut profoundly different in character. Snow has agreed to remain in the ranks of the Order, and until she is able to fend for herself, I will watch over her. \nSpecial: Miss Snow is an NPC under the complete control of the Storyteller. Lady Storm guards over her on her missions on behalf of the Order. \nWounds \n1.\n2.\n3.\nAdditional \nWound.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 227."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646296,"modifiedTime":1781557646296,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-miss-snow-227","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":227,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>- (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an apprentice ice mage, although I often cause disasters with \nmy powers. I am naive and always kind to others. \n \nGift – Snow Sorceress Apprentice: Miss Snow can use the Gifts of the \nSnow Sorceress and Winter’s Kiss, but when she does, she rolls a die, and \nif she rolls a 4 or higher, a magical disaster (determined by the Storyteller) \noccurs, complicating the situation.\nDescriptors and Gifts\nI am a powerful ice sorceress and can manipulate the weather. I want \nSnow to learn to be a Hunter, so I limit the use of my powers to solving \nproblems for her. \n• Snow Sorceress: Y ou can use magic to create and manipulate the cold. \nDescribe the effects of a spell that has one of the following Keywords as a condition: Ice, Snow, or Frost. Y ou could, for example, Create an Ice Bridge \nto cross a crevasse or Freeze an Enemy to immobilize it. Pay a cost of 1 to 2 \nSoma, decided by the Storyteller, to activate the spell. The effects you describe \nlast until the end of the Scene. The Soma cost is increased by 1 when environmental conditions are not compatible with cold.\nI am impassive and know how to assert my authority, nothing can \nshake my heart. I have a weakness for those who show true love or \nfriendship, and it comes naturally to me to help these people, although \nI do not want anyone to notice this weakness of mine. \n• Winter’s Kiss: In you lies the power of winter. When you give someone \na chaste kiss, you can choose one of the following effects:\n1. Erase one of their memories. It must be the memory of an event in the Scene \nin which you use this effect. Particularly capable Hunters and NPCs may require a Position Check for the effect to succeed.\n2. Make the subject immune to cold for the rest of the Scene. This will prevent \nthem from suffering Wounds from frost and make them immune to the effects \nof the Snow Sorceress Gift. \n3. Make an object extremely fragile. \nY ou can spend 1 Soma when you use this Gift to blow a kiss to the target, thus \navoiding physical contact.\nI have a special insight into understanding people and their intentions, \nand with my magic, I can quickly create help for the weak. I dislike people who talk too much and social events. \n• Dark Ego - Deus Ex Machina: When all seems lost, use your magic \nto make truth triumph. Reduce by 1 the Soma cost of spells you cast with \nthe Gift of the Snow Sorceress when your goal is to help someone. Once per \nExchange, you can spend 1 Soma to prevent one of your allies from taking \n1 Wound by protecting them with a wall of icy frost. Y ou can use the Gift of \nWinter’s Kiss as a free action once per Exchange.\nActivator: Step in and show your power to save a good-hearted person from the \ndanger that threatens them.\nEquipment\nA brooch in the shape of a sleigh / A small knife with an ice blade that never \nmelts / A scarf handmade by Miss Snow / Books of magic / A mirror fragment \nwith a strange magical aura.\nSoma\n 5\nPX\nLady Storm and \nMiss Snow\nIam a powerful witch who rules over winter and frost. Because of a betrayal, I was robbed of my \nbody for a long time and a new personality was created in me: Miss Snow. As much as I hate to admit \nit, it is thanks to Miss Snow that I have regained my full strength, and I intend to help her find her way. Thanks to my magic, I have given her a body, and now we are like twins: identical in appearance, \nbut profoundly different in character. Snow has agreed to remain in the ranks of the Order, and until she is able to fend for herself, I will watch over her. \nSpecial: Miss Snow is an NPC under the complete control of the Storyteller. Lady Storm guards over her on her missions on behalf of the Order. \nWounds \n1.\n2.\n3.\nAdditional \nWound.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646296,"modifiedTime":1781557646296,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"GEI9e3XyOywYFwlb","name":"Survivors of the First Expedition","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"jCSOXotmOD9epzTD","name":"Survivors of the First Expedition - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are Crown agents on the run, terrified by \nthe danger of the island.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 181.","positive":"We are Crown agents on the run, terrified by \nthe danger of the island.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643710,"modifiedTime":1781557643710,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"f4k72lOIeDZwjyIT","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are Crown agents on the run, terrified by \nthe danger of the island.\nAgenda: To be able to escape from this cursed island.\nInformation: At each encounter, 1d6 Survivors will be \navailable to talk about an adjacent Zone from which they \nare fleeing. The Storyteller decides what information the \nSurvivors have. When talking about the previous expedition, the Survivors will tell you that as soon as they docked \non the beach (Zone 2 - Beach page 188), the ship was attacked by a huge creature that they describe as a collection \nof different animals. The crew fled in all directions, scattering across the island as the ship was destroyed. Captain \nBoyce, who was in command of the ship, heroically stayed \nbehind to wrestle with the creature so that everyone could \nescape.\nSaxon Marauders</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 181."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643710,"modifiedTime":1781557643710,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-survivors-of-the-first-expedition-181","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":181,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are Crown agents on the run, terrified by \nthe danger of the island.\nAgenda: To be able to escape from this cursed island.\nInformation: At each encounter, 1d6 Survivors will be \navailable to talk about an adjacent Zone from which they \nare fleeing. The Storyteller decides what information the \nSurvivors have. When talking about the previous expedition, the Survivors will tell you that as soon as they docked \non the beach (Zone 2 - Beach page 188), the ship was attacked by a huge creature that they describe as a collection \nof different animals. The crew fled in all directions, scattering across the island as the ship was destroyed. Captain \nBoyce, who was in command of the ship, heroically stayed \nbehind to wrestle with the creature so that everyone could \nescape.\nSaxon Marauders</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To be able to escape from this cursed island.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643710,"modifiedTime":1781557643710,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"GSZV0gIfXbhRN4HJ","name":"Hugo the Potter","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"djoM3goMAxauxIpB","name":"Hugo the Potter - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an honest craftsman and have been a \npotter all my life. I have a friendly nature and tend to trust \npeople. \nHeidelberg’s Entrance Plaza\nDescriptor: A large square always filled with citizens and \ntravelers.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 135.","positive":"I am an honest craftsman and have been a \npotter all my life. I have a friendly nature and tend to trust \npeople. \nHeidelberg’s Entrance Plaza\nDescriptor: A large square always filled with citizens and \ntravelers.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641396,"modifiedTime":1781557641396,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"aHjt3cnOA0v1Ja5R","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am an honest craftsman and have been a \npotter all my life. I have a friendly nature and tend to trust \npeople. \nHeidelberg’s Entrance Plaza\nDescriptor: A large square always filled with citizens and \ntravelers. \nInformation: As the first Place that Bastian will use the \nMagic Tinderbox to escape the Hunters, this is where the \nHunters will start again after each Reset. Unlike normal humans, the Hunters will retain a memory of what happened \nat each Reset.\nFirst Reset: The Hunters will notice that some powerful \nmagic has taken effect, and time seems to have rewound \nto a few minutes before they meet Bastian. The deserter is \nabsent, but Hugo the Potter is behind his stall, smiling at \npassersby. The Black Cat walks between the legs of one of \nthe Hunters, stops to watch them with intelligent eyes, and \nthen walks away. \nSecond Reset: Same as the First Reset, except the Cat \nwill stop with the Hunters and try to get them to follow her, \nleading them to Britta’s house.\nThird Reset: Like the First Reset, but this time the Hunters will find Anselm Wagner waiting for them with an \nescort of ten gendarmes. The nobleman will tell the Hunters that he has received a report from a trusted man about \ntheir impending arrival in the city. The nobleman has made \nno request of the Order and wants no trouble, so he will \nask the Hunters to leave. It will be clear that Anselm has</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 135."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641396,"modifiedTime":1781557641396,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-hugo-the-potter-135","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":135,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am an honest craftsman and have been a \npotter all my life. I have a friendly nature and tend to trust \npeople. \nHeidelberg’s Entrance Plaza\nDescriptor: A large square always filled with citizens and \ntravelers. \nInformation: As the first Place that Bastian will use the \nMagic Tinderbox to escape the Hunters, this is where the \nHunters will start again after each Reset. Unlike normal humans, the Hunters will retain a memory of what happened \nat each Reset.\nFirst Reset: The Hunters will notice that some powerful \nmagic has taken effect, and time seems to have rewound \nto a few minutes before they meet Bastian. The deserter is \nabsent, but Hugo the Potter is behind his stall, smiling at \npassersby. The Black Cat walks between the legs of one of \nthe Hunters, stops to watch them with intelligent eyes, and \nthen walks away. \nSecond Reset: Same as the First Reset, except the Cat \nwill stop with the Hunters and try to get them to follow her, \nleading them to Britta’s house.\nThird Reset: Like the First Reset, but this time the Hunters will find Anselm Wagner waiting for them with an \nescort of ten gendarmes. The nobleman will tell the Hunters that he has received a report from a trusted man about \ntheir impending arrival in the city. The nobleman has made \nno request of the Order and wants no trouble, so he will \nask the Hunters to leave. It will be clear that Anselm has</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641396,"modifiedTime":1781557641396,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"H7UrhFvFlFsLPLCH","name":"Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"MMiNjpDATJggpGHt","name":"Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a spirit without peace and I wander the city of Murcia in search of my beloved children. My skin is cold and I feel no pain. \nThe lullaby I used to sing to my children is the only thing that gives me \na moment of peace.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 103.","positive":"I am a spirit without peace and I wander the city of Murcia in search of my beloved children. My skin is cold and I feel no pain. \nThe lullaby I used to sing to my children is the only thing that gives me \na moment of peace.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639868,"modifiedTime":1781557639868,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"GJgqdMRiT7b3kvOa","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a spirit without peace and I wander the city of Murcia in search of my beloved children. My skin is cold and I feel no pain. \nThe lullaby I used to sing to my children is the only thing that gives me \na moment of peace. \nAgenda: I will bring seven children into the water. They will become \nmy children.\nGift - Spirit of Tears: Blanca’s body does not follow the laws of life \nand death, and until her heart is at peace, she cannot be permanently eliminated. When Blanca’s Wounds are all marked, she crumbles \nto dust and her spirit returns to Blanca’s House, summoned by the \nMother’s Heart (page 107). At the beginning of the next Scene, Blanca heals all her Wounds. She starts each Scene as Intangible . If she \nacts to harm a living subject (inflicting 1 Wound, grabbing them, and \nsimilar actions), she becomes Tangible for the rest of the Scene. Once \nper Scene, Blanca can choose to become Intangible again.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 103."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639868,"modifiedTime":1781557639868,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-madre-blanca-de-las-l-grimas-103","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":103,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a spirit without peace and I wander the city of Murcia in search of my beloved children. My skin is cold and I feel no pain. \nThe lullaby I used to sing to my children is the only thing that gives me \na moment of peace. \nAgenda: I will bring seven children into the water. They will become \nmy children.\nGift - Spirit of Tears: Blanca’s body does not follow the laws of life \nand death, and until her heart is at peace, she cannot be permanently eliminated. When Blanca’s Wounds are all marked, she crumbles \nto dust and her spirit returns to Blanca’s House, summoned by the \nMother’s Heart (page 107). At the beginning of the next Scene, Blanca heals all her Wounds. She starts each Scene as Intangible . If she \nacts to harm a living subject (inflicting 1 Wound, grabbing them, and \nsimilar actions), she becomes Tangible for the rest of the Scene. Once \nper Scene, Blanca can choose to become Intangible again.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I will bring seven children into the water. They will become \nmy children.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639868,"modifiedTime":1781557639868,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"H7fUQrttoyvGsqwY","name":"Flora the Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ypatUbBQ7MZzZerI","name":"Flora the Witch - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a powerful witch who has dedicated her \nlife to the study of nature-based magic. I wish to be admired \nand recognized for my abilities as a witch.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 208.","positive":"I am a powerful witch who has dedicated her \nlife to the study of nature-based magic. I wish to be admired \nand recognized for my abilities as a witch.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645114,"modifiedTime":1781557645114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1Ponqv2CmCwBHTZB","name":"Gift - Power of the Shard","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The Shard of the Mirror of \nthe Other Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the \nperson it injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they \nact in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor \nor Agenda.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 208.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645114,"modifiedTime":1781557645114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MqonqGzY2iuxRawH","name":"Gift - Plant Witch","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Flora can manipulate nearby plants \nby animating them, and thanks to this power, she can perform up to 2 actions in the Exchange with a range equal to \nthe ground covered by the plants themselves. Through the \nplants, Flora can attempt to injure, immobilize, or manipulate a target.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 208.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645114,"modifiedTime":1781557645114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"kYsKl3bdAPz25P2t","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful witch who has dedicated her \nlife to the study of nature-based magic. I wish to be admired \nand recognized for my abilities as a witch. \nAgenda: To gain the respect of others through my powers \nand live a comfortable life. \nShard Descriptor: I am a clumsy witch who loves \nplants, but unfortunately I have forgotten how to take care \nof my beloved greenhouse. I am humble and don’t care what \nothers think of me, because all I want is to speak to the hearts \nof plants. \nShard Agenda: Take care of my greenhouse and keep \naway any pests that come after me. \nGift - Power of the Shard: The Shard of the Mirror of \nthe Other Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the \nperson it injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they \nact in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor \nor Agenda. \nGift - Plant Witch: Flora can manipulate nearby plants \nby animating them, and thanks to this power, she can perform up to 2 actions in the Exchange with a range equal to \nthe ground covered by the plants themselves. Through the \nplants, Flora can attempt to injure, immobilize, or manipulate a target. \nInformation: If the Hunters succeed in removing the \nShard from Flora’s eye, the old witch will come to her \nsenses, but the effects of the Shard will have permanent \nconsequences for her. Drained of all magical power, the \nold woman will try to bargain with the Hunters for the information she possesses in exchange for being exonerated \nof all charges. Flora will then talk about Gerda and Kay’s \nplan, as described in The story that led us here. Flora will \nnot know the location of Lady Storm’s castle, as its entrance \nis protected by powerful magic. However, she will tell the \nHunters that if they continue along the river bordering \nBergen, they can reach the small White Hospital: a facility \nwhere Gerda and Kay reside when they leave the castle. To \nget there, Flora will tell the Hunters to look for the Black \nFeather boat in the small river port of Bergen.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters decide to meet the Black \nFeathers through Lene. Go to SECOND SCENE OPTION \nB - Lene’s House. If they decide to leave directly instead, go \nto the THIRD SCENE - The Ambush of the Black Feathers.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 208."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645114,"modifiedTime":1781557645114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-flora-the-witch-208","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":208,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful witch who has dedicated her \nlife to the study of nature-based magic. I wish to be admired \nand recognized for my abilities as a witch. \nAgenda: To gain the respect of others through my powers \nand live a comfortable life. \nShard Descriptor: I am a clumsy witch who loves \nplants, but unfortunately I have forgotten how to take care \nof my beloved greenhouse. I am humble and don’t care what \nothers think of me, because all I want is to speak to the hearts \nof plants. \nShard Agenda: Take care of my greenhouse and keep \naway any pests that come after me. \nGift - Power of the Shard: The Shard of the Mirror of \nthe Other Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the \nperson it injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they \nact in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor \nor Agenda. \nGift - Plant Witch: Flora can manipulate nearby plants \nby animating them, and thanks to this power, she can perform up to 2 actions in the Exchange with a range equal to \nthe ground covered by the plants themselves. Through the \nplants, Flora can attempt to injure, immobilize, or manipulate a target. \nInformation: If the Hunters succeed in removing the \nShard from Flora’s eye, the old witch will come to her \nsenses, but the effects of the Shard will have permanent \nconsequences for her. Drained of all magical power, the \nold woman will try to bargain with the Hunters for the information she possesses in exchange for being exonerated \nof all charges. Flora will then talk about Gerda and Kay’s \nplan, as described in The story that led us here. Flora will \nnot know the location of Lady Storm’s castle, as its entrance \nis protected by powerful magic. However, she will tell the \nHunters that if they continue along the river bordering \nBergen, they can reach the small White Hospital: a facility \nwhere Gerda and Kay reside when they leave the castle. To \nget there, Flora will tell the Hunters to look for the Black \nFeather boat in the small river port of Bergen.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters decide to meet the Black \nFeathers through Lene. Go to SECOND SCENE OPTION \nB - Lene’s House. If they decide to leave directly instead, go \nto the THIRD SCENE - The Ambush of the Black Feathers.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To gain the respect of others through my powers \nand live a comfortable life. \nShard Descriptor: I am a clumsy witch who loves \nplants, but unfortunately I have forgotten how to take care \nof my beloved greenhouse. I am humble and don’t care what \nothers think of me, because all I want is to speak to the hearts \nof plants. \nShard Agenda: Take care of my greenhouse and keep \naway any pests that come after me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645114,"modifiedTime":1781557645114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"HHmItq1p1RhFzMao","name":"The Pit","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"z5RaTnxhez1ijT4v","name":"The Pit - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A large, deep pit with strangely smooth walls.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters cross the pit to enter the \nvillage of Smaragd. Go to SECOND SCENE - The Emerald \nVillage.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nEmerald Village\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Once you cross the Pit you \nfind yourself in a small village of houses, built amongst the \ntrees. It only takes a few steps to understand that something \nis wrong. You feel disoriented and it is difficult for you to keep \ntrack of which direction you are moving. The small village \nnow looks like a labyrinth, huge and intricate.\nPlace: The small village of Smaragd which, by a wish \nmade by Henkle, appears as an infinite labyrinth.\nTime: It is impossible to mark the passage of time \nas day and night alternate every minute.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 240.","positive":"A large, deep pit with strangely smooth walls.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters cross the pit to enter the \nvillage of Smaragd. Go to SECOND SCENE - The Emerald \nVillage.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nEmerald Village\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Once you cross the Pit you \nfind yourself in a small village of houses, built amongst the \ntrees. It only takes a few steps to understand that something \nis wrong. You feel disoriented and it is difficult for you to keep \ntrack of which direction you are moving. The small village \nnow looks like a labyrinth, huge and intricate.\nPlace: The small village of Smaragd which, by a wish \nmade by Henkle, appears as an infinite labyrinth.\nTime: It is impossible to mark the passage of time \nas day and night alternate every minute.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624653,"modifiedTime":1781557624653,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mmsayvOVDnwN1RQX","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A large, deep pit with strangely smooth walls.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters cross the pit to enter the \nvillage of Smaragd. Go to SECOND SCENE - The Emerald \nVillage.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nEmerald Village\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Once you cross the Pit you \nfind yourself in a small village of houses, built amongst the \ntrees. It only takes a few steps to understand that something \nis wrong. You feel disoriented and it is difficult for you to keep \ntrack of which direction you are moving. The small village \nnow looks like a labyrinth, huge and intricate.\nPlace: The small village of Smaragd which, by a wish \nmade by Henkle, appears as an infinite labyrinth.\nTime: It is impossible to mark the passage of time \nas day and night alternate every minute.\nInformation: Henkle’s plan is \nto waste the Hunters’ time and \nprevent them from getting to \nthe center of the village. For \nthis he has deployed some \nsubordinates to set up an \nambush. Choose one of the following:\n ◆ Hirnloser will plan an ambush with the help of 4 \nVillagers. He and his men can move freely without \nbeing affected by the Illusory Labyrinth Threat. \n ◆ Lowe will go to meet the Hunters to challenge them \nin the open field, bringing with him 3 Villagers and 3 \nCanine Tigers. \n ◆ Dose will very simply attack the Hunters as soon as \nthey enter the village.\n ◆ 4 Villagers with 4 Canine Tigers\nThreat - Illusory Labyrinth</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 240."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624653,"modifiedTime":1781557624653,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-the-pit-240","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":240,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A large, deep pit with strangely smooth walls.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters cross the pit to enter the \nvillage of Smaragd. Go to SECOND SCENE - The Emerald \nVillage.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nEmerald Village\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Once you cross the Pit you \nfind yourself in a small village of houses, built amongst the \ntrees. It only takes a few steps to understand that something \nis wrong. You feel disoriented and it is difficult for you to keep \ntrack of which direction you are moving. The small village \nnow looks like a labyrinth, huge and intricate.\nPlace: The small village of Smaragd which, by a wish \nmade by Henkle, appears as an infinite labyrinth.\nTime: It is impossible to mark the passage of time \nas day and night alternate every minute.\nInformation: Henkle’s plan is \nto waste the Hunters’ time and \nprevent them from getting to \nthe center of the village. For \nthis he has deployed some \nsubordinates to set up an \nambush. Choose one of the following:\n ◆ Hirnloser will plan an ambush with the help of 4 \nVillagers. He and his men can move freely without \nbeing affected by the Illusory Labyrinth Threat. \n ◆ Lowe will go to meet the Hunters to challenge them \nin the open field, bringing with him 3 Villagers and 3 \nCanine Tigers. \n ◆ Dose will very simply attack the Hunters as soon as \nthey enter the village.\n ◆ 4 Villagers with 4 Canine Tigers\nThreat - Illusory Labyrinth</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624653,"modifiedTime":1781557624653,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Hnu9xe8PVx6QbmlC","name":"The Black Cat","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"BktaJxI8qe1Eaize","name":"The Black Cat - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a snappy kitten bound to the spirit of old \nBritta. Thanks to the witch’s power I can understand what \npeople are saying.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136.","positive":"I am a snappy kitten bound to the spirit of old \nBritta. Thanks to the witch’s power I can understand what \npeople are saying.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"J0XvMSJe98SLDFu4","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a snappy kitten bound to the spirit of old \nBritta. Thanks to the witch’s power I can understand what \npeople are saying. \nAgenda: Have the humans help me retrieve Britta’s three \nitems. \nFirst Reset: The Cat will observe the Hunters in the \nHeidelberg Entrance Plaza to understand why they are not \naffected by the Magic Tinderbox. It will then go \nto one of the Places to retrieve Britta’s items. \nSecond Reset: If the Hunters are interested, the Cat will lead them to Britta’s House to find her diary. If the diary has already \nbeen found, the Cat will take the Hunters to \none of the Places to retrieve the items. The \nCat will also have retrieved one of the items if \nthe Hunters have not already done so.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-the-black-cat-136","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":136,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a snappy kitten bound to the spirit of old \nBritta. Thanks to the witch’s power I can understand what \npeople are saying. \nAgenda: Have the humans help me retrieve Britta’s three \nitems. \nFirst Reset: The Cat will observe the Hunters in the \nHeidelberg Entrance Plaza to understand why they are not \naffected by the Magic Tinderbox. It will then go \nto one of the Places to retrieve Britta’s items. \nSecond Reset: If the Hunters are interested, the Cat will lead them to Britta’s House to find her diary. If the diary has already \nbeen found, the Cat will take the Hunters to \none of the Places to retrieve the items. The \nCat will also have retrieved one of the items if \nthe Hunters have not already done so.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Have the humans help me retrieve Britta’s three \nitems. \nFirst Reset: The Cat will observe the Hunters in the \nHeidelberg Entrance Plaza to understand why they are not \naffected by the Magic Tinderbox. It will then go \nto one of the Places to retrieve Britta’s items. \nSecond Reset: If the Hunters are interested, the Cat will lead them to Britta’s House to find her diary. If the diary has already \nbeen found, the Cat will take the Hunters to \none of the Places to retrieve the items. The \nCat will also have retrieved one of the items if \nthe Hunters have not already done so.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Hr3BUUFRPYkTC39R","name":"Sultan’s Guards","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"q5CsxYCx7w8VuQCq","name":"Sultan’s Guards - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the chosen Guards of the Sultan, and \nwith our warrior skills we protect our lord. \nThe Executioner</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 166.","positive":"We are the chosen Guards of the Sultan, and \nwith our warrior skills we protect our lord. \nThe Executioner","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642795,"modifiedTime":1781557642795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"IoEglam1B5yhCltV","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the chosen Guards of the Sultan, and \nwith our warrior skills we protect our lord. \nThe Executioner</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 166."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642795,"modifiedTime":1781557642795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-sultan-s-guards-166","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":166,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the chosen Guards of the Sultan, and \nwith our warrior skills we protect our lord. \nThe Executioner</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642795,"modifiedTime":1781557642795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IbkEWPGQlm3LQ22J","name":"Cernobog Potmešil The Child","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"1yKSugmpoEPv8lzy","name":"Cernobog Potmešil The Child - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The rubies I received allowed me to recover \nfrom the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I \nam now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger \nand resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of \nthe poor people of Prague.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","positive":"The rubies I received allowed me to recover \nfrom the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I \nam now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger \nand resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of \nthe poor people of Prague.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637921,"modifiedTime":1781557637921,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HWMnvrryHnhwQJpr","name":"Gift - The Ruby of Hate","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Černobog uses one of the two \nrubies he obtained from the Swallow as bait to achieve \nhis goals. When he distracts someone with the ruby, he \nprevents the use of a Gift for the duration of the Scene. If \nthe ruby is crushed, Černobog suffers 1 Wound.\nPrague Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: On the evening of the party, \nyou are greeted in the majestic ballroom of Prague Castle. \nA cascade of crystal chandeliers illuminates white arches \nfinished with gold, while large mirrors magnify the already \nremarkable size of the room, full of people dressed elegantly. \nYou hear your name announced aloud, and everyone seems \nintrigued by your presence. Ostromir introduces you to the \nvarious families of the city, but despite the superficially happy \natmosphere, the tension is palpable.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637921,"modifiedTime":1781557637921,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qZ9tSKaElkIDaOa5","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: The rubies I received allowed me to recover \nfrom the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I \nam now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger \nand resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of \nthe poor people of Prague. \nAgenda: Avenge my struggling mother / Make sure the rich \npay for their crimes.\nGift - The Ruby of Hate: Černobog uses one of the two \nrubies he obtained from the Swallow as bait to achieve \nhis goals. When he distracts someone with the ruby, he \nprevents the use of a Gift for the duration of the Scene. If \nthe ruby is crushed, Černobog suffers 1 Wound.\nPrague Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: On the evening of the party, \nyou are greeted in the majestic ballroom of Prague Castle. \nA cascade of crystal chandeliers illuminates white arches \nfinished with gold, while large mirrors magnify the already \nremarkable size of the room, full of people dressed elegantly. \nYou hear your name announced aloud, and everyone seems \nintrigued by your presence. Ostromir introduces you to the \nvarious families of the city, but despite the superficially happy \natmosphere, the tension is palpable. \nDescriptor: The great and magnificent Prague Castle.\nWhen the ball is at its busiest, a wall will be violently \ndestroyed by a large creature of flesh and metal crashing \n^^</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 173."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637921,"modifiedTime":1781557637921,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-cernobog-potme-il-the-child-173","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":173,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: The rubies I received allowed me to recover \nfrom the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I \nam now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger \nand resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of \nthe poor people of Prague. \nAgenda: Avenge my struggling mother / Make sure the rich \npay for their crimes.\nGift - The Ruby of Hate: Černobog uses one of the two \nrubies he obtained from the Swallow as bait to achieve \nhis goals. When he distracts someone with the ruby, he \nprevents the use of a Gift for the duration of the Scene. If \nthe ruby is crushed, Černobog suffers 1 Wound.\nPrague Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: On the evening of the party, \nyou are greeted in the majestic ballroom of Prague Castle. \nA cascade of crystal chandeliers illuminates white arches \nfinished with gold, while large mirrors magnify the already \nremarkable size of the room, full of people dressed elegantly. \nYou hear your name announced aloud, and everyone seems \nintrigued by your presence. Ostromir introduces you to the \nvarious families of the city, but despite the superficially happy \natmosphere, the tension is palpable. \nDescriptor: The great and magnificent Prague Castle.\nWhen the ball is at its busiest, a wall will be violently \ndestroyed by a large creature of flesh and metal crashing \n^^</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Avenge my struggling mother / Make sure the rich \npay for their crimes.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637921,"modifiedTime":1781557637921,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IzC7Qbc2FXzmUU2L","name":"Lisbet","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Pmf2llejd0ACr2pu","name":"Lisbet - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young widow and I settled in the village \nto start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, \nwhich have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. \nHowever, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143.","positive":"I am a young widow and I settled in the village \nto start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, \nwhich have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. \nHowever, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ReitLbLs1fJwDcs1","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young widow and I settled in the village \nto start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, \nwhich have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. \nHowever, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.\nAgenda: To save all the prisoners by convincing Talia to do \nthe right thing. \nThe Dungeons\nDescriptor: A series of tunnels and galleries full of barred \ndoors leading to the treasure room.\nTalia the Sleeper</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 143."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-lisbet-143","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":143,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young widow and I settled in the village \nto start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, \nwhich have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. \nHowever, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.\nAgenda: To save all the prisoners by convincing Talia to do \nthe right thing. \nThe Dungeons\nDescriptor: A series of tunnels and galleries full of barred \ndoors leading to the treasure room.\nTalia the Sleeper</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To save all the prisoners by convincing Talia to do \nthe right thing. \nThe Dungeons\nDescriptor: A series of tunnels and galleries full of barred \ndoors leading to the treasure room.\nTalia the Sleeper","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636357,"modifiedTime":1781557636357,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IzG9GpTHpv1ztm4Z","name":"Georg Slanina the Helper","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"1xjq9hLrCvQTcFZa","name":"Georg Slanina the Helper - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I \ndo, I become a beast.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 168.","positive":"I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I \ndo, I become a beast.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637733,"modifiedTime":1781557637733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lQRpeiMk94WkCxJf","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I \ndo, I become a beast. \nAgenda: Supporting my daughter, who now has to sell \nmatches on the street / Understanding why Konstantin fired \nme.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 168."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637733,"modifiedTime":1781557637733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-georg-slanina-the-helper-168","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":168,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I \ndo, I become a beast. \nAgenda: Supporting my daughter, who now has to sell \nmatches on the street / Understanding why Konstantin fired \nme.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Supporting my daughter, who now has to sell \nmatches on the street / Understanding why Konstantin fired \nme.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637733,"modifiedTime":1781557637733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"JInhHh6idtWffssf","name":"Nikola’s Reindeer","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"yywN1H4DZTTt2TUw","name":"Nikola’s Reindeer - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are reindeer mutated by Nikola’s magic, \nand we crave to sink our teeth into the flesh of living creatures.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 121.","positive":"We are reindeer mutated by Nikola’s magic, \nand we crave to sink our teeth into the flesh of living creatures.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640587,"modifiedTime":1781557640587,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HvYyuPmTcRU0ezRU","name":"Gift - Carnivore","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Nikola’s Reindeer have large, clumsy jaws \nthat they use to eat meat. Each Reindeer in the herd increases \nits OL by 1 when it attacks a marked target. A target is marked \nwhen it suffers 1 Wound from a Reindeer bite. Alternatively, \na Reindeer can use its action to inflict a Wound on itself and \ncover up to 3 targets within 20 feet with blood to mark them. A</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 121.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640587,"modifiedTime":1781557640587,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1B7kG1LY4t5iIsmR","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are reindeer mutated by Nikola’s magic, \nand we crave to sink our teeth into the flesh of living creatures. \nGift - Carnivore: Nikola’s Reindeer have large, clumsy jaws \nthat they use to eat meat. Each Reindeer in the herd increases \nits OL by 1 when it attacks a marked target. A target is marked \nwhen it suffers 1 Wound from a Reindeer bite. Alternatively, \na Reindeer can use its action to inflict a Wound on itself and \ncover up to 3 targets within 20 feet with blood to mark them. A</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 121."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640587,"modifiedTime":1781557640587,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-nikola-s-reindeer-121","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":121,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are reindeer mutated by Nikola’s magic, \nand we crave to sink our teeth into the flesh of living creatures. \nGift - Carnivore: Nikola’s Reindeer have large, clumsy jaws \nthat they use to eat meat. Each Reindeer in the herd increases \nits OL by 1 when it attacks a marked target. A target is marked \nwhen it suffers 1 Wound from a Reindeer bite. Alternatively, \na Reindeer can use its action to inflict a Wound on itself and \ncover up to 3 targets within 20 feet with blood to mark them. A</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640587,"modifiedTime":1781557640587,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"JMt67EgMsl4dvVUJ","name":"Klaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"jBSFpFwupuP1fZMR","name":"Klaus, the OzenaAfflicted Son - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a curious child. I \nlove foreigners because they always have \ninteresting stories to tell. I know I have a \ndreadful disease, but I have learned to live \nwith it.\nLowe the Coward \nHenchman</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 226.","positive":"I am a curious child. I \nlove foreigners because they always have \ninteresting stories to tell. I know I have a \ndreadful disease, but I have learned to live \nwith it.\nLowe the Coward \nHenchman","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dKIQOcv1hWWk1baa","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a curious child. I \nlove foreigners because they always have \ninteresting stories to tell. I know I have a \ndreadful disease, but I have learned to live \nwith it.\nLowe the Coward \nHenchman</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 226."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-klaus-the-ozenaafflicted-son-226","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":226,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a curious child. I \nlove foreigners because they always have \ninteresting stories to tell. I know I have a \ndreadful disease, but I have learned to live \nwith it.\nLowe the Coward \nHenchman</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"JPr8cLMqBrQHzmhB","name":"Lowe the Brave Fighter","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"XarDEFr8OHyOEq6P","name":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I became a proud warrior and realized my \nheroic potential. I never back down and set an example for \nmy teammates.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 241.","positive":"I became a proud warrior and realized my \nheroic potential. I never back down and set an example for \nmy teammates.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624693,"modifiedTime":1781557624693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"DXtNFEDukU7qQSUA","name":"Gift - Hero","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Lowe fears nothing and is immune to all forms \nof fear and magical control. After he acts, his allies receive \n+1 to their OL, inspired by their hero’s courage and words.\nHirnloser the Genius</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 241.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624693,"modifiedTime":1781557624693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3b3Mr4TSam2oSydk","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I became a proud warrior and realized my \nheroic potential. I never back down and set an example for \nmy teammates.\nAgenda: Stop the invaders and protect the village of \nSmaragd, which has elected me as its hero.\nGift - Hero: Lowe fears nothing and is immune to all forms \nof fear and magical control. After he acts, his allies receive \n+1 to their OL, inspired by their hero’s courage and words.\nHirnloser the Genius</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 241."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624693,"modifiedTime":1781557624693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-lowe-the-brave-fighter-241","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":241,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I became a proud warrior and realized my \nheroic potential. I never back down and set an example for \nmy teammates.\nAgenda: Stop the invaders and protect the village of \nSmaragd, which has elected me as its hero.\nGift - Hero: Lowe fears nothing and is immune to all forms \nof fear and magical control. After he acts, his allies receive \n+1 to their OL, inspired by their hero’s courage and words.\nHirnloser the Genius</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Stop the invaders and protect the village of \nSmaragd, which has elected me as its hero.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624693,"modifiedTime":1781557624693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"JWJCA3Pc9ABKVllm","name":"Akim the Tamer","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"mxuRidMcVy91cYIH","name":"Akim the Tamer - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a brave and skilled \ntamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear \nBerto are both dear to me, as they obey \nmy every command.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158.","positive":"I am a brave and skilled \ntamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear \nBerto are both dear to me, as they obey \nmy every command.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"VyTAIyfjwtqMHqhI","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a brave and skilled \ntamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear \nBerto are both dear to me, as they obey \nmy every command.\nAgenda: Perform and amaze the \naudience with my animals / Prevent \nanyone from harming Tasha and \nBerto, whom I consider as my children.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters keep Princesca informed of the \ninvestigation: the clever woman will quickly understand \nthat someone is framing her and will send Eduardo and \nFelipe to deal with the Kind Mother. If the Hunters don’t do \nsomething, the old witch won’t escape her fate. \nIf the Hunters defeat Francisca and Marta: the two \nsisters will tell them everything they know, imploring the \nHunters to help expose Cinder.\nIf the Hunters unmask Cinder: The Countess will \nuse the power of her magic to escape and run to the Kind \nMother for her help. Once she regains her voice thanks to \nCinder’s use of Wish, the Kind Mother will assist Cinder \nto eliminate the Hunters and then take her time making \nCinder pay. \nIf the Hunters understand who the Kind Mother \nreally is: The witch will offer her aid in exchange for her \nlife and will seek their help in regaining her voice. \nIf the Hunters seek the support of Azul: The Count \nwill pretend to be a fool and will even avoid taking measures \nagainst Cinder once she has been unmasked. The man is \nso willfully ignorant that he will ban the Hunters from the \ncity in order to keep his wife where she is, managing all the \nresponsibilities so he can lead a life of laziness. \nIf the Hunters trap Cinder during the anniversary \nparty: The woman will use magic to take control of Tasha \nand Berto, sending them against the Hunters. Akim will \nhinder the Hunters if they try to harm his beloved animals. \nCinder will try to escape to the Kind Mother by taking \nadvantage of the chaos. \nTasha the Tiger</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-akim-the-tamer-158","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":158,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a brave and skilled \ntamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear \nBerto are both dear to me, as they obey \nmy every command.\nAgenda: Perform and amaze the \naudience with my animals / Prevent \nanyone from harming Tasha and \nBerto, whom I consider as my children.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters keep Princesca informed of the \ninvestigation: the clever woman will quickly understand \nthat someone is framing her and will send Eduardo and \nFelipe to deal with the Kind Mother. If the Hunters don’t do \nsomething, the old witch won’t escape her fate. \nIf the Hunters defeat Francisca and Marta: the two \nsisters will tell them everything they know, imploring the \nHunters to help expose Cinder.\nIf the Hunters unmask Cinder: The Countess will \nuse the power of her magic to escape and run to the Kind \nMother for her help. Once she regains her voice thanks to \nCinder’s use of Wish, the Kind Mother will assist Cinder \nto eliminate the Hunters and then take her time making \nCinder pay. \nIf the Hunters understand who the Kind Mother \nreally is: The witch will offer her aid in exchange for her \nlife and will seek their help in regaining her voice. \nIf the Hunters seek the support of Azul: The Count \nwill pretend to be a fool and will even avoid taking measures \nagainst Cinder once she has been unmasked. The man is \nso willfully ignorant that he will ban the Hunters from the \ncity in order to keep his wife where she is, managing all the \nresponsibilities so he can lead a life of laziness. \nIf the Hunters trap Cinder during the anniversary \nparty: The woman will use magic to take control of Tasha \nand Berto, sending them against the Hunters. Akim will \nhinder the Hunters if they try to harm his beloved animals. \nCinder will try to escape to the Kind Mother by taking \nadvantage of the chaos. \nTasha the Tiger</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Perform and amaze the \naudience with my animals / Prevent \nanyone from harming Tasha and \nBerto, whom I consider as my children.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters keep Princesca informed of the \ninvestigation: the clever woman will quickly understand \nthat someone is framing her and will send Eduardo and \nFelipe to deal with the Kind Mother. If the Hunters don’t do \nsomething, the old witch won’t escape her fate. \nIf the Hunters defeat Francisca and Marta: the two \nsisters will tell them everything they know, imploring the \nHunters to help expose Cinder.\nIf the Hunters unmask Cinder: The Countess will \nuse the power of her magic to escape and run to the Kind \nMother for her help. Once she regains her voice thanks to \nCinder’s use of Wish, the Kind Mother will assist Cinder \nto eliminate the Hunters and then take her time making \nCinder pay. \nIf the Hunters understand who the Kind Mother \nreally is: The witch will offer her aid in exchange for her \nlife and will seek their help in regaining her voice. \nIf the Hunters seek the support of Azul: The Count \nwill pretend to be a fool and will even avoid taking measures \nagainst Cinder once she has been unmasked. The man is \nso willfully ignorant that he will ban the Hunters from the \ncity in order to keep his wife where she is, managing all the \nresponsibilities so he can lead a life of laziness. \nIf the Hunters trap Cinder during the anniversary \nparty: The woman will use magic to take control of Tasha \nand Berto, sending them against the Hunters. Akim will \nhinder the Hunters if they try to harm his beloved animals. \nCinder will try to escape to the Kind Mother by taking \nadvantage of the chaos. \nTasha the Tiger","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"JjhywroInzrid2j7","name":"The Doves","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"txCqaVKbLWh90dN3","name":"The Doves - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two doves enslaved by the power of \nCinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we \ndefend our mistress from all danger.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 155.","positive":"We are two doves enslaved by the power of \nCinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we \ndefend our mistress from all danger.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637013,"modifiedTime":1781557637013,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"BRdjHVbvlE5SsdHy","name":"Gift - Go for the Eyes","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The Doves are skilled at hitting \nthe enemies’ weak spots. When a Dove manages to inflict a \nWound, it inflicts 1 additional Wound. In case of a positive \nOutcome in a Defense Check, once per Scene, the Dove’s \nattack will still inflict 1 Wound. This Gift cannot be used \nmore than once against the same target \nduring the Scenario.\nThe Port of Vigo</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 155.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637013,"modifiedTime":1781557637013,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2HtGmSl6Sr0H2Xua","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two doves enslaved by the power of \nCinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we \ndefend our mistress from all danger. \nGift – Go for the Eyes: The Doves are skilled at hitting \nthe enemies’ weak spots. When a Dove manages to inflict a \nWound, it inflicts 1 additional Wound. In case of a positive \nOutcome in a Defense Check, once per Scene, the Dove’s \nattack will still inflict 1 Wound. This Gift cannot be used \nmore than once against the same target \nduring the Scenario.\nThe Port of Vigo\nDescriptor: The great city’s port where ships from all over \nthe world are docked. The alleys in front of the port are a \ncrossroads of taverns, shops, and leisure houses. Even in the \nmiddle of the night, there’s always life in the harbor. \nInformation: The Old Spinner resides in a small house \nin the eastern part of the pier, while the last corpse was \nfound in the western area.\nEast of the pier: The Hunters will be able to meet the \nKind Mother, who will present herself as an old silent \nseamstress. Cinder knows that the spinner is the Kind \nMother, but gives no sign that she knows. The old witch \nwill communicate with the Hunters with some difficulty \nand give them a brooch she found near the alley where \nshe saw the two cloaked silhouettes pass. The brooch bears \nthe coat of arms of the Di Bello family: the Kind Mother \nherself will give directions to the Di Bello house, located in \nthe upper quarters of the city. The old witch will not follow \nthe Hunters, as she does not want to be seen by Francisca \nand Marta.\nWest of the pier: The Hunters will find Eduardo and \nFelipe, two guards at the service of the Count of Vigo, \nguarding the crime scene. The body of the young prostitute \n(known as Estella) was moved to the icebox of an old fish \nwarehouse nearby.\n ◆ The two guards will tell the Hunters that no one has \nclaimed her body. She is most likely one of the many \npoor people just trying to get by. \n ◆ Examining Estella’s body will confirm the removal \nof all facial skin, performed with insane care. A very</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 155."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637013,"modifiedTime":1781557637013,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-the-doves-155","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":155,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two doves enslaved by the power of \nCinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we \ndefend our mistress from all danger. \nGift – Go for the Eyes: The Doves are skilled at hitting \nthe enemies’ weak spots. When a Dove manages to inflict a \nWound, it inflicts 1 additional Wound. In case of a positive \nOutcome in a Defense Check, once per Scene, the Dove’s \nattack will still inflict 1 Wound. This Gift cannot be used \nmore than once against the same target \nduring the Scenario.\nThe Port of Vigo\nDescriptor: The great city’s port where ships from all over \nthe world are docked. The alleys in front of the port are a \ncrossroads of taverns, shops, and leisure houses. Even in the \nmiddle of the night, there’s always life in the harbor. \nInformation: The Old Spinner resides in a small house \nin the eastern part of the pier, while the last corpse was \nfound in the western area.\nEast of the pier: The Hunters will be able to meet the \nKind Mother, who will present herself as an old silent \nseamstress. Cinder knows that the spinner is the Kind \nMother, but gives no sign that she knows. The old witch \nwill communicate with the Hunters with some difficulty \nand give them a brooch she found near the alley where \nshe saw the two cloaked silhouettes pass. The brooch bears \nthe coat of arms of the Di Bello family: the Kind Mother \nherself will give directions to the Di Bello house, located in \nthe upper quarters of the city. The old witch will not follow \nthe Hunters, as she does not want to be seen by Francisca \nand Marta.\nWest of the pier: The Hunters will find Eduardo and \nFelipe, two guards at the service of the Count of Vigo, \nguarding the crime scene. The body of the young prostitute \n(known as Estella) was moved to the icebox of an old fish \nwarehouse nearby.\n ◆ The two guards will tell the Hunters that no one has \nclaimed her body. She is most likely one of the many \npoor people just trying to get by. \n ◆ Examining Estella’s body will confirm the removal \nof all facial skin, performed with insane care. A very</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637013,"modifiedTime":1781557637013,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"K0MVDKEVocgRC3SI","name":"Clarence Browne the Younger Brother","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"q41RDhevGL5JMsXu","name":"Clarence Browne the Younger Brother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the youngest of the Pig Heads and, despite \nbelieving in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on \nit. From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back \nof my hand.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 209.","positive":"I am the youngest of the Pig Heads and, despite \nbelieving in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on \nit. From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back \nof my hand.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623863,"modifiedTime":1781557623863,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0TxjhyOyoLzhCOa9","name":"Gift - Slacker","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Clarence is a master of the art of \ndisappearing when things get tough. In the presence of \neven a small crowd, Clarence can leave a Scene when it \nis his turn to act, without anything or anyone being able \nto stop him. When using this Gift, Clarence hides in the \norchard, passing the entire following Scene there.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 209.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623863,"modifiedTime":1781557623863,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Gxy4v8zD6uaJmTB1","name":"Gift - Gang Leader","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a \nsecond time during the Exchange, even consecutively; \n3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for \na single action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe \nSlaughterhouse</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 209.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623863,"modifiedTime":1781557623863,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WZj7yovcrBd5hbSg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the youngest of the Pig Heads and, despite \nbelieving in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on \nit. From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back \nof my hand.\nAgenda: Having fun and lazing around all day, carrying on \nthe Pig Head’s cause in my spare time.\nGift - Slacker: Clarence is a master of the art of \ndisappearing when things get tough. In the presence of \neven a small crowd, Clarence can leave a Scene when it \nis his turn to act, without anything or anyone being able \nto stop him. When using this Gift, Clarence hides in the \norchard, passing the entire following Scene there. \nGift - Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a \nsecond time during the Exchange, even consecutively; \n3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for \na single action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe \nSlaughterhouse\nDescriptor: A huge gray building inside which cattle from \ncoastal pastures are slaughtered. Entry is forbidden to nonworkers.\nWhen the Hunters wander around the slaughterhouse, roll \n1 die to see how far they go without attracting attention, or \npresent the environments in sequence.\n1-2 The outdoor garden: It is more an open-air barn \nthan a garden patch. Bloodstains and excrement suggest \nthat the slaughter starts here. Several signs reading “No \nTrespassing” suggest that the area is very controlled.\n3-4 The slaughterhouse: Composed of a series of large \nspaces, several stairs lead to underground chambers where \nthe meat is preserved. Around ten workers are present day \nand night, all members of the Pig Heads.\n5-6 The salting room: A small room at the back of the \nbuilding, where Frank prepares the meat that will be served \nin the cafeterias throughout the city. During the day Frank \nis always present, intent on hiding the flesh of the God \nwithin freshly butchered beef.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 209."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623863,"modifiedTime":1781557623863,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-clarence-browne-the-younger-brother-209","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":209,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the youngest of the Pig Heads and, despite \nbelieving in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on \nit. From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back \nof my hand.\nAgenda: Having fun and lazing around all day, carrying on \nthe Pig Head’s cause in my spare time.\nGift - Slacker: Clarence is a master of the art of \ndisappearing when things get tough. In the presence of \neven a small crowd, Clarence can leave a Scene when it \nis his turn to act, without anything or anyone being able \nto stop him. When using this Gift, Clarence hides in the \norchard, passing the entire following Scene there. \nGift - Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a \nsecond time during the Exchange, even consecutively; \n3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for \na single action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe \nSlaughterhouse\nDescriptor: A huge gray building inside which cattle from \ncoastal pastures are slaughtered. Entry is forbidden to nonworkers.\nWhen the Hunters wander around the slaughterhouse, roll \n1 die to see how far they go without attracting attention, or \npresent the environments in sequence.\n1-2 The outdoor garden: It is more an open-air barn \nthan a garden patch. Bloodstains and excrement suggest \nthat the slaughter starts here. Several signs reading “No \nTrespassing” suggest that the area is very controlled.\n3-4 The slaughterhouse: Composed of a series of large \nspaces, several stairs lead to underground chambers where \nthe meat is preserved. Around ten workers are present day \nand night, all members of the Pig Heads.\n5-6 The salting room: A small room at the back of the \nbuilding, where Frank prepares the meat that will be served \nin the cafeterias throughout the city. During the day Frank \nis always present, intent on hiding the flesh of the God \nwithin freshly butchered beef.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Having fun and lazing around all day, carrying on \nthe Pig Head’s cause in my spare time.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623863,"modifiedTime":1781557623863,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"KAi3KmZt2mF0k7Es","name":"George Carnarvon","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"PSoO96E8aCTIrGHA","name":"George Carnarvon - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my \nservice to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. \nI fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my \ndaughter’s abduction.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","positive":"I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my \nservice to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. \nI fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my \ndaughter’s abduction.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Ig92uT0R44Z3jPPj","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my \nservice to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. \nI fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my \ndaughter’s abduction.\nAgenda: Stop the gang of rebels that plagues London, but \nmore than anything else find my beloved daughter Gwendolyn.\nCarnarvon House\nDescriptor: A rich and large mansion in the heart of \nLondon.\nJoanna called Nana the Servant</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-george-carnarvon-84","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":84,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my \nservice to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. \nI fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my \ndaughter’s abduction.\nAgenda: Stop the gang of rebels that plagues London, but \nmore than anything else find my beloved daughter Gwendolyn.\nCarnarvon House\nDescriptor: A rich and large mansion in the heart of \nLondon.\nJoanna called Nana the Servant</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Stop the gang of rebels that plagues London, but \nmore than anything else find my beloved daughter Gwendolyn.\nCarnarvon House\nDescriptor: A rich and large mansion in the heart of \nLondon.\nJoanna called Nana the Servant","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
