{"_id":"L1HlX8xTr8L1m4mM","name":"Hirnloser the Genius","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"9hUrX8lDPzVwARo6","name":"Hirnloser the Genius - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>My mind has become infallible, and I can \ncalculate and check any variable in seconds. I have a strategy \nfor every situation.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 241.","positive":"My mind has become infallible, and I can \ncalculate and check any variable in seconds. I have a strategy \nfor every situation.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624693,"modifiedTime":1781557624693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"GrexxrHhlQ6XB8XE","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: My mind has become infallible, and I can \ncalculate and check any variable in seconds. I have a strategy \nfor every situation.\nAgenda: Solve any potential problems that plague my \nbenefactor Norman Henkle.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 241."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624693,"modifiedTime":1781557624693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-hirnloser-the-genius-241","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":241,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: My mind has become infallible, and I can \ncalculate and check any variable in seconds. I have a strategy \nfor every situation.\nAgenda: Solve any potential problems that plague my \nbenefactor Norman Henkle.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Solve any potential problems that plague my \nbenefactor Norman Henkle.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624693,"modifiedTime":1781557624693,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"L9r3JRVmEPxUi8wO","name":"Wolfgang the “druid”","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"eBanm21tX0zmGDT3","name":"Wolfgang the “druid” - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled and renowned pharmacist, and \nthere is no herb or remedy that I am not familiar with.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 233.","positive":"I am a skilled and renowned pharmacist, and \nthere is no herb or remedy that I am not familiar with.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624451,"modifiedTime":1781557624451,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"j51raFRuI37xzO11","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled and renowned pharmacist, and \nthere is no herb or remedy that I am not familiar with.\nAgenda: I am enslaved by Helga’s power. My body moves at \nher will and therefore I sprinkle drops of her blood to animate \nthe forest to capture potential intruders.\nEnd of Scene: If captured, Wolfgang will reveal what \nhe knows to the Hunters. In the greenhouse, other poor \npeople like him work incessantly under Helga’s magical \ncontrol. In the village, a strange figure called the Porcelain \nPrincess ensures that no one can harm the witch. During \nthe interrogation, Wolfgang will be seized with sudden \nspasms and drown in his own blood. If Wolfgang has been \neliminated, the Hunters will simply have to choose which \nway to go.\nIf they go to the greenhouse, go to the SECOND SCENE - \nThe Greenhouse.\nIf they go to the Village go to the THIRD SCENE - The \nDoll’s Court.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nGreenhouse\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Following the path you reach \nan old manor house which has been remade as a greenhouse. \nMany men and women dressed in white, with tired and longsuffering expressions, work on small gardens. Strong smells of \nherbs and medicinal infusions fill the air.\nPlace: The greenhouse where the base for the Infusion of \nPurity is produced.\nTime: The sun is setting. \nInformation:\n ◆ Pharmacists are working on a strange potion. Those \nwho are experts in herbs will recognize the plants as \nBurdock, Nettle and Hyssop. \n ◆ If the Hunters approach the greenhouse, Manycorpses \nwill drop from the ceiling to stop the intruders.\n ◆ The Infusion of Purity cannot be completed, as the \nElderberry, which Dorothea took in her fight with \nManycorpses, is missing.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 233."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624451,"modifiedTime":1781557624451,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-wolfgang-the-druid-233","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":233,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled and renowned pharmacist, and \nthere is no herb or remedy that I am not familiar with.\nAgenda: I am enslaved by Helga’s power. My body moves at \nher will and therefore I sprinkle drops of her blood to animate \nthe forest to capture potential intruders.\nEnd of Scene: If captured, Wolfgang will reveal what \nhe knows to the Hunters. In the greenhouse, other poor \npeople like him work incessantly under Helga’s magical \ncontrol. In the village, a strange figure called the Porcelain \nPrincess ensures that no one can harm the witch. During \nthe interrogation, Wolfgang will be seized with sudden \nspasms and drown in his own blood. If Wolfgang has been \neliminated, the Hunters will simply have to choose which \nway to go.\nIf they go to the greenhouse, go to the SECOND SCENE - \nThe Greenhouse.\nIf they go to the Village go to the THIRD SCENE - The \nDoll’s Court.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nGreenhouse\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Following the path you reach \nan old manor house which has been remade as a greenhouse. \nMany men and women dressed in white, with tired and longsuffering expressions, work on small gardens. Strong smells of \nherbs and medicinal infusions fill the air.\nPlace: The greenhouse where the base for the Infusion of \nPurity is produced.\nTime: The sun is setting. \nInformation:\n ◆ Pharmacists are working on a strange potion. Those \nwho are experts in herbs will recognize the plants as \nBurdock, Nettle and Hyssop. \n ◆ If the Hunters approach the greenhouse, Manycorpses \nwill drop from the ceiling to stop the intruders.\n ◆ The Infusion of Purity cannot be completed, as the \nElderberry, which Dorothea took in her fight with \nManycorpses, is missing.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"I am enslaved by Helga’s power. My body moves at \nher will and therefore I sprinkle drops of her blood to animate \nthe forest to capture potential intruders.\nEnd of Scene: If captured, Wolfgang will reveal what \nhe knows to the Hunters. In the greenhouse, other poor \npeople like him work incessantly under Helga’s magical \ncontrol. In the village, a strange figure called the Porcelain \nPrincess ensures that no one can harm the witch. During \nthe interrogation, Wolfgang will be seized with sudden \nspasms and drown in his own blood. If Wolfgang has been \neliminated, the Hunters will simply have to choose which \nway to go.\nIf they go to the greenhouse, go to the SECOND SCENE - \nThe Greenhouse.\nIf they go to the Village go to the THIRD SCENE - The \nDoll’s Court.\nSECOND SCENE – The \nGreenhouse\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Following the path you reach \nan old manor house which has been remade as a greenhouse. \nMany men and women dressed in white, with tired and longsuffering expressions, work on small gardens. Strong smells of \nherbs and medicinal infusions fill the air.\nPlace: The greenhouse where the base for the Infusion of \nPurity is produced.\nTime: The sun is setting.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624451,"modifiedTime":1781557624451,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"LOYY4iIHUh8w7hJJ","name":"Captain of the Ivory Seeking Pirates","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"stOoVbpbGZbhAQ9i","name":"Captain of the Ivory Seeking Pirates - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an old sea wolf and I have faced all kinds \nof adventures. I am too old to be afraid of anything.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 158.","positive":"I am an old sea wolf and I have faced all kinds \nof adventures. I am too old to be afraid of anything.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642458,"modifiedTime":1781557642458,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lSwPQfBeNspRK0vO","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old sea wolf and I have faced all kinds \nof adventures. I am too old to be afraid of anything. \nAgenda: Earn as much as possible and risk as little as possible. \nGift - Old Bastard: The Captain is adept at using the sit-</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 158."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642458,"modifiedTime":1781557642458,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-captain-of-the-ivory-seeking-pirates-158","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":158,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old sea wolf and I have faced all kinds \nof adventures. I am too old to be afraid of anything. \nAgenda: Earn as much as possible and risk as little as possible. \nGift - Old Bastard: The Captain is adept at using the sit-</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Earn as much as possible and risk as little as possible.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642458,"modifiedTime":1781557642458,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"LXDBK32OYMTajXEQ","name":"Father Adrien","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ZFWbb6a08KGlnVtG","name":"Father Adrien - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young priest who chose to take holy \nvows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and \ndistillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 147.","positive":"I am a young priest who chose to take holy \nvows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and \ndistillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622202,"modifiedTime":1781557622202,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yloNsrhdekCWeqoy","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds) \nDescriptor: I am a young priest who chose to take holy \nvows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and \ndistillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life. \nAgenda: Accumulate wealth through absinthe smuggling \nand then flee across the ocean to rebuild my life in the new \nworld.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 147."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622202,"modifiedTime":1781557622202,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-father-adrien-147","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":147,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds) \nDescriptor: I am a young priest who chose to take holy \nvows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and \ndistillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life. \nAgenda: Accumulate wealth through absinthe smuggling \nand then flee across the ocean to rebuild my life in the new \nworld.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Accumulate wealth through absinthe smuggling \nand then flee across the ocean to rebuild my life in the new \nworld.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622202,"modifiedTime":1781557622202,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"MDneQMpkrawIQYAi","name":"Georg the Survivor","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"753psErBEub0wng1","name":"Georg the Survivor - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was \nliving in the streets.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138.","positive":"I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was \nliving in the streets.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tbpoIN3rcjAf7XrS","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was \nliving in the streets.\nAgenda: Escape from Stegeborg as soon as possible, so I can \nleave what I saw behind me and start a new life.\nThe Quiet Guards</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-georg-the-survivor-138","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":138,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was \nliving in the streets.\nAgenda: Escape from Stegeborg as soon as possible, so I can \nleave what I saw behind me and start a new life.\nThe Quiet Guards</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Escape from Stegeborg as soon as possible, so I can \nleave what I saw behind me and start a new life.\nThe Quiet Guards","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"MFC5SckAtnJTygZw","name":"Hazir’s Guards","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Vy8CFfLJwwv9mJ98","name":"Hazir’s Guards - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are well-trained in the protection of our \nmaster.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163.","positive":"We are well-trained in the protection of our \nmaster.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ZqrnwzhFDaTzIBSt","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are well-trained in the protection of our \nmaster.\nAgenda: Protect Hazir from all threats / Eliminate the beggar who persecutes our master.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 163."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-hazir-s-guards-163","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":163,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are well-trained in the protection of our \nmaster.\nAgenda: Protect Hazir from all threats / Eliminate the beggar who persecutes our master.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Protect Hazir from all threats / Eliminate the beggar who persecutes our master.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642583,"modifiedTime":1781557642583,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"MSlkQ7k9UhlLPZe3","name":"Dioniso Gonsalva called the Beast","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"nEkmJsqQzbqfy7oT","name":"Dioniso Gonsalva called the Beast - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young man afflicted by a curse \nthat turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps my incredible ferocity in check.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 130.","positive":"I am a young man afflicted by a curse \nthat turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps my incredible ferocity in check.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632137,"modifiedTime":1781557632137,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"F5yC9R5kmhjoPuYO","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young man afflicted by a curse \nthat turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps my incredible ferocity in check.\nAgenda: I would like to live alone with Bella \nin this paradise, and I only tolerate the House \nof Roses for the sake of my love for her / I \nwould like to show the full extent of my love \nto Bella, but until she gives herself to me, I \nwill have to take my frustration out on \nher handmaids.\nGift – The Beast: Dionysus can \nact twice during an Exchange. When \nmoving, Dionysus can jump up to thirty \nfeet and easily destroy any obstacle. \nWhen acting to save Bella, Dionysus \nincreases his Opposition Level by 1.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 130."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632137,"modifiedTime":1781557632137,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-dioniso-gonsalva-called-the-beast-130","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":130,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young man afflicted by a curse \nthat turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent \nkeeps my incredible ferocity in check.\nAgenda: I would like to live alone with Bella \nin this paradise, and I only tolerate the House \nof Roses for the sake of my love for her / I \nwould like to show the full extent of my love \nto Bella, but until she gives herself to me, I \nwill have to take my frustration out on \nher handmaids.\nGift – The Beast: Dionysus can \nact twice during an Exchange. When \nmoving, Dionysus can jump up to thirty \nfeet and easily destroy any obstacle. \nWhen acting to save Bella, Dionysus \nincreases his Opposition Level by 1.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I would like to live alone with Bella \nin this paradise, and I only tolerate the House \nof Roses for the sake of my love for her / I \nwould like to show the full extent of my love \nto Bella, but until she gives herself to me, I \nwill have to take my frustration out on \nher handmaids.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632137,"modifiedTime":1781557632137,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Mf1DhZTEW6pPnftV","name":"The Village Elders 1: Asmo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"hc20s2YzmAk1QgfY","name":"The Village Elders 1: Asmo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the leader of the elders, and my word is \nfinal when there is disagreement.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 118.","positive":"I am the leader of the elders, and my word is \nfinal when there is disagreement.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640522,"modifiedTime":1781557640522,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"D3yera7517M0cQFK","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the leader of the elders, and my word is \nfinal when there is disagreement.\nAgenda: To serve Nikola by reporting everything that happens in the village / To keep outside attention away from Rovaniemi and prevent Nikola from being forced to harm the \nvillagers.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 118."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640522,"modifiedTime":1781557640522,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-the-village-elders-1-asmo-118","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":118,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the leader of the elders, and my word is \nfinal when there is disagreement.\nAgenda: To serve Nikola by reporting everything that happens in the village / To keep outside attention away from Rovaniemi and prevent Nikola from being forced to harm the \nvillagers.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To serve Nikola by reporting everything that happens in the village / To keep outside attention away from Rovaniemi and prevent Nikola from being forced to harm the \nvillagers.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640522,"modifiedTime":1781557640522,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NAiTwOPlc2sHmUsq","name":"Alice’s special tea","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"KSjYBFi4x94Gmd7y","name":"Alice’s special tea - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A delicious tea mixed with a powerful \nsoporific.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177.","positive":"A delicious tea mixed with a powerful \nsoporific.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"iGfK99E4F0oTpV4N","name":"Gift - Sleep","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Those who drink the tea and fail their Defense \nCheck will fall into a deep sleep for over eight hours. Only \nsuffering severe pain (equivalent to receiving 1 Wound) or \nthe use of magic can awaken a sleeping subject.\nAlice Liddell The \nDirector</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QUAz1FAkUpkC5DOP","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A delicious tea mixed with a powerful \nsoporific.\nGift - Sleep: Those who drink the tea and fail their Defense \nCheck will fall into a deep sleep for over eight hours. Only \nsuffering severe pain (equivalent to receiving 1 Wound) or \nthe use of magic can awaken a sleeping subject.\nAlice Liddell The \nDirector</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-alice-s-special-tea-177","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":177,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A delicious tea mixed with a powerful \nsoporific.\nGift - Sleep: Those who drink the tea and fail their Defense \nCheck will fall into a deep sleep for over eight hours. Only \nsuffering severe pain (equivalent to receiving 1 Wound) or \nthe use of magic can awaken a sleeping subject.\nAlice Liddell The \nDirector</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NHa7KURLH2MrZzTW","name":"Conquers Death for Love","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"DPRZR6rJcAfryZ44","name":"Conquers Death for Love - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a knight devoted to my beloved Isolde \nand have returned from the dead to protect her.</p>","notes":"Isolde the Singer of Lost Love - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 172.","positive":"I am a knight devoted to my beloved Isolde \nand have returned from the dead to protect her.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643132,"modifiedTime":1781557643132,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"hRn8C5I5Z8hXyvvV","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a knight devoted to my beloved Isolde \nand have returned from the dead to protect her. \nAgenda: Defend Isolde from those who would harm her.\nGift - Immortal Love: Tristan is immune to all Wounds \nas long as Isolde has at least 1 Wound. The only way to \neliminate the Knight is to reduce Isolde to 0 Wounds, causing Tristan’s immediate destruction. When Tristan attacks \na target that has wounded Isolde, he increases his OL by 1 \nand inflicts 2 Wounds. \n•\nHow to handle Isolde the Singer of \nLost Love\nWhen Isolde enters the Scene, the Storyteller decides or \nrolls a die to see which NPC she possesses. Using this advantage, Isolde will deliberately try to create problems, using any hurt feelings caused by the actions of the NPCs or \nHunters involved in the Encounter. At the end of the Encounter, Isolde will evaluate how the Hunters acted based \non two parameters:\n ◆ If the Hunters take feelings into consideration and help \nthose in need even at the expense of their personal \ngoals, Isolde will not report them to the One Who Plots \nin the Shadows. \n ◆ If the Hunters did not care about the feelings of others, Isolde will punish them by reporting information \nabout them to The One Who Plots in the Shadows, \nwhich the Storyteller can use in the final confrontation \nof the Campaign or to better prepare a future Assassin \n(page 249 of the Broken Tales Core Book). Isolde receives Betrayed Love Tokens equal to half the number \nof Hunters directly involved (rounded down). She can \nuse the Tokens in the confrontation with the Hunters \nwhen she activates the Gift - Punish Those Who Despise Love. \nHunters can recognize Isolde’s presence by certain details \nthat the spirit includes when she possesses an NPC or appears as herself. She should have a certain way of speaking \nor an attitude that will be characteristic of any possessed \nNPC, regardless of their background or social status. When \nthe Hunters ask questions about the strange behavior, Isolde will either play dumb or try to shift the focus to the \nproblems she is creating for the Hunters to solve. \nIf the Hunters decide to corner the NPC because they realize something is wrong, Isolde will appear suddenly to activate her Gift - Punish Those Who Despise Love. \nNote: Introducing Isolde during an Encounter may require \na small amount of planning on the part of the Storyteller; \nwe have included a series of tables that can provide useful \nhooks for Isolde’s management.</p>","notes":"Isolde the Singer of Lost Love - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 172."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643132,"modifiedTime":1781557643132,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-isolde-the-singer-of-lost-love-conquers-death-for-love-172","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"isolde-the-singer-of-lost-love","adventureTitle":"Isolde the Singer of Lost Love","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":172,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Isolde the Singer of Lost Love","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a knight devoted to my beloved Isolde \nand have returned from the dead to protect her. \nAgenda: Defend Isolde from those who would harm her.\nGift - Immortal Love: Tristan is immune to all Wounds \nas long as Isolde has at least 1 Wound. The only way to \neliminate the Knight is to reduce Isolde to 0 Wounds, causing Tristan’s immediate destruction. When Tristan attacks \na target that has wounded Isolde, he increases his OL by 1 \nand inflicts 2 Wounds. \n•\nHow to handle Isolde the Singer of \nLost Love\nWhen Isolde enters the Scene, the Storyteller decides or \nrolls a die to see which NPC she possesses. Using this advantage, Isolde will deliberately try to create problems, using any hurt feelings caused by the actions of the NPCs or \nHunters involved in the Encounter. At the end of the Encounter, Isolde will evaluate how the Hunters acted based \non two parameters:\n ◆ If the Hunters take feelings into consideration and help \nthose in need even at the expense of their personal \ngoals, Isolde will not report them to the One Who Plots \nin the Shadows. \n ◆ If the Hunters did not care about the feelings of others, Isolde will punish them by reporting information \nabout them to The One Who Plots in the Shadows, \nwhich the Storyteller can use in the final confrontation \nof the Campaign or to better prepare a future Assassin \n(page 249 of the Broken Tales Core Book). Isolde receives Betrayed Love Tokens equal to half the number \nof Hunters directly involved (rounded down). She can \nuse the Tokens in the confrontation with the Hunters \nwhen she activates the Gift - Punish Those Who Despise Love. \nHunters can recognize Isolde’s presence by certain details \nthat the spirit includes when she possesses an NPC or appears as herself. She should have a certain way of speaking \nor an attitude that will be characteristic of any possessed \nNPC, regardless of their background or social status. When \nthe Hunters ask questions about the strange behavior, Isolde will either play dumb or try to shift the focus to the \nproblems she is creating for the Hunters to solve. \nIf the Hunters decide to corner the NPC because they realize something is wrong, Isolde will appear suddenly to activate her Gift - Punish Those Who Despise Love. \nNote: Introducing Isolde during an Encounter may require \na small amount of planning on the part of the Storyteller; \nwe have included a series of tables that can provide useful \nhooks for Isolde’s management.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Defend Isolde from those who would harm her.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643132,"modifiedTime":1781557643132,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NJO0ISLB2IzpqpCw","name":"Restless spirits","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"1mZrVsngrDdMw2ZH","name":"Restless spirits - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are restless souls and yearn for the essence \nof the living.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 151.","positive":"We are restless souls and yearn for the essence \nof the living.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622310,"modifiedTime":1781557622310,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"r3GaDz2qVqYvA6Ms","name":"Gift - Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>This NPC is in a spirit form and can only be \ndamaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs life energy \nand inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection and barriers \ncannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit is harmed by \nnon-magical means, it still will suffer a Wound. However, \nwhen the Spirit has no Wounds left, it disappears and \nrematerializes immediately. In doing so, all its Wounds are \nhealed, except those inflicted by magical means.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 151.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622310,"modifiedTime":1781557622310,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"v3hU1WbtNor7142g","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are restless souls and yearn for the essence \nof the living.\nAgenda: We sense Yvonne’s wrath, driving us to prey on the \nliving.\nGift - Spirit: This NPC is in a spirit form and can only be \ndamaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs life energy \nand inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection and barriers \ncannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit is harmed by \nnon-magical means, it still will suffer a Wound. However, \nwhen the Spirit has no Wounds left, it disappears and \nrematerializes immediately. In doing so, all its Wounds are \nhealed, except those inflicted by magical means. \nInformation: If a Hunter communicates with Spirits \nthrough the Gift Voice of the Spirits, they will be able to \nlearn of Yvonne’s presence.\nThe Cemetery\nDescriptor: The great cemetery of Paris, protected by \nhigh walls and well-maintained thanks to the work of many \ncustodians. Strange noises and a strong smell of death come \nfrom the mass graves.\nInformation: The cemetery is currently under the control \nof Lorenzo Scannapecore, an Italian doctor hired by the city \nof Paris to manage the excessive number of corpses inside \nthe mass graves. Lorenzo has sent the cemetery keepers \naway with the excuse of requiring quiet for his studies. \nHowever, that was only a ruse to secretly host Alizée, a nun \nhe has fallen in love with and whom he keeps safe from the \nsevere judgment of the Church. Lorenzo’s intent is to wait \nuntil the new year to embark with his beloved towards the \nNew World.\n ◆ Speaking with Lorenzo, the Hunters can learn about \nthe dire state of the mass graves of the cemetery, which \nin fact is about to explode due to the excessive number \nof decaying corpses. Lorenzo will appear strangely \nnervous, looking wary. The man fears that the Hunters \nmay discover Alizée hidden among the tombstones.\n ◆ Lorenzo is also a good astrologer and will be able to tell \nthe Hunters about the passage of Morituris and how, \naccording to the legend, this gives power to the spirits.\n ◆ Alizée will observe the Hunters from behind some \ntombstones, trying not to be discovered. However, she \nwill always remain nearby, ready to intervene to help \nher beloved.\n ◆ Alizée will try not to reveal her abilities. When cornered, \nshe may report that the spirits are very agitated, both \ndue to the presence of a very powerful and hateful \nspirit among them, and due to the imminent passage \nof the comet.\n ◆ Strange smells and noises come from the mass graves. \nLorenzo will say that it is the dead bodies generating</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 151."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622310,"modifiedTime":1781557622310,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-restless-spirits-151","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":151,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are restless souls and yearn for the essence \nof the living.\nAgenda: We sense Yvonne’s wrath, driving us to prey on the \nliving.\nGift - Spirit: This NPC is in a spirit form and can only be \ndamaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs life energy \nand inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection and barriers \ncannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit is harmed by \nnon-magical means, it still will suffer a Wound. However, \nwhen the Spirit has no Wounds left, it disappears and \nrematerializes immediately. In doing so, all its Wounds are \nhealed, except those inflicted by magical means. \nInformation: If a Hunter communicates with Spirits \nthrough the Gift Voice of the Spirits, they will be able to \nlearn of Yvonne’s presence.\nThe Cemetery\nDescriptor: The great cemetery of Paris, protected by \nhigh walls and well-maintained thanks to the work of many \ncustodians. Strange noises and a strong smell of death come \nfrom the mass graves.\nInformation: The cemetery is currently under the control \nof Lorenzo Scannapecore, an Italian doctor hired by the city \nof Paris to manage the excessive number of corpses inside \nthe mass graves. Lorenzo has sent the cemetery keepers \naway with the excuse of requiring quiet for his studies. \nHowever, that was only a ruse to secretly host Alizée, a nun \nhe has fallen in love with and whom he keeps safe from the \nsevere judgment of the Church. Lorenzo’s intent is to wait \nuntil the new year to embark with his beloved towards the \nNew World.\n ◆ Speaking with Lorenzo, the Hunters can learn about \nthe dire state of the mass graves of the cemetery, which \nin fact is about to explode due to the excessive number \nof decaying corpses. Lorenzo will appear strangely \nnervous, looking wary. The man fears that the Hunters \nmay discover Alizée hidden among the tombstones.\n ◆ Lorenzo is also a good astrologer and will be able to tell \nthe Hunters about the passage of Morituris and how, \naccording to the legend, this gives power to the spirits.\n ◆ Alizée will observe the Hunters from behind some \ntombstones, trying not to be discovered. However, she \nwill always remain nearby, ready to intervene to help \nher beloved.\n ◆ Alizée will try not to reveal her abilities. When cornered, \nshe may report that the spirits are very agitated, both \ndue to the presence of a very powerful and hateful \nspirit among them, and due to the imminent passage \nof the comet.\n ◆ Strange smells and noises come from the mass graves. \nLorenzo will say that it is the dead bodies generating</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"We sense Yvonne’s wrath, driving us to prey on the \nliving.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622310,"modifiedTime":1781557622310,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NMAauDUqMInvu8jC","name":"The Thieves","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"4AmSHJ5IXXVHAix1","name":"The Thieves - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are looters, skilled with scimitar and sling. \nOur numbers are our strength.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 162.","positive":"We are looters, skilled with scimitar and sling. \nOur numbers are our strength.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642567,"modifiedTime":1781557642567,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"oKCIUucLCrhIFZ5w","name":"Gift - Band of Thieves","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A Thief increases their OL by 1 \nas long as the total number of band members is greater than \nthe total number of enemies. \nThe Oasis</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 162.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642567,"modifiedTime":1781557642567,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Rcy46Bg2RBqZKZsm","name":"Gift - The Lair","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>While fighting inside the Oasis, Thieves \ncan benefit from the improvements they have made to the \nplace. Once per Exchange, one of these effects will be activated:</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 162.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642567,"modifiedTime":1781557642567,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"pb5Oz41MXmmwo36J","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are looters, skilled with scimitar and sling. \nOur numbers are our strength.\nAgenda: Protect our lair and discover the password to enter, \nwhich only our late leader knew.\nGift - Band of Thieves: A Thief increases their OL by 1 \nas long as the total number of band members is greater than \nthe total number of enemies. \nThe Oasis \nDescriptor: A large, lush oasis that the Thieves have transformed into the perfect hideout. \nGift - The Lair: While fighting inside the Oasis, Thieves \ncan benefit from the improvements they have made to the \nplace. Once per Exchange, one of these effects will be activated:</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 162."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642567,"modifiedTime":1781557642567,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-the-thieves-162","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":162,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are looters, skilled with scimitar and sling. \nOur numbers are our strength.\nAgenda: Protect our lair and discover the password to enter, \nwhich only our late leader knew.\nGift - Band of Thieves: A Thief increases their OL by 1 \nas long as the total number of band members is greater than \nthe total number of enemies. \nThe Oasis \nDescriptor: A large, lush oasis that the Thieves have transformed into the perfect hideout. \nGift - The Lair: While fighting inside the Oasis, Thieves \ncan benefit from the improvements they have made to the \nplace. Once per Exchange, one of these effects will be activated:</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Protect our lair and discover the password to enter, \nwhich only our late leader knew.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642567,"modifiedTime":1781557642567,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NNKe24tANUDNnihv","name":"The Hammerheads","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"bsin1dmqiVKZmsCW","name":"The Hammerheads - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We were once a ferocious team of skilled \nmercenaries, but now we are in Helga’s service. We were \ntamed by her magic and therefore we do anything and \neverything for her.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 237.","positive":"We were once a ferocious team of skilled \nmercenaries, but now we are in Helga’s service. We were \ntamed by her magic and therefore we do anything and \neverything for her.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624561,"modifiedTime":1781557624561,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ADevsedCdLWOMINv","name":"Gift - Hammerhead Helmet","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The heavy and distinctive \nHammerhead helmet opens like a flower on the shoulders \nand grants total head and chest protection, making the \nNPC immune to any Wound that can’t get past a thick layer \nof metal. An enemy can aim at the lower parts of the NPC \nto ignore the helmet. However, they receive 1 Penalty for \ntheir Check.\nOZena (Dorothea)\nDorothea’s profile is presented on page \n228, only her Agenda changes.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 237.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624561,"modifiedTime":1781557624561,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tX220RHJC1iQ2bf8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We were once a ferocious team of skilled \nmercenaries, but now we are in Helga’s service. We were \ntamed by her magic and therefore we do anything and \neverything for her.\nGift - Hammerhead Helmet: The heavy and distinctive \nHammerhead helmet opens like a flower on the shoulders \nand grants total head and chest protection, making the \nNPC immune to any Wound that can’t get past a thick layer \nof metal. An enemy can aim at the lower parts of the NPC \nto ignore the helmet. However, they receive 1 Penalty for \ntheir Check.\nOZena (Dorothea)\nDorothea’s profile is presented on page \n228, only her Agenda changes.\nAgenda: Free myself from the prison \nwhere Helga locked me up.\nEnd of Scene: Helga’s threat is \nended, either through combat or by \nconvincing her to let Dorothea go free. \nThe girl surrenders to the Hunters, \nrevealing that everything she did was \nordered by Norman Henkle, a doctor \nwho, like her, comes from another \nworld. Henkle settled in the center of the Black Forest, \nin a village called Smaragd. Henkle’s goal is to gather all \nthe pieces of the Compass Rose to summon the magical \ntornado. Dorothea realizes that Henkle is insane and reveals \nto the Hunters that even though she has been stopped, the \nman will still try to activate the half-reassembled artifact, \ncertainly with devastating results. Only Dorothea knows \nthe location of the village and she is willing to accompany \nthe Hunters, expressing sincere repentance.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are three Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters get the better of Wolfgang: Helga will \nlet him speak for a while so she can observe the Hunters \nclosely and then kill the man by drowning him in his own \nblood.\nWhen the Hunters start to get the better of a conflict \nwith Helga’s minions: the witch will detonate one of her \nminions in each Exchange to cover \nthe Hunters in her blood. Y ou can \ntry to control them later.\nIf Dorothea is saved by the \nHunters: she will stay by their \nside as an ally to take revenge on \nHelga. She will try to kill her even \nif the Hunters intend to negotiate.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 237."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624561,"modifiedTime":1781557624561,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-the-hammerheads-237","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":237,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We were once a ferocious team of skilled \nmercenaries, but now we are in Helga’s service. We were \ntamed by her magic and therefore we do anything and \neverything for her.\nGift - Hammerhead Helmet: The heavy and distinctive \nHammerhead helmet opens like a flower on the shoulders \nand grants total head and chest protection, making the \nNPC immune to any Wound that can’t get past a thick layer \nof metal. An enemy can aim at the lower parts of the NPC \nto ignore the helmet. However, they receive 1 Penalty for \ntheir Check.\nOZena (Dorothea)\nDorothea’s profile is presented on page \n228, only her Agenda changes.\nAgenda: Free myself from the prison \nwhere Helga locked me up.\nEnd of Scene: Helga’s threat is \nended, either through combat or by \nconvincing her to let Dorothea go free. \nThe girl surrenders to the Hunters, \nrevealing that everything she did was \nordered by Norman Henkle, a doctor \nwho, like her, comes from another \nworld. Henkle settled in the center of the Black Forest, \nin a village called Smaragd. Henkle’s goal is to gather all \nthe pieces of the Compass Rose to summon the magical \ntornado. Dorothea realizes that Henkle is insane and reveals \nto the Hunters that even though she has been stopped, the \nman will still try to activate the half-reassembled artifact, \ncertainly with devastating results. Only Dorothea knows \nthe location of the village and she is willing to accompany \nthe Hunters, expressing sincere repentance.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are three Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters get the better of Wolfgang: Helga will \nlet him speak for a while so she can observe the Hunters \nclosely and then kill the man by drowning him in his own \nblood.\nWhen the Hunters start to get the better of a conflict \nwith Helga’s minions: the witch will detonate one of her \nminions in each Exchange to cover \nthe Hunters in her blood. Y ou can \ntry to control them later.\nIf Dorothea is saved by the \nHunters: she will stay by their \nside as an ally to take revenge on \nHelga. She will try to kill her even \nif the Hunters intend to negotiate.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Free myself from the prison \nwhere Helga locked me up.\nEnd of Scene: Helga’s threat is \nended, either through combat or by \nconvincing her to let Dorothea go free. \nThe girl surrenders to the Hunters, \nrevealing that everything she did was \nordered by Norman Henkle, a doctor \nwho, like her, comes from another \nworld. Henkle settled in the center of the Black Forest, \nin a village called Smaragd. Henkle’s goal is to gather all \nthe pieces of the Compass Rose to summon the magical \ntornado. Dorothea realizes that Henkle is insane and reveals \nto the Hunters that even though she has been stopped, the \nman will still try to activate the half-reassembled artifact, \ncertainly with devastating results. Only Dorothea knows \nthe location of the village and she is willing to accompany \nthe Hunters, expressing sincere repentance.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are three Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nIf the Hunters get the better of Wolfgang: Helga will \nlet him speak for a while so she can observe the Hunters \nclosely and then kill the man by drowning him in his own \nblood.\nWhen the Hunters start to get the better of a conflict \nwith Helga’s minions: the witch will detonate one of her \nminions in each Exchange to cover \nthe Hunters in her blood. Y ou can \ntry to control them later.\nIf Dorothea is saved by the \nHunters: she will stay by their \nside as an ally to take revenge on \nHelga. She will try to kill her even \nif the Hunters intend to negotiate.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624561,"modifiedTime":1781557624561,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NPOMHHgnNpUTx75o","name":"Distrustful Inhabitants","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"n9OVUROtn7gESXy3","name":"Distrustful Inhabitants - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We don’t want to attract too much attention \nto Sinalunga, so we’re reluctant to talk to foreigners. Nobody \nhere wants to lose what they have gained through years of \nhard work.\nInformation from the townspeople: \nRoll a die or pick from the list.\n ◆ 1-2: 10 people have been found, but 11 went missing. \nNino’s body is still missing. He is Mastro Antonio’s \napprentice carpenter. Antonio is known as Mastro \n“Cherry” Ciliegia because of his squat and red nose. \n ◆ 3-4: Villa Cilesterino is haunted by the ghost of the \nold owner, Azzurra. She was burned at the stake for \nwitchcraft.\n ◆ 5-6: The high standard of living in Sinalunga led to the \nopening of Villa Balocchi, a tavern on the edge of town \nwhere one can find company as well as a comfortable \nbed. The tavern is managed by Amabile Burromo and \nis in open competition with the historic town inn, the \nGambero Rosso (meaning “the Red Prawn”).\nThe Old Well\nDescriptor: An old abandoned well in the middle of a \ndilapidated vineyard. A nauseating smell from the bottom of \nthe well reminds anyone who approaches of the horror that \nit hides.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 134.","positive":"We don’t want to attract too much attention \nto Sinalunga, so we’re reluctant to talk to foreigners. Nobody \nhere wants to lose what they have gained through years of \nhard work.\nInformation from the townspeople: \nRoll a die or pick from the list.\n ◆ 1-2: 10 people have been found, but 11 went missing. \nNino’s body is still missing. He is Mastro Antonio’s \napprentice carpenter. Antonio is known as Mastro \n“Cherry” Ciliegia because of his squat and red nose. \n ◆ 3-4: Villa Cilesterino is haunted by the ghost of the \nold owner, Azzurra. She was burned at the stake for \nwitchcraft.\n ◆ 5-6: The high standard of living in Sinalunga led to the \nopening of Villa Balocchi, a tavern on the edge of town \nwhere one can find company as well as a comfortable \nbed. The tavern is managed by Amabile Burromo and \nis in open competition with the historic town inn, the \nGambero Rosso (meaning “the Red Prawn”).\nThe Old Well\nDescriptor: An old abandoned well in the middle of a \ndilapidated vineyard. A nauseating smell from the bottom of \nthe well reminds anyone who approaches of the horror that \nit hides.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621795,"modifiedTime":1781557621795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mMIT8vGmQvYkYgQY","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: We don’t want to attract too much attention \nto Sinalunga, so we’re reluctant to talk to foreigners. Nobody \nhere wants to lose what they have gained through years of \nhard work.\nInformation from the townspeople: \nRoll a die or pick from the list.\n ◆ 1-2: 10 people have been found, but 11 went missing. \nNino’s body is still missing. He is Mastro Antonio’s \napprentice carpenter. Antonio is known as Mastro \n“Cherry” Ciliegia because of his squat and red nose. \n ◆ 3-4: Villa Cilesterino is haunted by the ghost of the \nold owner, Azzurra. She was burned at the stake for \nwitchcraft.\n ◆ 5-6: The high standard of living in Sinalunga led to the \nopening of Villa Balocchi, a tavern on the edge of town \nwhere one can find company as well as a comfortable \nbed. The tavern is managed by Amabile Burromo and \nis in open competition with the historic town inn, the \nGambero Rosso (meaning “the Red Prawn”).\nThe Old Well\nDescriptor: An old abandoned well in the middle of a \ndilapidated vineyard. A nauseating smell from the bottom of \nthe well reminds anyone who approaches of the horror that \nit hides.\nInformation: \n ◆ The bodies have already been removed and burned to \navoid infection and disease. \n ◆ When going down into the well, however, there are still \nsome remains and traces of blood. \n ◆ On the bottom, it is possible to find a carpenter’s chisel \nthat Geppetto lost while moving the corpses. \nThe Gambero Rosso Inn\nDescriptor: A small and cozy tavern, full of bottles of good \nwine.\nInformation: \n ◆ Speaking with the innkeeper, a big fat man named \nDuccio, the Hunters will learn that Villa Balocchi is a \nplace steeped in sin, where men and women gamble \nand entertain themselves in shady encounters. \nDuring the evening, Geppetto is at the Gambero Rosso and \nwill not hesitate to play out his little rehearsed spectacle of \nthe worried father for whoever shows up. Geppetto will \ndescribe Carlo as an annoying child with a pair of old, \nelegant shoes that Geppetto gave him for his first day of \nschool.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 134."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621795,"modifiedTime":1781557621795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-distrustful-inhabitants-134","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":134,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: We don’t want to attract too much attention \nto Sinalunga, so we’re reluctant to talk to foreigners. Nobody \nhere wants to lose what they have gained through years of \nhard work.\nInformation from the townspeople: \nRoll a die or pick from the list.\n ◆ 1-2: 10 people have been found, but 11 went missing. \nNino’s body is still missing. He is Mastro Antonio’s \napprentice carpenter. Antonio is known as Mastro \n“Cherry” Ciliegia because of his squat and red nose. \n ◆ 3-4: Villa Cilesterino is haunted by the ghost of the \nold owner, Azzurra. She was burned at the stake for \nwitchcraft.\n ◆ 5-6: The high standard of living in Sinalunga led to the \nopening of Villa Balocchi, a tavern on the edge of town \nwhere one can find company as well as a comfortable \nbed. The tavern is managed by Amabile Burromo and \nis in open competition with the historic town inn, the \nGambero Rosso (meaning “the Red Prawn”).\nThe Old Well\nDescriptor: An old abandoned well in the middle of a \ndilapidated vineyard. A nauseating smell from the bottom of \nthe well reminds anyone who approaches of the horror that \nit hides.\nInformation: \n ◆ The bodies have already been removed and burned to \navoid infection and disease. \n ◆ When going down into the well, however, there are still \nsome remains and traces of blood. \n ◆ On the bottom, it is possible to find a carpenter’s chisel \nthat Geppetto lost while moving the corpses. \nThe Gambero Rosso Inn\nDescriptor: A small and cozy tavern, full of bottles of good \nwine.\nInformation: \n ◆ Speaking with the innkeeper, a big fat man named \nDuccio, the Hunters will learn that Villa Balocchi is a \nplace steeped in sin, where men and women gamble \nand entertain themselves in shady encounters. \nDuring the evening, Geppetto is at the Gambero Rosso and \nwill not hesitate to play out his little rehearsed spectacle of \nthe worried father for whoever shows up. Geppetto will \ndescribe Carlo as an annoying child with a pair of old, \nelegant shoes that Geppetto gave him for his first day of \nschool.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621795,"modifiedTime":1781557621795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NeL2a4sXOsrPPPON","name":"Elizaveta – The cruel bride","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"sZjTiPIMRAVlDkf9","name":"Elizaveta – The cruel bride - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever \nis needed to get what I want.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122.","positive":"I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever \nis needed to get what I want.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qL8cfXf0ZNiKDYm5","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever \nis needed to get what I want.\nAgenda: To maintain the comforts and luxuries I have \nearned. That means ridding myself of my annoying daughter \nIskra.\nVincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of \nthe Guards</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-elizaveta-the-cruel-bride-122","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":122,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever \nis needed to get what I want.\nAgenda: To maintain the comforts and luxuries I have \nearned. That means ridding myself of my annoying daughter \nIskra.\nVincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of \nthe Guards</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To maintain the comforts and luxuries I have \nearned. That means ridding myself of my annoying daughter \nIskra.\nVincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of \nthe Guards","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"OoVt4RfL76CcCH7J","name":"Fairies (The King's Awakening)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"5Ao82gvjPMkf8ql2","name":"Fairies - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are fairies and we love company and good \nstories. We like humans, even though they tend to age too fast \nby our standards.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 196.","positive":"We are fairies and we love company and good \nstories. We like humans, even though they tend to age too fast \nby our standards.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644332,"modifiedTime":1781557644332,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1Ry5Fs4FP4aFD1ry","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPCs (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are fairies and we love company and good \nstories. We like humans, even though they tend to age too fast \nby our standards. \nAgenda: Entertain nice people for as long as possible. \nGift - A Midsummer Night’s Dream: Talking to Fairies for a long time can be fatal for a human, as time passes \nfaster in their presence. After a minute of conversation, the \nsubject can make a Defense Check to see if they are getting \nold. If successful, the subject can end the conversation. If \nunsuccessful, the subject loses 2 Soma, and if the subject is \nalready at 0 Soma, the subject loses 1 Wound. Succeeding \nwith a Cost is possible, but the easiest way to interrupt the \neffect of the Gift is to feel pain, so the Cost will always be \n1 Wound. A new Check can be made after each minute of \nconversation. An outside party may attempt to break the effect of this Gift with words (Position Check) or by inflicting \n1 Wound (Automatic).\nFairy information:\n ◆ They come from the great lake where the house once \nstood, the home of the Lady who cared for all the magical creatures on the island. The Lady then decided \nto leave, fed up with the many brave young men who \ncame to the lake, insistent on gaining her blessing.\n ◆ The Fairies have always stayed to guard the Lake, but \non the day the Hunters arrived, a grumpy old man who \nclearly looked like a Sorcerer appeared at the lake accompanied by a huge knight in armor as black as night. \nThe old man frightened off the Fairies, who, peering \nfrom a distance, clearly saw the two of them walking \nalong the shores of the Lake, searching for something.\n ◆ The island contains many illusions that prevent ordinary mortals from discovering certain truths. The Fairies possess a Fairy Crystal that allows those who look \nthrough it to see the illusions. They are willing to give \nup the Crystal, but only in exchange for something of \nequal value. If the Hunters do not know what to propose, the Fairies will say that a beautiful treasure is \nguarded by a Knight in the Forest to the east.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 196."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644332,"modifiedTime":1781557644332,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-fairies-196","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":196,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPCs (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are fairies and we love company and good \nstories. We like humans, even though they tend to age too fast \nby our standards. \nAgenda: Entertain nice people for as long as possible. \nGift - A Midsummer Night’s Dream: Talking to Fairies for a long time can be fatal for a human, as time passes \nfaster in their presence. After a minute of conversation, the \nsubject can make a Defense Check to see if they are getting \nold. If successful, the subject can end the conversation. If \nunsuccessful, the subject loses 2 Soma, and if the subject is \nalready at 0 Soma, the subject loses 1 Wound. Succeeding \nwith a Cost is possible, but the easiest way to interrupt the \neffect of the Gift is to feel pain, so the Cost will always be \n1 Wound. A new Check can be made after each minute of \nconversation. An outside party may attempt to break the effect of this Gift with words (Position Check) or by inflicting \n1 Wound (Automatic).\nFairy information:\n ◆ They come from the great lake where the house once \nstood, the home of the Lady who cared for all the magical creatures on the island. The Lady then decided \nto leave, fed up with the many brave young men who \ncame to the lake, insistent on gaining her blessing.\n ◆ The Fairies have always stayed to guard the Lake, but \non the day the Hunters arrived, a grumpy old man who \nclearly looked like a Sorcerer appeared at the lake accompanied by a huge knight in armor as black as night. \nThe old man frightened off the Fairies, who, peering \nfrom a distance, clearly saw the two of them walking \nalong the shores of the Lake, searching for something.\n ◆ The island contains many illusions that prevent ordinary mortals from discovering certain truths. The Fairies possess a Fairy Crystal that allows those who look \nthrough it to see the illusions. They are willing to give \nup the Crystal, but only in exchange for something of \nequal value. If the Hunters do not know what to propose, the Fairies will say that a beautiful treasure is \nguarded by a Knight in the Forest to the east.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Entertain nice people for as long as possible.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644332,"modifiedTime":1781557644332,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"PthHXRiJUYJdGSzL","name":"The Gang of the Lost Boys","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"E6k4gyKMgC8447Os","name":"The Gang of the Lost Boys - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are young rebels who have lost everything \nand are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","positive":"We are young rebels who have lost everything \nand are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Igapo7f1Bp9Yv7LV","name":"Gift - Gang Seal","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Each gang member has a tattooed eye \non their right hand that allows them to see and use the Seals \nof the Cauldron Fae scattered throughout London.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CmMngv5O4K7k0yCq","name":"Gift - Rioter","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Each gang member increases his OL by \n1 when acting with the support of at least one teammate. \nEach member has a magic berry that they can throw which \nwill explode on contact, inflicting 1 Wound on all targets \nwithin several feet. A Defense Check allows a target to leap \naway from the blast zone. \nKensington Gardens</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"i8FwIcX5aAi3sOoY","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young rebels who have lost everything \nand are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.\nAgenda: To help Pietrik in his plan for the destruction of \nLondon. \nGift – Gang Seal: Each gang member has a tattooed eye \non their right hand that allows them to see and use the Seals \nof the Cauldron Fae scattered throughout London.\nGift – Rioter: Each gang member increases his OL by \n1 when acting with the support of at least one teammate. \nEach member has a magic berry that they can throw which \nwill explode on contact, inflicting 1 Wound on all targets \nwithin several feet. A Defense Check allows a target to leap \naway from the blast zone. \nKensington Gardens\nDescriptor: A large green area in the heart of London. \nAccess to the gardens is prohibited due to ongoing \nmaintenance work. \nInformation: The Kensington Gardens have been long \nabandoned because the Cauldron Fae uses her magic to \ncreate unending problems for the gardeners. No one has \nentered the gardens for over a year and Pietrik has used an \nold gardeners’ house as a prison to keep Gwendolyn locked \nup. The girl hasn’t tried to escape and hopes, so far in vain, \nto convince Pietrik to give up on his destructive plans. \nIt is possible to descend through a well in \nthe eastern part of the park to access the \nCauldron Fae’s Lair. \nSeals: The Gardens are literally full of \nSeals.\nGwendolyn</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-the-gang-of-the-lost-boys-88","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":88,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young rebels who have lost everything \nand are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.\nAgenda: To help Pietrik in his plan for the destruction of \nLondon. \nGift – Gang Seal: Each gang member has a tattooed eye \non their right hand that allows them to see and use the Seals \nof the Cauldron Fae scattered throughout London.\nGift – Rioter: Each gang member increases his OL by \n1 when acting with the support of at least one teammate. \nEach member has a magic berry that they can throw which \nwill explode on contact, inflicting 1 Wound on all targets \nwithin several feet. A Defense Check allows a target to leap \naway from the blast zone. \nKensington Gardens\nDescriptor: A large green area in the heart of London. \nAccess to the gardens is prohibited due to ongoing \nmaintenance work. \nInformation: The Kensington Gardens have been long \nabandoned because the Cauldron Fae uses her magic to \ncreate unending problems for the gardeners. No one has \nentered the gardens for over a year and Pietrik has used an \nold gardeners’ house as a prison to keep Gwendolyn locked \nup. The girl hasn’t tried to escape and hopes, so far in vain, \nto convince Pietrik to give up on his destructive plans. \nIt is possible to descend through a well in \nthe eastern part of the park to access the \nCauldron Fae’s Lair. \nSeals: The Gardens are literally full of \nSeals.\nGwendolyn</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To help Pietrik in his plan for the destruction of \nLondon.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"QMRqZrZG0fuwdBiq","name":"Restless Spirit","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"t2xCr9VOHgh0FV8m","name":"Restless Spirit - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the spirit of a person who died under \nunpleasant circumstances. I hate life and only want to \nharm the living with my powers.</p>","notes":"Rome, City of the Order - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 68.","positive":"I am the spirit of a person who died under \nunpleasant circumstances. I hate life and only want to \nharm the living with my powers.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638487,"modifiedTime":1781557638487,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"O0uxUxh28vjbCdIP","name":"Gift - Spiritic Power","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The Restless Spirit can only \nbe permanently Wounded by magic. Wounds inflicted \nby other means may disperse the Spirit in the current \nScene, but it may return in another Scene with Wounds \ninflicted by mundane methods restored. The spirit can \nact 2 times during an Exchange, but not consecutively. \nAlthough intangible, the spirit can use its ghostly powers to push or grab people and objects.\n6: The Baron of the mansion: The Spirit is very distracted, \nand to keep his attention focused, it is necessary to over -\ncome the Head in the Clouds Threat. \nThreat - Head in the Clouds</p>","notes":"Rome, City of the Order - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 68.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638487,"modifiedTime":1781557638487,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"VHY28EDE1TVZRzEB","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the spirit of a person who died under \nunpleasant circumstances. I hate life and only want to \nharm the living with my powers.\nGift - Spiritic Power: The Restless Spirit can only \nbe permanently Wounded by magic. Wounds inflicted \nby other means may disperse the Spirit in the current \nScene, but it may return in another Scene with Wounds \ninflicted by mundane methods restored. The spirit can \nact 2 times during an Exchange, but not consecutively. \nAlthough intangible, the spirit can use its ghostly powers to push or grab people and objects.\n6: The Baron of the mansion: The Spirit is very distracted, \nand to keep his attention focused, it is necessary to over -\ncome the Head in the Clouds Threat. \nThreat - Head in the Clouds</p>","notes":"Rome, City of the Order - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 68."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638487,"modifiedTime":1781557638487,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-rome-city-of-the-order-restless-spirit-68","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"rome-city-of-the-order","adventureTitle":"Rome, City of the Order","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":68,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Rome, City of the Order","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the spirit of a person who died under \nunpleasant circumstances. I hate life and only want to \nharm the living with my powers.\nGift - Spiritic Power: The Restless Spirit can only \nbe permanently Wounded by magic. Wounds inflicted \nby other means may disperse the Spirit in the current \nScene, but it may return in another Scene with Wounds \ninflicted by mundane methods restored. The spirit can \nact 2 times during an Exchange, but not consecutively. \nAlthough intangible, the spirit can use its ghostly powers to push or grab people and objects.\n6: The Baron of the mansion: The Spirit is very distracted, \nand to keep his attention focused, it is necessary to over -\ncome the Head in the Clouds Threat. \nThreat - Head in the Clouds</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638487,"modifiedTime":1781557638487,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"QRMoJUQwFHOGBjsf","name":"Rikke the Nomad","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"6V7JzdVL854azQyU","name":"Rikke the Nomad - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a northern nomad and have always tried \nto lead my companions on the right path. I am used to the \nhard life of the forest and know how to move and hunt well.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 216.","positive":"I am a northern nomad and have always tried \nto lead my companions on the right path. I am used to the \nhard life of the forest and know how to move and hunt well.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645651,"modifiedTime":1781557645651,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WqgGXRbfBXy0ecdx","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a northern nomad and have always tried \nto lead my companions on the right path. I am used to the \nhard life of the forest and know how to move and hunt well.\nAgenda: To make my nomadic family prosperous. \nShard Descriptor: I am a nomad from the north, \ntrying to accumulate as much wealth as possible in order to \nmove to a more hospitable climate. I hate the hard life in these \nlatitudes and to survive I exploit my faithful companions. \nShard Agenda: Gather as much wealth as I can \nthrough banditry and then run far away, leaving my entire \nclan to their fate. \nGift - Power of the Shard: The Shard of the Mirror of the \nOther Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the person \nit injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they act in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor or Agenda. \n3</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 216."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645651,"modifiedTime":1781557645651,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-rikke-the-nomad-216","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":216,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a northern nomad and have always tried \nto lead my companions on the right path. I am used to the \nhard life of the forest and know how to move and hunt well.\nAgenda: To make my nomadic family prosperous. \nShard Descriptor: I am a nomad from the north, \ntrying to accumulate as much wealth as possible in order to \nmove to a more hospitable climate. I hate the hard life in these \nlatitudes and to survive I exploit my faithful companions. \nShard Agenda: Gather as much wealth as I can \nthrough banditry and then run far away, leaving my entire \nclan to their fate. \nGift - Power of the Shard: The Shard of the Mirror of the \nOther Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the person \nit injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they act in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor or Agenda. \n3</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To make my nomadic family prosperous. \nShard Descriptor: I am a nomad from the north, \ntrying to accumulate as much wealth as possible in order to \nmove to a more hospitable climate. I hate the hard life in these \nlatitudes and to survive I exploit my faithful companions. \nShard Agenda: Gather as much wealth as I can \nthrough banditry and then run far away, leaving my entire \nclan to their fate.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645651,"modifiedTime":1781557645651,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Qmx0mCECyz9piL8t","name":"City Guards","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"XJtZ4mmQYRKJBaXZ","name":"City Guards - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are skilled soldiers defending the city.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 160.","positive":"We are skilled soldiers defending the city.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642505,"modifiedTime":1781557642505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MniOX5K5ziL6VJXD","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are skilled soldiers defending the city. \nAgenda: We obey Aladdin’s orders because we fear his \nwrath, but we also want to stop his madness. \nJasmina the Brave</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 160."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642505,"modifiedTime":1781557642505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-city-guards-160","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":160,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are skilled soldiers defending the city. \nAgenda: We obey Aladdin’s orders because we fear his \nwrath, but we also want to stop his madness. \nJasmina the Brave</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"We obey Aladdin’s orders because we fear his \nwrath, but we also want to stop his madness. \nJasmina the Brave","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642505,"modifiedTime":1781557642505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"R8rbit29JCWlGupr","name":"Columns of Eternal Sleep","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"ivRi42zV3cVTu8u7","name":"Columns of Eternal Sleep - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A column of magical ice capable of absorbing \nliving things and enveloping them in a deadly frost.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 222.","positive":"A column of magical ice capable of absorbing \nliving things and enveloping them in a deadly frost.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645979,"modifiedTime":1781557645979,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OxC07sakoCfXHC5p","name":"Gift - Glacial Embrace","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A target that fails a Check when \nthe column tries to absorb them is wrapped in ice and takes \n1 Wound. During each action, the encased subject can attempt to free themselves by making a Position Check, suffering 1 Wound if they fail. When they run out of Wounds, \nthe target is completely absorbed by the column. An NPC \nautomatically suffers 1 Wound with each of its actions until it has consumed all of its Wounds. At the Storyteller’s \ndiscretion, a particularly skilled NPC may choose to free \nthemselves with one of their actions. \nENCOUNTER ROOM – Me-morial Church</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 222.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645979,"modifiedTime":1781557645979,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wmyYU8xMrwNNj4ST","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A column of magical ice capable of absorbing \nliving things and enveloping them in a deadly frost.\nGift - Glacial Embrace: A target that fails a Check when \nthe column tries to absorb them is wrapped in ice and takes \n1 Wound. During each action, the encased subject can attempt to free themselves by making a Position Check, suffering 1 Wound if they fail. When they run out of Wounds, \nthe target is completely absorbed by the column. An NPC \nautomatically suffers 1 Wound with each of its actions until it has consumed all of its Wounds. At the Storyteller’s \ndiscretion, a particularly skilled NPC may choose to free \nthemselves with one of their actions. \nENCOUNTER ROOM – Me-morial Church\nDescriptor: A large Gothic church made entirely of ice. \nSmall snowflakes fall from the large vault in the ceiling and \nfloat gently to the ground. \nInformation: The snowflakes are imbued with Lady \nStorm’s power and are capable of erasing the memory of \nthose they touch. If a subject does not find a way to protect \nthemselves from contact, they will suffer the effect of the \nThreat - Snow of Memory. In the main altar is a large shrine \nwith an object inside: this is a Treasure of the Order, which \nthe Storyteller must choose at will from those presented \nfrom page 19. It takes two minutes to sprint through the \nChurch.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 222."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645979,"modifiedTime":1781557645979,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-columns-of-eternal-sleep-222","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":222,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A column of magical ice capable of absorbing \nliving things and enveloping them in a deadly frost.\nGift - Glacial Embrace: A target that fails a Check when \nthe column tries to absorb them is wrapped in ice and takes \n1 Wound. During each action, the encased subject can attempt to free themselves by making a Position Check, suffering 1 Wound if they fail. When they run out of Wounds, \nthe target is completely absorbed by the column. An NPC \nautomatically suffers 1 Wound with each of its actions until it has consumed all of its Wounds. At the Storyteller’s \ndiscretion, a particularly skilled NPC may choose to free \nthemselves with one of their actions. \nENCOUNTER ROOM – Me-morial Church\nDescriptor: A large Gothic church made entirely of ice. \nSmall snowflakes fall from the large vault in the ceiling and \nfloat gently to the ground. \nInformation: The snowflakes are imbued with Lady \nStorm’s power and are capable of erasing the memory of \nthose they touch. If a subject does not find a way to protect \nthemselves from contact, they will suffer the effect of the \nThreat - Snow of Memory. In the main altar is a large shrine \nwith an object inside: this is a Treasure of the Order, which \nthe Storyteller must choose at will from those presented \nfrom page 19. It takes two minutes to sprint through the \nChurch.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645979,"modifiedTime":1781557645979,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"RXBZvznqtw7obEpE","name":"Stallo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"KHHtFh0hZDUhwdm8","name":"Stallo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an old troll and my appetite is \nmatched only by my strength. A bird has made its nest on \nmy head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the \neye, which is incredibly annoying!</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 188.","positive":"I am an old troll and my appetite is \nmatched only by my strength. A bird has made its nest on \nmy head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the \neye, which is incredibly annoying!","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lwWTgFyH39XOF4cv","name":"Gift - Troll","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Stallo possesses enormous strength and \neach Position Check for a physical action attempted \nagainst him receives 1 Penalty. At the end of each of his \nactions, Stallo recovers 1 Wound he suffered. When he \nreaches 0 Wounds, the troll will collapse to the ground, \nonly to regenerate within minutes. \n5: A saddled warhorse, magnificent and white as fresh \nsnow, is grazing in the tall grass. This mount belonged to \none of the knights who met a dire fate in the search for \nTuvstarr. The steed will be reluctant to be approached, but</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 188.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lKo1A8XEgoeMQ7rd","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old troll and my appetite is \nmatched only by my strength. A bird has made its nest on \nmy head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the \neye, which is incredibly annoying!\nGift – Troll: Stallo possesses enormous strength and \neach Position Check for a physical action attempted \nagainst him receives 1 Penalty. At the end of each of his \nactions, Stallo recovers 1 Wound he suffered. When he \nreaches 0 Wounds, the troll will collapse to the ground, \nonly to regenerate within minutes. \n5: A saddled warhorse, magnificent and white as fresh \nsnow, is grazing in the tall grass. This mount belonged to \none of the knights who met a dire fate in the search for \nTuvstarr. The steed will be reluctant to be approached, but</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 188."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-stallo-188","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":188,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old troll and my appetite is \nmatched only by my strength. A bird has made its nest on \nmy head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the \neye, which is incredibly annoying!\nGift – Troll: Stallo possesses enormous strength and \neach Position Check for a physical action attempted \nagainst him receives 1 Penalty. At the end of each of his \nactions, Stallo recovers 1 Wound he suffered. When he \nreaches 0 Wounds, the troll will collapse to the ground, \nonly to regenerate within minutes. \n5: A saddled warhorse, magnificent and white as fresh \nsnow, is grazing in the tall grass. This mount belonged to \none of the knights who met a dire fate in the search for \nTuvstarr. The steed will be reluctant to be approached, but</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623341,"modifiedTime":1781557623341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"RpyYQ46DbpXXGaT0","name":"Eyes of Aladdin","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"RkevbrbcWPtt77SJ","name":"Eyes of Aladdin - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Magic eyes that keep watch on the whole city.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 161.","positive":"Magic eyes that keep watch on the whole city.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642536,"modifiedTime":1781557642536,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TrlGL92cVXkzuR1C","name":"Gift - Big Brother","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>At the beginning of each Scene, a \nstranger in the city must make a Defense Check against this \nThreat. Roll 1 die and apply the result to all subjects who \nfailed.\n1-2: Aladdin learns 1 Gift of the observed subject. During \na confrontation with Aladdin, the learned Gift is automatically considered blocked by the third effect of the Gift - \nWishing Lamp. \n3-4: Aladdin turns an unsuspecting passerby into a Monster to attack the foreigners. \n5-6: A lightning bolt springs from the eye, dealing 1 \nWound to the target. A Defense Check can prevent this effect.\n4B The Forty Thieves\nThe story that led us here...\nThe ship lands on a large, mostly deserted island with only \none town. In the harbor, the Hunters meet Baba, a poor man \nbegging for help in rescuing his brother, who has been kidnapped by a band of terrible Thieves. They live in an oasis \nnear the city, but no one has ever been able to pinpoint the \nexact location of their lair. Baba knows the magic word to \naccess the hideout, having heard his brother speak of it. He \nwill lead the Hunters to the oasis, promising them a share of \nthe Thieves’ treasure as a reward. \nPlace: A large oasis in the desert, full of palm trees and \nwaterholes.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 161.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642536,"modifiedTime":1781557642536,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ZUf9G1mNXrwcCmvR","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: Magic eyes that keep watch on the whole city. \nGift - Big Brother: At the beginning of each Scene, a \nstranger in the city must make a Defense Check against this \nThreat. Roll 1 die and apply the result to all subjects who \nfailed.\n1-2: Aladdin learns 1 Gift of the observed subject. During \na confrontation with Aladdin, the learned Gift is automatically considered blocked by the third effect of the Gift - \nWishing Lamp. \n3-4: Aladdin turns an unsuspecting passerby into a Monster to attack the foreigners. \n5-6: A lightning bolt springs from the eye, dealing 1 \nWound to the target. A Defense Check can prevent this effect.\n4B The Forty Thieves\nThe story that led us here...\nThe ship lands on a large, mostly deserted island with only \none town. In the harbor, the Hunters meet Baba, a poor man \nbegging for help in rescuing his brother, who has been kidnapped by a band of terrible Thieves. They live in an oasis \nnear the city, but no one has ever been able to pinpoint the \nexact location of their lair. Baba knows the magic word to \naccess the hideout, having heard his brother speak of it. He \nwill lead the Hunters to the oasis, promising them a share of \nthe Thieves’ treasure as a reward. \nPlace: A large oasis in the desert, full of palm trees and \nwaterholes. \nInformation: In fact, Baba has already killed most of the \nThieves with the help of Dirana, a skilled slave girl in his \nservice. However, the woman is trapped in the gang’s secret \nlair, and Baba plans to free her and recover the treasure. His \ngoal is to get the Hunters to fight the remaining ten Thieves \nand lock himself in their lair, waiting for the survivors of \nthe battle to leave. Baba will not tell anyone how to open the \nlair, saying that he cannot fully trust the Hunters without a \ndemonstration of their good faith. \nChallenges: Confront the ten remaining Thieves, preventing Baba from entering the secret lair alone and closing \nthe door behind him. Dirana is a fearsome fighter and, once \nfreed, will face the Hunters to defend her master.\nHow to get the Tarì: If Baba fails to lock himself in the \ncave, he will offer the coin to the Hunters for their services, \nbegging them to let him live. \nBaba the Poor Conman</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 161."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642536,"modifiedTime":1781557642536,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-eyes-of-aladdin-161","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":161,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: Magic eyes that keep watch on the whole city. \nGift - Big Brother: At the beginning of each Scene, a \nstranger in the city must make a Defense Check against this \nThreat. Roll 1 die and apply the result to all subjects who \nfailed.\n1-2: Aladdin learns 1 Gift of the observed subject. During \na confrontation with Aladdin, the learned Gift is automatically considered blocked by the third effect of the Gift - \nWishing Lamp. \n3-4: Aladdin turns an unsuspecting passerby into a Monster to attack the foreigners. \n5-6: A lightning bolt springs from the eye, dealing 1 \nWound to the target. A Defense Check can prevent this effect.\n4B The Forty Thieves\nThe story that led us here...\nThe ship lands on a large, mostly deserted island with only \none town. In the harbor, the Hunters meet Baba, a poor man \nbegging for help in rescuing his brother, who has been kidnapped by a band of terrible Thieves. They live in an oasis \nnear the city, but no one has ever been able to pinpoint the \nexact location of their lair. Baba knows the magic word to \naccess the hideout, having heard his brother speak of it. He \nwill lead the Hunters to the oasis, promising them a share of \nthe Thieves’ treasure as a reward. \nPlace: A large oasis in the desert, full of palm trees and \nwaterholes. \nInformation: In fact, Baba has already killed most of the \nThieves with the help of Dirana, a skilled slave girl in his \nservice. However, the woman is trapped in the gang’s secret \nlair, and Baba plans to free her and recover the treasure. His \ngoal is to get the Hunters to fight the remaining ten Thieves \nand lock himself in their lair, waiting for the survivors of \nthe battle to leave. Baba will not tell anyone how to open the \nlair, saying that he cannot fully trust the Hunters without a \ndemonstration of their good faith. \nChallenges: Confront the ten remaining Thieves, preventing Baba from entering the secret lair alone and closing \nthe door behind him. Dirana is a fearsome fighter and, once \nfreed, will face the Hunters to defend her master.\nHow to get the Tarì: If Baba fails to lock himself in the \ncave, he will offer the coin to the Hunters for their services, \nbegging them to let him live. \nBaba the Poor Conman</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642536,"modifiedTime":1781557642536,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"RyOjMUZNEqGzcy8A","name":"The Scarred Knight","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"HHKGaPqJhsbOuhtq","name":"The Scarred Knight - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a former knight of the Round Table, dishonorably banished by my king for falling in love with his queen. \nMy fighting skills are unparalleled, and my face is completely \nscarred as punishment for my sins.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 185.","positive":"I am a former knight of the Round Table, dishonorably banished by my king for falling in love with his queen. \nMy fighting skills are unparalleled, and my face is completely \nscarred as punishment for my sins.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643869,"modifiedTime":1781557643869,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0bhzWgU4h9s62JKS","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a former knight of the Round Table, dishonorably banished by my king for falling in love with his queen. \nMy fighting skills are unparalleled, and my face is completely \nscarred as punishment for my sins.\nAgenda: To find my beloved Guinevere and escape Avalon \nwith her. \nInformation: The Scarred Knight is wandering in search \nof his beloved Guinevere and will make himself available to \nspeak to the Hunters. The man will say that his beloved is \ndisguised as a common Villager, but can be recognized by the \nfeather-shaped brooch he gave her as a token of his love. The \nScarred Knight will not reveal his face or name, but he promises incredible riches to Hunters who help him. If a Hunter \nhas a Descriptor related to madness or understanding the behavior of others, they will clearly understand that the Scarred \nKnight is insane, and an endless obsession burns in his eyes. \nIf the Hunters eliminate the Scarred Knight, he will not appear in Zone 11 - Town of Stow (page 197).\n Merlin’s Shadow</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 185."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643869,"modifiedTime":1781557643869,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-the-scarred-knight-185","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":185,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a former knight of the Round Table, dishonorably banished by my king for falling in love with his queen. \nMy fighting skills are unparalleled, and my face is completely \nscarred as punishment for my sins.\nAgenda: To find my beloved Guinevere and escape Avalon \nwith her. \nInformation: The Scarred Knight is wandering in search \nof his beloved Guinevere and will make himself available to \nspeak to the Hunters. The man will say that his beloved is \ndisguised as a common Villager, but can be recognized by the \nfeather-shaped brooch he gave her as a token of his love. The \nScarred Knight will not reveal his face or name, but he promises incredible riches to Hunters who help him. If a Hunter \nhas a Descriptor related to madness or understanding the behavior of others, they will clearly understand that the Scarred \nKnight is insane, and an endless obsession burns in his eyes. \nIf the Hunters eliminate the Scarred Knight, he will not appear in Zone 11 - Town of Stow (page 197).\n Merlin’s Shadow</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"To find my beloved Guinevere and escape Avalon \nwith her.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643869,"modifiedTime":1781557643869,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"S3fURzRdz5ipCa6j","name":"Abel the Young Lover","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"pJAvRNB6Moi8x64b","name":"Abel the Young Lover - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young baker who has always been in \nlove with Bianca.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 112.","positive":"I am a young baker who has always been in \nlove with Bianca.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628486,"modifiedTime":1781557628486,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xZ16QXDaMmes9FY8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young baker who has always been in \nlove with Bianca.\nAgenda: To find Bianca, as I cannot believe that she has \nabandoned Lohr, nor that her parents would let her go so \neasily.\nSvenn’s House\nDescriptor: A beautiful manor house, now converted \ninto a museum of hunting trophies.\nInformation: Svenn will greet the Hunters \nwith kindness, boasting that he is the man the \nKarenmann family trusts the most. Svenn will tell \nthem of the doubts he has about Old Bruna and \nof the fact that some secrets related to the death \nof Ottone could be hidden in the woman’s house. \nSvenn will advise the Hunters to act with caution, \nso as not to alarm the inhabitants of Lohr, but he \nwill make himself available to distract the woman, \ndriving her away from home with an excuse.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 112."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628486,"modifiedTime":1781557628486,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-abel-the-young-lover-112","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":112,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a young baker who has always been in \nlove with Bianca.\nAgenda: To find Bianca, as I cannot believe that she has \nabandoned Lohr, nor that her parents would let her go so \neasily.\nSvenn’s House\nDescriptor: A beautiful manor house, now converted \ninto a museum of hunting trophies.\nInformation: Svenn will greet the Hunters \nwith kindness, boasting that he is the man the \nKarenmann family trusts the most. Svenn will tell \nthem of the doubts he has about Old Bruna and \nof the fact that some secrets related to the death \nof Ottone could be hidden in the woman’s house. \nSvenn will advise the Hunters to act with caution, \nso as not to alarm the inhabitants of Lohr, but he \nwill make himself available to distract the woman, \ndriving her away from home with an excuse.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To find Bianca, as I cannot believe that she has \nabandoned Lohr, nor that her parents would let her go so \neasily.\nSvenn’s House\nDescriptor: A beautiful manor house, now converted \ninto a museum of hunting trophies.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628486,"modifiedTime":1781557628486,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"SBqogICdyx08kVjU","name":"Rabbit Automaton","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"zhhUjBqYo7WTcdVs","name":"Rabbit Automaton - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible \njumps and crush everything when landing.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 176.","positive":"I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible \njumps and crush everything when landing.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MsIWHvv8amwnR9FC","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible \njumps and crush everything when landing.\nGift - Leap: When it acts, the Automaton can free \nitself from any engagement with ease by jumping away. \nIf it lands on a victim, it increases its OL by 1 for the \nattack and if it inflicts 1 Wound, the target will also be \nknocked to the ground.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 176."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-rabbit-automaton-176","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":176,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an automaton in the service of Hatta \nCarter. Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible \njumps and crush everything when landing.\nGift - Leap: When it acts, the Automaton can free \nitself from any engagement with ease by jumping away. \nIf it lands on a victim, it increases its OL by 1 for the \nattack and if it inflicts 1 Wound, the target will also be \nknocked to the ground.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"SCg5nazk8rKy1MT1","name":"Lene the Old Mobster","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"MJoG8Fgzfx9xZfFQ","name":"Lene the Old Mobster - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the ruthless queen of Bergen’s under -\nworld, and I have no qualms about conducting my shady \nbusiness. Everyone in the city fears me, and I use my reputation to intimidate those foolish enough to turn against me.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 209.","positive":"I am the ruthless queen of Bergen’s under -\nworld, and I have no qualms about conducting my shady \nbusiness. Everyone in the city fears me, and I use my reputation to intimidate those foolish enough to turn against me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645177,"modifiedTime":1781557645177,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5apBtZ6hblsQf6Bg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the ruthless queen of Bergen’s under -\nworld, and I have no qualms about conducting my shady \nbusiness. Everyone in the city fears me, and I use my reputation to intimidate those foolish enough to turn against me. \nAgenda: Making money by taking advantage of people’s \ndesperation, taking what they have to offer without really \nleading them to Gerda and Kay. \nInformation: When the Hunters confront Lene, the old \nwoman will reveal that Gerda and Kay are staying at the \nsmall White Hospital, a medical facility that can be reached \nby sailing north along the river. Lene will give the Hunters \na pass that the Black Feathers will recognize as valid for \nboarding their boat to make the journey.\nLene will try hard to hide the fact that she is Gerda’s mother, fearing that this information will get her into even more \ntrouble than her daughter’s scheme. When this connection \nis made and Lene is cornered, she will reveal some infor -\nmation about her daughter to the Hunters. At this point, \nthe Storyteller can decide what to reveal about Gerda by \nconsulting her profile on page 223.\nLene’s Cutthroat</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 209."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645177,"modifiedTime":1781557645177,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-lene-the-old-mobster-209","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":209,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the ruthless queen of Bergen’s under -\nworld, and I have no qualms about conducting my shady \nbusiness. Everyone in the city fears me, and I use my reputation to intimidate those foolish enough to turn against me. \nAgenda: Making money by taking advantage of people’s \ndesperation, taking what they have to offer without really \nleading them to Gerda and Kay. \nInformation: When the Hunters confront Lene, the old \nwoman will reveal that Gerda and Kay are staying at the \nsmall White Hospital, a medical facility that can be reached \nby sailing north along the river. Lene will give the Hunters \na pass that the Black Feathers will recognize as valid for \nboarding their boat to make the journey.\nLene will try hard to hide the fact that she is Gerda’s mother, fearing that this information will get her into even more \ntrouble than her daughter’s scheme. When this connection \nis made and Lene is cornered, she will reveal some infor -\nmation about her daughter to the Hunters. At this point, \nthe Storyteller can decide what to reveal about Gerda by \nconsulting her profile on page 223.\nLene’s Cutthroat</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Making money by taking advantage of people’s \ndesperation, taking what they have to offer without really \nleading them to Gerda and Kay.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645177,"modifiedTime":1781557645177,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"TOy90f0zyWyUW3rr","name":"Arthur Browne the Big Brother","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"88moMe9fiYLjozXg","name":"Arthur Browne the Big Brother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as \nthe mastermind of the gang. Living in my natural prison has \ntaught me how to see even in total darkness.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","positive":"I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as \nthe mastermind of the gang. Living in my natural prison has \ntaught me how to see even in total darkness.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"FfWn8LYulhg3r43Q","name":"Gift - The Flesh of The God Under the Mine","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Arthur \ncan tear pieces of flesh from the God’s head to harness its \npowers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes \na Spawn of the God and begins to grow disgustingly, \nengaging all nearby enemies. Arthur can tear one piece of \nmeat off per action, up to a maximum of 3.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"BICWp0IaICubAVk1","name":"Gift - Gang Leader","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act \na second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; \n3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for \na single action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe God Under \nthe Mine</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Q3gNMixeISebzB3E","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as \nthe mastermind of the gang. Living in my natural prison has \ntaught me how to see even in total darkness.\nAgenda: Take revenge on Bardolf for corrupting everything \nI built in Whitehaven and regain control of the city / \nTransforming all the inhabitants of Whitehaven into Pig \nHeads.\nGift - The Flesh of The God Under the Mine: Arthur \ncan tear pieces of flesh from the God’s head to harness its \npowers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes \na Spawn of the God and begins to grow disgustingly, \nengaging all nearby enemies. Arthur can tear one piece of \nmeat off per action, up to a maximum of 3.\nGift - Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act \na second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; \n3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for \na single action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe God Under \nthe Mine</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 212."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-arthur-browne-the-big-brother-212","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":212,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as \nthe mastermind of the gang. Living in my natural prison has \ntaught me how to see even in total darkness.\nAgenda: Take revenge on Bardolf for corrupting everything \nI built in Whitehaven and regain control of the city / \nTransforming all the inhabitants of Whitehaven into Pig \nHeads.\nGift - The Flesh of The God Under the Mine: Arthur \ncan tear pieces of flesh from the God’s head to harness its \npowers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes \na Spawn of the God and begins to grow disgustingly, \nengaging all nearby enemies. Arthur can tear one piece of \nmeat off per action, up to a maximum of 3.\nGift - Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act \na second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; \n3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for \na single action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe God Under \nthe Mine</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Take revenge on Bardolf for corrupting everything \nI built in Whitehaven and regain control of the city / \nTransforming all the inhabitants of Whitehaven into Pig \nHeads.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623942,"modifiedTime":1781557623942,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"TYiUc3rDgAsvl9ql","name":"The Maws","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"3xz1HbsCKa17aLDo","name":"The Maws - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are a new people, children of the great \nMaw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our \nstrength and speed are incredible.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 97.","positive":"We are a new people, children of the great \nMaw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our \nstrength and speed are incredible.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626309,"modifiedTime":1781557626309,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"z9gpQYAKbQqby9cg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are a new people, children of the great \nMaw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our \nstrength and speed are incredible. \nAgenda: We obey Gréte and Hanse, they are the firstborns, \nthey know the right path / Satiate our infinite hunger, even at \nthe cost of disobeying the firstborns.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their \noriginal appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as \na common child. When they unleash their power, the body \nshifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing \na long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a \nhigher OL category for every physical action they perform \ninvolving speed, strength, or ferocity. A mutant perceives \nthe smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, and \nfor this reason every attempt to hide from their sense of \nsmell receives 1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour \nflesh (human or animal), they cannot stop until they have \nfinished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw inflicts \n1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound \nthey suffered.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 97."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626309,"modifiedTime":1781557626309,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-the-maws-97","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":97,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are a new people, children of the great \nMaw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our \nstrength and speed are incredible. \nAgenda: We obey Gréte and Hanse, they are the firstborns, \nthey know the right path / Satiate our infinite hunger, even at \nthe cost of disobeying the firstborns.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their \noriginal appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as \na common child. When they unleash their power, the body \nshifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing \na long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a \nhigher OL category for every physical action they perform \ninvolving speed, strength, or ferocity. A mutant perceives \nthe smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, and \nfor this reason every attempt to hide from their sense of \nsmell receives 1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour \nflesh (human or animal), they cannot stop until they have \nfinished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw inflicts \n1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound \nthey suffered.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"We obey Gréte and Hanse, they are the firstborns, \nthey know the right path / Satiate our infinite hunger, even at \nthe cost of disobeying the firstborns.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626309,"modifiedTime":1781557626309,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Tk0H4q2QpDyymJZJ","name":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"kiJ5YuyaURewvNbm","name":"Caterpillar of the Wonderful Lands - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two \nmeters long. I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the \ncarcasses of creatures I’ve devoured.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 175.","positive":"I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two \nmeters long. I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the \ncarcasses of creatures I’ve devoured.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622955,"modifiedTime":1781557622955,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jPHV4h0JzKNl0r4h","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two \nmeters long. I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the \ncarcasses of creatures I’ve devoured.\nGift - Hunter Caterpillar: When a Caterpillar moves, any \nhuman-sized subject in its path risks being overwhelmed. \nWhoever is in the Caterpillar’s way must perform a \nDefense Check in order not to end up knocked down. The \nCaterpillar inflicts 1 Additional Wound against people \nprone on the ground.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 175."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622955,"modifiedTime":1781557622955,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-caterpillar-of-the-wonderful-lands-175","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":175,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two \nmeters long. I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the \ncarcasses of creatures I’ve devoured.\nGift - Hunter Caterpillar: When a Caterpillar moves, any \nhuman-sized subject in its path risks being overwhelmed. \nWhoever is in the Caterpillar’s way must perform a \nDefense Check in order not to end up knocked down. The \nCaterpillar inflicts 1 Additional Wound against people \nprone on the ground.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622955,"modifiedTime":1781557622955,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"U1RISqZxe1YweXN6","name":"Lost Trails","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"Km0Lu82FWSDy94me","name":"Lost Trails - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>It is not easy to follow the drag tracks in the \nforest and keep alert for predators. \nIn case of failure, the Hunters will be caught off guard by a \nherd of Nikola’s Reindeer. \nThe Badalisk’s Lair\nDescriptor: A large natural cave that emits a strong stench \nof death and decay.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 122.","positive":"It is not easy to follow the drag tracks in the \nforest and keep alert for predators. \nIn case of failure, the Hunters will be caught off guard by a \nherd of Nikola’s Reindeer. \nThe Badalisk’s Lair\nDescriptor: A large natural cave that emits a strong stench \nof death and decay.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640618,"modifiedTime":1781557640618,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xNRAtMG6EOPuAhv9","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: It is not easy to follow the drag tracks in the \nforest and keep alert for predators. \nIn case of failure, the Hunters will be caught off guard by a \nherd of Nikola’s Reindeer. \nThe Badalisk’s Lair\nDescriptor: A large natural cave that emits a strong stench \nof death and decay. \nInformation: The tracks end at the mouth of the gorge, \nwhere there is no snow on the rock: this indicates that a \nlarge creature often moves to the mouth. Many human remains and various objects can be found inside the cave. The \ndeeper you go, the darker it gets.\nThreat – The Sleeping Badalisk</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 122."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640618,"modifiedTime":1781557640618,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-lost-trails-122","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":122,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: It is not easy to follow the drag tracks in the \nforest and keep alert for predators. \nIn case of failure, the Hunters will be caught off guard by a \nherd of Nikola’s Reindeer. \nThe Badalisk’s Lair\nDescriptor: A large natural cave that emits a strong stench \nof death and decay. \nInformation: The tracks end at the mouth of the gorge, \nwhere there is no snow on the rock: this indicates that a \nlarge creature often moves to the mouth. Many human remains and various objects can be found inside the cave. The \ndeeper you go, the darker it gets.\nThreat – The Sleeping Badalisk</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640618,"modifiedTime":1781557640618,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"UI6QX2afJvM7LDAn","name":"Kråke","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"pUI2iwzT026kCyUa","name":"Kråke - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled assassin, and I can corner any \nopponent with my saber. My swordsmanship is such that I \ncan deflect any weapon.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 210.","positive":"I am a skilled assassin, and I can corner any \nopponent with my saber. My swordsmanship is such that I \ncan deflect any weapon.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645318,"modifiedTime":1781557645318,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fKHhNLCpjfmjn28b","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled assassin, and I can corner any \nopponent with my saber. My swordsmanship is such that I \ncan deflect any weapon. \nAgenda: Escort those who have paid the correct amount to \nthe White Hospital / Eliminate any potential threat to Gerda \nand Kay’s business. \nGift - The Rook: Once per Scene, Kråke can transform \ninto a rook and escape by flying away. If she makes a sur -\nprise attack, Kråke inflicts 1 Additional Wound. \n3</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 210."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645318,"modifiedTime":1781557645318,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-kr-ke-210","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":210,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled assassin, and I can corner any \nopponent with my saber. My swordsmanship is such that I \ncan deflect any weapon. \nAgenda: Escort those who have paid the correct amount to \nthe White Hospital / Eliminate any potential threat to Gerda \nand Kay’s business. \nGift - The Rook: Once per Scene, Kråke can transform \ninto a rook and escape by flying away. If she makes a sur -\nprise attack, Kråke inflicts 1 Additional Wound. \n3</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Escort those who have paid the correct amount to \nthe White Hospital / Eliminate any potential threat to Gerda \nand Kay’s business.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645318,"modifiedTime":1781557645318,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"URi5ONWolZT4U8MV","name":"Dionysus’ Mastiffs","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"y3BoedlEwO8OQFOT","name":"Dionysus’ Mastiffs - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our \nleader, Dionysus.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","positive":"We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our \nleader, Dionysus.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1HKiPajEOltlavKu","name":"Gift - Pack","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Any action taken while surrounded by 2 \nor more Mastiffs receives 1 Penalty. A Mastiff can use its \naction to howl and alert Dionysus, who will arrive within \n2 Exchanges.\nFrancesca Cantalupo</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"U7alNb0sLTD3bTx5","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our \nleader, Dionysus.\nAgenda: Hunt down any intruders arriving on the island.\nGift – Pack: Any action taken while surrounded by 2 \nor more Mastiffs receives 1 Penalty. A Mastiff can use its \naction to howl and alert Dionysus, who will arrive within \n2 Exchanges.\nFrancesca Cantalupo</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-dionysus-mastiffs-128","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":128,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our \nleader, Dionysus.\nAgenda: Hunt down any intruders arriving on the island.\nGift – Pack: Any action taken while surrounded by 2 \nor more Mastiffs receives 1 Penalty. A Mastiff can use its \naction to howl and alert Dionysus, who will arrive within \n2 Exchanges.\nFrancesca Cantalupo</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Hunt down any intruders arriving on the island.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Ud8oGwfslmjTt19K","name":"Guardians of the Tomb","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"CIzfOkXgMxDWiCr4","name":"Guardians of the Tomb - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are an order of fighting Guardians, and \nour vow of loyalty comes before all else. Only the taste of human flesh can distract us from our duty.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 156.","positive":"We are an order of fighting Guardians, and \nour vow of loyalty comes before all else. Only the taste of human flesh can distract us from our duty.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642395,"modifiedTime":1781557642395,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"izro5DlJrSOFklKF","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are an order of fighting Guardians, and \nour vow of loyalty comes before all else. Only the taste of human flesh can distract us from our duty.\nAgenda: Defend the tomb from intruders. \n6A The Crystal Cliffs\nThe story that led us here...\nOverwhelmed by a strong current, the ship is pushed toward \na large group of rocks that Sinbad recognizes as very dangerous. The crystal that makes up the rocks is fragile, but also \nextremely sharp, and touching them would damage the ship’s \nhull. Beneath the crystal layer, the “rocks” are made up of all \nsorts of precious stones, and in each of them lies a real treasure. Even though the main goal is to get out unharmed, there \nmight be a Tarì among all the riches. \nPlace: A large group of crystal rocks reflecting the sunlight.\nInformation: It’s not easy to shatter the crystal without \ndangerous shards flying everywhere. Sinbad can keep control of the ship, but it will be up to the Hunters to clear the \nway. \nChallenges: Destroy the crystal rocks that block the path \nand recover valuable items from the inner rocks. At least 4 \nrocks must be cleared to cross this part of the sea. \nHow to get the Tarì: If the Hunters find at least 5 valuables, the Tarì will also be in the sixth rock.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 156."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642395,"modifiedTime":1781557642395,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-guardians-of-the-tomb-156","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":156,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are an order of fighting Guardians, and \nour vow of loyalty comes before all else. Only the taste of human flesh can distract us from our duty.\nAgenda: Defend the tomb from intruders. \n6A The Crystal Cliffs\nThe story that led us here...\nOverwhelmed by a strong current, the ship is pushed toward \na large group of rocks that Sinbad recognizes as very dangerous. The crystal that makes up the rocks is fragile, but also \nextremely sharp, and touching them would damage the ship’s \nhull. Beneath the crystal layer, the “rocks” are made up of all \nsorts of precious stones, and in each of them lies a real treasure. Even though the main goal is to get out unharmed, there \nmight be a Tarì among all the riches. \nPlace: A large group of crystal rocks reflecting the sunlight.\nInformation: It’s not easy to shatter the crystal without \ndangerous shards flying everywhere. Sinbad can keep control of the ship, but it will be up to the Hunters to clear the \nway. \nChallenges: Destroy the crystal rocks that block the path \nand recover valuable items from the inner rocks. At least 4 \nrocks must be cleared to cross this part of the sea. \nHow to get the Tarì: If the Hunters find at least 5 valuables, the Tarì will also be in the sixth rock.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Defend the tomb from intruders. \n6A The Crystal Cliffs\nThe story that led us here...\nOverwhelmed by a strong current, the ship is pushed toward \na large group of rocks that Sinbad recognizes as very dangerous. The crystal that makes up the rocks is fragile, but also \nextremely sharp, and touching them would damage the ship’s \nhull. Beneath the crystal layer, the “rocks” are made up of all \nsorts of precious stones, and in each of them lies a real treasure. Even though the main goal is to get out unharmed, there \nmight be a Tarì among all the riches. \nPlace: A large group of crystal rocks reflecting the sunlight.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642395,"modifiedTime":1781557642395,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Un45IQfWZv7lRhhc","name":"Pernille The Lapland Woman","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"C15HlmJqA3GWJTKa","name":"Pernille The Lapland Woman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a fearsome ice witch who learned the art \nof magic from the famous Lady Storm.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 217.","positive":"I am a fearsome ice witch who learned the art \nof magic from the famous Lady Storm.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645672,"modifiedTime":1781557645672,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WDyjuAlLZehSu415","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fearsome ice witch who learned the art \nof magic from the famous Lady Storm.\nAgenda: Earn as much as possible without risking my life.\nGift - Ice Magic: Pernille can manipulate frost to create \nice at a range of sixty feet. When she acts, she can choose \none of the following effects:\n1. Ice Rain: The sharp fragments can hit up to 3 targets, \ncausing 1 Wound.\n4</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 217."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645672,"modifiedTime":1781557645672,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-pernille-the-lapland-woman-217","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":217,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fearsome ice witch who learned the art \nof magic from the famous Lady Storm.\nAgenda: Earn as much as possible without risking my life.\nGift - Ice Magic: Pernille can manipulate frost to create \nice at a range of sixty feet. When she acts, she can choose \none of the following effects:\n1. Ice Rain: The sharp fragments can hit up to 3 targets, \ncausing 1 Wound.\n4</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Earn as much as possible without risking my life.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645672,"modifiedTime":1781557645672,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"UwJ9K9me766rPKkG","name":"Bianca Karenmann","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"B4jFoLwr2RmuVxB5","name":"Bianca Karenmann - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in \npeace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. \nIt also gives me the power to make living beings explode from \nwithin.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 117.","positive":"I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in \npeace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. \nIt also gives me the power to make living beings explode from \nwithin.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628721,"modifiedTime":1781557628721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"P2UVH5puSyrie5rW","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in \npeace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. \nIt also gives me the power to make living beings explode from \nwithin.\nAgenda: I want what’s best for the whole village of Lohr, even \nif it means sacrificing myself.\nGift – The Curse of Bloodwhite: Thanks to the power of \nthe curse, Bianca is stronger and more resilient than normal. \nFor this reason, at the end of each Scene she recovers 1 \nWound. This effect even allows Bianca to return from \ndeath. Bianca’s power can detonate the body of living \nbeings and, once per Exchange, her action can inflict \n1 automatic Wound to a target. No Defense Check is \nallowed.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 117."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628721,"modifiedTime":1781557628721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-bianca-karenmann-117","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":117,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in \npeace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. \nIt also gives me the power to make living beings explode from \nwithin.\nAgenda: I want what’s best for the whole village of Lohr, even \nif it means sacrificing myself.\nGift – The Curse of Bloodwhite: Thanks to the power of \nthe curse, Bianca is stronger and more resilient than normal. \nFor this reason, at the end of each Scene she recovers 1 \nWound. This effect even allows Bianca to return from \ndeath. Bianca’s power can detonate the body of living \nbeings and, once per Exchange, her action can inflict \n1 automatic Wound to a target. No Defense Check is \nallowed.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"I want what’s best for the whole village of Lohr, even \nif it means sacrificing myself.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628721,"modifiedTime":1781557628721,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"V3aej9PnKXxpjfNG","name":"Treasury Door","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"jYM9HHfUdciNio6c","name":"Treasury Door - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A huge metal door reinforced to resist any \nburglary attempt. The combination to open it is 05031762, \nAlena’s date of birth.\nRobbers</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 140.","positive":"A huge metal door reinforced to resist any \nburglary attempt. The combination to open it is 05031762, \nAlena’s date of birth.\nRobbers","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641635,"modifiedTime":1781557641635,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"S2GUTMydSNTEYF2D","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A huge metal door reinforced to resist any \nburglary attempt. The combination to open it is 05031762, \nAlena’s date of birth.\nRobbers</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 140."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641635,"modifiedTime":1781557641635,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-treasury-door-140","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":140,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A huge metal door reinforced to resist any \nburglary attempt. The combination to open it is 05031762, \nAlena’s date of birth.\nRobbers</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641635,"modifiedTime":1781557641635,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"V9IAg6Fwh0wxEi98","name":"Cheshire The Faithful Lynx","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"BIPh40QA0D7dcoWq","name":"Cheshire The Faithful Lynx - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a snappy and aggressive lynx. I roam the \nhalls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 172.","positive":"I am a snappy and aggressive lynx. I roam the \nhalls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622892,"modifiedTime":1781557622892,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"afxWxopUtkX8Hja5","name":"Gift - Elusive","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to the power infused in Wonder, \nCheshire can disappear and reappear a short distance away, \nand move through doors and walls. Cheshire can always \nmove without anyone being able to stop her. All actions to \nattack or capture Cheshire receive 1 Penalty because of the \nconstant appearance and disappearance of the lynx. This \nGift is not affected by the Place of Pure Madness Gift.\nWonderBedlam</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 172.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622892,"modifiedTime":1781557622892,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qDFZweiJfvPYBz6E","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a snappy and aggressive lynx. I roam the \nhalls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress.\nGift - Elusive: Thanks to the power infused in Wonder, \nCheshire can disappear and reappear a short distance away, \nand move through doors and walls. Cheshire can always \nmove without anyone being able to stop her. All actions to \nattack or capture Cheshire receive 1 Penalty because of the \nconstant appearance and disappearance of the lynx. This \nGift is not affected by the Place of Pure Madness Gift.\nWonderBedlam\nDescriptor: I am a building animated by sheer madness \nand no one can attempt to alter me without Alice Liddell’s \npermission.\nGift - Place of Pure Madness: When a subject \nattempts an action or uses a Gift to change Wonder’s insane \nstructure (such as breaking through walls or circumventing \npassageways), the building’s inherent magic activates. \nBefore the action taken is resolved, roll a die to see where \nthe subject will end up being teleported.\n1-2: The Rabbit Hole. \n3-4: The Labyrinth of Doors. \n5-6: The Caterpillars’ Greenhouse.\nThis magical shift causes a side effect that lasts throughout \nthe Scene; roll a die to determine what happens.\n1-2 Shrunk: The subject receives the Descriptor I am half \nthe size I was, all my physical abilities are diminished as well.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 172."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622892,"modifiedTime":1781557622892,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-cheshire-the-faithful-lynx-172","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":172,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a snappy and aggressive lynx. I roam the \nhalls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress.\nGift - Elusive: Thanks to the power infused in Wonder, \nCheshire can disappear and reappear a short distance away, \nand move through doors and walls. Cheshire can always \nmove without anyone being able to stop her. All actions to \nattack or capture Cheshire receive 1 Penalty because of the \nconstant appearance and disappearance of the lynx. This \nGift is not affected by the Place of Pure Madness Gift.\nWonderBedlam\nDescriptor: I am a building animated by sheer madness \nand no one can attempt to alter me without Alice Liddell’s \npermission.\nGift - Place of Pure Madness: When a subject \nattempts an action or uses a Gift to change Wonder’s insane \nstructure (such as breaking through walls or circumventing \npassageways), the building’s inherent magic activates. \nBefore the action taken is resolved, roll a die to see where \nthe subject will end up being teleported.\n1-2: The Rabbit Hole. \n3-4: The Labyrinth of Doors. \n5-6: The Caterpillars’ Greenhouse.\nThis magical shift causes a side effect that lasts throughout \nthe Scene; roll a die to determine what happens.\n1-2 Shrunk: The subject receives the Descriptor I am half \nthe size I was, all my physical abilities are diminished as well.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622892,"modifiedTime":1781557622892,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VCdkr5v1qL50t83H","name":"Marcel the Time-Waster","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"lwbV342cYWFfQLCn","name":"Marcel the Time-Waster - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I frequently wander the town and may be found \nanywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no \none believed my story because I am too young.\n5 Corinne the Housekeeper</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","positive":"I frequently wander the town and may be found \nanywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no \none believed my story because I am too young.\n5 Corinne the Housekeeper","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"AoHatYstbxtUV229","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I frequently wander the town and may be found \nanywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no \none believed my story because I am too young.\n5 Corinne the Housekeeper</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-marcel-the-time-waster-123","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":123,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I frequently wander the town and may be found \nanywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no \none believed my story because I am too young.\n5 Corinne the Housekeeper</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VMg6iY66YQc2yWP5","name":"The Sleeping Badalisk","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"66vvUnkL46jYPyDJ","name":"The Sleeping Badalisk - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The Badalisk sleeps most of the time, but if you \ndisturb it, it will wake up ready to devour anything.\nNote: This Threat is activated when Hunters make a loud \nnoise, turn on a light, or come close enough for the Badalisk to smell them. If the Badalisk does not awaken, it can be \nexamined closely while it is dormant. If the Badalisk suffers \n1 Wound, it will wake immediately.\nThe Badalisk</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 122.","positive":"The Badalisk sleeps most of the time, but if you \ndisturb it, it will wake up ready to devour anything.\nNote: This Threat is activated when Hunters make a loud \nnoise, turn on a light, or come close enough for the Badalisk to smell them. If the Badalisk does not awaken, it can be \nexamined closely while it is dormant. If the Badalisk suffers \n1 Wound, it will wake immediately.\nThe Badalisk","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640618,"modifiedTime":1781557640618,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OxSPCxVUAvNIPyDI","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: The Badalisk sleeps most of the time, but if you \ndisturb it, it will wake up ready to devour anything.\nNote: This Threat is activated when Hunters make a loud \nnoise, turn on a light, or come close enough for the Badalisk to smell them. If the Badalisk does not awaken, it can be \nexamined closely while it is dormant. If the Badalisk suffers \n1 Wound, it will wake immediately.\nThe Badalisk</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 122."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640618,"modifiedTime":1781557640618,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-the-sleeping-badalisk-122","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":122,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: The Badalisk sleeps most of the time, but if you \ndisturb it, it will wake up ready to devour anything.\nNote: This Threat is activated when Hunters make a loud \nnoise, turn on a light, or come close enough for the Badalisk to smell them. If the Badalisk does not awaken, it can be \nexamined closely while it is dormant. If the Badalisk suffers \n1 Wound, it will wake immediately.\nThe Badalisk</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640618,"modifiedTime":1781557640618,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VajAANlL1MTiZXJP","name":"The Gang of Bats","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"OFydzNpa4kO4SHER","name":"The Gang of Bats - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are street urchins, used to stealing to survive. \nWith Pepe at our head, we are not afraid of anything.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 105.","positive":"We are street urchins, used to stealing to survive. \nWith Pepe at our head, we are not afraid of anything.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639930,"modifiedTime":1781557639930,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Ta0H1ELXhYRxlAGI","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are street urchins, used to stealing to survive. \nWith Pepe at our head, we are not afraid of anything. \nAgenda: Help Pepe make the Gang prosper / Help Pepe overcome \nthe trauma of his family’s death. \nGift - United Gang: Each member of the Gang possesses a trait \nthat is identified by an addition to their Descriptor. \nBenedicto: I am the oldest in the Gang, and my strength is feared \neven by adults.\nCarmina: I am agile, fast, and a good climber. \nFelix: I am the smallest of the Gang and can squeeze into any hole. \nInez: I am the smartest of the Gang and have read many books.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 105."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639930,"modifiedTime":1781557639930,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-the-gang-of-bats-105","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":105,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are street urchins, used to stealing to survive. \nWith Pepe at our head, we are not afraid of anything. \nAgenda: Help Pepe make the Gang prosper / Help Pepe overcome \nthe trauma of his family’s death. \nGift - United Gang: Each member of the Gang possesses a trait \nthat is identified by an addition to their Descriptor. \nBenedicto: I am the oldest in the Gang, and my strength is feared \neven by adults.\nCarmina: I am agile, fast, and a good climber. \nFelix: I am the smallest of the Gang and can squeeze into any hole. \nInez: I am the smartest of the Gang and have read many books.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Help Pepe make the Gang prosper / Help Pepe overcome \nthe trauma of his family’s death.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639930,"modifiedTime":1781557639930,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VdGNzNvjyaIDpV7M","name":"Black Wolves of Greskar’s Pack","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"4oidBWVAHkxd9qV6","name":"Black Wolves of Greskar’s Pack - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are fierce black wolves, we hate \nhumans and obey only our pack leader.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 127.","positive":"We are fierce black wolves, we hate \nhumans and obey only our pack leader.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621429,"modifiedTime":1781557621429,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YqdfRwpgWgwAbZ9b","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are fierce black wolves, we hate \nhumans and obey only our pack leader.\nAgenda: Follow without hesitation every order \nfrom the pack’s alpha.\nGift - The Power of the Pack: Any action \ntaken while being engaged by two or more Wolves \nreceives 1 Penalty.\nStory Events\nIn this Scenario, there are six main Events. As Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.\nIf the raids of the wolves are not stopped in one day: \nmany of Gerard’s soldiers will be eliminated, victims of a much \nmore intense attack than those that have occurred so far, taking \nplace at the gates of the palace. After the furious assault, the \ncity’s defenses will be reduced to a minimum and it will be very \neasy for Iskra to break into the Dubois palace under the cover of \ndarkness.\nIf a Hunter finds Iskra’s pendant in the well: Anastazia \nwill contact them, showing them a vision of Iskra as a child \ndrinking at the Oaks Glade. The spirit of Iskra’s grandmother, \nwhile unable to communicate directly, will try to make the \nHunters understand that Iskra is not a monster.\nIf Elizaveta goes out of town for any reason: Iskra will \nimmediately smell her scent and rush to eliminate her regardless \nof any risk. Confronted with her mother, the little girl will lose all \nrestraint and refuse to listen to reason.\nIf Iskra is captured: the wolf pack led by a furious Greskar \nwill launch a tremendous attack on Durfort. Elizaveta will try to \neliminate her daughter with a powerful poison.\nIf Iskra is killed: Anastazia’s spirit will turn on her murderer, \nsending visions of Elizaveta trying to wash the blood of a dead \nchild from her hands.\nIf someone accuses Elizaveta: Gerard will deny everything \nout of fear and shame, invoking concrete and irrefutable \nevidence. Elizaveta, for her part, will play the role of the victim, \nalways trying to highlight the danger posed by the wolves.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 127."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621439,"modifiedTime":1781557621439,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-black-wolves-of-greskar-s-pack-127","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":127,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are fierce black wolves, we hate \nhumans and obey only our pack leader.\nAgenda: Follow without hesitation every order \nfrom the pack’s alpha.\nGift - The Power of the Pack: Any action \ntaken while being engaged by two or more Wolves \nreceives 1 Penalty.\nStory Events\nIn this Scenario, there are six main Events. As Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.\nIf the raids of the wolves are not stopped in one day: \nmany of Gerard’s soldiers will be eliminated, victims of a much \nmore intense attack than those that have occurred so far, taking \nplace at the gates of the palace. After the furious assault, the \ncity’s defenses will be reduced to a minimum and it will be very \neasy for Iskra to break into the Dubois palace under the cover of \ndarkness.\nIf a Hunter finds Iskra’s pendant in the well: Anastazia \nwill contact them, showing them a vision of Iskra as a child \ndrinking at the Oaks Glade. The spirit of Iskra’s grandmother, \nwhile unable to communicate directly, will try to make the \nHunters understand that Iskra is not a monster.\nIf Elizaveta goes out of town for any reason: Iskra will \nimmediately smell her scent and rush to eliminate her regardless \nof any risk. Confronted with her mother, the little girl will lose all \nrestraint and refuse to listen to reason.\nIf Iskra is captured: the wolf pack led by a furious Greskar \nwill launch a tremendous attack on Durfort. Elizaveta will try to \neliminate her daughter with a powerful poison.\nIf Iskra is killed: Anastazia’s spirit will turn on her murderer, \nsending visions of Elizaveta trying to wash the blood of a dead \nchild from her hands.\nIf someone accuses Elizaveta: Gerard will deny everything \nout of fear and shame, invoking concrete and irrefutable \nevidence. Elizaveta, for her part, will play the role of the victim, \nalways trying to highlight the danger posed by the wolves.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Follow without hesitation every order \nfrom the pack’s alpha.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621439,"modifiedTime":1781557621439,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VdGkQADJIQEVOhl2","name":"Haunted Door","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"KVvb6zmx1Y66yp5N","name":"Haunted Door - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A creaking old door imbued with all of Merlin’s \nmagical power.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 191.","positive":"A creaking old door imbued with all of Merlin’s \nmagical power.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644115,"modifiedTime":1781557644115,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7rvolSqtLezExtNU","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A creaking old door imbued with all of Merlin’s \nmagical power.\nGift - Away with the Harassers: Attempting to open \nthe door without the Tower Key triggers the magical effects \nbelow. If the Defense Check fails, the Storyteller rolls a die \nto determine the consequences. \n1-2: Loses all remaining Soma.\n3-4: Suffers 2 Wounds. \n5-6: Ends with the whole group in another Zone. \nInside the Tower, the Hunters will find all manner of magical devilry, as well as clear evidence in books and scrolls \nthat the place belongs to a Sorcerer named Merlin. With \ntime, the Hunters can uncover Merlin’s diary and, at the \nStoryteller’s discretion, a Treasure of the Order.\nThe diary is mostly written in an incomprehensible language, but there are notes written in red ink that are in \ncommon English.\nNote 1: An overly righteous and beloved king is more dangerous than the worst of tyrants, for when raising a hand against \nhim an entire people will rise to shield him.\nNote 2: Virtue is like a weed, it grows despite all efforts to \npull it up.\nNote 3: It may not be handy, but the bottom of a lake is always a good place to hide. \nNote 4: White beach, safe harbor.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 191."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644115,"modifiedTime":1781557644115,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-haunted-door-191","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":191,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A creaking old door imbued with all of Merlin’s \nmagical power.\nGift - Away with the Harassers: Attempting to open \nthe door without the Tower Key triggers the magical effects \nbelow. If the Defense Check fails, the Storyteller rolls a die \nto determine the consequences. \n1-2: Loses all remaining Soma.\n3-4: Suffers 2 Wounds. \n5-6: Ends with the whole group in another Zone. \nInside the Tower, the Hunters will find all manner of magical devilry, as well as clear evidence in books and scrolls \nthat the place belongs to a Sorcerer named Merlin. With \ntime, the Hunters can uncover Merlin’s diary and, at the \nStoryteller’s discretion, a Treasure of the Order.\nThe diary is mostly written in an incomprehensible language, but there are notes written in red ink that are in \ncommon English.\nNote 1: An overly righteous and beloved king is more dangerous than the worst of tyrants, for when raising a hand against \nhim an entire people will rise to shield him.\nNote 2: Virtue is like a weed, it grows despite all efforts to \npull it up.\nNote 3: It may not be handy, but the bottom of a lake is always a good place to hide. \nNote 4: White beach, safe harbor.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644115,"modifiedTime":1781557644115,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VzJj6uGlV9WJt1Nd","name":"Eduardo and Felipe","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"g7kDmSX2ZYYQfBaX","name":"Eduardo and Felipe - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two guards who are content to leave \nthinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as \nlittle as possible. \nThe Di Bello Family \nHouse\nDescriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois \ndistricts of Vigo.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 156.","positive":"We are two guards who are content to leave \nthinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as \nlittle as possible. \nThe Di Bello Family \nHouse\nDescriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois \ndistricts of Vigo.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637071,"modifiedTime":1781557637071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Pho3DT6zVuNtQVj3","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two guards who are content to leave \nthinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as \nlittle as possible. \nThe Di Bello Family \nHouse\nDescriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois \ndistricts of Vigo.\nInformation: Francisca and Marta live in the house \ntheir mother abandoned. The two sisters traveled around \nthe world for a long time, but it was in mystical Prague \nthey underwent the strange rite that sewed their bodies \ntogether. Now, the two women act as one creature, each \nwearing on her foot one of the glass slippers that the Kind \nMother gave them. Francisca and Marta will be hostile to \nthe Hunters until they discover their identity. At that point,</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 156."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637071,"modifiedTime":1781557637071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-eduardo-and-felipe-156","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":156,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two guards who are content to leave \nthinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as \nlittle as possible. \nThe Di Bello Family \nHouse\nDescriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois \ndistricts of Vigo.\nInformation: Francisca and Marta live in the house \ntheir mother abandoned. The two sisters traveled around \nthe world for a long time, but it was in mystical Prague \nthey underwent the strange rite that sewed their bodies \ntogether. Now, the two women act as one creature, each \nwearing on her foot one of the glass slippers that the Kind \nMother gave them. Francisca and Marta will be hostile to \nthe Hunters until they discover their identity. At that point,</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637071,"modifiedTime":1781557637071,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"WERs78LDIHfbhvvp","name":"Svenn the Skilled Hunter","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Silaool8thDbBCPd","name":"Svenn the Skilled Hunter - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the \nprey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world \nand I’m used to handling every situation without too many \nscruples.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","positive":"I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the \nprey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world \nand I’m used to handling every situation without too many \nscruples.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CfmyexPWOB6buiQA","name":"Gift - The Solver","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Svenn takes great care of solving and \nfixing all the problems of those who offer him a job. Against \nany attempt at mind control, gathering information, or \ntrying to intimidate him, Svenn’s OL is Hard 7. \nBruna’s House</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0jAV0kjUIvUtX7MR","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the \nprey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world \nand I’m used to handling every situation without too many \nscruples.\nAgenda: To make Bruna take the blame to divert attention \nfrom Bianca / Pretend to help the Hunters to make sure they \nclose the case as quickly as possible.\nGift – The Solver: Svenn takes great care of solving and \nfixing all the problems of those who offer him a job. Against \nany attempt at mind control, gathering information, or \ntrying to intimidate him, Svenn’s OL is Hard 7. \nBruna’s House\nDescriptor: A small old house with a \ngarden full of medicinal plants.\nInformation: Bruna lives alone since \nher husband’s death. Anyone who \nknows herbs will understand that \nthe woman has good botanical \nknowledge. Under the bed, \nSvenn hid a bag with a book of \nblasphemous rituals and a lock \nof blond hair that belonged to \nOttone.\nBruna the Poor Witch</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 113."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-svenn-the-skilled-hunter-113","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":113,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the \nprey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world \nand I’m used to handling every situation without too many \nscruples.\nAgenda: To make Bruna take the blame to divert attention \nfrom Bianca / Pretend to help the Hunters to make sure they \nclose the case as quickly as possible.\nGift – The Solver: Svenn takes great care of solving and \nfixing all the problems of those who offer him a job. Against \nany attempt at mind control, gathering information, or \ntrying to intimidate him, Svenn’s OL is Hard 7. \nBruna’s House\nDescriptor: A small old house with a \ngarden full of medicinal plants.\nInformation: Bruna lives alone since \nher husband’s death. Anyone who \nknows herbs will understand that \nthe woman has good botanical \nknowledge. Under the bed, \nSvenn hid a bag with a book of \nblasphemous rituals and a lock \nof blond hair that belonged to \nOttone.\nBruna the Poor Witch</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To make Bruna take the blame to divert attention \nfrom Bianca / Pretend to help the Hunters to make sure they \nclose the case as quickly as possible.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628565,"modifiedTime":1781557628565,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"WyN0L7cyRZ5xCRoX","name":"Marionette","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"QZVOsiTIiBr0xQtU","name":"Marionette - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are souls cursed by Azzurra in the wooden \nbodies of marionettes. We hate all living beings and want to \nbe destroyed to be free again.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 136.","positive":"We are souls cursed by Azzurra in the wooden \nbodies of marionettes. We hate all living beings and want to \nbe destroyed to be free again.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621843,"modifiedTime":1781557621843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"pxUuzxbIX4EXLyuk","name":"Gift - Boundless Rage","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Azzurra’s power animates and \nforces the Marionettes to do evil acts. When a Marionette \nsuffers the last Wound it will immediately spring on the \nenemy with incredible momentum as Azzurra’s power \ncompels them one last time. The Marionette can take a</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 136.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621843,"modifiedTime":1781557621843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Ns9L8KOqGdOjoVw0","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are souls cursed by Azzurra in the wooden \nbodies of marionettes. We hate all living beings and want to \nbe destroyed to be free again.\nAgenda: Attacking every human we meet.\nGift - Boundless Rage: Azzurra’s power animates and \nforces the Marionettes to do evil acts. When a Marionette \nsuffers the last Wound it will immediately spring on the \nenemy with incredible momentum as Azzurra’s power \ncompels them one last time. The Marionette can take a</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 136."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621843,"modifiedTime":1781557621843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-marionette-136","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":136,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: We are souls cursed by Azzurra in the wooden \nbodies of marionettes. We hate all living beings and want to \nbe destroyed to be free again.\nAgenda: Attacking every human we meet.\nGift - Boundless Rage: Azzurra’s power animates and \nforces the Marionettes to do evil acts. When a Marionette \nsuffers the last Wound it will immediately spring on the \nenemy with incredible momentum as Azzurra’s power \ncompels them one last time. The Marionette can take a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Attacking every human we meet.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621843,"modifiedTime":1781557621843,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"X2gS4rMGqqZOjTkD","name":"Carlo The Living Puppet","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"56ZmqF6tRH3KR0PN","name":"Carlo The Living Puppet - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The \nlies I tell become reality for a short time.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137.","positive":"I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The \nlies I tell become reality for a short time.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"u5l2drU2i5DHp4UL","name":"Gift - Lies","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Carlo can bring the lies he tells to life \nby creating a Descriptor that allows him to \nperform incredible feats. All lies must be \ncentered on him. For example: I can walk \nthrough walls or I am invisible to the human \neye. The effects of the lies’ power are literal. \nFor this reason, Carlo would not be able to \ngo through a closed door and he would be \nseen by animals. The effect of Lies lasts for 1 \nScene or until a new lie is told.\nLucino - The Good Friend</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9EhENolSn7XflNJM","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The \nlies I tell become reality for a short time.\nAgenda: Living a carefree life without responsibility / I don’t \nwant to abandon Sinalunga and my new friend Lucino, but \nI’m always afraid that Geppetto and Antonio will catch me. \nGift - Lies: Carlo can bring the lies he tells to life \nby creating a Descriptor that allows him to \nperform incredible feats. All lies must be \ncentered on him. For example: I can walk \nthrough walls or I am invisible to the human \neye. The effects of the lies’ power are literal. \nFor this reason, Carlo would not be able to \ngo through a closed door and he would be \nseen by animals. The effect of Lies lasts for 1 \nScene or until a new lie is told.\nLucino - The Good Friend</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-carlo-the-living-puppet-137","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":137,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The \nlies I tell become reality for a short time.\nAgenda: Living a carefree life without responsibility / I don’t \nwant to abandon Sinalunga and my new friend Lucino, but \nI’m always afraid that Geppetto and Antonio will catch me. \nGift - Lies: Carlo can bring the lies he tells to life \nby creating a Descriptor that allows him to \nperform incredible feats. All lies must be \ncentered on him. For example: I can walk \nthrough walls or I am invisible to the human \neye. The effects of the lies’ power are literal. \nFor this reason, Carlo would not be able to \ngo through a closed door and he would be \nseen by animals. The effect of Lies lasts for 1 \nScene or until a new lie is told.\nLucino - The Good Friend</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Living a carefree life without responsibility / I don’t \nwant to abandon Sinalunga and my new friend Lucino, but \nI’m always afraid that Geppetto and Antonio will catch me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XF9VWOu2Ny4ccXyt","name":"Lost Children","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ccw6RZ8SEZ0TGGlM","name":"Lost Children - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are restless spirits spawned by Blanca’s \nmadness. We hate living things and try to take them with us \nto the waters of the Segura River to drown them, just as we \nwere.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 106.","positive":"We are restless spirits spawned by Blanca’s \nmadness. We hate living things and try to take them with us \nto the waters of the Segura River to drown them, just as we \nwere.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639946,"modifiedTime":1781557639946,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KQnW2QMgapDShpPU","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are restless spirits spawned by Blanca’s \nmadness. We hate living things and try to take them with us \nto the waters of the Segura River to drown them, just as we \nwere. \nAgenda: Choose a target and drag it to the Segura River to \ndrown it. \nGift - Suffering Spirit: As an action, a Lost Child will \nalways attempt to snatch a target. In the event of a Defense \nCheck Failure, apply the result based on where the action \ntakes place.\nWithin 100 feet of the Segura River: The Lost \nChild jumps into the river, taking the target with it. \nThe Lost Child suffers 1 Wound while the target is in \nthe depths of the River, see Threat - The Segura River \non page 106.\nAnywhere else: The Lost Child envelops the target</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 106."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639946,"modifiedTime":1781557639946,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-lost-children-106","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":106,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are restless spirits spawned by Blanca’s \nmadness. We hate living things and try to take them with us \nto the waters of the Segura River to drown them, just as we \nwere. \nAgenda: Choose a target and drag it to the Segura River to \ndrown it. \nGift - Suffering Spirit: As an action, a Lost Child will \nalways attempt to snatch a target. In the event of a Defense \nCheck Failure, apply the result based on where the action \ntakes place.\nWithin 100 feet of the Segura River: The Lost \nChild jumps into the river, taking the target with it. \nThe Lost Child suffers 1 Wound while the target is in \nthe depths of the River, see Threat - The Segura River \non page 106.\nAnywhere else: The Lost Child envelops the target</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Choose a target and drag it to the Segura River to \ndrown it.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639946,"modifiedTime":1781557639946,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XNJjucfR3Pvv7jAW","name":"Alexandra the Mother","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"JRTjGNGreb3z8UqR","name":"Alexandra the Mother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. \nThe curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget \nwhat I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can \nonly grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the \nforgiveness of my daughter.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 142.","positive":"I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. \nThe curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget \nwhat I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can \nonly grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the \nforgiveness of my daughter.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636337,"modifiedTime":1781557636337,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"X6BnZpqksgmuVFZL","name":"Gift - Deformed Orc","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Alexandra is a huge monster with \nherculean strength. She can act twice during an Exchange, \nbut not consecutively. The curse makes Alexandra resistant \nto magic. Any action using magic that involves her receives \n1 Penalty.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 142.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636337,"modifiedTime":1781557636337,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"S4Sf0i6CdeX0VoPo","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (5 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. \nThe curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget \nwhat I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can \nonly grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the \nforgiveness of my daughter.\nAgenda: After more than fifty years of a cursed existence, \nI have come to understand the damage my sins have done. \nUnable to beg for her forgiveness, I show my daughter how \nmuch I regret the past by doing anything she asks of me.\nGift – Deformed Orc: Alexandra is a huge monster with \nherculean strength. She can act twice during an Exchange, \nbut not consecutively. The curse makes Alexandra resistant \nto magic. Any action using magic that involves her receives \n1 Penalty.\nInformation: Upon her death, Alexandra’s body \nwill reverse to that of a gorgeous middle-aged woman. \nAlexandra is the only one, besides Accursio, who has a key \nto the Dungeons.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 142."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636338,"modifiedTime":1781557636338,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-alexandra-the-mother-142","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":142,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (5 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. \nThe curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget \nwhat I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can \nonly grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the \nforgiveness of my daughter.\nAgenda: After more than fifty years of a cursed existence, \nI have come to understand the damage my sins have done. \nUnable to beg for her forgiveness, I show my daughter how \nmuch I regret the past by doing anything she asks of me.\nGift – Deformed Orc: Alexandra is a huge monster with \nherculean strength. She can act twice during an Exchange, \nbut not consecutively. The curse makes Alexandra resistant \nto magic. Any action using magic that involves her receives \n1 Penalty.\nInformation: Upon her death, Alexandra’s body \nwill reverse to that of a gorgeous middle-aged woman. \nAlexandra is the only one, besides Accursio, who has a key \nto the Dungeons.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":5},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"After more than fifty years of a cursed existence, \nI have come to understand the damage my sins have done. \nUnable to beg for her forgiveness, I show my daughter how \nmuch I regret the past by doing anything she asks of me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636338,"modifiedTime":1781557636338,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XPKGOCVwuWfgjRqr","name":"Berto the Bear","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"iInoOXu3yScnWPUB","name":"Berto the Bear - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a strong and massive trained \nbear.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158.","positive":"I am a strong and massive trained \nbear.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"smeRW1vCHocIMIka","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a strong and massive trained \nbear.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-berto-the-bear-158","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":158,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a strong and massive trained \nbear.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XXHLTaJfcZY1ZB5Z","name":"6: Soila","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Mn9Mj9uPW7tS60NG","name":"6: Soila - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a teacher and I am responsible for the \neducation of the children in the village.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 120.","positive":"I am a teacher and I am responsible for the \neducation of the children in the village.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640571,"modifiedTime":1781557640571,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"p8dfv6DdmNSyLfnH","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a teacher and I am responsible for the \neducation of the children in the village. \nAgenda: Keeping Rovaniemi families together. \nInformation: Soila will say that Nikola’s behavior was always strange. For example, he always came to the village \nafter sunset and never entered anyone’s house without a \nproper formal invitation. More than once, Soila has seen \nhim lose his temper over the issue. But the Patron’s eccentric behavior is nothing compared to all the good he has \ndone for the Village. Soila knows all the families who live \nin the Village and is responsible for welcoming newcomers. \nShe will tell you that Tommi and Jutta are two good people, but too reserved to adapt to the rules of the community. Soila has even offered to help them pay the pledge, but \nTommi is too proud to go into debt.\nThe Forest around \nRovaniemi\nDescriptor: A dense forest, always covered by a thick blanket of snow. It is easy to find tracks in the snow.\nInformation: It is possible to reach Nikola’s estate from \nthe forest in a six-hour walk. Every three hours, the following Encounters are possible. The Storyteller can choose \nwhich or roll a die. \n1-2: The Tracks\n3-4: Nikola’s Reindeer\n5-6: Remains of the Merchant Wagon\nThe Tracks\nThe Hunters see the tracks of a single person who veered \noff the path and got lost in the forest. They were left by the \nfirst Hunter to arrive in Rovaniemi and lead to the Hunting \nLodge. See page 120.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 120."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640571,"modifiedTime":1781557640571,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-6-soila-120","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":120,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a teacher and I am responsible for the \neducation of the children in the village. \nAgenda: Keeping Rovaniemi families together. \nInformation: Soila will say that Nikola’s behavior was always strange. For example, he always came to the village \nafter sunset and never entered anyone’s house without a \nproper formal invitation. More than once, Soila has seen \nhim lose his temper over the issue. But the Patron’s eccentric behavior is nothing compared to all the good he has \ndone for the Village. Soila knows all the families who live \nin the Village and is responsible for welcoming newcomers. \nShe will tell you that Tommi and Jutta are two good people, but too reserved to adapt to the rules of the community. Soila has even offered to help them pay the pledge, but \nTommi is too proud to go into debt.\nThe Forest around \nRovaniemi\nDescriptor: A dense forest, always covered by a thick blanket of snow. It is easy to find tracks in the snow.\nInformation: It is possible to reach Nikola’s estate from \nthe forest in a six-hour walk. Every three hours, the following Encounters are possible. The Storyteller can choose \nwhich or roll a die. \n1-2: The Tracks\n3-4: Nikola’s Reindeer\n5-6: Remains of the Merchant Wagon\nThe Tracks\nThe Hunters see the tracks of a single person who veered \noff the path and got lost in the forest. They were left by the \nfirst Hunter to arrive in Rovaniemi and lead to the Hunting \nLodge. See page 120.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Keeping Rovaniemi families together.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640571,"modifiedTime":1781557640571,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XaRaWCGIjxoWksbk","name":"Illusory Panorama","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"M1eYSlkgEkzV6qzv","name":"Illusory Panorama - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A false image that adapts to weather conditions. Small, repetitive details are the only sign that something is wrong, such as a flock of seagulls flying following a \ncyclic trajectory and clouds that seem stuck in the same position.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 200.","positive":"A false image that adapts to weather conditions. Small, repetitive details are the only sign that something is wrong, such as a flock of seagulls flying following a \ncyclic trajectory and clouds that seem stuck in the same position.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644552,"modifiedTime":1781557644552,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fJxHgQpbvyhWtkQX","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A false image that adapts to weather conditions. Small, repetitive details are the only sign that something is wrong, such as a flock of seagulls flying following a \ncyclic trajectory and clouds that seem stuck in the same position.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 200."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644552,"modifiedTime":1781557644552,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-illusory-panorama-200","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":200,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A false image that adapts to weather conditions. Small, repetitive details are the only sign that something is wrong, such as a flock of seagulls flying following a \ncyclic trajectory and clouds that seem stuck in the same position.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644552,"modifiedTime":1781557644552,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XlLWIGkRCJ4NcRJ0","name":"Pietrik","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"jY0Hestx4CSH76E1","name":"Pietrik - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with \nall my strength.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 87.","positive":"I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with \nall my strength.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XuLguQgtNmtIjNCP","name":"Gift - The Needle of Living Shadows","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Thanks to the power of the magic needle \nthe Cauldron Fae gave him, once per Scene Pietrik can separate the shadow from \nhis body and make it act like an NPC with its own profile. The shadow has 1 \nWound and can slip through the smallest crack.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 87.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"zgyMKjdlKgZkYyHg","name":"Gift - Personal Seal","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Pietrik has the Seal of Disbelief tattooed on the palm \nof his hand, so once per Scene, he can activate the Gift The Magic of Disbelief \n(page 84). As with the Gang Seal Gift (page 87), Pietrik can activate any \nSeal present in London. \nThe Skullem Factory</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 87.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yLoQGQAiQbFfzXqg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with \nall my strength.\nAgenda: Destroy all the factories to avenge my sister’s death / Convince Gwendolyn to \njoin my gang because I have fallen in love with her. \nGift – The Needle of Living Shadows: Thanks to the power of the magic needle \nthe Cauldron Fae gave him, once per Scene Pietrik can separate the shadow from \nhis body and make it act like an NPC with its own profile. The shadow has 1 \nWound and can slip through the smallest crack. \nGift – Personal Seal: Pietrik has the Seal of Disbelief tattooed on the palm \nof his hand, so once per Scene, he can activate the Gift The Magic of Disbelief \n(page 84). As with the Gang Seal Gift (page 87), Pietrik can activate any \nSeal present in London. \nThe Skullem Factory\nDescriptor: A large shipyard in which metal components for ships are \nbeing assembled.\nInformation: Inside the factory, there are two large industrial \novens for metal welding. The goal of the Lost Boys is to blow \nthem up by throwing the magic berries that Pietrik has given \nout into them. The raid will take place at night and involves 10 \nLost Boys, in addition to Pietrik. \nSeals: The only Seal in the area of the Skullem Factory is \nlocated in the alley at the back of the building.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 87."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-pietrik-87","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":87,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with \nall my strength.\nAgenda: Destroy all the factories to avenge my sister’s death / Convince Gwendolyn to \njoin my gang because I have fallen in love with her. \nGift – The Needle of Living Shadows: Thanks to the power of the magic needle \nthe Cauldron Fae gave him, once per Scene Pietrik can separate the shadow from \nhis body and make it act like an NPC with its own profile. The shadow has 1 \nWound and can slip through the smallest crack. \nGift – Personal Seal: Pietrik has the Seal of Disbelief tattooed on the palm \nof his hand, so once per Scene, he can activate the Gift The Magic of Disbelief \n(page 84). As with the Gang Seal Gift (page 87), Pietrik can activate any \nSeal present in London. \nThe Skullem Factory\nDescriptor: A large shipyard in which metal components for ships are \nbeing assembled.\nInformation: Inside the factory, there are two large industrial \novens for metal welding. The goal of the Lost Boys is to blow \nthem up by throwing the magic berries that Pietrik has given \nout into them. The raid will take place at night and involves 10 \nLost Boys, in addition to Pietrik. \nSeals: The only Seal in the area of the Skullem Factory is \nlocated in the alley at the back of the building.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Destroy all the factories to avenge my sister’s death / Convince Gwendolyn to \njoin my gang because I have fallen in love with her.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625744,"modifiedTime":1781557625744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XnmPVkAv7MEDq8Gx","name":"The Executioner","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"vlouZErpm7KZdpi7","name":"The Executioner - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a ruthless enforcer, and with one stroke of \nmy scimitar I can cut a man in two.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 166.","positive":"I am a ruthless enforcer, and with one stroke of \nmy scimitar I can cut a man in two.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642795,"modifiedTime":1781557642795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"aJHDnA9m2MEFCxpo","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a ruthless enforcer, and with one stroke of \nmy scimitar I can cut a man in two. \nGift - Art of Death: Wounds inflicted by the Executioner \nare not easily healed and will remain for the next Leg unless \nthe Hunter can heal them with an Interlude, Gifts, or by \nusing the Gift of Sinbad - The Sailing Ship. \nEpilogue of the Leg: Whatever the outcome, Sherazade \nis now in the hands of the Hunters. She can be used as a \nHunter for the next few Legs if the Players wish.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 166."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642795,"modifiedTime":1781557642795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-the-executioner-166","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":166,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a ruthless enforcer, and with one stroke of \nmy scimitar I can cut a man in two. \nGift - Art of Death: Wounds inflicted by the Executioner \nare not easily healed and will remain for the next Leg unless \nthe Hunter can heal them with an Interlude, Gifts, or by \nusing the Gift of Sinbad - The Sailing Ship. \nEpilogue of the Leg: Whatever the outcome, Sherazade \nis now in the hands of the Hunters. She can be used as a \nHunter for the next few Legs if the Players wish.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642795,"modifiedTime":1781557642795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XpSypIhKHdJvmhrg","name":"Mtyrya the Fairy also called the Cauldron Fae","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"vzANKQeXKtmk6IQZ","name":"Mtyrya the Fairy also called the Cauldron Fae - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks \nto my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 85.","positive":"I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks \nto my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"h80U6Xnf4KmuzdGW","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks \nto my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.\nAgenda: Prevent humans from covering my beloved land with dirty, stinking factories / Save \nPietrik from the punishment I plan to inflict upon London.\nGift – The Magic of Disbelief: As an action, the Cauldron Fae can formulate a magic \nsentence including the fragment I don’t believe and make its effect concrete. For example, \n“I don’t believe in gravity” would allow her to fly, while “I don’t believe the Hunters of the \nOrder exist” would allow her to hurt the Hunters in an attempt to make them disappear. \nIf the statement does not have offensive effects, the duration of the power is generally for \nthe entire Scene. If, on the other hand, the effect is likely to harm a target, it will inflict \n1 Wound without the possibility of attempting a Defense Check. Those who use magic can \ntry to counteract the Magic of Disbelief, and preventing Mtyrya from speaking words would \nautomatically cancel the Gift’s effect.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 85."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-mtyrya-the-fairy-also-called-the-cauldron-fae-85","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":85,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks \nto my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.\nAgenda: Prevent humans from covering my beloved land with dirty, stinking factories / Save \nPietrik from the punishment I plan to inflict upon London.\nGift – The Magic of Disbelief: As an action, the Cauldron Fae can formulate a magic \nsentence including the fragment I don’t believe and make its effect concrete. For example, \n“I don’t believe in gravity” would allow her to fly, while “I don’t believe the Hunters of the \nOrder exist” would allow her to hurt the Hunters in an attempt to make them disappear. \nIf the statement does not have offensive effects, the duration of the power is generally for \nthe entire Scene. If, on the other hand, the effect is likely to harm a target, it will inflict \n1 Wound without the possibility of attempting a Defense Check. Those who use magic can \ntry to counteract the Magic of Disbelief, and preventing Mtyrya from speaking words would \nautomatically cancel the Gift’s effect.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Prevent humans from covering my beloved land with dirty, stinking factories / Save \nPietrik from the punishment I plan to inflict upon London.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625700,"modifiedTime":1781557625700,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Xqx8QtD5z8u8BLiY","name":"Antonio Ciliegia Gullible Alchemist","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Q6Vhyl8vKDOfg4Up","name":"Antonio Ciliegia Gullible Alchemist - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an old alchemist who has never discovered \nanything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck \nis never on my side.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 140.","positive":"I am an old alchemist who has never discovered \nanything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck \nis never on my side.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621931,"modifiedTime":1781557621931,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"AdL14qrj43fHAf5v","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old alchemist who has never discovered \nanything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck \nis never on my side.\nAgenda: Obtaining the secret of eternal life thanks to \nalchemy. \nGift - Unlucky Alchemist: Antonio can rely on a series \nof alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides \nin his tunic. When using a vial he rolls 1 die. On a 5 or \n6 something goes wrong and Antonio suffers 1 Wound \ndue to his proverbial bad luck. 1. Fire: The target and the \nsurrounding area catch fire. All targets involved suffer 1 \nWound. If the fire is not extinguished, burning targets \nsuffer 1 Wound per action. 2. Thunder: The target \nis knocked over thirty feet away and ends up on the \nground. If they hit something they will suffer 1 \nWound. 3. Glue: an adhesive compound that \nquickly solidifies in the air. The target will be \nparalyzed until the compound is removed. \nThe Glue can take 2 Wounds.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 140."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621931,"modifiedTime":1781557621931,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-antonio-ciliegia-gullible-alchemist-140","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":140,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an old alchemist who has never discovered \nanything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck \nis never on my side.\nAgenda: Obtaining the secret of eternal life thanks to \nalchemy. \nGift - Unlucky Alchemist: Antonio can rely on a series \nof alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides \nin his tunic. When using a vial he rolls 1 die. On a 5 or \n6 something goes wrong and Antonio suffers 1 Wound \ndue to his proverbial bad luck. 1. Fire: The target and the \nsurrounding area catch fire. All targets involved suffer 1 \nWound. If the fire is not extinguished, burning targets \nsuffer 1 Wound per action. 2. Thunder: The target \nis knocked over thirty feet away and ends up on the \nground. If they hit something they will suffer 1 \nWound. 3. Glue: an adhesive compound that \nquickly solidifies in the air. The target will be \nparalyzed until the compound is removed. \nThe Glue can take 2 Wounds.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Obtaining the secret of eternal life thanks to \nalchemy.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621931,"modifiedTime":1781557621931,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"YGXVCaLUGypKyAbF","name":"Father Cristoforo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"qblMo68mazYndcf9","name":"Father Cristoforo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a humble provincial priest and I have \nbeen responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas \nfor years.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 126.","positive":"I am a humble provincial priest and I have \nbeen responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas \nfor years.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629772,"modifiedTime":1781557629772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fzJSK0zg8qrD0xbN","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a humble provincial priest and I have \nbeen responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas \nfor years. \nAgenda: I have reason to believe that the House of Roses is \na place of blasphemy and damnation, so I want the Church \nto investigate.\nInformation from the conversation with \nCristoforo: The humble priest will welcome the Hunters \nin the small church of San Carlo. The man will show \nreverence to the work of the Order and will seem aware of \nwho the Hunters really are.\n ◆ Cristoforo will say that the island once was a \nmonastery where the residents dedicated themselves to \nblasphemous rites. The Church intervened by putting \nthem all at the stake.\n ◆ Martana Island is a name on the lips of many young \npeople, who tell of a place of feasts and pleasures far \nfrom the severe but holy eye of God. Many young women \ngo out of their way to get to sail to the island. \n ◆ Cristoforo taught the ways of God to the unfortunate \nDionysus, being troubled by the savagery that the young \nman struggled to control. \n ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters \nthat Cristoforo does not really know what is happening on \nthe island, but he is firmly convinced that it is nothing good.\n ◆ Trying not to be overheard by prying ears, Cristoforo will \ntell the Hunters that a couple of faithful friends have a small \nboat and can take the Hunters to the island at night, landing \non a little-used beach. \nMartana Island\nDescriptor: A small island in the center of Lake Bolsena. Covered \nmostly by dense vegetation, the island includes a sanctuary, a \nsmall pier, and a mansion recently built by the Gonsalvas.\nThere are five locations available on the island:\n ◆ The Pier: Where all ships arriving from Capodimonte dock. \nThe pier is under the control of Bella and her worshippers. \nIf the Hunters accept Pietro Gonsalva’s transportation offer, \nthey will arrive there in the late afternoon.\n ◆ The White Beach: A small beach of rocks and earth to the \neast of the island. It is located on the opposite side of the \nisland from the few inhabited places. If the Hunters accept \nFather Cristoforo’s offer of transportation, they will reach \nthe beach at night.\n ◆ The Sanctuary: All the young people who have become \nprisoners of the House of Roses live here.\n ◆ The Mansion: The House of Roses is a sumptuous villa that \nDionysus had built for Bella.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 126."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629772,"modifiedTime":1781557629772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-father-cristoforo-126","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":126,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a humble provincial priest and I have \nbeen responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas \nfor years. \nAgenda: I have reason to believe that the House of Roses is \na place of blasphemy and damnation, so I want the Church \nto investigate.\nInformation from the conversation with \nCristoforo: The humble priest will welcome the Hunters \nin the small church of San Carlo. The man will show \nreverence to the work of the Order and will seem aware of \nwho the Hunters really are.\n ◆ Cristoforo will say that the island once was a \nmonastery where the residents dedicated themselves to \nblasphemous rites. The Church intervened by putting \nthem all at the stake.\n ◆ Martana Island is a name on the lips of many young \npeople, who tell of a place of feasts and pleasures far \nfrom the severe but holy eye of God. Many young women \ngo out of their way to get to sail to the island. \n ◆ Cristoforo taught the ways of God to the unfortunate \nDionysus, being troubled by the savagery that the young \nman struggled to control. \n ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters \nthat Cristoforo does not really know what is happening on \nthe island, but he is firmly convinced that it is nothing good.\n ◆ Trying not to be overheard by prying ears, Cristoforo will \ntell the Hunters that a couple of faithful friends have a small \nboat and can take the Hunters to the island at night, landing \non a little-used beach. \nMartana Island\nDescriptor: A small island in the center of Lake Bolsena. Covered \nmostly by dense vegetation, the island includes a sanctuary, a \nsmall pier, and a mansion recently built by the Gonsalvas.\nThere are five locations available on the island:\n ◆ The Pier: Where all ships arriving from Capodimonte dock. \nThe pier is under the control of Bella and her worshippers. \nIf the Hunters accept Pietro Gonsalva’s transportation offer, \nthey will arrive there in the late afternoon.\n ◆ The White Beach: A small beach of rocks and earth to the \neast of the island. It is located on the opposite side of the \nisland from the few inhabited places. If the Hunters accept \nFather Cristoforo’s offer of transportation, they will reach \nthe beach at night.\n ◆ The Sanctuary: All the young people who have become \nprisoners of the House of Roses live here.\n ◆ The Mansion: The House of Roses is a sumptuous villa that \nDionysus had built for Bella.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"I have reason to believe that the House of Roses is \na place of blasphemy and damnation, so I want the Church \nto investigate.\nInformation from the conversation with \nCristoforo: The humble priest will welcome the Hunters \nin the small church of San Carlo. The man will show \nreverence to the work of the Order and will seem aware of \nwho the Hunters really are.\n ◆ Cristoforo will say that the island once was a \nmonastery where the residents dedicated themselves to \nblasphemous rites. The Church intervened by putting \nthem all at the stake.\n ◆ Martana Island is a name on the lips of many young \npeople, who tell of a place of feasts and pleasures far \nfrom the severe but holy eye of God. Many young women \ngo out of their way to get to sail to the island. \n ◆ Cristoforo taught the ways of God to the unfortunate \nDionysus, being troubled by the savagery that the young \nman struggled to control. \n ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters \nthat Cristoforo does not really know what is happening on \nthe island, but he is firmly convinced that it is nothing good.\n ◆ Trying not to be overheard by prying ears, Cristoforo will \ntell the Hunters that a couple of faithful friends have a small \nboat and can take the Hunters to the island at night, landing \non a little-used beach. \nMartana Island\nDescriptor: A small island in the center of Lake Bolsena. Covered \nmostly by dense vegetation, the island includes a sanctuary, a \nsmall pier, and a mansion recently built by the Gonsalvas.\nThere are five locations available on the island:\n ◆ The Pier: Where all ships arriving from Capodimonte dock. \nThe pier is under the control of Bella and her worshippers. \nIf the Hunters accept Pietro Gonsalva’s transportation offer, \nthey will arrive there in the late afternoon.\n ◆ The White Beach: A small beach of rocks and earth to the \neast of the island. It is located on the opposite side of the \nisland from the few inhabited places. If the Hunters accept \nFather Cristoforo’s offer of transportation, they will reach \nthe beach at night.\n ◆ The Sanctuary: All the young people who have become \nprisoners of the House of Roses live here.\n ◆ The Mansion: The House of Roses is a sumptuous villa that \nDionysus had built for Bella.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557629772,"modifiedTime":1781557629772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"YwnmImWpaqtQKbmb","name":"Bella’s Handmaids","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"eZO5HGpVvrpPB1pp","name":"Bella’s Handmaids - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are \nready to have a good time – anytime.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","positive":"We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are \nready to have a good time – anytime.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CrITrc1MmQfR5YSv","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are \nready to have a good time – anytime.\nAgenda: We have tasted happiness in the House of Roses \nand we will not allow anyone to take us back to our former, \nmiserable lives.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-bella-s-handmaids-128","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":128,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are \nready to have a good time – anytime.\nAgenda: We have tasted happiness in the House of Roses \nand we will not allow anyone to take us back to our former, \nmiserable lives.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"We have tasted happiness in the House of Roses \nand we will not allow anyone to take us back to our former, \nmiserable lives.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ZCOZ7g0JaUPbdclj","name":"Merlin’s Shadow","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Uc3NCGfoNs6m9Nzq","name":"Merlin’s Shadow - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the shadow of the mighty sorcerer Merlin, \nand with my touch, I can freeze anything. I constantly receive \nvisions of what my former master is doing.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 185.","positive":"I am the shadow of the mighty sorcerer Merlin, \nand with my touch, I can freeze anything. I constantly receive \nvisions of what my former master is doing.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643869,"modifiedTime":1781557643869,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"NceHfdjyKGJJECiO","name":"Gift - Shadow Body","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>In semi- or total darkness, Merlin’s</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 185.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643869,"modifiedTime":1781557643869,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jZ6nLHvlt7awdDla","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the shadow of the mighty sorcerer Merlin, \nand with my touch, I can freeze anything. I constantly receive \nvisions of what my former master is doing. \nAgenda: Kill the precious Hunters Merlin has sent as a way \nof taking revenge on him for leaving me alone to guard Avalon. \nGift - Shadow Body: In semi- or total darkness, Merlin’s</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 185."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643869,"modifiedTime":1781557643869,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-merlin-s-shadow-185","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":185,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the shadow of the mighty sorcerer Merlin, \nand with my touch, I can freeze anything. I constantly receive \nvisions of what my former master is doing. \nAgenda: Kill the precious Hunters Merlin has sent as a way \nof taking revenge on him for leaving me alone to guard Avalon. \nGift - Shadow Body: In semi- or total darkness, Merlin’s</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Kill the precious Hunters Merlin has sent as a way \nof taking revenge on him for leaving me alone to guard Avalon.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643869,"modifiedTime":1781557643869,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Zfuj6tv0FGwMdHmv","name":"Big Black Wolf","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"d2X63EF9fNvZEKoR","name":"Big Black Wolf - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a huge, mighty \nwerewolf. I have to constantly prove my \nstrength to stay the alpha of the pack.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126.","positive":"I am a huge, mighty \nwerewolf. I have to constantly prove my \nstrength to stay the alpha of the pack.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"A1AthVgqAfHl4FvH","name":"Gift - Big Wolf","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Greskar is an enormous \nblack wolf, as big as a horse. When he \ngrabs someone with his jaws, in addition \nto inflicting a Wound, he can drag or \nhurl them away as if they were a rag doll. \nOnce per Scene, Geskar’s bite can inflict \n1 additional Wound.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4ZfkCLpfn4lZ3Uzx","name":"Gift - The Wolf’s Smell","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Greskar’s \nsense of smell is infallible. The big wolf \nwill always be able to identify someone if \nhe knows their scent, ignoring all kinds \nof disguises and even magic.\nRed-Hood Iskra</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WQCqIT3Mvl20TdNh","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a huge, mighty \nwerewolf. I have to constantly prove my \nstrength to stay the alpha of the pack.\nAgenda: Protect Iskra and devour as \nmany humans as possible.\nGift - Big Wolf: Greskar is an enormous \nblack wolf, as big as a horse. When he \ngrabs someone with his jaws, in addition \nto inflicting a Wound, he can drag or \nhurl them away as if they were a rag doll. \nOnce per Scene, Geskar’s bite can inflict \n1 additional Wound.\nGift - The Wolf’s Smell: Greskar’s \nsense of smell is infallible. The big wolf \nwill always be able to identify someone if \nhe knows their scent, ignoring all kinds \nof disguises and even magic.\nRed-Hood Iskra</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 126."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-big-black-wolf-126","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":126,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a huge, mighty \nwerewolf. I have to constantly prove my \nstrength to stay the alpha of the pack.\nAgenda: Protect Iskra and devour as \nmany humans as possible.\nGift - Big Wolf: Greskar is an enormous \nblack wolf, as big as a horse. When he \ngrabs someone with his jaws, in addition \nto inflicting a Wound, he can drag or \nhurl them away as if they were a rag doll. \nOnce per Scene, Geskar’s bite can inflict \n1 additional Wound.\nGift - The Wolf’s Smell: Greskar’s \nsense of smell is infallible. The big wolf \nwill always be able to identify someone if \nhe knows their scent, ignoring all kinds \nof disguises and even magic.\nRed-Hood Iskra</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Protect Iskra and devour as \nmany humans as possible.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621407,"modifiedTime":1781557621407,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ZnXhtG3dL3EPHadN","name":"Villa Wagner’s Guard","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"VlsEecGahLj3FNW7","name":"Villa Wagner’s Guard - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are loyal and well-trained for our duties as \nguardians.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 139.","positive":"We are loyal and well-trained for our duties as \nguardians.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641605,"modifiedTime":1781557641605,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"FqJ496uFcadq199F","name":"Gift - Guard Corps","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>During an action, increase their OL \nby 1 if they are defending Villa Wagner from a threat or \nperceived threat.\nAlena Wagner</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 139.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641606,"modifiedTime":1781557641606,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"13rYFHwjgUDJzyV8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are loyal and well-trained for our duties as \nguardians. \nGift - Guard Corps: During an action, increase their OL \nby 1 if they are defending Villa Wagner from a threat or \nperceived threat.\nAlena Wagner</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 139."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641606,"modifiedTime":1781557641606,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-villa-wagner-s-guard-139","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":139,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are loyal and well-trained for our duties as \nguardians. \nGift - Guard Corps: During an action, increase their OL \nby 1 if they are defending Villa Wagner from a threat or \nperceived threat.\nAlena Wagner</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641606,"modifiedTime":1781557641606,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Zw1LjGuofeWS9t67","name":"The Segura River","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"NPXtt5vUdyut0Im6","name":"The Segura River - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Strong currents and icy waters make the Segura River dangerous even for experienced swimmers. \nThe Monastery\nDescriptor: An old monastery that once housed a group \nof monks. Now only a few rooms and the large courtyard are \nusable.\nMorning: From the Monastery garden comes the cackle \nof children playing. With them is Sister Esperanza, a nun \nwho helps Father Neron keep the little marked ones safe \nfrom Blanca’s sight. There are a total of six children in the \nMonastery (all reported missing from the River Market). \nWhen questioned, Sister Esperanza will not hesitate to \nstand up for Father Neron. The nun will say that the priest \nwanders around the Market in the morning, while in the afternoon he worries about finding the children’s families to \ntell them that their little ones are safe under the protection \nof the Church. Father Neron makes donations to the children’s families to ensure their cooperation, with the promise of a reunion on the first day of December. \nAfternoon: Father Neron is present as he prepares donations for the families of the children who live in the Monastery. Sister Esperanza takes care of the children.\nEvening: Father Neron is the small library of the Monastery, studying books on exorcism. Sister Esperanza sleeps \nin the underground rooms with the children.\nSister Esperanza</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 107.","positive":"Strong currents and icy waters make the Segura River dangerous even for experienced swimmers. \nThe Monastery\nDescriptor: An old monastery that once housed a group \nof monks. Now only a few rooms and the large courtyard are \nusable.\nMorning: From the Monastery garden comes the cackle \nof children playing. With them is Sister Esperanza, a nun \nwho helps Father Neron keep the little marked ones safe \nfrom Blanca’s sight. There are a total of six children in the \nMonastery (all reported missing from the River Market). \nWhen questioned, Sister Esperanza will not hesitate to \nstand up for Father Neron. The nun will say that the priest \nwanders around the Market in the morning, while in the afternoon he worries about finding the children’s families to \ntell them that their little ones are safe under the protection \nof the Church. Father Neron makes donations to the children’s families to ensure their cooperation, with the promise of a reunion on the first day of December. \nAfternoon: Father Neron is present as he prepares donations for the families of the children who live in the Monastery. Sister Esperanza takes care of the children.\nEvening: Father Neron is the small library of the Monastery, studying books on exorcism. Sister Esperanza sleeps \nin the underground rooms with the children.\nSister Esperanza","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640056,"modifiedTime":1781557640056,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"f5vshlw2eilVZWrv","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: Strong currents and icy waters make the Segura River dangerous even for experienced swimmers. \nThe Monastery\nDescriptor: An old monastery that once housed a group \nof monks. Now only a few rooms and the large courtyard are \nusable.\nMorning: From the Monastery garden comes the cackle \nof children playing. With them is Sister Esperanza, a nun \nwho helps Father Neron keep the little marked ones safe \nfrom Blanca’s sight. There are a total of six children in the \nMonastery (all reported missing from the River Market). \nWhen questioned, Sister Esperanza will not hesitate to \nstand up for Father Neron. The nun will say that the priest \nwanders around the Market in the morning, while in the afternoon he worries about finding the children’s families to \ntell them that their little ones are safe under the protection \nof the Church. Father Neron makes donations to the children’s families to ensure their cooperation, with the promise of a reunion on the first day of December. \nAfternoon: Father Neron is present as he prepares donations for the families of the children who live in the Monastery. Sister Esperanza takes care of the children.\nEvening: Father Neron is the small library of the Monastery, studying books on exorcism. Sister Esperanza sleeps \nin the underground rooms with the children.\nSister Esperanza</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 107."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640056,"modifiedTime":1781557640056,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-the-segura-river-107","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":107,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: Strong currents and icy waters make the Segura River dangerous even for experienced swimmers. \nThe Monastery\nDescriptor: An old monastery that once housed a group \nof monks. Now only a few rooms and the large courtyard are \nusable.\nMorning: From the Monastery garden comes the cackle \nof children playing. With them is Sister Esperanza, a nun \nwho helps Father Neron keep the little marked ones safe \nfrom Blanca’s sight. There are a total of six children in the \nMonastery (all reported missing from the River Market). \nWhen questioned, Sister Esperanza will not hesitate to \nstand up for Father Neron. The nun will say that the priest \nwanders around the Market in the morning, while in the afternoon he worries about finding the children’s families to \ntell them that their little ones are safe under the protection \nof the Church. Father Neron makes donations to the children’s families to ensure their cooperation, with the promise of a reunion on the first day of December. \nAfternoon: Father Neron is present as he prepares donations for the families of the children who live in the Monastery. Sister Esperanza takes care of the children.\nEvening: Father Neron is the small library of the Monastery, studying books on exorcism. Sister Esperanza sleeps \nin the underground rooms with the children.\nSister Esperanza</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640056,"modifiedTime":1781557640056,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ZwkK0tfly4CzaNhV","name":"Troll Craftsman","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"NZuZqPd8rEU3CcLI","name":"Troll Craftsman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled craftsman and have served Lady \nStorm for decades, creating stunning ice mirrors for her. I can \nmanipulate the reflected images as if they were real.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 223.","positive":"I am a skilled craftsman and have served Lady \nStorm for decades, creating stunning ice mirrors for her. I can \nmanipulate the reflected images as if they were real.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646130,"modifiedTime":1781557646130,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"64bgWDBhuQL4Xetm","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled craftsman and have served Lady \nStorm for decades, creating stunning ice mirrors for her. I can \nmanipulate the reflected images as if they were real. \nAgenda: Rebuilding the Mirror of the Other Self for my \nLady Storm. \nSpecial Agenda (Prince Trollo the Innocent): I have \nalways wanted an apprentice to pass my art on to, and he \nseems perfect. Whether he wants to or not. \nGift - The Mirrored Reality: Although blinded, the \nTroll can see the world around it through the mirrors scattered throughout the room, thanks to the glare of the shards \nin his eyes. The Troll can act against a target by striking at \na reflected image without the target being able to make a \nDefense Check to avoid it.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 223."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646130,"modifiedTime":1781557646130,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-troll-craftsman-223","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":223,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled craftsman and have served Lady \nStorm for decades, creating stunning ice mirrors for her. I can \nmanipulate the reflected images as if they were real. \nAgenda: Rebuilding the Mirror of the Other Self for my \nLady Storm. \nSpecial Agenda (Prince Trollo the Innocent): I have \nalways wanted an apprentice to pass my art on to, and he \nseems perfect. Whether he wants to or not. \nGift - The Mirrored Reality: Although blinded, the \nTroll can see the world around it through the mirrors scattered throughout the room, thanks to the glare of the shards \nin his eyes. The Troll can act against a target by striking at \na reflected image without the target being able to make a \nDefense Check to avoid it.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Rebuilding the Mirror of the Other Self for my \nLady Storm.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646130,"modifiedTime":1781557646130,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"a0cPa2cdbWYRBeIu","name":"Britta the Beheaded Witch","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"mAm6azoyBhYQj2AH","name":"Britta the Beheaded Witch - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled witch who only desires a quiet \nlife. Since I no longer have a head, I cannot speak or utter \nmagic formulas.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 142.","positive":"I am a skilled witch who only desires a quiet \nlife. Since I no longer have a head, I cannot speak or utter \nmagic formulas.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641698,"modifiedTime":1781557641698,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dRDrhLrZfyrGJOkN","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled witch who only desires a quiet \nlife. Since I no longer have a head, I cannot speak or utter \nmagic formulas. \nAgenda: To find my head that Bastian threw in the river. \nInformation: Britta’s body will revive when two of her \nthree magical items are placed on her. In this state, Britta \nwill not be able to speak, but she will be able to write, informing the Hunters that she knows where her head is and \nwill go to retrieve it. In the meantime, Britta will ask the \nHunters to retrieve the third object to complete her resur -\nrection. \nBritta the Witch</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 142."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641698,"modifiedTime":1781557641698,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-britta-the-beheaded-witch-142","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":142,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled witch who only desires a quiet \nlife. Since I no longer have a head, I cannot speak or utter \nmagic formulas. \nAgenda: To find my head that Bastian threw in the river. \nInformation: Britta’s body will revive when two of her \nthree magical items are placed on her. In this state, Britta \nwill not be able to speak, but she will be able to write, informing the Hunters that she knows where her head is and \nwill go to retrieve it. In the meantime, Britta will ask the \nHunters to retrieve the third object to complete her resur -\nrection. \nBritta the Witch</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To find my head that Bastian threw in the river.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641698,"modifiedTime":1781557641698,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"a4tN8nbbmkfHjcXj","name":"Princesca of Vigo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"sxgGlpRsthsr7y7Z","name":"Princesca of Vigo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am Cinder and, thanks to \nmagic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind \nPrincesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind \nMother, I control the entire city. I am cold and \ndetermined and I won’t let anyone stand in \nmy way.</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 154.","positive":"I am Cinder and, thanks to \nmagic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind \nPrincesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind \nMother, I control the entire city. I am cold and \ndetermined and I won’t let anyone stand in \nmy way.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Pi1xkCoEcYzZypUq","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC \n(3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am Cinder and, thanks to \nmagic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind \nPrincesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind \nMother, I control the entire city. I am cold and \ndetermined and I won’t let anyone stand in \nmy way. \nAgenda: Gain wealth and power by \nmanipulating my stupid husband / Solving \nthe mystery of the new killer who behaves \nexactly as I did ten years ago. \nGift – Kind Magic: Cinder is able \nto use the magic that the Kind Mother taught her. As an action, Cinder \ncan cast one of the following spells. \n1. Animal Servants: A group of \nanimals (up to 6 subjects) blindly \nobeys the will of Cinder, even per -\nforming suicidal actions. Cinder \nhas used this power many times \non a pair of doves until they \nhave been completely enslaved \n(see The Doves on page 154); \n2. Transmutation: An ob -\nject or a portion of the environment mutates to be transformed into something else. \nThe mutation lasts through-</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 154."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-princesca-of-vigo-154","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":154,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC \n(3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am Cinder and, thanks to \nmagic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind \nPrincesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind \nMother, I control the entire city. I am cold and \ndetermined and I won’t let anyone stand in \nmy way. \nAgenda: Gain wealth and power by \nmanipulating my stupid husband / Solving \nthe mystery of the new killer who behaves \nexactly as I did ten years ago. \nGift – Kind Magic: Cinder is able \nto use the magic that the Kind Mother taught her. As an action, Cinder \ncan cast one of the following spells. \n1. Animal Servants: A group of \nanimals (up to 6 subjects) blindly \nobeys the will of Cinder, even per -\nforming suicidal actions. Cinder \nhas used this power many times \non a pair of doves until they \nhave been completely enslaved \n(see The Doves on page 154); \n2. Transmutation: An ob -\nject or a portion of the environment mutates to be transformed into something else. \nThe mutation lasts through-</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Gain wealth and power by \nmanipulating my stupid husband / Solving \nthe mystery of the new killer who behaves \nexactly as I did ten years ago.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636919,"modifiedTime":1781557636919,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"a9SyNIvdJu36AmvM","name":"Alissa of Norfolk The Rebel","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"viH27i8R4j6orKRo","name":"Alissa of Norfolk The Rebel - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I have been physically tested by my stay in \nWonder, but my mind is still strong. My love for Alicia kept \nme in the real world.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 178.","positive":"I have been physically tested by my stay in \nWonder, but my mind is still strong. My love for Alicia kept \nme in the real world.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623025,"modifiedTime":1781557623025,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tazHYgsNZUvr2YS3","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I have been physically tested by my stay in \nWonder, but my mind is still strong. My love for Alicia kept \nme in the real world.\nAgenda: Escape from Wonder and my old life and make a \nfuture with Alicia.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nWhen the Hunters visit the third Cure Room \nwithout first meeting Alicia: they will encounter \nAlicia, who is lost. The young woman will be reluctant to \nreveal her true identity but will give her name and introduce \nherself as a patient.\nOn a regular basis, if the Hunters waste time in the \nEntrance Hall of Wonder: one of the bedlam Patients \nwill walk out of one of the three doors into another. The \nPatient will mumble disjointed words such as “see beyond” \nor “go under” .\nIf the Hunters cause too much havoc in a Cure \nRoom: Alice will take control of Cheshire and order the \nHunters to leave, or try to surprise them by making it clear \nthat they are being watched.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 178."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623025,"modifiedTime":1781557623025,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-alissa-of-norfolk-the-rebel-178","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":178,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I have been physically tested by my stay in \nWonder, but my mind is still strong. My love for Alicia kept \nme in the real world.\nAgenda: Escape from Wonder and my old life and make a \nfuture with Alicia.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nWhen the Hunters visit the third Cure Room \nwithout first meeting Alicia: they will encounter \nAlicia, who is lost. The young woman will be reluctant to \nreveal her true identity but will give her name and introduce \nherself as a patient.\nOn a regular basis, if the Hunters waste time in the \nEntrance Hall of Wonder: one of the bedlam Patients \nwill walk out of one of the three doors into another. The \nPatient will mumble disjointed words such as “see beyond” \nor “go under” .\nIf the Hunters cause too much havoc in a Cure \nRoom: Alice will take control of Cheshire and order the \nHunters to leave, or try to surprise them by making it clear \nthat they are being watched.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Escape from Wonder and my old life and make a \nfuture with Alicia.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nWhen the Hunters visit the third Cure Room \nwithout first meeting Alicia: they will encounter \nAlicia, who is lost. The young woman will be reluctant to \nreveal her true identity but will give her name and introduce \nherself as a patient.\nOn a regular basis, if the Hunters waste time in the \nEntrance Hall of Wonder: one of the bedlam Patients \nwill walk out of one of the three doors into another. The \nPatient will mumble disjointed words such as “see beyond” \nor “go under” .\nIf the Hunters cause too much havoc in a Cure \nRoom: Alice will take control of Cheshire and order the \nHunters to leave, or try to surprise them by making it clear \nthat they are being watched.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623025,"modifiedTime":1781557623025,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"aHv66BRLRFpTDj6c","name":"Vincenzo Carabiniere","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"n0Scl0VOH76dZ9sW","name":"Vincenzo Carabiniere - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my \nbest to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me \naway from battlefields.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 133.","positive":"I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my \nbest to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me \naway from battlefields.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621670,"modifiedTime":1781557621670,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9mJQrXsH35LgvHtt","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my \nbest to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me \naway from battlefields.\nAgenda: Find out what lies behind the disappearances in \nSinalunga.\nSinalunga\nDescriptor: A small town in the Tuscan hills. Thanks to its \nfamously delicious wine, many in the town manage to have a \ngood standard of living.\nBy wandering around town and talking to the inhabitants, \nthe Hunters can get some information. The fear that \nan intervention by the Grand Duchy could upset life in \nSinalunga means the inhabitants are reluctant to speak to \nanyone other than the authorities. Only Lapo and Cino, \nwho are not particularly bright, won’t hesitate to talk with \nthe Hunters, though only with the promise of a reward.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 133."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621670,"modifiedTime":1781557621670,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-vincenzo-carabiniere-133","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":133,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my \nbest to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me \naway from battlefields.\nAgenda: Find out what lies behind the disappearances in \nSinalunga.\nSinalunga\nDescriptor: A small town in the Tuscan hills. Thanks to its \nfamously delicious wine, many in the town manage to have a \ngood standard of living.\nBy wandering around town and talking to the inhabitants, \nthe Hunters can get some information. The fear that \nan intervention by the Grand Duchy could upset life in \nSinalunga means the inhabitants are reluctant to speak to \nanyone other than the authorities. Only Lapo and Cino, \nwho are not particularly bright, won’t hesitate to talk with \nthe Hunters, though only with the promise of a reward.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Find out what lies behind the disappearances in \nSinalunga.\nSinalunga\nDescriptor: A small town in the Tuscan hills. Thanks to its \nfamously delicious wine, many in the town manage to have a \ngood standard of living.\nBy wandering around town and talking to the inhabitants, \nthe Hunters can get some information. The fear that \nan intervention by the Grand Duchy could upset life in \nSinalunga means the inhabitants are reluctant to speak to \nanyone other than the authorities. Only Lapo and Cino, \nwho are not particularly bright, won’t hesitate to talk with \nthe Hunters, though only with the promise of a reward.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621670,"modifiedTime":1781557621670,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"aM2KkGTF3GaQLM0y","name":"Armsmen of the City","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"kvmKaWJFkyHOva8h","name":"Armsmen of the City - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are swordsmen and have gained experience during the war. We carry out the orders of those who pay \nus without making too much trouble.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136.","positive":"We are swordsmen and have gained experience during the war. We carry out the orders of those who pay \nus without making too much trouble.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"AZz9mimrUmKGLNTA","name":"Gift - Companions in Arms","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>During an action, they \nincrease their OL by 1 if at least one other Armsman is present. \nCutthroat</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"o0Y6PbS0Wrh6cdUu","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are swordsmen and have gained experience during the war. We carry out the orders of those who pay \nus without making too much trouble. \nGift - Companions in Arms: During an action, they \nincrease their OL by 1 if at least one other Armsman is present. \nCutthroat</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-armsmen-of-the-city-136","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":136,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are swordsmen and have gained experience during the war. We carry out the orders of those who pay \nus without making too much trouble. \nGift - Companions in Arms: During an action, they \nincrease their OL by 1 if at least one other Armsman is present. \nCutthroat</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"aPI4ynNXcWYNte2M","name":"Arthur","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"cLtgc0R5sTMNhoDj","name":"Arthur - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the king of Camelot, and my word is law. \nThanks to the power of the Grail, my body is immortal and I \npossess abilities far beyond those of ordinary men.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 195.","positive":"I am the king of Camelot, and my word is law. \nThanks to the power of the Grail, my body is immortal and I \npossess abilities far beyond those of ordinary men.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644317,"modifiedTime":1781557644317,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"kIDRvZJzmuOMZV15","name":"Gift - The True Power of the Grail","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Arthur is immortal, which means that any Wounds inflicted on him will \nheal immediately. Arthur can act up to 3 times in an Exchange, but not back to back.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 195.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644317,"modifiedTime":1781557644317,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"NBs6AiqR8C9oEY8n","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the king of Camelot, and my word is law. \nThanks to the power of the Grail, my body is immortal and I \npossess abilities far beyond those of ordinary men.\nAgenda: Bring back my bride, Guinevere, to rule all of Europe by my side / Prepare the army for battle and make all my \nsubjects immortal warriors. \nGift - The True Power of the Grail: Arthur is immortal, which means that any Wounds inflicted on him will \nheal immediately. Arthur can act up to 3 times in an Exchange, but not back to back.\nGift - Merlin’s Curse: Deprived of the Virtues by Merlin’s magic, Arthur has become a mad and powerful being \nwho has abandoned his humanity. Activating the power of \nthe Virtues awakens the king’s true soul, making him more \nhuman. Each Virtue consumed in front of Arthur will have \nthe following effect:\nLove: Lower his OL by 2.\nInnocence: Lower the number of Wounds by 3. \nFaith: He loses his immortality and, if brought to 0 \nWounds, is permanently killed. \nCourage: Acts only 1 time per Exchange. \nWisdom: He regains his wits and realizes that what he is \ndoing is wrong. Arthur’s Agenda changes to: Lead my kingdom to peace by finding a place in this new world.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 195."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644317,"modifiedTime":1781557644317,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-arthur-195","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":195,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the king of Camelot, and my word is law. \nThanks to the power of the Grail, my body is immortal and I \npossess abilities far beyond those of ordinary men.\nAgenda: Bring back my bride, Guinevere, to rule all of Europe by my side / Prepare the army for battle and make all my \nsubjects immortal warriors. \nGift - The True Power of the Grail: Arthur is immortal, which means that any Wounds inflicted on him will \nheal immediately. Arthur can act up to 3 times in an Exchange, but not back to back.\nGift - Merlin’s Curse: Deprived of the Virtues by Merlin’s magic, Arthur has become a mad and powerful being \nwho has abandoned his humanity. Activating the power of \nthe Virtues awakens the king’s true soul, making him more \nhuman. Each Virtue consumed in front of Arthur will have \nthe following effect:\nLove: Lower his OL by 2.\nInnocence: Lower the number of Wounds by 3. \nFaith: He loses his immortality and, if brought to 0 \nWounds, is permanently killed. \nCourage: Acts only 1 time per Exchange. \nWisdom: He regains his wits and realizes that what he is \ndoing is wrong. Arthur’s Agenda changes to: Lead my kingdom to peace by finding a place in this new world.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Bring back my bride, Guinevere, to rule all of Europe by my side / Prepare the army for battle and make all my \nsubjects immortal warriors.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644317,"modifiedTime":1781557644317,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"aR6I02MpVk8UJXzQ","name":"Magic Greenhouse","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"MZOgb65J6imQgUN0","name":"Magic Greenhouse - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A greenhouse filled with strange plants imbued with Flora’s magical powers.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 207.","positive":"A greenhouse filled with strange plants imbued with Flora’s magical powers.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645098,"modifiedTime":1781557645098,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"6Vbtc1tmP2vxGNjk","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A greenhouse filled with strange plants imbued with Flora’s magical powers. \nGift - Wild Plants: The Greenhouse plants will identify \nanyone other than Flora as a threat. The plants rely on smell \nto detect intruders, so they can be fooled. If a person enters \nthe Greenhouse, roll 1 die:\n1-2: A carnivorous plant attempts to bite the target to inflict 1 Wound. \n3-4: A colored pollen covers the target, which takes 1 \nPenalty on all actions while in the Greenhouse. A Defense \nCheck is needed to avoid the pollen.\n5-6: A large flower emits a sharp hissing sound that stuns \nthe target and causes them to lose 1 Soma (1 Wound, in the \ncase of an NPC).</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 207."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645098,"modifiedTime":1781557645098,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-magic-greenhouse-207","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":207,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A greenhouse filled with strange plants imbued with Flora’s magical powers. \nGift - Wild Plants: The Greenhouse plants will identify \nanyone other than Flora as a threat. The plants rely on smell \nto detect intruders, so they can be fooled. If a person enters \nthe Greenhouse, roll 1 die:\n1-2: A carnivorous plant attempts to bite the target to inflict 1 Wound. \n3-4: A colored pollen covers the target, which takes 1 \nPenalty on all actions while in the Greenhouse. A Defense \nCheck is needed to avoid the pollen.\n5-6: A large flower emits a sharp hissing sound that stuns \nthe target and causes them to lose 1 Soma (1 Wound, in the \ncase of an NPC).</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645098,"modifiedTime":1781557645098,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"aaaVIu94EdM3iz5t","name":"Twrch Trwyth","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"hnq47bRD9TjpCpGq","name":"Twrch Trwyth - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a strong and fast boar, I know every corner of the island and all the secret paths.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 183.","positive":"I am a strong and fast boar, I know every corner of the island and all the secret paths.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643784,"modifiedTime":1781557643784,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5loQRqPyg9RuNQOE","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a strong and fast boar, I know every corner of the island and all the secret paths.\nAgenda: Find food without getting caught.\nGift - Magic Boar: Whenever the Twrch Trwyth avoids \nan action by someone who is hunting him, he gets 1 Escape Token. As an action, and by spending 2 Escape Tokens, the Twrch Trwyth can leave the Scene without anyone being able to stop it. Even when dead, the body of the \nTwrch Trwyth continues to give off an inviting scent and \nglow with an intense magical light. Processing the Twrch \nTrwyth’s flesh can yield 1 Delightful Flesh token. Whoever \nconsumes it will recover 1 Wound and 2 Soma.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 183."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643784,"modifiedTime":1781557643784,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-twrch-trwyth-183","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":183,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a strong and fast boar, I know every corner of the island and all the secret paths.\nAgenda: Find food without getting caught.\nGift - Magic Boar: Whenever the Twrch Trwyth avoids \nan action by someone who is hunting him, he gets 1 Escape Token. As an action, and by spending 2 Escape Tokens, the Twrch Trwyth can leave the Scene without anyone being able to stop it. Even when dead, the body of the \nTwrch Trwyth continues to give off an inviting scent and \nglow with an intense magical light. Processing the Twrch \nTrwyth’s flesh can yield 1 Delightful Flesh token. Whoever \nconsumes it will recover 1 Wound and 2 Soma.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Find food without getting caught.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643784,"modifiedTime":1781557643784,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"bDXVT7iueVIuEAqR","name":"Alice Liddell The Director","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"3Zvt7fBeVgEdcNG7","name":"Alice Liddell The Director - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the director of Wonder and, thanks to the \npower of madness, I can enter people’s minds to heal them.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177.","positive":"I am the director of Wonder and, thanks to the \npower of madness, I can enter people’s minds to heal them.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7NLiXIDelI6lJH2p","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the director of Wonder and, thanks to the \npower of madness, I can enter people’s minds to heal them.\nAgenda: Safeguard what I have built within Wonder and \nall the incredible discoveries that the magic of madness can \ngive to mankind / Solve every problem by transforming it into \na Patient to be treated.\nGift - Alice from Other Worlds: As an action, Alice \ncan attempt to possess the body of a person or animal by \nlooking into their eyes. Hunters can make a Defense Check \nto prevent this. Alice can both act through the body she \ncontrols and continue to use her Gifts and Descriptors. \nThe possession ends when Alice’s body suffers 1 Wound. \nAlice cannot control more than 3 common subjects or a \nsingle Hunter at the same time.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 177."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-alice-liddell-the-director-177","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":177,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the director of Wonder and, thanks to the \npower of madness, I can enter people’s minds to heal them.\nAgenda: Safeguard what I have built within Wonder and \nall the incredible discoveries that the magic of madness can \ngive to mankind / Solve every problem by transforming it into \na Patient to be treated.\nGift - Alice from Other Worlds: As an action, Alice \ncan attempt to possess the body of a person or animal by \nlooking into their eyes. Hunters can make a Defense Check \nto prevent this. Alice can both act through the body she \ncontrols and continue to use her Gifts and Descriptors. \nThe possession ends when Alice’s body suffers 1 Wound. \nAlice cannot control more than 3 common subjects or a \nsingle Hunter at the same time.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Safeguard what I have built within Wonder and \nall the incredible discoveries that the magic of madness can \ngive to mankind / Solve every problem by transforming it into \na Patient to be treated.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623002,"modifiedTime":1781557623002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"bDjj0aC0XxxDrLgB","name":"Nikola’ Servants","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"UBafEpp0MeFHAEhb","name":"Nikola’ Servants - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We live and work only to serve our master Nikola. We are skilled in handicrafts and in using the toy factory to eliminate any intruders.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 124.","positive":"We live and work only to serve our master Nikola. We are skilled in handicrafts and in using the toy factory to eliminate any intruders.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640649,"modifiedTime":1781557640649,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wibfPL4oZRQiddmt","name":"Gift - Enslaved to Nikola","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>While Nikola’s charm is active, \na Servant is immune to all mind control effects and cannot be manipulated by social interaction. Nikola’s charm is \nconsidered dark magic performed by a supernatural being.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 124.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640649,"modifiedTime":1781557640649,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"AiEhA1efHl4EHmhW","name":"Gift - Toymakers","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>As long as they are inside the factory, \na Servant receives the following effects.\n1. They increase their OL by 1 when acting to eliminate or \ncapture an intruder.\n2. They can move around the factory using hooks, toys \non wheels, and more without anyone being able to stop \nthem.\nNikola’s Mansion</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 124.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640649,"modifiedTime":1781557640649,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"koEOPto5Q7W7Rk3x","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We live and work only to serve our master Nikola. We are skilled in handicrafts and in using the toy factory to eliminate any intruders. \nAgenda: Produce high-quality toys and then ship them to \npoor children / Eliminate any intruder who is not a resident \nof Rovaniemi.\nGift - Enslaved to Nikola: While Nikola’s charm is active, \na Servant is immune to all mind control effects and cannot be manipulated by social interaction. Nikola’s charm is \nconsidered dark magic performed by a supernatural being. \nGift - Toymakers: As long as they are inside the factory, \na Servant receives the following effects.\n1. They increase their OL by 1 when acting to eliminate or \ncapture an intruder.\n2. They can move around the factory using hooks, toys \non wheels, and more without anyone being able to stop \nthem.\nNikola’s Mansion\nDescriptor: A small mansion, richly furnished and filled \nwith all sorts of occult heirlooms.\nInformation: The situation at the Mansion is different if \nthe Hunters arrive by day or by night.\nNight: Nikola is present and can fully use his powers. With \nhim are the 3 Helpers. \nDay: Nikola is resting in the crypt and will only wake up \nif he hears a racket at its entrance. The Helpers are present \nand active.\nA large painting in the main hall shows Nikola when he was \nstill a Wallachian nobleman. The painting is dated 1602. \nBelow the painting is a lever that, when pulled, opens the \ntrapdoor to Nikola’s crypt.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 124."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640649,"modifiedTime":1781557640649,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-nikola-servants-124","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":124,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We live and work only to serve our master Nikola. We are skilled in handicrafts and in using the toy factory to eliminate any intruders. \nAgenda: Produce high-quality toys and then ship them to \npoor children / Eliminate any intruder who is not a resident \nof Rovaniemi.\nGift - Enslaved to Nikola: While Nikola’s charm is active, \na Servant is immune to all mind control effects and cannot be manipulated by social interaction. Nikola’s charm is \nconsidered dark magic performed by a supernatural being. \nGift - Toymakers: As long as they are inside the factory, \na Servant receives the following effects.\n1. They increase their OL by 1 when acting to eliminate or \ncapture an intruder.\n2. They can move around the factory using hooks, toys \non wheels, and more without anyone being able to stop \nthem.\nNikola’s Mansion\nDescriptor: A small mansion, richly furnished and filled \nwith all sorts of occult heirlooms.\nInformation: The situation at the Mansion is different if \nthe Hunters arrive by day or by night.\nNight: Nikola is present and can fully use his powers. With \nhim are the 3 Helpers. \nDay: Nikola is resting in the crypt and will only wake up \nif he hears a racket at its entrance. The Helpers are present \nand active.\nA large painting in the main hall shows Nikola when he was \nstill a Wallachian nobleman. The painting is dated 1602. \nBelow the painting is a lever that, when pulled, opens the \ntrapdoor to Nikola’s crypt.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Produce high-quality toys and then ship them to \npoor children / Eliminate any intruder who is not a resident \nof Rovaniemi.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640649,"modifiedTime":1781557640649,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"bLThYnpmTlW7L3X1","name":"The Gallant Knight","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"FuH8CS9cY9wOKyav","name":"The Gallant Knight - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a respected and experienced knight of the \nkingdom. My skill is only matched by my honor.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 192.","positive":"I am a respected and experienced knight of the \nkingdom. My skill is only matched by my honor.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623467,"modifiedTime":1781557623467,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"JmAF4x8n8MQEqfd1","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a respected and experienced knight of the \nkingdom. My skill is only matched by my honor.\nAgenda: Respect my knightly duties and serve the young \nPrincess Tuvstarr / Save the kingdom from what’s happening.\nGift - Gallant Knight: The Knight is incredibly skilled, \nbut he would never use his full abilities against anyone \nhe doesn’t consider truly evil. When defending against \nan enemy attack, his mastery increases his OL by 1. The \nKnight will never inflict the final Wound on a target if he \ndoesn’t feel it truly deserves death.\nEnd of Scene: After finding out where Tuvstarr is, the \nHunters can proceed to the FIFTH SCENE - The Castle of \nDreams.\nFIFTH SCENE – The Castle of \nDreams\nRead aloud to the Hunters: “ Ahead, you see a castle \nbigger than any other building in the country. The roof shines \nwith gold while the tallest tower is like another sun, shining \never so bright. Looking around you, however, you notice that \neverything seems to be nothing more than a false reflection \nof reality. Farmers at work, animals in the fields, the King \nand Queen themselves you see at the gates of the castle, all do \nnothing but smile and nod. They speak in a low voice and say \ncomforting things like: “Stay here, everything is fine, the lands \nare fresh and full of life. ” You realize that they are nothing \nmore than simple, idealized creations of Tuvstarr’s memories, \nbut full of joy and warmth. ”</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 192."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623467,"modifiedTime":1781557623467,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-the-gallant-knight-192","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":192,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a respected and experienced knight of the \nkingdom. My skill is only matched by my honor.\nAgenda: Respect my knightly duties and serve the young \nPrincess Tuvstarr / Save the kingdom from what’s happening.\nGift - Gallant Knight: The Knight is incredibly skilled, \nbut he would never use his full abilities against anyone \nhe doesn’t consider truly evil. When defending against \nan enemy attack, his mastery increases his OL by 1. The \nKnight will never inflict the final Wound on a target if he \ndoesn’t feel it truly deserves death.\nEnd of Scene: After finding out where Tuvstarr is, the \nHunters can proceed to the FIFTH SCENE - The Castle of \nDreams.\nFIFTH SCENE – The Castle of \nDreams\nRead aloud to the Hunters: “ Ahead, you see a castle \nbigger than any other building in the country. The roof shines \nwith gold while the tallest tower is like another sun, shining \never so bright. Looking around you, however, you notice that \neverything seems to be nothing more than a false reflection \nof reality. Farmers at work, animals in the fields, the King \nand Queen themselves you see at the gates of the castle, all do \nnothing but smile and nod. They speak in a low voice and say \ncomforting things like: “Stay here, everything is fine, the lands \nare fresh and full of life. ” You realize that they are nothing \nmore than simple, idealized creations of Tuvstarr’s memories, \nbut full of joy and warmth. ”</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Respect my knightly duties and serve the young \nPrincess Tuvstarr / Save the kingdom from what’s happening.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623467,"modifiedTime":1781557623467,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"c9AnvTO9lRCAZx8d","name":"The Pig Heads","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"aVrzsqnEMQoCbZ90","name":"The Pig Heads - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are a band of revolutionaries in the service \nof the three brothers. The God’s flesh gives us power and fills \nus with the anger we need to wage our war.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208.","positive":"We are a band of revolutionaries in the service \nof the three brothers. The God’s flesh gives us power and fills \nus with the anger we need to wage our war.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"VgBL0WMpDG7EESmU","name":"Gift - Pigs’ Gang","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>When they act, each member of the \ngang changes to become stronger. Their head becomes \nthat of a pig and only another Pig Head will be able to \ncommunicate with them. Their mutation grants a random \npower, roll 1 die. 1. Strength, able to inflict 1 additional \nWound once per Scene; 2. Speed , once per Scene acts \n2 times consecutively; 3. Resistance , +1 Wound; \n4. Abomination , +1 to Opposition Level; 5. Grunt , \nonce per Scene can emit a loud squeal, enemies who hear it \nreceive 1 Penalty on their next action; 6. Out of control , \nthe OL rises to Hard 7 but, at the end of their action, the \nNPC explodes into a cloud of flesh and blood.\nMartha Browne the Mother</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"c3rxifHeE9XhdC1J","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are a band of revolutionaries in the service \nof the three brothers. The God’s flesh gives us power and fills \nus with the anger we need to wage our war.\nGift – Pigs’ Gang: When they act, each member of the \ngang changes to become stronger. Their head becomes \nthat of a pig and only another Pig Head will be able to \ncommunicate with them. Their mutation grants a random \npower, roll 1 die. 1. Strength, able to inflict 1 additional \nWound once per Scene; 2. Speed , once per Scene acts \n2 times consecutively; 3. Resistance , +1 Wound; \n4. Abomination , +1 to Opposition Level; 5. Grunt , \nonce per Scene can emit a loud squeal, enemies who hear it \nreceive 1 Penalty on their next action; 6. Out of control , \nthe OL rises to Hard 7 but, at the end of their action, the \nNPC explodes into a cloud of flesh and blood.\nMartha Browne the Mother</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-the-pig-heads-208","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":208,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are a band of revolutionaries in the service \nof the three brothers. The God’s flesh gives us power and fills \nus with the anger we need to wage our war.\nGift – Pigs’ Gang: When they act, each member of the \ngang changes to become stronger. Their head becomes \nthat of a pig and only another Pig Head will be able to \ncommunicate with them. Their mutation grants a random \npower, roll 1 die. 1. Strength, able to inflict 1 additional \nWound once per Scene; 2. Speed , once per Scene acts \n2 times consecutively; 3. Resistance , +1 Wound; \n4. Abomination , +1 to Opposition Level; 5. Grunt , \nonce per Scene can emit a loud squeal, enemies who hear it \nreceive 1 Penalty on their next action; 6. Out of control , \nthe OL rises to Hard 7 but, at the end of their action, the \nNPC explodes into a cloud of flesh and blood.\nMartha Browne the Mother</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"cExnTGYOM4HyjllW","name":"Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"CPUpieqhBt6JK0cH","name":"Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am one of the most prominent alchemists in \nPrague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 167.","positive":"I am one of the most prominent alchemists in \nPrague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637513,"modifiedTime":1781557637513,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QMrpL9mGKDn5Ytwq","name":"Gift - The Secrets of Metal","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Konstantin knows arcane \nwords that allow him to control metal. Any action against \nhim involving a metal weapon or bludgeoning tool receives \n1 Penalty. Starting from moderate amounts of raw materials, \nKonstantin can also forge various metal objects with \nunusual properties. The Storyteller must create a Descriptor \nthat outlines this property (for example: The alloy of this \ndagger violently repels other metals).</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 167.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637513,"modifiedTime":1781557637513,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"r2pZOPZTbuMXMIyu","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am one of the most prominent alchemists in \nPrague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me. \nAgenda: Create a Golem thanks to my alchemical studies \nand prove that no noble title or institutional position can \npossibly compare to my alchemical knowledge. \nGift – The Secrets of Metal: Konstantin knows arcane \nwords that allow him to control metal. Any action against \nhim involving a metal weapon or bludgeoning tool receives \n1 Penalty. Starting from moderate amounts of raw materials, \nKonstantin can also forge various metal objects with \nunusual properties. The Storyteller must create a Descriptor \nthat outlines this property (for example: The alloy of this \ndagger violently repels other metals). \nGift – The Secrets of Flesh: Once per Scene, when a \nmetallic body is in the vicinity of warm flesh, whether it’s still \nattached to the body or only recently removed, Konstantin \ncan utter some arcane words, forcing the two elements to \nmerge. The procedure causes 1 immediate Wound, and 1 \nadditional Wound during the painful medical procedure \nnecessary to untangle flesh and metal.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 167."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637513,"modifiedTime":1781557637513,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-konstantin-svoboda-the-alchemist-167","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":167,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am one of the most prominent alchemists in \nPrague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me. \nAgenda: Create a Golem thanks to my alchemical studies \nand prove that no noble title or institutional position can \npossibly compare to my alchemical knowledge. \nGift – The Secrets of Metal: Konstantin knows arcane \nwords that allow him to control metal. Any action against \nhim involving a metal weapon or bludgeoning tool receives \n1 Penalty. Starting from moderate amounts of raw materials, \nKonstantin can also forge various metal objects with \nunusual properties. The Storyteller must create a Descriptor \nthat outlines this property (for example: The alloy of this \ndagger violently repels other metals). \nGift – The Secrets of Flesh: Once per Scene, when a \nmetallic body is in the vicinity of warm flesh, whether it’s still \nattached to the body or only recently removed, Konstantin \ncan utter some arcane words, forcing the two elements to \nmerge. The procedure causes 1 immediate Wound, and 1 \nadditional Wound during the painful medical procedure \nnecessary to untangle flesh and metal.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Create a Golem thanks to my alchemical studies \nand prove that no noble title or institutional position can \npossibly compare to my alchemical knowledge.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637513,"modifiedTime":1781557637513,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"cdfqE4FCJrnaggRo","name":"Saxon Marauders","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"5sb4meHFne58B18H","name":"Saxon Marauders - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are fierce marauders who have come to \nAvalon to conquer the island. We are experts in group combat and support each other.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 181.","positive":"We are fierce marauders who have come to \nAvalon to conquer the island. We are experts in group combat and support each other.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643710,"modifiedTime":1781557643710,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YLXKUVPwwdDqCQQt","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are fierce marauders who have come to \nAvalon to conquer the island. We are experts in group combat and support each other. \nAgenda: Attack and capture anyone we meet along the way.\nGift - Marauders: When attacking an enemy, Marauders \nincrease their OL by 1 if they have numerical superiority.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 181."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643710,"modifiedTime":1781557643710,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-saxon-marauders-181","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":181,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are fierce marauders who have come to \nAvalon to conquer the island. We are experts in group combat and support each other. \nAgenda: Attack and capture anyone we meet along the way.\nGift - Marauders: When attacking an enemy, Marauders \nincrease their OL by 1 if they have numerical superiority.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Attack and capture anyone we meet along the way.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643710,"modifiedTime":1781557643710,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ciuWB7uIm1FQkvc2","name":"Dose The Tin Man","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"65dAz0vdOBZpWbg3","name":"Dose The Tin Man - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Leprosy has destroyed my appearance, but \nmy body is still that of the Mountain, the name by which \nI performed as a street artist in shows of strength and \nendurance. Under my heavy armor I fear nothing.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 228.","positive":"Leprosy has destroyed my appearance, but \nmy body is still that of the Mountain, the name by which \nI performed as a street artist in shows of strength and \nendurance. Under my heavy armor I fear nothing.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624325,"modifiedTime":1781557624325,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PiKiTbYxj4O4R8RI","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: Leprosy has destroyed my appearance, but \nmy body is still that of the Mountain, the name by which \nI performed as a street artist in shows of strength and \nendurance. Under my heavy armor I fear nothing.\nAgenda: I am in love with OZena, disfigured by the disease \njust like me. I am aware that she will never return my feelings \nand that is why the only thing I can do is serve her, even to \nmy death.\nGift - The Tin Man: Dose is completely covered in thick \narmor made of metal and other salvaged materials, such as \na large stove and the hull of a boat. The only unarmored spot \nis a small door in the stove that was once used to remove \nembers, which is located above his heart. It is not possible \nto hurt Dose unless one first finds a way to penetrate his \narmor or uses an attack that can clearly overcome his \ndefenses.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 228."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624325,"modifiedTime":1781557624325,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-dose-the-tin-man-228","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":228,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: Leprosy has destroyed my appearance, but \nmy body is still that of the Mountain, the name by which \nI performed as a street artist in shows of strength and \nendurance. Under my heavy armor I fear nothing.\nAgenda: I am in love with OZena, disfigured by the disease \njust like me. I am aware that she will never return my feelings \nand that is why the only thing I can do is serve her, even to \nmy death.\nGift - The Tin Man: Dose is completely covered in thick \narmor made of metal and other salvaged materials, such as \na large stove and the hull of a boat. The only unarmored spot \nis a small door in the stove that was once used to remove \nembers, which is located above his heart. It is not possible \nto hurt Dose unless one first finds a way to penetrate his \narmor or uses an attack that can clearly overcome his \ndefenses.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I am in love with OZena, disfigured by the disease \njust like me. I am aware that she will never return my feelings \nand that is why the only thing I can do is serve her, even to \nmy death.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624325,"modifiedTime":1781557624325,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dJyeQkZti2sYRcVz","name":"Tasha the Tiger","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Mo7GBOjHIeAFJnD7","name":"Tasha the Tiger - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a fast and \naggressive, though trained, tiger.\nBerto the Bear</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158.","positive":"I am a fast and \naggressive, though trained, tiger.\nBerto the Bear","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8XMWL1rYW26DOWct","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor \nNPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fast and \naggressive, though trained, tiger.\nBerto the Bear</p>","notes":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 158."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-tasha-the-tiger-158","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","adventureTitle":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":158,"role":"Scenario Actor"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Scenario Actor","notes":"<p>– Minor \nNPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fast and \naggressive, though trained, tiger.\nBerto the Bear</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637149,"modifiedTime":1781557637149,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dWmQnibLJPNGYWcd","name":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"mUKDq1nGLmWOce71","name":"Didier the Grumpy Old Man - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He \nknew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who \neven married a foreigner!</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","positive":"I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He \nknew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who \neven married a foreigner!","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"thKKZBRcBgLqLchP","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He \nknew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who \neven married a foreigner!</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-didier-the-grumpy-old-man-123","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":123,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He \nknew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who \neven married a foreigner!</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"daI8hCrdh9u3oA5l","name":"Intricate Maze","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"yWu2UinzpGPlxDx0","name":"Intricate Maze - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The great forest of Camelot is a tangle of vegetation perpetually shrouded in mist.\nIn case of Failure, the Storyteller decides which Zone the \nHunters will land in.\nThe Magic Glade\nDescriptor: A small clearing within a circle formed by ancient oaks. Inside, one can clearly feel the magic hovering in \nthe air, tickling the skin.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 192.","positive":"The great forest of Camelot is a tangle of vegetation perpetually shrouded in mist.\nIn case of Failure, the Storyteller decides which Zone the \nHunters will land in.\nThe Magic Glade\nDescriptor: A small clearing within a circle formed by ancient oaks. Inside, one can clearly feel the magic hovering in \nthe air, tickling the skin.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644146,"modifiedTime":1781557644146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Bjeuj31vunonWAGV","name":"Gift - Place of Peace and Magic","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The Magic Glade is \na place of peace and serenity. Those who rest in it for a few \nminutes recover 1 Soma. The same subject cannot benefit from this effect more than once per Scene. Invoking an \nInterlude within the Magic Glade does not generate an advancement in Merlin’s Agenda. \nThe Green Garden</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 192.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644146,"modifiedTime":1781557644146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ezPGlZD3gPUJUplC","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: The great forest of Camelot is a tangle of vegetation perpetually shrouded in mist.\nIn case of Failure, the Storyteller decides which Zone the \nHunters will land in.\nThe Magic Glade\nDescriptor: A small clearing within a circle formed by ancient oaks. Inside, one can clearly feel the magic hovering in \nthe air, tickling the skin.\nGift - Place of Peace and Magic: The Magic Glade is \na place of peace and serenity. Those who rest in it for a few \nminutes recover 1 Soma. The same subject cannot benefit from this effect more than once per Scene. Invoking an \nInterlude within the Magic Glade does not generate an advancement in Merlin’s Agenda. \nThe Green Garden\nDescriptor: A lush field of flowers, in the center of which \nstands a small stone altar engraved with pagan symbols. \nInformation: As soon as a subject enters the flowery \nfield, a figure covered in ancient armor and foliage stands \nthreateningly. The Green Knight will never leave the flower \nfield, remaining to defend the altar. The only way to avoid \nthe wrath of the Green Knight is to show respect to the ancient gods. By eliminating the Green Knight, the Hunters \ncan get their hands on the Treasure of the Order, the Ax of \nRetribution (page 192). \nThe Green Knight</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 192."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644146,"modifiedTime":1781557644146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-intricate-maze-192","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":192,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: The great forest of Camelot is a tangle of vegetation perpetually shrouded in mist.\nIn case of Failure, the Storyteller decides which Zone the \nHunters will land in.\nThe Magic Glade\nDescriptor: A small clearing within a circle formed by ancient oaks. Inside, one can clearly feel the magic hovering in \nthe air, tickling the skin.\nGift - Place of Peace and Magic: The Magic Glade is \na place of peace and serenity. Those who rest in it for a few \nminutes recover 1 Soma. The same subject cannot benefit from this effect more than once per Scene. Invoking an \nInterlude within the Magic Glade does not generate an advancement in Merlin’s Agenda. \nThe Green Garden\nDescriptor: A lush field of flowers, in the center of which \nstands a small stone altar engraved with pagan symbols. \nInformation: As soon as a subject enters the flowery \nfield, a figure covered in ancient armor and foliage stands \nthreateningly. The Green Knight will never leave the flower \nfield, remaining to defend the altar. The only way to avoid \nthe wrath of the Green Knight is to show respect to the ancient gods. By eliminating the Green Knight, the Hunters \ncan get their hands on the Treasure of the Order, the Ax of \nRetribution (page 192). \nThe Green Knight</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644146,"modifiedTime":1781557644146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dkxYuUu36dRYwqUF","name":"Director of the Theater","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"KPmiwJFNSdXaLFEW","name":"Director of the Theater - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the young and ambitious assistant of \nGabriel Černý. Our differences were known.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 171.","positive":"I am the young and ambitious assistant of \nGabriel Černý. Our differences were known.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637827,"modifiedTime":1781557637827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fFoCmcc81sMthtDo","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young and ambitious assistant of \nGabriel Černý. Our differences were known. \nAgenda: Make sure I am not blamed for the murder / \nMake sure it doesn’t turn out that I facilitated the murder. \nThe Circus of the Azure Sun\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Just outside the walls of \nPrague, a battered blue and white tent stands in a muddy \nfield. Some smaller tents are surrounded by wooden wagons, \nwhile a secondary tent connected to the larger one acts as \na shelter from the weather for animals. There is a strange \nsilence, as if the field had been abandoned, except for a \nsubdued metallic sound coming from the animal tent.\nDescriptor: A dilapidated tent in the middle of a muddy \nfield. Wooden carriages and abandoned animal cages.\nThe camp is not actually abandoned, and at several hours \nof the day it’s possible to see a young boy hanging around \nthe tents (Černobog). Konstantin spends every free \nmoment in the animal tent, where he is assembling the \nPrince, while the main tent is mostly empty, except for the \npresence of a huge nest made up of brushes and mud built \na few meters from the ground, and accessible only through \nthe stairs or the ropes of the acrobats. \nInformation: Entering the Circus of the Azure Sun \nwithout being seen by Černobog is difficult but, once \ninside, Hunters can access some or all of the following \ninformation:\n ◆ There is a large basin containing human remains, \nstill wearing some uniforms of the Circus of the \nAzure Sun. These are the artists who did not leave the \ncircus after the acquisition of Černobog, now simple \nspare parts for the Prince. It will be possible to find a \nhacksaw nearby. \n ◆ On a desk you can find an invitation to the dance at \nPrague Castle, under the name Konstantin Svoboda. \nOn another sheet there seems to be a rudimentary \nmap of the city, with a path traced (the one Konstantin \nplans to use to get the Prince to the Castle). \n ◆ The nest, suspended in the center of the tent, is made \nup of mud and branches and is extremely similar to \nthat of a swallow. It’s big enough to accommodate a \nhuman being. This is where Alexandr rests when he’s \nnot out murdering someone. \n ◆ Approaching the circus at night, the Hunters will be \nable to see strange lights coming from the animal tent: \nKonstantin is in fact finalizing the preparations before \nactivating the Prince.\nRefer to the Events section of the Scenario to better manage \nthe situation. \n^</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 171."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637827,"modifiedTime":1781557637827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-director-of-the-theater-171","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":171,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young and ambitious assistant of \nGabriel Černý. Our differences were known. \nAgenda: Make sure I am not blamed for the murder / \nMake sure it doesn’t turn out that I facilitated the murder. \nThe Circus of the Azure Sun\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Just outside the walls of \nPrague, a battered blue and white tent stands in a muddy \nfield. Some smaller tents are surrounded by wooden wagons, \nwhile a secondary tent connected to the larger one acts as \na shelter from the weather for animals. There is a strange \nsilence, as if the field had been abandoned, except for a \nsubdued metallic sound coming from the animal tent.\nDescriptor: A dilapidated tent in the middle of a muddy \nfield. Wooden carriages and abandoned animal cages.\nThe camp is not actually abandoned, and at several hours \nof the day it’s possible to see a young boy hanging around \nthe tents (Černobog). Konstantin spends every free \nmoment in the animal tent, where he is assembling the \nPrince, while the main tent is mostly empty, except for the \npresence of a huge nest made up of brushes and mud built \na few meters from the ground, and accessible only through \nthe stairs or the ropes of the acrobats. \nInformation: Entering the Circus of the Azure Sun \nwithout being seen by Černobog is difficult but, once \ninside, Hunters can access some or all of the following \ninformation:\n ◆ There is a large basin containing human remains, \nstill wearing some uniforms of the Circus of the \nAzure Sun. These are the artists who did not leave the \ncircus after the acquisition of Černobog, now simple \nspare parts for the Prince. It will be possible to find a \nhacksaw nearby. \n ◆ On a desk you can find an invitation to the dance at \nPrague Castle, under the name Konstantin Svoboda. \nOn another sheet there seems to be a rudimentary \nmap of the city, with a path traced (the one Konstantin \nplans to use to get the Prince to the Castle). \n ◆ The nest, suspended in the center of the tent, is made \nup of mud and branches and is extremely similar to \nthat of a swallow. It’s big enough to accommodate a \nhuman being. This is where Alexandr rests when he’s \nnot out murdering someone. \n ◆ Approaching the circus at night, the Hunters will be \nable to see strange lights coming from the animal tent: \nKonstantin is in fact finalizing the preparations before \nactivating the Prince.\nRefer to the Events section of the Scenario to better manage \nthe situation. \n^</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Make sure I am not blamed for the murder / \nMake sure it doesn’t turn out that I facilitated the murder. \nThe Circus of the Azure Sun\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Just outside the walls of \nPrague, a battered blue and white tent stands in a muddy \nfield. Some smaller tents are surrounded by wooden wagons, \nwhile a secondary tent connected to the larger one acts as \na shelter from the weather for animals. There is a strange \nsilence, as if the field had been abandoned, except for a \nsubdued metallic sound coming from the animal tent.\nDescriptor: A dilapidated tent in the middle of a muddy \nfield. Wooden carriages and abandoned animal cages.\nThe camp is not actually abandoned, and at several hours \nof the day it’s possible to see a young boy hanging around \nthe tents (Černobog). Konstantin spends every free \nmoment in the animal tent, where he is assembling the \nPrince, while the main tent is mostly empty, except for the \npresence of a huge nest made up of brushes and mud built \na few meters from the ground, and accessible only through \nthe stairs or the ropes of the acrobats.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637827,"modifiedTime":1781557637827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"dodxEP8aviLbmldH","name":"The Food of the Gods","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"ElOXsSj7ahBcS3Oz","name":"The Food of the Gods - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a \npowerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","positive":"All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a \npowerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LFDklJZfp4EYWMYZ","name":"Gift - The Drug of the True Self","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Whoever eats food \ntreated with this powerful drug loses all inhibition. Anyone \nwho fails the Defense Check to resist the effect receives 2 \nDrug Tokens. During a Scene, the Storyteller can spend 1 \nDrug Token to activate one of the following effects. 1. The \nTrue Self: Immediately activates the Hunter’s Dark Ego \nwithout them suffering the Wound generated by not using \nthe Activator. 2. Dulled Senses: The Storyteller decides \nwhat type of Outcome the Hunter is aiming for after they \nhave declared an action. \nBella’s Handmaids</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OQV6s2UCVhZpLWiV","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a \npowerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.\nGift – The Drug of the True Self: Whoever eats food \ntreated with this powerful drug loses all inhibition. Anyone \nwho fails the Defense Check to resist the effect receives 2 \nDrug Tokens. During a Scene, the Storyteller can spend 1 \nDrug Token to activate one of the following effects. 1. The \nTrue Self: Immediately activates the Hunter’s Dark Ego \nwithout them suffering the Wound generated by not using \nthe Activator. 2. Dulled Senses: The Storyteller decides \nwhat type of Outcome the Hunter is aiming for after they \nhave declared an action. \nBella’s Handmaids</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-the-food-of-the-gods-128","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":128,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a \npowerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.\nGift – The Drug of the True Self: Whoever eats food \ntreated with this powerful drug loses all inhibition. Anyone \nwho fails the Defense Check to resist the effect receives 2 \nDrug Tokens. During a Scene, the Storyteller can spend 1 \nDrug Token to activate one of the following effects. 1. The \nTrue Self: Immediately activates the Hunter’s Dark Ego \nwithout them suffering the Wound generated by not using \nthe Activator. 2. Dulled Senses: The Storyteller decides \nwhat type of Outcome the Hunter is aiming for after they \nhave declared an action. \nBella’s Handmaids</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"eJM3c2QiRAH3qMxU","name":"Fairies (Tuvstarr's Reflection)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"pekLzU4Lq5L7rb93","name":"Fairies - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are Fairies, spirits of nature \nwho move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 189.","positive":"We are Fairies, spirits of nature \nwho move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"j3jPkSZ68E1p1hXf","name":"Gift - Madness","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Made mad by the light of the crown, the \nFairies rage at anyone who tries to touch it. Two or more \nFairies can attack together to make a single action with a \nbonus to the OL equal to the number of fairies involved. If \nthe action succeeds, in addition to inflicting 1 Wound, the \ntarget will be thrown into the swamp to be drowned. Once \nin the water, the target can attempt to break out of the flurry \nof drowned, dead hands pulling from the bottom with a</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 189.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"u2p5ijay1h8QI0E2","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are Fairies, spirits of nature \nwho move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans.\nAgenda: Defend the crown that Tuvstarr has given us and \ndance forever wrapped in its sweet light. \nGift – Madness: Made mad by the light of the crown, the \nFairies rage at anyone who tries to touch it. Two or more \nFairies can attack together to make a single action with a \nbonus to the OL equal to the number of fairies involved. If \nthe action succeeds, in addition to inflicting 1 Wound, the \ntarget will be thrown into the swamp to be drowned. Once \nin the water, the target can attempt to break out of the flurry \nof drowned, dead hands pulling from the bottom with a</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 189."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-fairies-189","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":189,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are Fairies, spirits of nature \nwho move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans.\nAgenda: Defend the crown that Tuvstarr has given us and \ndance forever wrapped in its sweet light. \nGift – Madness: Made mad by the light of the crown, the \nFairies rage at anyone who tries to touch it. Two or more \nFairies can attack together to make a single action with a \nbonus to the OL equal to the number of fairies involved. If \nthe action succeeds, in addition to inflicting 1 Wound, the \ntarget will be thrown into the swamp to be drowned. Once \nin the water, the target can attempt to break out of the flurry \nof drowned, dead hands pulling from the bottom with a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Defend the crown that Tuvstarr has given us and \ndance forever wrapped in its sweet light.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"eqQimfuVXQ5rhHbM","name":"The dregs of society, always ready to serve the King of Crime","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"2VYMCtPQKIBsIMno","name":"The dregs of society, always ready to serve the King of Crime - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a lowlife who lives off theft and extortion. \nI draw strength from my fellow gang members and am not \nstupid enough to go at it alone.</p>","notes":"Nemesis - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 90.","positive":"I am a lowlife who lives off theft and extortion. \nI draw strength from my fellow gang members and am not \nstupid enough to go at it alone.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639210,"modifiedTime":1781557639210,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7AZo9IInYRYUCLOV","name":"Gift - Band","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Those who possess this Gift increase their \nOpposition Level by 1 when acting against a target with the \nsupport of one or more companions.\nSicario\nRuthless assassin in the pay of the King of Crime.</p>","notes":"Nemesis - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 90.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639210,"modifiedTime":1781557639210,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sdRSoIBRCOGcLou5","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a lowlife who lives off theft and extortion. \nI draw strength from my fellow gang members and am not \nstupid enough to go at it alone. \nAgenda: Carry out the boss’s orders without asking too \nmany questions. \nGift - Band: Those who possess this Gift increase their \nOpposition Level by 1 when acting against a target with the \nsupport of one or more companions.\nSicario\nRuthless assassin in the pay of the King of Crime.</p>","notes":"Nemesis - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 90."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639210,"modifiedTime":1781557639210,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nemesis-the-dregs-of-society-always-ready-to-serve-the-king-of-crime-90","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nemesis","adventureTitle":"Nemesis","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":90,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nemesis","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a lowlife who lives off theft and extortion. \nI draw strength from my fellow gang members and am not \nstupid enough to go at it alone. \nAgenda: Carry out the boss’s orders without asking too \nmany questions. \nGift - Band: Those who possess this Gift increase their \nOpposition Level by 1 when acting against a target with the \nsupport of one or more companions.\nSicario\nRuthless assassin in the pay of the King of Crime.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Carry out the boss’s orders without asking too \nmany questions.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639210,"modifiedTime":1781557639210,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"f68iqkEfz2pFZdQj","name":"Basil the Survivor","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"IdorBfLfppY6vCXN","name":"Basil the Survivor - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a coward only concerned with making \nends meet.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 86.","positive":"I am a coward only concerned with making \nends meet.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625729,"modifiedTime":1781557625729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"AgBweE1XwW4xxm6a","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a coward only concerned with making \nends meet. \nAgenda: To get back on my feet and escape from London, \naway from rebels and magic.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 86."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625729,"modifiedTime":1781557625729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-basil-the-survivor-86","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":86,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a coward only concerned with making \nends meet. \nAgenda: To get back on my feet and escape from London, \naway from rebels and magic.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To get back on my feet and escape from London, \naway from rebels and magic.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625729,"modifiedTime":1781557625729,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"fAeubWQlsAkoppa2","name":"Gwendolyn","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"7ojmkbYhxPLdB5t2","name":"Gwendolyn - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the young heir of \nthe Carnarvon family, but I dream \nof a life of travel and freedom, \nexploring the world. I am good at \ntelling stories, and that is how I \ngot closer to Pietrik.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88.","positive":"I am the young heir of \nthe Carnarvon family, but I dream \nof a life of travel and freedom, \nexploring the world. I am good at \ntelling stories, and that is how I \ngot closer to Pietrik.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"h8ARL1pXNi4FsWmm","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young heir of \nthe Carnarvon family, but I dream \nof a life of travel and freedom, \nexploring the world. I am good at \ntelling stories, and that is how I \ngot closer to Pietrik.\nAgenda: To convince Pietrik \nto desist from his revenge. \nI understand how much \npain his heart holds and \nI would like to welcome \nhim into my family to \ngive him a different \nfuture.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 88."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-gwendolyn-88","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":88,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young heir of \nthe Carnarvon family, but I dream \nof a life of travel and freedom, \nexploring the world. I am good at \ntelling stories, and that is how I \ngot closer to Pietrik.\nAgenda: To convince Pietrik \nto desist from his revenge. \nI understand how much \npain his heart holds and \nI would like to welcome \nhim into my family to \ngive him a different \nfuture.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To convince Pietrik \nto desist from his revenge. \nI understand how much \npain his heart holds and \nI would like to welcome \nhim into my family to \ngive him a different \nfuture.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625775,"modifiedTime":1781557625775,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"fu7okVnWjuVMr9nJ","name":"Ruthless assassin in the pay of the King of Crime","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"wAI3vYczpMhHUpN0","name":"Ruthless assassin in the pay of the King of Crime - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a capable killer and always act in cold \nblood.</p>","notes":"Nemesis - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 90.","positive":"I am a capable killer and always act in cold \nblood.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639226,"modifiedTime":1781557639226,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ZPZEqkRgPF98Dtsh","name":"Gift - Assassin","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Those who possess this Gift increase \ntheir Opposition Level by 1 when acting from the shadows \nor in low light. When the NPC makes an attack that catches \nthe target by surprise, they inflict 1 Additional Wound. \nThe Raven Clan \nInspired by the Seven Ravens [Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was a family in which only sons \nwere born. The father and mother longed for a daughter \nand prayed for a long time to receive this grace. When the \nbaby girl finally arrived, the family’s enthusiasm quickly faded. The newborn was extremely weak and the doctor made \nit clear that she would not be saved without a miracle. The \nfather then sent the seven sons in search of a powerful witch \nwho lived not far from the village. When they arrived at the \nwitch’s house, the seven brothers were given a jar of magic \nwater that could give strength and vitality. The seven began \nto argue over who should carry the jar, as they all wanted to \nreceive compliments from their father. In the struggle, the jar \nfell to the ground and shattered into a thousand pieces, scattering the precious water. When they returned home, there \nwas nothing to do for their little sister. The father, in despair, \ncursed his children for fighting over the jar like greedy ravens \nover a piece of meat. The witch heard the man’s grief and, \nas punishment, turned the seven brothers into seven ravens, \nforever condemned to a life as watchers, never to be shown \naffection again.</p>","notes":"Nemesis - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 90.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639226,"modifiedTime":1781557639226,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XVExalT5M8drKa5j","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a capable killer and always act in cold \nblood. \nAgenda: Eliminate the Boss’ designated targets by striking \nfrom the shadows. \nGift - Assassin: Those who possess this Gift increase \ntheir Opposition Level by 1 when acting from the shadows \nor in low light. When the NPC makes an attack that catches \nthe target by surprise, they inflict 1 Additional Wound. \nThe Raven Clan \nInspired by the Seven Ravens [Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was a family in which only sons \nwere born. The father and mother longed for a daughter \nand prayed for a long time to receive this grace. When the \nbaby girl finally arrived, the family’s enthusiasm quickly faded. The newborn was extremely weak and the doctor made \nit clear that she would not be saved without a miracle. The \nfather then sent the seven sons in search of a powerful witch \nwho lived not far from the village. When they arrived at the \nwitch’s house, the seven brothers were given a jar of magic \nwater that could give strength and vitality. The seven began \nto argue over who should carry the jar, as they all wanted to \nreceive compliments from their father. In the struggle, the jar \nfell to the ground and shattered into a thousand pieces, scattering the precious water. When they returned home, there \nwas nothing to do for their little sister. The father, in despair, \ncursed his children for fighting over the jar like greedy ravens \nover a piece of meat. The witch heard the man’s grief and, \nas punishment, turned the seven brothers into seven ravens, \nforever condemned to a life as watchers, never to be shown \naffection again.</p>","notes":"Nemesis - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 90."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639226,"modifiedTime":1781557639226,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nemesis-ruthless-assassin-in-the-pay-of-the-king-of-crime-90","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nemesis","adventureTitle":"Nemesis","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":90,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nemesis","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a capable killer and always act in cold \nblood. \nAgenda: Eliminate the Boss’ designated targets by striking \nfrom the shadows. \nGift - Assassin: Those who possess this Gift increase \ntheir Opposition Level by 1 when acting from the shadows \nor in low light. When the NPC makes an attack that catches \nthe target by surprise, they inflict 1 Additional Wound. \nThe Raven Clan \nInspired by the Seven Ravens [Opponent)\nOnce upon a time, there was a family in which only sons \nwere born. The father and mother longed for a daughter \nand prayed for a long time to receive this grace. When the \nbaby girl finally arrived, the family’s enthusiasm quickly faded. The newborn was extremely weak and the doctor made \nit clear that she would not be saved without a miracle. The \nfather then sent the seven sons in search of a powerful witch \nwho lived not far from the village. When they arrived at the \nwitch’s house, the seven brothers were given a jar of magic \nwater that could give strength and vitality. The seven began \nto argue over who should carry the jar, as they all wanted to \nreceive compliments from their father. In the struggle, the jar \nfell to the ground and shattered into a thousand pieces, scattering the precious water. When they returned home, there \nwas nothing to do for their little sister. The father, in despair, \ncursed his children for fighting over the jar like greedy ravens \nover a piece of meat. The witch heard the man’s grief and, \nas punishment, turned the seven brothers into seven ravens, \nforever condemned to a life as watchers, never to be shown \naffection again.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Eliminate the Boss’ designated targets by striking \nfrom the shadows.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639226,"modifiedTime":1781557639226,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"fvrwTpXt6aGB6xS8","name":"Hatta Carter The Mad Inventor","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"TzNNksOac1josXoX","name":"Hatta Carter The Mad Inventor - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my \ntime. My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings \nand aggressiveness.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 176.","positive":"I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my \ntime. My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings \nand aggressiveness.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3sj6hqg4kujXkmyY","name":"Gift - Time Clocks","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Hatta can manipulate one of his clocks \nto influence time. 1. Slow: Once per Scene, Hatta increases \nhis OL by 2 when defending against a threat. 2. Speed \nUp: Once per Scene, Hatta and one of his Automata can \nact, immediately stopping anyone’s action regardless of the \nsituation in the narrative. If an Automaton has already acted, \nit can act again thanks to this Gift.\nRabbit Automaton</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 176.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"nB93Ofr1VtsysnX8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my \ntime. My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings \nand aggressiveness.\nAgenda: I want the company of witty people and not cold \nautomata. I long for the chats I had with Alice.\nGift - Time Clocks: Hatta can manipulate one of his clocks \nto influence time. 1. Slow: Once per Scene, Hatta increases \nhis OL by 2 when defending against a threat. 2. Speed \nUp: Once per Scene, Hatta and one of his Automata can \nact, immediately stopping anyone’s action regardless of the \nsituation in the narrative. If an Automaton has already acted, \nit can act again thanks to this Gift.\nRabbit Automaton</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 176."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-hatta-carter-the-mad-inventor-176","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":176,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my \ntime. My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings \nand aggressiveness.\nAgenda: I want the company of witty people and not cold \nautomata. I long for the chats I had with Alice.\nGift - Time Clocks: Hatta can manipulate one of his clocks \nto influence time. 1. Slow: Once per Scene, Hatta increases \nhis OL by 2 when defending against a threat. 2. Speed \nUp: Once per Scene, Hatta and one of his Automata can \nact, immediately stopping anyone’s action regardless of the \nsituation in the narrative. If an Automaton has already acted, \nit can act again thanks to this Gift.\nRabbit Automaton</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I want the company of witty people and not cold \nautomata. I long for the chats I had with Alice.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622970,"modifiedTime":1781557622970,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gFlKWo0MgxAqPZKa","name":"The Mother’s Heart","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"zts69yqPEZHqPgwU","name":"The Mother’s Heart - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>An agglomeration of floating garbage, pulsating like a rotting heart.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 108.","positive":"An agglomeration of floating garbage, pulsating like a rotting heart.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640070,"modifiedTime":1781557640070,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OW2WLUmIkCP1xuyG","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: An agglomeration of floating garbage, pulsating like a rotting heart. \nGift - A Mother’s Fury: As soon as the Heart suffers \n1 Wound, Blanca will appear to defend it. The call of the \nHeart cannot be prevented in any way.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 108."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640070,"modifiedTime":1781557640070,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-the-mother-s-heart-108","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":108,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: An agglomeration of floating garbage, pulsating like a rotting heart. \nGift - A Mother’s Fury: As soon as the Heart suffers \n1 Wound, Blanca will appear to defend it. The call of the \nHeart cannot be prevented in any way.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640070,"modifiedTime":1781557640070,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gTiJbKeBtxQ1SPdG","name":"Anne the Little Chatterer","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"4f1ahFaT0GS7Y9gP","name":"Anne the Little Chatterer - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her \ninformed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy \nbecause I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.\n2 Nicholas the Huntsman</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","positive":"Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her \ninformed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy \nbecause I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.\n2 Nicholas the Huntsman","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jtrSmWgkHjQ2vTUH","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her \ninformed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy \nbecause I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.\n2 Nicholas the Huntsman</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-anne-the-little-chatterer-123","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":123,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her \ninformed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy \nbecause I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.\n2 Nicholas the Huntsman</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gVk9uPyi546y0Nou","name":"Monsters Summoned by Aladdin","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"pEEkr1K8iq6diev6","name":"Monsters Summoned by Aladdin - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are mindless monsters, using claws and \ntentacles to snatch prey.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 160.","positive":"We are mindless monsters, using claws and \ntentacles to snatch prey.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642505,"modifiedTime":1781557642505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"67ZFHVVEd641HxYh","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC \n(2 Wounds - 4 Monsters)\nDescriptor: We are mindless monsters, using claws and \ntentacles to snatch prey.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 160."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642505,"modifiedTime":1781557642505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-monsters-summoned-by-aladdin-160","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":160,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC \n(2 Wounds - 4 Monsters)\nDescriptor: We are mindless monsters, using claws and \ntentacles to snatch prey.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642505,"modifiedTime":1781557642505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gZhFNSOgQvktKjb8","name":"Beáta Czernin the Noblewoman","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"FHi9LSBsYap1JvTC","name":"Beáta Czernin the Noblewoman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage \nof it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly \ncause annoyances.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 166.","positive":"I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage \nof it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly \ncause annoyances.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dkPxp1besOCsGRLY","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage \nof it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly \ncause annoyances. \nAgenda: Distancing myself from my late lover Danek in the \neyes of my husband and family / Finding out which monster \nmay have murdered him in this way.\nThe Alchemical \nLaboratory\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You reach the workshop \nfrom a small staircase on one side of Haštalská, the street \nin Prague that runs alongside the Church of St. Castulus. A \nstone corridor leads you to what looks like the entrance to \na cell, protected by a wooden door reinforced by large iron \nbars. Konstantin pulls out a large key that he hangs on his \nneck and makes his way inside the laboratory, where the \nsoft light of lanterns hanging on the wall illuminates a cold \nspace similar to a tomb. Built of red brick and furnished with \nwooden tables and benches, the workshop houses hundreds \nof stills, bottles, and parchments abandoned on dusty shelves. \nDried plants and other esoteric trinkets hang from the ceiling. \nIn the center of the room is a forge, which Konstantin uses \nto process minerals of various kinds, while in the corner an \nelegant wooden desk is covered with paperwork, inks, and \npens for writing. What strikes you most is the almost total \ndevastation of a wing of the laboratory, now a pile of rubble, \nglass, and split wooden boards. On the ground, a dry puddle \nof god-knows-what emits a nauseating stench. Konstantin</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 166."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-be-ta-czernin-the-noblewoman-166","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":166,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage \nof it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly \ncause annoyances. \nAgenda: Distancing myself from my late lover Danek in the \neyes of my husband and family / Finding out which monster \nmay have murdered him in this way.\nThe Alchemical \nLaboratory\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You reach the workshop \nfrom a small staircase on one side of Haštalská, the street \nin Prague that runs alongside the Church of St. Castulus. A \nstone corridor leads you to what looks like the entrance to \na cell, protected by a wooden door reinforced by large iron \nbars. Konstantin pulls out a large key that he hangs on his \nneck and makes his way inside the laboratory, where the \nsoft light of lanterns hanging on the wall illuminates a cold \nspace similar to a tomb. Built of red brick and furnished with \nwooden tables and benches, the workshop houses hundreds \nof stills, bottles, and parchments abandoned on dusty shelves. \nDried plants and other esoteric trinkets hang from the ceiling. \nIn the center of the room is a forge, which Konstantin uses \nto process minerals of various kinds, while in the corner an \nelegant wooden desk is covered with paperwork, inks, and \npens for writing. What strikes you most is the almost total \ndevastation of a wing of the laboratory, now a pile of rubble, \nglass, and split wooden boards. On the ground, a dry puddle \nof god-knows-what emits a nauseating stench. Konstantin</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Distancing myself from my late lover Danek in the \neyes of my husband and family / Finding out which monster \nmay have murdered him in this way.\nThe Alchemical \nLaboratory\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You reach the workshop \nfrom a small staircase on one side of Haštalská, the street \nin Prague that runs alongside the Church of St. Castulus. A \nstone corridor leads you to what looks like the entrance to \na cell, protected by a wooden door reinforced by large iron \nbars. Konstantin pulls out a large key that he hangs on his \nneck and makes his way inside the laboratory, where the \nsoft light of lanterns hanging on the wall illuminates a cold \nspace similar to a tomb. Built of red brick and furnished with \nwooden tables and benches, the workshop houses hundreds \nof stills, bottles, and parchments abandoned on dusty shelves. \nDried plants and other esoteric trinkets hang from the ceiling. \nIn the center of the room is a forge, which Konstantin uses \nto process minerals of various kinds, while in the corner an \nelegant wooden desk is covered with paperwork, inks, and \npens for writing. What strikes you most is the almost total \ndevastation of a wing of the laboratory, now a pile of rubble, \nglass, and split wooden boards. On the ground, a dry puddle \nof god-knows-what emits a nauseating stench. Konstantin","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637466,"modifiedTime":1781557637466,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gbesf2SWWOaBwIpe","name":"Porcelain Dolls","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"az6aghVLYpbrzS3q","name":"Porcelain Dolls - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the devoted guards of the Porcelain \nPrincess. Everyone fears us for our martial ability.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 235.","positive":"We are the devoted guards of the Porcelain \nPrincess. Everyone fears us for our martial ability.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"AE0rYOzRp7LtxlGq","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the devoted guards of the Porcelain \nPrincess. Everyone fears us for our martial ability. \nAgenda: Fulfill every wish of the Porcelain Princess.\nGift - Armed Guard: Each Doll is armed differently. \nRoll 1 die: 1. Spear, the Doll can make exceptional jumps \nand can always keep an enemy at a distance; 2. Double \nknife, 2 attacks per Exchange; 3. Great Blade, once per \nScene inflicts 1 additional Wound; 4. Whip, 9 feet range, \nwhoever fails the Defense Check becomes entangled; 5. \nBlood, the blade of the weapon is soaked in Helga’s blood; \n6. Shield, +1 OL to defend themselves or an ally.\nEnd of Scene: By defeating the Porcelain Princess or \npersuading her away from Helga’s service, the Hunters will \nobtain the key to enter Helga’s palace. When questioned, \nthe Princess will reveal that her lady intends to perform \nan arcane rite during the night that involves sacrificing \nDorothea. Go to SCENE FOUR - The Red Witch of the \nSouth.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 235."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-porcelain-dolls-235","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":235,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the devoted guards of the Porcelain \nPrincess. Everyone fears us for our martial ability. \nAgenda: Fulfill every wish of the Porcelain Princess.\nGift - Armed Guard: Each Doll is armed differently. \nRoll 1 die: 1. Spear, the Doll can make exceptional jumps \nand can always keep an enemy at a distance; 2. Double \nknife, 2 attacks per Exchange; 3. Great Blade, once per \nScene inflicts 1 additional Wound; 4. Whip, 9 feet range, \nwhoever fails the Defense Check becomes entangled; 5. \nBlood, the blade of the weapon is soaked in Helga’s blood; \n6. Shield, +1 OL to defend themselves or an ally.\nEnd of Scene: By defeating the Porcelain Princess or \npersuading her away from Helga’s service, the Hunters will \nobtain the key to enter Helga’s palace. When questioned, \nthe Princess will reveal that her lady intends to perform \nan arcane rite during the night that involves sacrificing \nDorothea. Go to SCENE FOUR - The Red Witch of the \nSouth.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Fulfill every wish of the Porcelain Princess.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gkCmYVYxpNbuxYqo","name":"Yvonne the Spirit who Longs for Revenge","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"CQIJiqS2jtk9oDpH","name":"Yvonne the Spirit who Longs for Revenge - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a restless spirit who can manipulate fire.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 150.","positive":"I am a restless spirit who can manipulate fire.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622287,"modifiedTime":1781557622287,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qC67M1d9hfsArVkx","name":"Gift - Spirit","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Yvonne is in a spirit form and can only \ntruly be damaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs \nlife energy and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection \nand barriers cannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit \nis harmed by non-magical means, she still will suffer a \nWound. However, when Yvonne has no Wounds left, she \ndisappears and rematerializes immediately. In doing so, all \nher Wounds are healed, except those inflicted by magical \nmeans. Once per Scene, Yvonne can call 3 Restless Spirits \nto her who will obey her will.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 150.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622287,"modifiedTime":1781557622287,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ZowmQCxK90RWUESG","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a restless spirit who can manipulate fire.\nAgenda: Get revenge on Adrien and all those who ignored \nmy death / Set Paris ablaze with the fires of the dead.\nGift - Spirit: Yvonne is in a spirit form and can only \ntruly be damaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs \nlife energy and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection \nand barriers cannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit \nis harmed by non-magical means, she still will suffer a \nWound. However, when Yvonne has no Wounds left, she \ndisappears and rematerializes immediately. In doing so, all \nher Wounds are healed, except those inflicted by magical \nmeans. Once per Scene, Yvonne can call 3 Restless Spirits \nto her who will obey her will.\nGift - Soul of Fire: Yvonne can manipulate fire at will. \nThis Gift only affects a fire that is already lit. Manipulating \nfire, for Yvonne, is considered an additional action. The fire \ninflicts 1 Wound and if the Defense Check is an Outcome \nwith a Cost, the target will continue to burn. During the \nfollowing Exchange, if not put out, the fire will inflict \n1 additional Wound. Thanks to her power, Yvonne can \nmultiply the width and size of a flame by up to ten times.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 150."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622287,"modifiedTime":1781557622287,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-yvonne-the-spirit-who-longs-for-revenge-150","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":150,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a restless spirit who can manipulate fire.\nAgenda: Get revenge on Adrien and all those who ignored \nmy death / Set Paris ablaze with the fires of the dead.\nGift - Spirit: Yvonne is in a spirit form and can only \ntruly be damaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs \nlife energy and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection \nand barriers cannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit \nis harmed by non-magical means, she still will suffer a \nWound. However, when Yvonne has no Wounds left, she \ndisappears and rematerializes immediately. In doing so, all \nher Wounds are healed, except those inflicted by magical \nmeans. Once per Scene, Yvonne can call 3 Restless Spirits \nto her who will obey her will.\nGift - Soul of Fire: Yvonne can manipulate fire at will. \nThis Gift only affects a fire that is already lit. Manipulating \nfire, for Yvonne, is considered an additional action. The fire \ninflicts 1 Wound and if the Defense Check is an Outcome \nwith a Cost, the target will continue to burn. During the \nfollowing Exchange, if not put out, the fire will inflict \n1 additional Wound. Thanks to her power, Yvonne can \nmultiply the width and size of a flame by up to ten times.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Get revenge on Adrien and all those who ignored \nmy death / Set Paris ablaze with the fires of the dead.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622287,"modifiedTime":1781557622287,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gpLvPYdmihnTEIYA","name":"Nikola Lupei","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"6wvizxqQPqc3nds2","name":"Nikola Lupei - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a powerful vampire with a \ngood heart, and I just want to live in peace \nand quiet. The power I draw from blood \nmakes my body strong and fast.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 125.","positive":"I am a powerful vampire with a \ngood heart, and I just want to live in peace \nand quiet. The power I draw from blood \nmakes my body strong and fast.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640759,"modifiedTime":1781557640759,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"kkeopnENB2o7E7Xv","name":"Gift - Power of the Vampire","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The curse that plagues Nikola’s \nblood gives him great powers, but \nalso some weaknesses.\nPowers: Each can be used by Nikola once per Scene.\n1: Recover 1 Wound.\n2: Turn into mist.\n3: Enslave a subject with his gaze. Perform a Defense \nCheck against Nikola’s OL to resist. An enslaved subject \nshares what they see and hear with Nikola and will do \nwhatever the vampire commands. Nikola does not have to \nbe present to command the slave, but the subject must be \nawake and alert. Enslavement ends when the subject suffers 1 Wound.\nWeaknesses: Nikola cannot enter a place he has never been unless first invited by the person who lives there. \nWhen exposed to sunlight, Nikola loses 1 Wound per \nminute. Nikola can only be permanently eliminated if the \nlast of his Wounds is inflicted by a magical or consecrated \nweapon.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 125.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640759,"modifiedTime":1781557640759,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OzonhyHocNXSXxHW","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful vampire with a \ngood heart, and I just want to live in peace \nand quiet. The power I draw from blood \nmakes my body strong and fast. \nAgenda: Find a way to get rid of the \nBadalisk without harming the people \nof Rovaniemi / Keep my secret and my \nlife in Rovaniemi. \nGift - Power of the Vampire: \nThe curse that plagues Nikola’s \nblood gives him great powers, but \nalso some weaknesses.\nPowers: Each can be used by Nikola once per Scene.\n1: Recover 1 Wound.\n2: Turn into mist.\n3: Enslave a subject with his gaze. Perform a Defense \nCheck against Nikola’s OL to resist. An enslaved subject \nshares what they see and hear with Nikola and will do \nwhatever the vampire commands. Nikola does not have to \nbe present to command the slave, but the subject must be \nawake and alert. Enslavement ends when the subject suffers 1 Wound.\nWeaknesses: Nikola cannot enter a place he has never been unless first invited by the person who lives there. \nWhen exposed to sunlight, Nikola loses 1 Wound per \nminute. Nikola can only be permanently eliminated if the \nlast of his Wounds is inflicted by a magical or consecrated \nweapon.\nGift - Occult Scholar: Nikola knows many rituals and \npossesses arcane objects to cast spells. He used these pow-</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 125."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640759,"modifiedTime":1781557640759,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-nikola-lupei-125","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":125,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful vampire with a \ngood heart, and I just want to live in peace \nand quiet. The power I draw from blood \nmakes my body strong and fast. \nAgenda: Find a way to get rid of the \nBadalisk without harming the people \nof Rovaniemi / Keep my secret and my \nlife in Rovaniemi. \nGift - Power of the Vampire: \nThe curse that plagues Nikola’s \nblood gives him great powers, but \nalso some weaknesses.\nPowers: Each can be used by Nikola once per Scene.\n1: Recover 1 Wound.\n2: Turn into mist.\n3: Enslave a subject with his gaze. Perform a Defense \nCheck against Nikola’s OL to resist. An enslaved subject \nshares what they see and hear with Nikola and will do \nwhatever the vampire commands. Nikola does not have to \nbe present to command the slave, but the subject must be \nawake and alert. Enslavement ends when the subject suffers 1 Wound.\nWeaknesses: Nikola cannot enter a place he has never been unless first invited by the person who lives there. \nWhen exposed to sunlight, Nikola loses 1 Wound per \nminute. Nikola can only be permanently eliminated if the \nlast of his Wounds is inflicted by a magical or consecrated \nweapon.\nGift - Occult Scholar: Nikola knows many rituals and \npossesses arcane objects to cast spells. He used these pow-</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Find a way to get rid of the \nBadalisk without harming the people \nof Rovaniemi / Keep my secret and my \nlife in Rovaniemi.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640759,"modifiedTime":1781557640759,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"h5wu3BJRfPbh0zVW","name":"Sir Dagonet the Madman","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ru6jTOJk3M0RP167","name":"Sir Dagonet the Madman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a crazy, violent knight and I will not hesitate to use my sword to get what I want. No one can afford \nto ignore me.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 184.","positive":"I am a crazy, violent knight and I will not hesitate to use my sword to get what I want. No one can afford \nto ignore me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643831,"modifiedTime":1781557643831,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"kfOhwor5pr6KKFac","name":"Gift - Don’t Underestimate the Buffoon","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Dagonet is \na true master of foul play. During a battle, Dagonet can attempt a low blow in addition to his action and choose one \nof the following effects:\n1. Blade in the Boot: Dagonet draws it after attacking a \ntarget and inflicts 1 Additional Wound. Only a Hunter with \na dueling ability Descriptor can make a Defense Check to \navoid it.\n2. Sand in the Eyes: Activated before a Dagonet attack, \nthe target cannot use any of their Gifts during the Exchange.\n3. Find a Shield: When Dagonet is attacked, he can avoid \n1 Wound by having another closeby target hit instead. \nDagonet cannot use the same effect on the same target \nmore than once during the Scenario.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 184.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643831,"modifiedTime":1781557643831,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"SECmS9TqwAHdxuoU","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a crazy, violent knight and I will not hesitate to use my sword to get what I want. No one can afford \nto ignore me. \nAgenda: Eliminate any possible threat to my king / Find \nGuinevere, but instead of leading her back to Arthur, I plan \nto kill her and pass off her death as a tragic accident. \nGift - Don’t Underestimate the Buffoon: Dagonet is \na true master of foul play. During a battle, Dagonet can attempt a low blow in addition to his action and choose one \nof the following effects:\n1. Blade in the Boot: Dagonet draws it after attacking a \ntarget and inflicts 1 Additional Wound. Only a Hunter with \na dueling ability Descriptor can make a Defense Check to \navoid it.\n2. Sand in the Eyes: Activated before a Dagonet attack, \nthe target cannot use any of their Gifts during the Exchange.\n3. Find a Shield: When Dagonet is attacked, he can avoid \n1 Wound by having another closeby target hit instead. \nDagonet cannot use the same effect on the same target \nmore than once during the Scenario.\nInformation: Dagonet is a lunatic and will never reveal \nwhat he knows, even if he is defeated or tortured. However, \nbeing a true madman, it is possible to make him talk by \nprovoking him during combat. Dagonet is on a mission for \nArthur to find Guinevere, who has escaped from the castle. \nThe king has a soft spot for his queen and will not start the \nwar until she returns to his side. Dagonet also knows the \nwhereabouts of Percival, whom he now considers useless \nto the cause. He has even tried to kill him, but one way or \nanother, the knight always comes back to life (Zone 12 - \nCliff, page 197).\nThe Red Knight</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 184."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643831,"modifiedTime":1781557643831,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-sir-dagonet-the-madman-184","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":184,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a crazy, violent knight and I will not hesitate to use my sword to get what I want. No one can afford \nto ignore me. \nAgenda: Eliminate any possible threat to my king / Find \nGuinevere, but instead of leading her back to Arthur, I plan \nto kill her and pass off her death as a tragic accident. \nGift - Don’t Underestimate the Buffoon: Dagonet is \na true master of foul play. During a battle, Dagonet can attempt a low blow in addition to his action and choose one \nof the following effects:\n1. Blade in the Boot: Dagonet draws it after attacking a \ntarget and inflicts 1 Additional Wound. Only a Hunter with \na dueling ability Descriptor can make a Defense Check to \navoid it.\n2. Sand in the Eyes: Activated before a Dagonet attack, \nthe target cannot use any of their Gifts during the Exchange.\n3. Find a Shield: When Dagonet is attacked, he can avoid \n1 Wound by having another closeby target hit instead. \nDagonet cannot use the same effect on the same target \nmore than once during the Scenario.\nInformation: Dagonet is a lunatic and will never reveal \nwhat he knows, even if he is defeated or tortured. However, \nbeing a true madman, it is possible to make him talk by \nprovoking him during combat. Dagonet is on a mission for \nArthur to find Guinevere, who has escaped from the castle. \nThe king has a soft spot for his queen and will not start the \nwar until she returns to his side. Dagonet also knows the \nwhereabouts of Percival, whom he now considers useless \nto the cause. He has even tried to kill him, but one way or \nanother, the knight always comes back to life (Zone 12 - \nCliff, page 197).\nThe Red Knight</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Eliminate any possible threat to my king / Find \nGuinevere, but instead of leading her back to Arthur, I plan \nto kill her and pass off her death as a tragic accident.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643831,"modifiedTime":1781557643831,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hBH7lEuepKz6wOED","name":"A group of faithful Paladins in the service of Saint George","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"PKIobwdbKfdkEUjQ","name":"A group of faithful Paladins in the service of Saint George - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a Paladin in the service of the great Saint \nGeorge himself and his word, for me, is law. Years of training \nhave made me adept at fighting the Broken Tales.\nNote: Each Paladin has a different Downside, indicated in \nthe Paladin Gift.</p>","notes":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 221.","positive":"I am a Paladin in the service of the great Saint \nGeorge himself and his word, for me, is law. Years of training \nhave made me adept at fighting the Broken Tales.\nNote: Each Paladin has a different Downside, indicated in \nthe Paladin Gift.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624146,"modifiedTime":1781557624146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sevzcYmdfB3ir7os","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a Paladin in the service of the great Saint \nGeorge himself and his word, for me, is law. Years of training \nhave made me adept at fighting the Broken Tales.\nNote: Each Paladin has a different Downside, indicated in \nthe Paladin Gift.\nGift - Paladins: Each Paladin has a name and a dedicated \nGift, and a Downside to add to the standard Descriptor. \nThe Storyteller rolls 1 die to decide which Paladin follows \nSaint George in the Witch Hunt. Saint Geoge has a number \nof Paladins equal to that of the Hunters he hunts.</p>","notes":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 221."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624146,"modifiedTime":1781557624146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-a-group-of-faithful-paladins-in-the-service-of-saint-george-221","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","adventureTitle":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":221,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a Paladin in the service of the great Saint \nGeorge himself and his word, for me, is law. Years of training \nhave made me adept at fighting the Broken Tales.\nNote: Each Paladin has a different Downside, indicated in \nthe Paladin Gift.\nGift - Paladins: Each Paladin has a name and a dedicated \nGift, and a Downside to add to the standard Descriptor. \nThe Storyteller rolls 1 die to decide which Paladin follows \nSaint George in the Witch Hunt. Saint Geoge has a number \nof Paladins equal to that of the Hunters he hunts.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624146,"modifiedTime":1781557624146,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hT2hmZ0MV65immv8","name":"Edward the Miners’ Chief","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"hhEYCousw6i8WNm2","name":"Edward the Miners’ Chief - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn \nhis death. Everyone in the mine does what I say, and I hate \nforeigners who want to poke their nose into my work. I allow \nFrank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died.\nThe Cave of the \nGod Under the \nMine\nDescriptor: A large natural cave, which Arthur has made \ninto a home. You can enter only by descending from a narrow \nwell. In the north wall, the enormous pig head of the God \ngasps and groans as it waits to wake up.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 211.","positive":"I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn \nhis death. Everyone in the mine does what I say, and I hate \nforeigners who want to poke their nose into my work. I allow \nFrank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died.\nThe Cave of the \nGod Under the \nMine\nDescriptor: A large natural cave, which Arthur has made \ninto a home. You can enter only by descending from a narrow \nwell. In the north wall, the enormous pig head of the God \ngasps and groans as it waits to wake up.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623910,"modifiedTime":1781557623910,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"eGpq0c5BJSNVEPIR","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn \nhis death. Everyone in the mine does what I say, and I hate \nforeigners who want to poke their nose into my work. I allow \nFrank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died.\nThe Cave of the \nGod Under the \nMine\nDescriptor: A large natural cave, which Arthur has made \ninto a home. You can enter only by descending from a narrow \nwell. In the north wall, the enormous pig head of the God \ngasps and groans as it waits to wake up.\nGift - Arthur’s House: The mastermind behind the Pig \nHeads worked hard to make the Cave an intruder-proof \nhaven. If someone drops from the well, Arthur will be \nalerted (a Position Check can avoid this). At the bottom of \nthe well is a large tub that Arthur can fill with boiling water. \nWhoever arrives through the well suffers 1 Wound if they \nhave no way of avoiding the hot water. Inside the room, \nArthur can turn the lights on and off thanks to a system \nhe has invented, throwing the chamber into either light or \ndarkness. While intruders wander blindly, Arthur can use \nhis knowledge of the place to move freely.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 211."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623910,"modifiedTime":1781557623910,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-edward-the-miners-chief-211","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":211,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn \nhis death. Everyone in the mine does what I say, and I hate \nforeigners who want to poke their nose into my work. I allow \nFrank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died.\nThe Cave of the \nGod Under the \nMine\nDescriptor: A large natural cave, which Arthur has made \ninto a home. You can enter only by descending from a narrow \nwell. In the north wall, the enormous pig head of the God \ngasps and groans as it waits to wake up.\nGift - Arthur’s House: The mastermind behind the Pig \nHeads worked hard to make the Cave an intruder-proof \nhaven. If someone drops from the well, Arthur will be \nalerted (a Position Check can avoid this). At the bottom of \nthe well is a large tub that Arthur can fill with boiling water. \nWhoever arrives through the well suffers 1 Wound if they \nhave no way of avoiding the hot water. Inside the room, \nArthur can turn the lights on and off thanks to a system \nhe has invented, throwing the chamber into either light or \ndarkness. While intruders wander blindly, Arthur can use \nhis knowledge of the place to move freely.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623910,"modifiedTime":1781557623910,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hacLdQzJ1rB6IRER","name":"Emma the Childhood Friend","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"bTdFuNDgMNqK4RpA","name":"Emma the Childhood Friend - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a childhood friend of Clarence and have \na special relationship with him. He has always promised that \nhe will take me away from this place, but I know that he will \nnever abandon his brothers. I understand that he has a big \nsecret, but tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark.\nThe Orchard\nDescriptor: A large apple orchard which, before the arrival \nof the factories, was one of the main sources of work in the \ncity. Now, however, it is abandoned and represents a home for \nall those who cannot get a job.\nWhen the Hunters roam the orchard, roll 1 die, or present \nthe encounters in sequence.\n1-2 The orchard: The trees have been neglected and on \nthe ground there are still abandoned tools and baskets for \nharvesting apples. A sign next to a tool shed reads “Gift \ncourtesy of the Browne family” .\n3-4 Clarence’s shack: A rickety rundown house with a \nthatched roof. Inside, it is possible to find a rusty key that \nsays “slaughterhouse” and a sketched map of the mines that \nsays “well” . Around the hut there are always 1d6 + 2 Pig \nHeads.\n5-6 Clarence: The youngest of the Browne brothers is \nlying on the ground, visibly drunk, under an apple tree. \nClarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take \nthem off guard.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208.","positive":"I am a childhood friend of Clarence and have \na special relationship with him. He has always promised that \nhe will take me away from this place, but I know that he will \nnever abandon his brothers. I understand that he has a big \nsecret, but tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark.\nThe Orchard\nDescriptor: A large apple orchard which, before the arrival \nof the factories, was one of the main sources of work in the \ncity. Now, however, it is abandoned and represents a home for \nall those who cannot get a job.\nWhen the Hunters roam the orchard, roll 1 die, or present \nthe encounters in sequence.\n1-2 The orchard: The trees have been neglected and on \nthe ground there are still abandoned tools and baskets for \nharvesting apples. A sign next to a tool shed reads “Gift \ncourtesy of the Browne family” .\n3-4 Clarence’s shack: A rickety rundown house with a \nthatched roof. Inside, it is possible to find a rusty key that \nsays “slaughterhouse” and a sketched map of the mines that \nsays “well” . Around the hut there are always 1d6 + 2 Pig \nHeads.\n5-6 Clarence: The youngest of the Browne brothers is \nlying on the ground, visibly drunk, under an apple tree. \nClarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take \nthem off guard.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QHqCroREZSXamXRg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a childhood friend of Clarence and have \na special relationship with him. He has always promised that \nhe will take me away from this place, but I know that he will \nnever abandon his brothers. I understand that he has a big \nsecret, but tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark.\nThe Orchard\nDescriptor: A large apple orchard which, before the arrival \nof the factories, was one of the main sources of work in the \ncity. Now, however, it is abandoned and represents a home for \nall those who cannot get a job.\nWhen the Hunters roam the orchard, roll 1 die, or present \nthe encounters in sequence.\n1-2 The orchard: The trees have been neglected and on \nthe ground there are still abandoned tools and baskets for \nharvesting apples. A sign next to a tool shed reads “Gift \ncourtesy of the Browne family” .\n3-4 Clarence’s shack: A rickety rundown house with a \nthatched roof. Inside, it is possible to find a rusty key that \nsays “slaughterhouse” and a sketched map of the mines that \nsays “well” . Around the hut there are always 1d6 + 2 Pig \nHeads.\n5-6 Clarence: The youngest of the Browne brothers is \nlying on the ground, visibly drunk, under an apple tree. \nClarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take \nthem off guard.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-emma-the-childhood-friend-208","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":208,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a childhood friend of Clarence and have \na special relationship with him. He has always promised that \nhe will take me away from this place, but I know that he will \nnever abandon his brothers. I understand that he has a big \nsecret, but tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark.\nThe Orchard\nDescriptor: A large apple orchard which, before the arrival \nof the factories, was one of the main sources of work in the \ncity. Now, however, it is abandoned and represents a home for \nall those who cannot get a job.\nWhen the Hunters roam the orchard, roll 1 die, or present \nthe encounters in sequence.\n1-2 The orchard: The trees have been neglected and on \nthe ground there are still abandoned tools and baskets for \nharvesting apples. A sign next to a tool shed reads “Gift \ncourtesy of the Browne family” .\n3-4 Clarence’s shack: A rickety rundown house with a \nthatched roof. Inside, it is possible to find a rusty key that \nsays “slaughterhouse” and a sketched map of the mines that \nsays “well” . Around the hut there are always 1d6 + 2 Pig \nHeads.\n5-6 Clarence: The youngest of the Browne brothers is \nlying on the ground, visibly drunk, under an apple tree. \nClarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take \nthem off guard.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hngJhB848FoERbHT","name":"Satu","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"kD9rsTUGhWqpepba","name":"Satu - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a former dancer who has lost everything. \nI am but a shadow of my former self.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","positive":"I am a former dancer who has lost everything. \nI am but a shadow of my former self.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622625,"modifiedTime":1781557622625,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1o0Y4WyArRt6Rp4K","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a former dancer who has lost everything. \nI am but a shadow of my former self.\nAgenda: Defend my son Erik, the only reason that I keep \ngoing.\nErik</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622625,"modifiedTime":1781557622625,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-satu-162","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":162,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a former dancer who has lost everything. \nI am but a shadow of my former self.\nAgenda: Defend my son Erik, the only reason that I keep \ngoing.\nErik</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Defend my son Erik, the only reason that I keep \ngoing.\nErik","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622625,"modifiedTime":1781557622625,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hpwNpiYcdbzVqyln","name":"Gréte","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"VIla8J2Kh6M6fjaF","name":"Gréte - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the incarnation of \nthe power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my \nspeed are unbelievable.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 96.","positive":"I am the incarnation of \nthe power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my \nspeed are unbelievable.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626262,"modifiedTime":1781557626262,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OQcPYZe7Ufp4D1aq","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the incarnation of \nthe power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my \nspeed are unbelievable. \nAgenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future \nfor the Maw’s offspring. Unlike my brother Hanse, I still have \na shred of humanity and I wouldn’t want to devour anyone \nindiscriminately / I want to convince my friend Ina to become \na Maw.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their \noriginal appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as \na common child. When they unleash their power, the body \nshifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 96."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626262,"modifiedTime":1781557626262,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-gr-te-96","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":96,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC \n(4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the incarnation of \nthe power of the great Maw. My body \nregenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my \nspeed are unbelievable. \nAgenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future \nfor the Maw’s offspring. Unlike my brother Hanse, I still have \na shred of humanity and I wouldn’t want to devour anyone \nindiscriminately / I want to convince my friend Ina to become \na Maw.\nGift – Mutant Maw: As long as they maintain their \noriginal appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as \na common child. When they unleash their power, the body \nshifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future \nfor the Maw’s offspring. Unlike my brother Hanse, I still have \na shred of humanity and I wouldn’t want to devour anyone \nindiscriminately / I want to convince my friend Ina to become \na Maw.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626262,"modified