{"_id":"i2RmsiiX8qAFnhL8","name":"Bardolf’s personal guard","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Ls9YOxcjMj7umEiq","name":"Bardolf’s personal guard - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are long-time mercenaries, paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 206.","positive":"We are long-time mercenaries, paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623800,"modifiedTime":1781557623800,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WzgcOraH21iscXIe","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are long-time mercenaries, paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 206."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623800,"modifiedTime":1781557623800,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-bardolf-s-personal-guard-206","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":206,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are long-time mercenaries, paid handsomely by Bardolf for our loyalty.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623800,"modifiedTime":1781557623800,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"i2ex3sEid5jautBg","name":"Restless Knights","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"U5c0xyL2kSmyyQOr","name":"Restless Knights - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the souls of restless knights, resurrected \nat the behest of our king. Our decaying bodies advance ceaselessly, waiting to march to war.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 183.","positive":"We are the souls of restless knights, resurrected \nat the behest of our king. Our decaying bodies advance ceaselessly, waiting to march to war.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643784,"modifiedTime":1781557643784,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"aZyVW0yJPhrCH9s4","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the souls of restless knights, resurrected \nat the behest of our king. Our decaying bodies advance ceaselessly, waiting to march to war. \nAgenda: Kill all humans we come across to strengthen the \nranks of our king’s army. \nInformation: When encountered, the Storyteller rolls \n2d6 to determine the number of Restless Knights. Their \nhorde attacks all living creatures, making no distinction between Hunters and NPCs. If the horde is not destroyed, it \nmoves one Zone by attacking those it encounters. The Storyteller secretly decides which Zone the horde has moved \nto and does not make the Encounter roll when the Hunters arrive there. Any other damage done by the Peaceless \nKnights is at the discretion of the Storyteller.\nTwrch Trwyth</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 183."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643784,"modifiedTime":1781557643784,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-restless-knights-183","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":183,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the souls of restless knights, resurrected \nat the behest of our king. Our decaying bodies advance ceaselessly, waiting to march to war. \nAgenda: Kill all humans we come across to strengthen the \nranks of our king’s army. \nInformation: When encountered, the Storyteller rolls \n2d6 to determine the number of Restless Knights. Their \nhorde attacks all living creatures, making no distinction between Hunters and NPCs. If the horde is not destroyed, it \nmoves one Zone by attacking those it encounters. The Storyteller secretly decides which Zone the horde has moved \nto and does not make the Encounter roll when the Hunters arrive there. Any other damage done by the Peaceless \nKnights is at the discretion of the Storyteller.\nTwrch Trwyth</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Kill all humans we come across to strengthen the \nranks of our king’s army.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643784,"modifiedTime":1781557643784,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"j5U4JjSkqRDnG7Qe","name":"Martha Browne the Mother","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"TGp40gz8iBrHXV2o","name":"Martha Browne the Mother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the mother of three brothers, and I am \nso old that I have almost completely lost my sight. My son \nFrank takes care of me, but he doesn’t tell me anything. I \nam convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a \nmother tells me so.\nEmma the Childhood Friend</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208.","positive":"I am the mother of three brothers, and I am \nso old that I have almost completely lost my sight. My son \nFrank takes care of me, but he doesn’t tell me anything. I \nam convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a \nmother tells me so.\nEmma the Childhood Friend","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mAaW8JTzaPhNJgxI","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the mother of three brothers, and I am \nso old that I have almost completely lost my sight. My son \nFrank takes care of me, but he doesn’t tell me anything. I \nam convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a \nmother tells me so.\nEmma the Childhood Friend</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 208."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-martha-browne-the-mother-208","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":208,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the mother of three brothers, and I am \nso old that I have almost completely lost my sight. My son \nFrank takes care of me, but he doesn’t tell me anything. I \nam convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a \nmother tells me so.\nEmma the Childhood Friend</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623848,"modifiedTime":1781557623848,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"jT42NkONmpCcDEUN","name":"Tommi and Jutta","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"81qSurHAyVNskm0m","name":"Tommi and Jutta - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two young prospectors, made tough by \na life of hardship and strong by the love that unites us.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 118.","positive":"We are two young prospectors, made tough by \na life of hardship and strong by the love that unites us.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640506,"modifiedTime":1781557640506,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"uDgf8TfmXzsiNVvA","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPCs (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two young prospectors, made tough by \na life of hardship and strong by the love that unites us.\nAgenda: To save our son Lari from that absurd pledge.\nThe Village of Rovaniemi\nDescriptor: A small town of prospectors where everyone \nknows everyone else.\nInformation: The streets and the small square are littered \nwith gold panning equipment, carts, and baskets for sorting. The numerous wrought-iron plaques remind everyone \nthat these are all donations from Nikola Lupei. The villagers \nare shy towards the Hunters, avoiding any contact. \nRovaniemi Town Hall\nDescriptor: One of the few brick houses in the village. The \nimposing wrought iron door has a large plaque engraved with \nwords of gratitude for the town’s benefactor, Nikola Lupei.\nWhenever the Hunters visit the Town Hall, they will find 2 \nVillage Elders. The Storyteller can decide which ones they \nare, or roll a die to determine. The following information \ncan be obtained from all elders:\n ◆ A week ago, a Hunter from the Order arrived, asked \na few questions, then left for Nikola’s estate and was \nnever seen again. \n ◆ Nikola rarely comes to the Village now and seems to be \nvery busy. The villagers never go to him spontaneously, \nbut wait for him to show up.\nIt is possible to meet all the elders, but it takes time: for \nevery hour the Hunters spend in the Village, they can meet \none elder. \nThe Village Elders \n1: Asmo</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 118."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640522,"modifiedTime":1781557640522,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-tommi-and-jutta-118","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":118,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPCs (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two young prospectors, made tough by \na life of hardship and strong by the love that unites us.\nAgenda: To save our son Lari from that absurd pledge.\nThe Village of Rovaniemi\nDescriptor: A small town of prospectors where everyone \nknows everyone else.\nInformation: The streets and the small square are littered \nwith gold panning equipment, carts, and baskets for sorting. The numerous wrought-iron plaques remind everyone \nthat these are all donations from Nikola Lupei. The villagers \nare shy towards the Hunters, avoiding any contact. \nRovaniemi Town Hall\nDescriptor: One of the few brick houses in the village. The \nimposing wrought iron door has a large plaque engraved with \nwords of gratitude for the town’s benefactor, Nikola Lupei.\nWhenever the Hunters visit the Town Hall, they will find 2 \nVillage Elders. The Storyteller can decide which ones they \nare, or roll a die to determine. The following information \ncan be obtained from all elders:\n ◆ A week ago, a Hunter from the Order arrived, asked \na few questions, then left for Nikola’s estate and was \nnever seen again. \n ◆ Nikola rarely comes to the Village now and seems to be \nvery busy. The villagers never go to him spontaneously, \nbut wait for him to show up.\nIt is possible to meet all the elders, but it takes time: for \nevery hour the Hunters spend in the Village, they can meet \none elder. \nThe Village Elders \n1: Asmo</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To save our son Lari from that absurd pledge.\nThe Village of Rovaniemi\nDescriptor: A small town of prospectors where everyone \nknows everyone else.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640522,"modifiedTime":1781557640522,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"jtZTDUpXa8swDWBI","name":"Francesca Cantalupo","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"wXKAutPMQt3g6ENk","name":"Francesca Cantalupo - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128.","positive":"I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"U5EySmYTUS4HVjtr","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.\nAgenda: Flee the island to return to my father / Avenge \nLetizia’s death and punish Bellina for always being a selfish, \njealous child.\nThe Sanctuary\nDescriptor: An ancient monastery converted into a small \npleasure town. \nInformation: 20 Handmaids and 10 Servants are \nalways present in the Sanctuary. All the inhabitants of the \nSanctuary live surrounded by food and pleasures of the \nflesh, in a state of constant and perverse ecstasy. Bella adds \ndrugs to both food and drinks so that the inhabitants of the \nSanctuary lose their inhibitions.\nThreat – The Food of the Gods</p>","notes":"The House of Roses - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 128."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-the-house-of-roses-francesca-cantalupo-128","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","adventureTitle":"The House of Roses","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":128,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The House of Roses","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.\nAgenda: Flee the island to return to my father / Avenge \nLetizia’s death and punish Bellina for always being a selfish, \njealous child.\nThe Sanctuary\nDescriptor: An ancient monastery converted into a small \npleasure town. \nInformation: 20 Handmaids and 10 Servants are \nalways present in the Sanctuary. All the inhabitants of the \nSanctuary live surrounded by food and pleasures of the \nflesh, in a state of constant and perverse ecstasy. Bella adds \ndrugs to both food and drinks so that the inhabitants of the \nSanctuary lose their inhibitions.\nThreat – The Food of the Gods</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Flee the island to return to my father / Avenge \nLetizia’s death and punish Bellina for always being a selfish, \njealous child.\nThe Sanctuary\nDescriptor: An ancient monastery converted into a small \npleasure town.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557632091,"modifiedTime":1781557632091,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"jx3IEo5q5hDiyR6v","name":"The Quiet Guards","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Gch41TwU0rKT3sjz","name":"The Quiet Guards - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused \nwith some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations \nhave driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of \nTalia.</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138.","positive":"We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused \nwith some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations \nhave driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of \nTalia.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TQ8GE8X6XZ6rmTTO","name":"Gift - Quiet Guards","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A Quiet Guard no longer possesses \na mind and acts as an object under the control of Talia. That \nis why they cannot be mentally manipulated or frightened \nin any way. Each Quiet Guard is a human body fused with a \npart of the castle. Roll a die or choose a mutation.\n1. Tools: The Guard’s arms are an agglomeration of tools, \nsuch as shears and hammers. When attacking, the Guard is</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5L0LXdcl2xkaDdXE","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused \nwith some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations \nhave driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of \nTalia.\nGift – Quiet Guards: A Quiet Guard no longer possesses \na mind and acts as an object under the control of Talia. That \nis why they cannot be mentally manipulated or frightened \nin any way. Each Quiet Guard is a human body fused with a \npart of the castle. Roll a die or choose a mutation.\n1. Tools: The Guard’s arms are an agglomeration of tools, \nsuch as shears and hammers. When attacking, the Guard is</p>","notes":"Stegeborg's Quiet - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 138."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-stegeborgs-quiet-the-quiet-guards-138","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","adventureTitle":"Stegeborg's Quiet","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":138,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Stegeborg's Quiet","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused \nwith some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations \nhave driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of \nTalia.\nGift – Quiet Guards: A Quiet Guard no longer possesses \na mind and acts as an object under the control of Talia. That \nis why they cannot be mentally manipulated or frightened \nin any way. Each Quiet Guard is a human body fused with a \npart of the castle. Roll a die or choose a mutation.\n1. Tools: The Guard’s arms are an agglomeration of tools, \nsuch as shears and hammers. When attacking, the Guard is</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557636197,"modifiedTime":1781557636197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"kM2hGmHJnUN5LENC","name":"Reinsdyr the Guide","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"quMTsNTmirpo5oyf","name":"Reinsdyr the Guide - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a very experienced guide and know all \nthe secrets of survival in the north. I can take down any enemy with ax and pistol without making too much of a fuss.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 215.","positive":"I am a very experienced guide and know all \nthe secrets of survival in the north. I can take down any enemy with ax and pistol without making too much of a fuss.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645510,"modifiedTime":1781557645510,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QBS02HiO70soZWkx","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a very experienced guide and know all \nthe secrets of survival in the north. I can take down any enemy with ax and pistol without making too much of a fuss. \nAgenda: Escort wealthy Frozen Madness victims to Pernille’s \nhouse and share the proceeds of the robberies with Rikke.\nGift – Die Hard: Reinsdyr is resilient and a difficult opponent even for Hunters. The guide can act twice during \nan Exchange, using his ax to hit an enemy in melee combat \nand his gun to hit a target at a distance. When he suffers \n1 Wound, Reinsdyr can immediately make an additional \nattack against the one who wounded him.\nEnd of Scene: With or without Reinsdyr, the Hunters \nmust go to Pernille’s house, go to SCENE THREE - The \nJourney.\n2b</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 215."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645510,"modifiedTime":1781557645510,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-reinsdyr-the-guide-215","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":215,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a very experienced guide and know all \nthe secrets of survival in the north. I can take down any enemy with ax and pistol without making too much of a fuss. \nAgenda: Escort wealthy Frozen Madness victims to Pernille’s \nhouse and share the proceeds of the robberies with Rikke.\nGift – Die Hard: Reinsdyr is resilient and a difficult opponent even for Hunters. The guide can act twice during \nan Exchange, using his ax to hit an enemy in melee combat \nand his gun to hit a target at a distance. When he suffers \n1 Wound, Reinsdyr can immediately make an additional \nattack against the one who wounded him.\nEnd of Scene: With or without Reinsdyr, the Hunters \nmust go to Pernille’s house, go to SCENE THREE - The \nJourney.\n2b</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Escort wealthy Frozen Madness victims to Pernille’s \nhouse and share the proceeds of the robberies with Rikke.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645510,"modifiedTime":1781557645510,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"kRU4D9NcqLqeHvQw","name":"Berend the Crazed Captain","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"GWRKVEgFAcvei4Lv","name":"Berend the Crazed Captain - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the captain of the previous expedition \nand the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by \nmasking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 98.","positive":"I am the captain of the previous expedition \nand the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by \nmasking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"eSvDH8Y6SEV8Rpa7","name":"Gift - Stinking Survivor","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Berend managed to avoid \nbeing devoured by the Maws, but what he saw happen \nto his companions scarred his mind forever. The man \nconstantly covers himself with rotten fish because he has \ndiscovered the stench conceals him from the Maws. \nBerend will never be targeted by a Maw unless he \ntakes direct action against them. As long as he \nis at the port of Vík í Mýrdal, Berend can move \nwith great skill through the alleys and take \nany companions anywhere in the city without \nattracting the attention of the Maws. Each \ntime he uses this ability, he rolls 1 die: on 5 \nor 6, Berend convinces himself that he has \nseen other survivors and makes noise in an \nattempt to get their attention. It will be \nclear to those that accompany him that \nthe whole situation is nothing \nmore than a figment \nof the poor man’s \ndistressed mind.\nVík í Mýrdal’s Lighthouse</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 98.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"88W9OnIhVgHmj4XK","name":"Gift - Safe Haven from the Maws","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The stacks of rotten \nfish that Berend and Althea constantly throw at the foot of \nthe lighthouse keep the Maws away. The Maws lose all trace \nof someone who takes refuge in the lighthouse. While near \nthe lighthouse, Maws reduce their Opposition Level by 1.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 98.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"e4NNxQ9WEguSBwfj","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the captain of the previous expedition \nand the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by \nmasking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.\nAgenda: Wait for someone to come from the mainland to \nsave me.\nGift – Stinking Survivor: Berend managed to avoid \nbeing devoured by the Maws, but what he saw happen \nto his companions scarred his mind forever. The man \nconstantly covers himself with rotten fish because he has \ndiscovered the stench conceals him from the Maws. \nBerend will never be targeted by a Maw unless he \ntakes direct action against them. As long as he \nis at the port of Vík í Mýrdal, Berend can move \nwith great skill through the alleys and take \nany companions anywhere in the city without \nattracting the attention of the Maws. Each \ntime he uses this ability, he rolls 1 die: on 5 \nor 6, Berend convinces himself that he has \nseen other survivors and makes noise in an \nattempt to get their attention. It will be \nclear to those that accompany him that \nthe whole situation is nothing \nmore than a figment \nof the poor man’s \ndistressed mind.\nVík í Mýrdal’s Lighthouse\nDescriptor: An old lighthouse in the oldest part of the port \nof Vík í Mýrdal. Crates of fish have been broken open and \nspilled around the lighthouse, their contents left to rot in the \nsun. Now, the air reeks in a nauseating way.\nGift – Safe Haven from the Maws: The stacks of rotten \nfish that Berend and Althea constantly throw at the foot of \nthe lighthouse keep the Maws away. The Maws lose all trace \nof someone who takes refuge in the lighthouse. While near \nthe lighthouse, Maws reduce their Opposition Level by 1.\nInformation: Althea will have a great deal of information \nfor the Hunters. She has been trapped for a month now, and \nhas taken the opportunity to study the Maws in depth.\n ◆ The Maws look like children mutated by something. \nThey are strong, fast, and seem to follow the smell of \nhuman flesh.\n ◆ Some desperate people fleeing from the village of Hosn \nhave told them of two “leaders” of the Maws, brother \nand sister, who apparently are smarter and more \npowerful than the others.\n ◆ After overhearing Maws talking to each other, Althea \nrealized that the volcano is a sacred place for those \nstrange beings that humans must not enter.\n ◆ Both the village and the volcano are two days’ walk \nfrom Vík í Mýrdal, but in different directions.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 98."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-berend-the-crazed-captain-98","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":98,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the captain of the previous expedition \nand the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by \nmasking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.\nAgenda: Wait for someone to come from the mainland to \nsave me.\nGift – Stinking Survivor: Berend managed to avoid \nbeing devoured by the Maws, but what he saw happen \nto his companions scarred his mind forever. The man \nconstantly covers himself with rotten fish because he has \ndiscovered the stench conceals him from the Maws. \nBerend will never be targeted by a Maw unless he \ntakes direct action against them. As long as he \nis at the port of Vík í Mýrdal, Berend can move \nwith great skill through the alleys and take \nany companions anywhere in the city without \nattracting the attention of the Maws. Each \ntime he uses this ability, he rolls 1 die: on 5 \nor 6, Berend convinces himself that he has \nseen other survivors and makes noise in an \nattempt to get their attention. It will be \nclear to those that accompany him that \nthe whole situation is nothing \nmore than a figment \nof the poor man’s \ndistressed mind.\nVík í Mýrdal’s Lighthouse\nDescriptor: An old lighthouse in the oldest part of the port \nof Vík í Mýrdal. Crates of fish have been broken open and \nspilled around the lighthouse, their contents left to rot in the \nsun. Now, the air reeks in a nauseating way.\nGift – Safe Haven from the Maws: The stacks of rotten \nfish that Berend and Althea constantly throw at the foot of \nthe lighthouse keep the Maws away. The Maws lose all trace \nof someone who takes refuge in the lighthouse. While near \nthe lighthouse, Maws reduce their Opposition Level by 1.\nInformation: Althea will have a great deal of information \nfor the Hunters. She has been trapped for a month now, and \nhas taken the opportunity to study the Maws in depth.\n ◆ The Maws look like children mutated by something. \nThey are strong, fast, and seem to follow the smell of \nhuman flesh.\n ◆ Some desperate people fleeing from the village of Hosn \nhave told them of two “leaders” of the Maws, brother \nand sister, who apparently are smarter and more \npowerful than the others.\n ◆ After overhearing Maws talking to each other, Althea \nrealized that the volcano is a sacred place for those \nstrange beings that humans must not enter.\n ◆ Both the village and the volcano are two days’ walk \nfrom Vík í Mýrdal, but in different directions.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Wait for someone to come from the mainland to \nsave me.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626341,"modifiedTime":1781557626341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"kpMF0fMVRyAIosq4","name":"The poor people of Paris","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"AbHDvWMw8dKopOIb","name":"The poor people of Paris - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are the poor and desperate who have \nno other home but the catacombs.\nWhen the Hunters interact with the poor, you can \ndecide or roll a die to learn their history and what \ninformation they can give.\n1. Marie lost all her children and her husband to \nthe war. She had grown fond of little Yvonne and \nweeps for the end she met.\n2. Claude is a soldier who lost a leg in the war. \nHe wanted to go into business with the Ravens \nwho live in the east side of the catacombs, but \nthey are all young and arrogant and have \nturned down his offer.\n3. Brigitte is a little girl who lost her parents \nduring the most recent plague. She knew \nYvonne and occasionally went to sell candles \nwith her. She knows that Adrien had taken \nYvonne into his service to do small jobs in the \nsacristy.\n4. Jerome is an old man who has almost \ncompletely lost his sight. In the past, he was \na skilled goldsmith, until his blindness left \nhim without a job. He will say that he heard</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 148.","positive":"We are the poor and desperate who have \nno other home but the catacombs.\nWhen the Hunters interact with the poor, you can \ndecide or roll a die to learn their history and what \ninformation they can give.\n1. Marie lost all her children and her husband to \nthe war. She had grown fond of little Yvonne and \nweeps for the end she met.\n2. Claude is a soldier who lost a leg in the war. \nHe wanted to go into business with the Ravens \nwho live in the east side of the catacombs, but \nthey are all young and arrogant and have \nturned down his offer.\n3. Brigitte is a little girl who lost her parents \nduring the most recent plague. She knew \nYvonne and occasionally went to sell candles \nwith her. She knows that Adrien had taken \nYvonne into his service to do small jobs in the \nsacristy.\n4. Jerome is an old man who has almost \ncompletely lost his sight. In the past, he was \na skilled goldsmith, until his blindness left \nhim without a job. He will say that he heard","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622234,"modifiedTime":1781557622234,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ThJhEzxxQoZDiOCA","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the poor and desperate who have \nno other home but the catacombs.\nWhen the Hunters interact with the poor, you can \ndecide or roll a die to learn their history and what \ninformation they can give.\n1. Marie lost all her children and her husband to \nthe war. She had grown fond of little Yvonne and \nweeps for the end she met.\n2. Claude is a soldier who lost a leg in the war. \nHe wanted to go into business with the Ravens \nwho live in the east side of the catacombs, but \nthey are all young and arrogant and have \nturned down his offer.\n3. Brigitte is a little girl who lost her parents \nduring the most recent plague. She knew \nYvonne and occasionally went to sell candles \nwith her. She knows that Adrien had taken \nYvonne into his service to do small jobs in the \nsacristy.\n4. Jerome is an old man who has almost \ncompletely lost his sight. In the past, he was \na skilled goldsmith, until his blindness left \nhim without a job. He will say that he heard</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 148."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622234,"modifiedTime":1781557622234,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-the-poor-people-of-paris-148","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":148,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are the poor and desperate who have \nno other home but the catacombs.\nWhen the Hunters interact with the poor, you can \ndecide or roll a die to learn their history and what \ninformation they can give.\n1. Marie lost all her children and her husband to \nthe war. She had grown fond of little Yvonne and \nweeps for the end she met.\n2. Claude is a soldier who lost a leg in the war. \nHe wanted to go into business with the Ravens \nwho live in the east side of the catacombs, but \nthey are all young and arrogant and have \nturned down his offer.\n3. Brigitte is a little girl who lost her parents \nduring the most recent plague. She knew \nYvonne and occasionally went to sell candles \nwith her. She knows that Adrien had taken \nYvonne into his service to do small jobs in the \nsacristy.\n4. Jerome is an old man who has almost \ncompletely lost his sight. In the past, he was \na skilled goldsmith, until his blindness left \nhim without a job. He will say that he heard</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622234,"modifiedTime":1781557622234,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"l83D0OgDURPWmq9W","name":"Ulrich Rotten Eye","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"DKexB79VB52AO5i6","name":"Ulrich Rotten Eye - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a former criminal with experience in the \nuse of poisons. I opened my gambling den looking for a less \ndangerous life, but I don’t back down when there’s money to \nbe made.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 138.","positive":"I am a former criminal with experience in the \nuse of poisons. I opened my gambling den looking for a less \ndangerous life, but I don’t back down when there’s money to \nbe made.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641569,"modifiedTime":1781557641569,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ge0a8MnXGXlVmoLE","name":"Gift - Poisoned Dagger","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Ulrich’s weapon is imbued with \na powerful poison. The poison first enters play when the \nweapon inflicts 1 Wound, causing 1 Penalty to the target’s \nactions. The effect lasts until the victim takes an antidote or \nhas an Interlude. \nThreat - Poisoned Drink</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 138.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641569,"modifiedTime":1781557641569,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lIVs4EZbGIdBKcSr","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a former criminal with experience in the \nuse of poisons. I opened my gambling den looking for a less \ndangerous life, but I don’t back down when there’s money to \nbe made.\nGift - Poisoned Dagger: Ulrich’s weapon is imbued with \na powerful poison. The poison first enters play when the \nweapon inflicts 1 Wound, causing 1 Penalty to the target’s \nactions. The effect lasts until the victim takes an antidote or \nhas an Interlude. \nThreat - Poisoned Drink</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 138."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641569,"modifiedTime":1781557641569,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-ulrich-rotten-eye-138","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":138,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a former criminal with experience in the \nuse of poisons. I opened my gambling den looking for a less \ndangerous life, but I don’t back down when there’s money to \nbe made.\nGift - Poisoned Dagger: Ulrich’s weapon is imbued with \na powerful poison. The poison first enters play when the \nweapon inflicts 1 Wound, causing 1 Penalty to the target’s \nactions. The effect lasts until the victim takes an antidote or \nhas an Interlude. \nThreat - Poisoned Drink</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641569,"modifiedTime":1781557641569,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"mKAuXdCBRpdu6J27","name":"Sailors","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"KT5EPAdOnV8ctDgN","name":"Sailors - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We \nare skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 95.","positive":"We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We \nare skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bWx5wygaQpw9Vhoz","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We \nare skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.\nAgenda: Execute Arne’s orders and avoid in any way having to \nface the supernatural.</p>","notes":"Hunger Island - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 95."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-hunger-island-sailors-95","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"hunger-island","adventureTitle":"Hunger Island","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":95,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Hunger Island","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We \nare skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.\nAgenda: Execute Arne’s orders and avoid in any way having to \nface the supernatural.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Execute Arne’s orders and avoid in any way having to \nface the supernatural.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557626239,"modifiedTime":1781557626239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"mLo5BPNKWX8NhOvf","name":"The Tunnels","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"tBx4A4GeYZbZVmcd","name":"The Tunnels - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A dense network of tunnels \nthat all look alike.\nGetting lost in the Tunnels will force \nthe Hunters to waste several hours \nbefore finding the exit.\n4 - The Ravens’ Hideout: This part of \nthe catacombs is only frequented by scoundrels who had \nbusiness with Adrien. A couple of broken bottles of absinthe \nare scattered among some makeshift beds. To those with a \nsensitive sense of smell, the scent of alcohol is still strong. \nAn old dagger and a wooden crucifix are the only other \nnoteworthy details.</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 149.","positive":"A dense network of tunnels \nthat all look alike.\nGetting lost in the Tunnels will force \nthe Hunters to waste several hours \nbefore finding the exit.\n4 - The Ravens’ Hideout: This part of \nthe catacombs is only frequented by scoundrels who had \nbusiness with Adrien. A couple of broken bottles of absinthe \nare scattered among some makeshift beds. To those with a \nsensitive sense of smell, the scent of alcohol is still strong. \nAn old dagger and a wooden crucifix are the only other \nnoteworthy details.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622268,"modifiedTime":1781557622268,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lyNx28RlkFO5ohR8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A dense network of tunnels \nthat all look alike.\nGetting lost in the Tunnels will force \nthe Hunters to waste several hours \nbefore finding the exit.\n4 - The Ravens’ Hideout: This part of \nthe catacombs is only frequented by scoundrels who had \nbusiness with Adrien. A couple of broken bottles of absinthe \nare scattered among some makeshift beds. To those with a \nsensitive sense of smell, the scent of alcohol is still strong. \nAn old dagger and a wooden crucifix are the only other \nnoteworthy details.\nInformation: If the Hunters arrive here before sunset, they \nwill find Olivier preparing his escape. When night falls, they \nwill find his charred corpse.\nOlivier the Raven on the run</p>","notes":"The Smile in the Darkness - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 149."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622268,"modifiedTime":1781557622268,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-smile-in-the-darkness-the-tunnels-149","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","adventureTitle":"The Smile in the Darkness","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":149,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Smile in the Darkness","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A dense network of tunnels \nthat all look alike.\nGetting lost in the Tunnels will force \nthe Hunters to waste several hours \nbefore finding the exit.\n4 - The Ravens’ Hideout: This part of \nthe catacombs is only frequented by scoundrels who had \nbusiness with Adrien. A couple of broken bottles of absinthe \nare scattered among some makeshift beds. To those with a \nsensitive sense of smell, the scent of alcohol is still strong. \nAn old dagger and a wooden crucifix are the only other \nnoteworthy details.\nInformation: If the Hunters arrive here before sunset, they \nwill find Olivier preparing his escape. When night falls, they \nwill find his charred corpse.\nOlivier the Raven on the run</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622268,"modifiedTime":1781557622268,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"n3jxoVxBqZM9xIJi","name":"Joanna called Nana the Servant","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"AHjDuOwvEUpocvFL","name":"Joanna called Nana the Servant - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal \nservant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I \nam as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84.","positive":"I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal \nservant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I \nam as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"q0DMED0up3bhWf9E","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal \nservant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I \nam as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.\nInformation: Joanna will tell the Hunters that she often \nheard Gwendolyn chatting with a boy in her room, but \nwhen she came in to figure out who it was, she never found \nanyone. Gwendolyn has always avoided revealing the boy’s \nidentity, convincing Nana that he was some noble son of \na good family in the city. Searching Gwendolyn’s room, \nthe Hunters will find some poppy petals under the bed. \nNana will say that those flowers can only be found in the \nKensington Gardens in London.\nSeals: There is only one Seal in the Carnarvon villa, \ninscribed on the east wall of Gwendolyn’s room.</p>","notes":"I Don't Believe - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 84."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-dont-believe-joanna-called-nana-the-servant-84","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","adventureTitle":"I Don't Believe","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":84,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Don't Believe","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal \nservant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I \nam as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.\nInformation: Joanna will tell the Hunters that she often \nheard Gwendolyn chatting with a boy in her room, but \nwhen she came in to figure out who it was, she never found \nanyone. Gwendolyn has always avoided revealing the boy’s \nidentity, convincing Nana that he was some noble son of \na good family in the city. Searching Gwendolyn’s room, \nthe Hunters will find some poppy petals under the bed. \nNana will say that those flowers can only be found in the \nKensington Gardens in London.\nSeals: There is only one Seal in the Carnarvon villa, \ninscribed on the east wall of Gwendolyn’s room.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557625638,"modifiedTime":1781557625638,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"nm5dwWRqcfXJR0R1","name":"Skutt the Moose","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"mZ4x1TQKS9Ayh2nF","name":"Skutt the Moose - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a majestic and magnificent moose, \nravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr’s magic which \nkeeps me alive.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 186.","positive":"I am a majestic and magnificent moose, \nravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr’s magic which \nkeeps me alive.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623290,"modifiedTime":1781557623290,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"57THB9AN4KFSyvjD","name":"Gift - Spectral Presence","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Skutt cannot truly be \neliminated as long as Tuvstarr’s wish keeps him alive. \nThe moose can move through fog, disappearing and \nreappearing even many feet away. Within the fog, no one \ncan stop or impede Skutt’s movement. When he suffers \nhis third Wound, Skutt falls apart, only to revive in the \nfollowing Scene.</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 186.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623290,"modifiedTime":1781557623290,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bD28HWvzuyREpv8Y","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a majestic and magnificent moose, \nravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr’s magic which \nkeeps me alive.\nAgenda: I have to find someone to save Tuvstarr from the \nblack pond and the illusion she fell into, because I can’t get in \n/ Protect Tuvstarr above all else, even if it means having the \nworld rot away.\nGift - Spectral Presence: Skutt cannot truly be \neliminated as long as Tuvstarr’s wish keeps him alive. \nThe moose can move through fog, disappearing and \nreappearing even many feet away. Within the fog, no one \ncan stop or impede Skutt’s movement. When he suffers \nhis third Wound, Skutt falls apart, only to revive in the \nfollowing Scene.\nInformation: Skutt is a Main NPC that Hunters can \nencounter in any Scene. He will always appear accompanied \nby a thick fog, stinking of rot, and surrounded by pale \nmoths. From his horns, like a ghostly veil, hangs the torn \nfabric of a knightly cloak, and a spear is half driven into \nhis body.\nIf the Hunters fight: Skutt is not interested in the fight \nbut is still a proud animal, so he will lash out at the enemy, \ncharging with his antlers. \nIf the Hunters talk to Skutt: He can tell how he took \nTuvstarr to the sacred pond, deep in the woods. Whatever \nTuvstarr did by diving into the lake, it wreaked havoc on the</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 186."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623291,"modifiedTime":1781557623291,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-skutt-the-moose-186","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":186,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a majestic and magnificent moose, \nravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr’s magic which \nkeeps me alive.\nAgenda: I have to find someone to save Tuvstarr from the \nblack pond and the illusion she fell into, because I can’t get in \n/ Protect Tuvstarr above all else, even if it means having the \nworld rot away.\nGift - Spectral Presence: Skutt cannot truly be \neliminated as long as Tuvstarr’s wish keeps him alive. \nThe moose can move through fog, disappearing and \nreappearing even many feet away. Within the fog, no one \ncan stop or impede Skutt’s movement. When he suffers \nhis third Wound, Skutt falls apart, only to revive in the \nfollowing Scene.\nInformation: Skutt is a Main NPC that Hunters can \nencounter in any Scene. He will always appear accompanied \nby a thick fog, stinking of rot, and surrounded by pale \nmoths. From his horns, like a ghostly veil, hangs the torn \nfabric of a knightly cloak, and a spear is half driven into \nhis body.\nIf the Hunters fight: Skutt is not interested in the fight \nbut is still a proud animal, so he will lash out at the enemy, \ncharging with his antlers. \nIf the Hunters talk to Skutt: He can tell how he took \nTuvstarr to the sacred pond, deep in the woods. Whatever \nTuvstarr did by diving into the lake, it wreaked havoc on the</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"I have to find someone to save Tuvstarr from the \nblack pond and the illusion she fell into, because I can’t get in \n/ Protect Tuvstarr above all else, even if it means having the \nworld rot away.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623291,"modifiedTime":1781557623291,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"o7QQfZR11eFM1Hrn","name":"Erik","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"zU1uSSOcusgVPuG1","name":"Erik - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a lively child who can never sit still.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162.","positive":"I am a lively child who can never sit still.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"a3etM74GBUxWAqU7","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a lively child who can never sit still. \nAgenda: Understand who Andersen really is, and why he \ntook my mom and me out of the misery we lived in.\nChristian</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 162."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-erik-162","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":162,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a lively child who can never sit still. \nAgenda: Understand who Andersen really is, and why he \ntook my mom and me out of the misery we lived in.\nChristian</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Understand who Andersen really is, and why he \ntook my mom and me out of the misery we lived in.\nChristian","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622631,"modifiedTime":1781557622631,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"o8tf2dgFQ5XWzFZa","name":"Bastian Soldat","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"suIOIhHPoNf87bxT","name":"Bastian Soldat - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a deserter with no qualities other than a \ngreat desire to live a good life with minimal effort. My only \nvirtue is that I have incredible nerve.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 134.","positive":"I am a deserter with no qualities other than a \ngreat desire to live a good life with minimal effort. My only \nvirtue is that I have incredible nerve.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641302,"modifiedTime":1781557641302,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"h9YJKJmpA5QZi9qB","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a deserter with no qualities other than a \ngreat desire to live a good life with minimal effort. My only \nvirtue is that I have incredible nerve.\nAgenda: Emptying the coffers of the Wagner family in order \nto pretend to be rich in Alena’s eyes and convince her to run \naway with me to Copenhagen. \nGift - Magic Tinderbox: Thanks to this powerful magical object, Bastian can go back in time whenever the situation would prevent him from completing his Agenda. This \nmagical effect cannot be stopped except by the magic word \nthat only Britta knows. Each time Bastian rewinds time, the \nStoryteller secretly accumulates 1 Reset Token. Each token</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 134."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641302,"modifiedTime":1781557641302,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-bastian-soldat-134","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":134,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a deserter with no qualities other than a \ngreat desire to live a good life with minimal effort. My only \nvirtue is that I have incredible nerve.\nAgenda: Emptying the coffers of the Wagner family in order \nto pretend to be rich in Alena’s eyes and convince her to run \naway with me to Copenhagen. \nGift - Magic Tinderbox: Thanks to this powerful magical object, Bastian can go back in time whenever the situation would prevent him from completing his Agenda. This \nmagical effect cannot be stopped except by the magic word \nthat only Britta knows. Each time Bastian rewinds time, the \nStoryteller secretly accumulates 1 Reset Token. Each token</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Emptying the coffers of the Wagner family in order \nto pretend to be rich in Alena’s eyes and convince her to run \naway with me to Copenhagen.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641302,"modifiedTime":1781557641302,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"oWLUbcyu5IIEjLAE","name":"Magic Menhirs","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"4MqvVuXSybMltovs","name":"Magic Menhirs - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A circle of ancient stones laid at the dawn of \ntime.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 197.","positive":"A circle of ancient stones laid at the dawn of \ntime.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644370,"modifiedTime":1781557644370,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Iy5Bqfi4Y4hSNYGQ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A circle of ancient stones laid at the dawn of \ntime. \nGift - Magical Journey: Activating the power of the \nstones is easy, but getting exactly where you want to go is \nmuch less so. The journey requires a Position Check: with a \nsingle roll, the person activating the power can take all objects within the Circle with them. Depending on the result \nof the Check, different effects are achieved.\nFailure: Successful journey but the wrong destination. \nThe Storyteller chooses the arrival Zone from among those \nadjacent to the original destination. \nOutcome with a Cost: Successful journey but with some \ninterference. Each subject loses 1 Equipment decided by \nthe Storyteller. The missing Equipment has been transported in a Zone adjacent to the one of arrival.\nStandard Outcome: Successful trip, no problems. \nOutcome with an Increment: Complimentary panoramic view. Before arriving, travelers can observe the \ndestination while lingering safely in the astral dimension \nthey have traveled through. The Storyteller will reveal some \ninformation about the Zone.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 197."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644370,"modifiedTime":1781557644370,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-magic-menhirs-197","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":197,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A circle of ancient stones laid at the dawn of \ntime. \nGift - Magical Journey: Activating the power of the \nstones is easy, but getting exactly where you want to go is \nmuch less so. The journey requires a Position Check: with a \nsingle roll, the person activating the power can take all objects within the Circle with them. Depending on the result \nof the Check, different effects are achieved.\nFailure: Successful journey but the wrong destination. \nThe Storyteller chooses the arrival Zone from among those \nadjacent to the original destination. \nOutcome with a Cost: Successful journey but with some \ninterference. Each subject loses 1 Equipment decided by \nthe Storyteller. The missing Equipment has been transported in a Zone adjacent to the one of arrival.\nStandard Outcome: Successful trip, no problems. \nOutcome with an Increment: Complimentary panoramic view. Before arriving, travelers can observe the \ndestination while lingering safely in the astral dimension \nthey have traveled through. The Storyteller will reveal some \ninformation about the Zone.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644370,"modifiedTime":1781557644370,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"oyXjpDzqoYsRuf0H","name":"Crystal Rock","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"Va2ChMEt5x3ujEDx","name":"Crystal Rock - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a fragile, sharp agglomeration of crystal. \nThe wrong vibration can make me explode. \nNote: The Storyteller rolls 1 die or chooses from the list to \ncomplete the Threat Descriptor. \n1: A flock of seagulls nested among the rocks. \n2: Part of me juts underwater dangerously. \n3: My crystal is harder than normal. \n4: I am, in reality, a floating block moving without control.\n5: My crystal reflects sunlight much more intensely than nor -\nmal. I blind those who approach.\n6: I am filled with subtle overgrowths extending in every direction.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 157.","positive":"I am a fragile, sharp agglomeration of crystal. \nThe wrong vibration can make me explode. \nNote: The Storyteller rolls 1 die or chooses from the list to \ncomplete the Threat Descriptor. \n1: A flock of seagulls nested among the rocks. \n2: Part of me juts underwater dangerously. \n3: My crystal is harder than normal. \n4: I am, in reality, a floating block moving without control.\n5: My crystal reflects sunlight much more intensely than nor -\nmal. I blind those who approach.\n6: I am filled with subtle overgrowths extending in every direction.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642426,"modifiedTime":1781557642426,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bGPNFFOxeRhvo8gh","name":"Gift - Sensitive to Vibration","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>If a crystal is destroyed \nwithout obtaining a positive Outcome on a Check, the ship \nreceives 1 Damage Token. The person who caused the explosion gets 1 Wound and loses 1 Soma. If there are 2 or more \nDamage Tokens on the ship at the end of the Leg, Sinbad will \nnot be able to use his Gift - The Sailing Ship, regardless of \nwhether he is bored or not, and will go directly to the next \nLeg. \n“B” Legs (Second, Fifth, and Seventh)\nRoll 1 die to determine the Leg. Increase the result by 1 if you \nobtain a Leg you have already faced. Alternatively, choose directly which Leg you prefer to play.\n1B Raging Rocs\nNote: This Leg can only be played after Leg 3A - The Roc. If \nthe Hunters have not yet faced it, consider this a 1A roll.\nThe story that led us here...\nTwo huge winged figures appear in the sky, identical to the large \nbird that tried to nest on the ship. The creatures have huge boulders in their talons and seem intent on dropping them on the \ndeck. Sinbad begs the Hunters to save the ship before he cautiously flees below deck. \nPlace: Sinbad’s ship in the middle of the sea.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 157.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642426,"modifiedTime":1781557642426,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TdUir45E7oJ2Hzuo","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: I am a fragile, sharp agglomeration of crystal. \nThe wrong vibration can make me explode. \nNote: The Storyteller rolls 1 die or chooses from the list to \ncomplete the Threat Descriptor. \n1: A flock of seagulls nested among the rocks. \n2: Part of me juts underwater dangerously. \n3: My crystal is harder than normal. \n4: I am, in reality, a floating block moving without control.\n5: My crystal reflects sunlight much more intensely than nor -\nmal. I blind those who approach.\n6: I am filled with subtle overgrowths extending in every direction.\nGift - Sensitive to Vibration: If a crystal is destroyed \nwithout obtaining a positive Outcome on a Check, the ship \nreceives 1 Damage Token. The person who caused the explosion gets 1 Wound and loses 1 Soma. If there are 2 or more \nDamage Tokens on the ship at the end of the Leg, Sinbad will \nnot be able to use his Gift - The Sailing Ship, regardless of \nwhether he is bored or not, and will go directly to the next \nLeg. \n“B” Legs (Second, Fifth, and Seventh)\nRoll 1 die to determine the Leg. Increase the result by 1 if you \nobtain a Leg you have already faced. Alternatively, choose directly which Leg you prefer to play.\n1B Raging Rocs\nNote: This Leg can only be played after Leg 3A - The Roc. If \nthe Hunters have not yet faced it, consider this a 1A roll.\nThe story that led us here...\nTwo huge winged figures appear in the sky, identical to the large \nbird that tried to nest on the ship. The creatures have huge boulders in their talons and seem intent on dropping them on the \ndeck. Sinbad begs the Hunters to save the ship before he cautiously flees below deck. \nPlace: Sinbad’s ship in the middle of the sea. \nInformation: Sinbad has hidden a Roc egg that he secretly \nretrieved from the nest the last time around. The old sailor is \ntoo greedy to return it, and intends to use the Hunters to get \nrid of the two Rocs. \nChallenges: Deflect the fall of the 4 boulders the Rocs intend to drop on the ship and convince Sinbad to return the \negg.\nHow to get the Tarì: When the egg is returned, one of the \nRocs will drop the coin on the deck of the ship. \nRoc\nSee Dark Presence on page 13.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 157."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642426,"modifiedTime":1781557642426,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-crystal-rock-157","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":157,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: I am a fragile, sharp agglomeration of crystal. \nThe wrong vibration can make me explode. \nNote: The Storyteller rolls 1 die or chooses from the list to \ncomplete the Threat Descriptor. \n1: A flock of seagulls nested among the rocks. \n2: Part of me juts underwater dangerously. \n3: My crystal is harder than normal. \n4: I am, in reality, a floating block moving without control.\n5: My crystal reflects sunlight much more intensely than nor -\nmal. I blind those who approach.\n6: I am filled with subtle overgrowths extending in every direction.\nGift - Sensitive to Vibration: If a crystal is destroyed \nwithout obtaining a positive Outcome on a Check, the ship \nreceives 1 Damage Token. The person who caused the explosion gets 1 Wound and loses 1 Soma. If there are 2 or more \nDamage Tokens on the ship at the end of the Leg, Sinbad will \nnot be able to use his Gift - The Sailing Ship, regardless of \nwhether he is bored or not, and will go directly to the next \nLeg. \n“B” Legs (Second, Fifth, and Seventh)\nRoll 1 die to determine the Leg. Increase the result by 1 if you \nobtain a Leg you have already faced. Alternatively, choose directly which Leg you prefer to play.\n1B Raging Rocs\nNote: This Leg can only be played after Leg 3A - The Roc. If \nthe Hunters have not yet faced it, consider this a 1A roll.\nThe story that led us here...\nTwo huge winged figures appear in the sky, identical to the large \nbird that tried to nest on the ship. The creatures have huge boulders in their talons and seem intent on dropping them on the \ndeck. Sinbad begs the Hunters to save the ship before he cautiously flees below deck. \nPlace: Sinbad’s ship in the middle of the sea. \nInformation: Sinbad has hidden a Roc egg that he secretly \nretrieved from the nest the last time around. The old sailor is \ntoo greedy to return it, and intends to use the Hunters to get \nrid of the two Rocs. \nChallenges: Deflect the fall of the 4 boulders the Rocs intend to drop on the ship and convince Sinbad to return the \negg.\nHow to get the Tarì: When the egg is returned, one of the \nRocs will drop the coin on the deck of the ship. \nRoc\nSee Dark Presence on page 13.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642426,"modifiedTime":1781557642426,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"p69rVus9bbNmcSzs","name":"2: Elna","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"OOTD94taDGWuNY8Y","name":"2: Elna - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a good weaver and know many legends \nof the area.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 119.","positive":"I am a good weaver and know many legends \nof the area.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640549,"modifiedTime":1781557640549,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"huMvDxTKd46NCTQj","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a good weaver and know many legends \nof the area.\nAgenda: I want my daughter Jaana to come home, but \nwithout openly siding against Nikola Lupei.\nInformation: Elna’s family is among those who did not \ninitially pay the pledge, and her daughter Jaana has disappeared. The old woman will tell you that her daughter is \nwell and has settled in Nikola’s mansion, where she works \nas a toy factory worker. When questioned about the night \nof the disappearance, Elna will say that no one noticed anything and that there were no signs of forced entry. Talking \nto Elna, it will become clear that she misses her daughter \nvery much. \n3: Mikko</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 119."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640549,"modifiedTime":1781557640549,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-2-elna-119","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":119,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a good weaver and know many legends \nof the area.\nAgenda: I want my daughter Jaana to come home, but \nwithout openly siding against Nikola Lupei.\nInformation: Elna’s family is among those who did not \ninitially pay the pledge, and her daughter Jaana has disappeared. The old woman will tell you that her daughter is \nwell and has settled in Nikola’s mansion, where she works \nas a toy factory worker. When questioned about the night \nof the disappearance, Elna will say that no one noticed anything and that there were no signs of forced entry. Talking \nto Elna, it will become clear that she misses her daughter \nvery much. \n3: Mikko</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I want my daughter Jaana to come home, but \nwithout openly siding against Nikola Lupei.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640549,"modifiedTime":1781557640549,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"pEU3m4b0ZqZh6qEA","name":"Geppetto Gullible Alchemist Apprentice","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"UVOgY6G0CcCGNmOr","name":"Geppetto Gullible Alchemist Apprentice - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a poor man who has always been looking \nfor a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy \nfrom master Antonio.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 135.","positive":"I am a poor man who has always been looking \nfor a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy \nfrom master Antonio.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621827,"modifiedTime":1781557621827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RiDbhlPP3sz9qsU2","name":"Gift - Improvised Alchemist","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Geppetto can rely on \na series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that \nhe hides under a tacky yellow wig. When he throws a vial, \nroll a die: 1-2 Explosive: The liquid explodes on contact \nwith the air, causing 1 Wound to everyone within thirty \nfeet. Thick black smoke will engulf the whole area; 3-4 \nStench: A nauseating odor fills the air giving 1 Penalty to \nall actions within the area for the rest of the Scene; 5-6 Air \nBomb: All subjects in an area of thirty feet are knocked \nback and fall to the ground. If they hit an obstacle they can \nsuffer 1 Wound. Geppetto is immune to the effects of his \nalchemical concoctions.\nThe Old Carpenter’s Shop</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 135.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621827,"modifiedTime":1781557621827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"EZ2v4CYGVaNB5Khf","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a poor man who has always been looking \nfor a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy \nfrom master Antonio.\nAgenda: Pretend to be Carlo’s father and find him / Obtain \nthe secret of eternal life, thanks to alchemy.\nGift - Improvised Alchemist: Geppetto can rely on \na series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that \nhe hides under a tacky yellow wig. When he throws a vial, \nroll a die: 1-2 Explosive: The liquid explodes on contact \nwith the air, causing 1 Wound to everyone within thirty \nfeet. Thick black smoke will engulf the whole area; 3-4 \nStench: A nauseating odor fills the air giving 1 Penalty to \nall actions within the area for the rest of the Scene; 5-6 Air \nBomb: All subjects in an area of thirty feet are knocked \nback and fall to the ground. If they hit an obstacle they can \nsuffer 1 Wound. Geppetto is immune to the effects of his \nalchemical concoctions.\nThe Old Carpenter’s Shop\nDescriptor: Once the alchemical laboratory of Mastro \nAntonio, the carpenter’s shop was abandoned after the \ndiscovery of the corpses. \nInformation: \n ◆ The place is a normal carpenter’s shop, abandoned for \nsome time. The only element that catches the Hunters’ \nattention is a series of chisels on the wall, with one</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 135."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621827,"modifiedTime":1781557621827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-geppetto-gullible-alchemist-apprentice-135","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":135,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a poor man who has always been looking \nfor a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy \nfrom master Antonio.\nAgenda: Pretend to be Carlo’s father and find him / Obtain \nthe secret of eternal life, thanks to alchemy.\nGift - Improvised Alchemist: Geppetto can rely on \na series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that \nhe hides under a tacky yellow wig. When he throws a vial, \nroll a die: 1-2 Explosive: The liquid explodes on contact \nwith the air, causing 1 Wound to everyone within thirty \nfeet. Thick black smoke will engulf the whole area; 3-4 \nStench: A nauseating odor fills the air giving 1 Penalty to \nall actions within the area for the rest of the Scene; 5-6 Air \nBomb: All subjects in an area of thirty feet are knocked \nback and fall to the ground. If they hit an obstacle they can \nsuffer 1 Wound. Geppetto is immune to the effects of his \nalchemical concoctions.\nThe Old Carpenter’s Shop\nDescriptor: Once the alchemical laboratory of Mastro \nAntonio, the carpenter’s shop was abandoned after the \ndiscovery of the corpses. \nInformation: \n ◆ The place is a normal carpenter’s shop, abandoned for \nsome time. The only element that catches the Hunters’ \nattention is a series of chisels on the wall, with one</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Pretend to be Carlo’s father and find him / Obtain \nthe secret of eternal life, thanks to alchemy.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621827,"modifiedTime":1781557621827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"pF0qJYpDhPtMt1JL","name":"Lene’s Cutthroat","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"vezMUVekVImCVyVi","name":"Lene’s Cutthroat - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are ruthless scoundrels and protect our territory from any intruder.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 209.","positive":"We are ruthless scoundrels and protect our territory from any intruder.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645177,"modifiedTime":1781557645177,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RFsIvcZ2iDSoozcO","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC \n(1 Wound - 12 Gang Members)\nDescriptor: We are ruthless scoundrels and protect our territory from any intruder.\nGift - Neighborhood Gang: A Cutthroat increases their \nOL by 1 when they act to wound or capture a target they \nconsider an intruder on their territory. \nEnd of Scene: The Hunters decide to meet the Black \nFeathers. Go to the THIRD SCENE - The Ambush of the \nBlack Feathers. If they decide to meet Flora instead, go to \nSECOND SCENE OPTION A - Flora’s Greenhouse.\n2b</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 209."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645177,"modifiedTime":1781557645177,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-lene-s-cutthroat-209","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":209,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC \n(1 Wound - 12 Gang Members)\nDescriptor: We are ruthless scoundrels and protect our territory from any intruder.\nGift - Neighborhood Gang: A Cutthroat increases their \nOL by 1 when they act to wound or capture a target they \nconsider an intruder on their territory. \nEnd of Scene: The Hunters decide to meet the Black \nFeathers. Go to the THIRD SCENE - The Ambush of the \nBlack Feathers. If they decide to meet Flora instead, go to \nSECOND SCENE OPTION A - Flora’s Greenhouse.\n2b</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645177,"modifiedTime":1781557645177,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"pi9Lq1h4SeB6m7UP","name":"The Badalisk","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"6woIiWzSfzfWxcD0","name":"The Badalisk - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a huge dirty red sack encrusted with the \nbloody remains of past meals. I have a large mouth with \nwhich I devour my prey in one gulp.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 122.","positive":"I am a huge dirty red sack encrusted with the \nbloody remains of past meals. I have a large mouth with \nwhich I devour my prey in one gulp.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640618,"modifiedTime":1781557640618,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qUJcVl3EUQZctM9W","name":"Gift - Huge Mouth","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>When the Badalisk attacks a target \nand the target fails their Defense Check, the Badalisk can \nchoose between two effects:\n1. Inflicts 1 additional Wound with its bite. The target can \nalso be thrown a distance of thirty feet or have one of its \npieces of equipment swallowed by the Badalisk.\n2. Swallow the target so that they end up in its giant belly. \nThis effect can also be activated when the target gains an \nOutcome with a Cost on a Defense Check, but in this \ncase, they will only lose one piece of equipment as it is \nswallowed by the giant maw.\nA subject trapped inside the Badalisk can use their action to \nactively attempt to escape. Depending on their ability, this \nwill be resolved as follows:</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 122.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640618,"modifiedTime":1781557640618,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9JLoS5FeoeaSAPmr","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a huge dirty red sack encrusted with the \nbloody remains of past meals. I have a large mouth with \nwhich I devour my prey in one gulp. \nAgenda: Eating whatever comes my way to satiate my endless hunger. \nGift - Huge Mouth: When the Badalisk attacks a target \nand the target fails their Defense Check, the Badalisk can \nchoose between two effects:\n1. Inflicts 1 additional Wound with its bite. The target can \nalso be thrown a distance of thirty feet or have one of its \npieces of equipment swallowed by the Badalisk.\n2. Swallow the target so that they end up in its giant belly. \nThis effect can also be activated when the target gains an \nOutcome with a Cost on a Defense Check, but in this \ncase, they will only lose one piece of equipment as it is \nswallowed by the giant maw.\nA subject trapped inside the Badalisk can use their action to \nactively attempt to escape. Depending on their ability, this \nwill be resolved as follows:</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 122."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640618,"modifiedTime":1781557640618,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-the-badalisk-122","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":122,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a huge dirty red sack encrusted with the \nbloody remains of past meals. I have a large mouth with \nwhich I devour my prey in one gulp. \nAgenda: Eating whatever comes my way to satiate my endless hunger. \nGift - Huge Mouth: When the Badalisk attacks a target \nand the target fails their Defense Check, the Badalisk can \nchoose between two effects:\n1. Inflicts 1 additional Wound with its bite. The target can \nalso be thrown a distance of thirty feet or have one of its \npieces of equipment swallowed by the Badalisk.\n2. Swallow the target so that they end up in its giant belly. \nThis effect can also be activated when the target gains an \nOutcome with a Cost on a Defense Check, but in this \ncase, they will only lose one piece of equipment as it is \nswallowed by the giant maw.\nA subject trapped inside the Badalisk can use their action to \nactively attempt to escape. Depending on their ability, this \nwill be resolved as follows:</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Eating whatever comes my way to satiate my endless hunger.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640618,"modifiedTime":1781557640618,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"pvQm5fhsSAFm9qZ4","name":"Subjects of great skill who serve the Wise Fairy to uphold justice","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"2fywsOORUOPyFCeg","name":"Subjects of great skill who serve the Wise Fairy to uphold justice - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a hero, always ready to fight for the Wise \nFairy. I have a one-sided view of the truth and only believe \nwhat my lady says.</p>","notes":"Nemesis - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 93.","positive":"I am a hero, always ready to fight for the Wise \nFairy. I have a one-sided view of the truth and only believe \nwhat my lady says.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639362,"modifiedTime":1781557639362,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ZMjZQ0d9nMCIW8Tf","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a hero, always ready to fight for the Wise \nFairy. I have a one-sided view of the truth and only believe \nwhat my lady says. \nAgenda: Fulfilling every wish of the Wise Fairy. \nGift - Heroic Soul: The NPC will even ignore death to \nsatisfy the Wise Fairy. When they suffer their final Wound, \nthey can act one last time before leaving the battle. When \nthey enter the Scene, they can use a power granted by the \nWand of Creation, complete with a Descriptor created by \nthe Storyteller.</p>","notes":"Nemesis - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 93."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639362,"modifiedTime":1781557639362,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nemesis-subjects-of-great-skill-who-serve-the-wise-fairy-to-uphold-justice-93","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nemesis","adventureTitle":"Nemesis","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":93,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nemesis","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a hero, always ready to fight for the Wise \nFairy. I have a one-sided view of the truth and only believe \nwhat my lady says. \nAgenda: Fulfilling every wish of the Wise Fairy. \nGift - Heroic Soul: The NPC will even ignore death to \nsatisfy the Wise Fairy. When they suffer their final Wound, \nthey can act one last time before leaving the battle. When \nthey enter the Scene, they can use a power granted by the \nWand of Creation, complete with a Descriptor created by \nthe Storyteller.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Fulfilling every wish of the Wise Fairy.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639362,"modifiedTime":1781557639362,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"pySHxt3kDSkvDH8T","name":"Poisoned Drink","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"VBvXRKEiKsFMj39P","name":"Poisoned Drink - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A fine, tasteless, odorless poison that can be \nadded to any beverage.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 138.","positive":"A fine, tasteless, odorless poison that can be \nadded to any beverage.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641569,"modifiedTime":1781557641569,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qBgJQ6ZHI2HVrlt8","name":"Gift - Poison","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Those who ingest the Poisoned Drink suffer 1 Wound and receive 1 Penalty until they take an antidote or rest in an Interlude. \nVilla Wagner</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 138.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641569,"modifiedTime":1781557641569,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"g5OtVJvUPkRtvdBa","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A fine, tasteless, odorless poison that can be \nadded to any beverage. \nGift - Poison: Those who ingest the Poisoned Drink suffer 1 Wound and receive 1 Penalty until they take an antidote or rest in an Interlude. \nVilla Wagner\nDescriptor: An imposing mansion surrounded by gardens, \nponds, and mazes of hedges. \nInformation: It’s impossible to enter the Villa without an \ninvitation from the Wagner family, but there are no fences \nand, except for a few gardeners, it is easy to wander inconspicuously around the large gardens. Alena is often found \non the large balcony of her room on the second floor, reading a good book and sipping tea. Alena will tell you that \nBastian often brings her very good and expensive cakes that \nhe buys at the famous Golden Plate Tavern. The young woman is unclear about who Bastian really is, but it will be obvious that she is attracted to the funny little man and finds \nhis awkward attempts to court her tender.\nIf Bastian is present: He will be under Alena’s balcony \nreciting some love poetry. As soon as he sees the Hunters, \nhe will try to escape by slipping into one of the hedge mazes.\nIf the Black Cat is present: It can be seen on the balcony being petted by Alena. The Cat pretends to purr in \naffection as she clearly tries to snatch a pendant from the \nyoung woman’s neck.\nFirst Reset: If this is the first time he encounters the \nHunters in this Place, Bastian will try to escape. However, \nif the Hunters have already met him here, Bastian will not \nappear again.\nSecond Reset: Same as the First Reset, except that a \ngroup of guards (2 per Hunter) will enter the Scene when \nthe Hunters approach Alena. The leader of the guards will \nsay that by Lord Wagner’s order, no one can enter the garden of the Villa. If the Hunters can get the captain to talk</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 138."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641569,"modifiedTime":1781557641569,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-poisoned-drink-138","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":138,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A fine, tasteless, odorless poison that can be \nadded to any beverage. \nGift - Poison: Those who ingest the Poisoned Drink suffer 1 Wound and receive 1 Penalty until they take an antidote or rest in an Interlude. \nVilla Wagner\nDescriptor: An imposing mansion surrounded by gardens, \nponds, and mazes of hedges. \nInformation: It’s impossible to enter the Villa without an \ninvitation from the Wagner family, but there are no fences \nand, except for a few gardeners, it is easy to wander inconspicuously around the large gardens. Alena is often found \non the large balcony of her room on the second floor, reading a good book and sipping tea. Alena will tell you that \nBastian often brings her very good and expensive cakes that \nhe buys at the famous Golden Plate Tavern. The young woman is unclear about who Bastian really is, but it will be obvious that she is attracted to the funny little man and finds \nhis awkward attempts to court her tender.\nIf Bastian is present: He will be under Alena’s balcony \nreciting some love poetry. As soon as he sees the Hunters, \nhe will try to escape by slipping into one of the hedge mazes.\nIf the Black Cat is present: It can be seen on the balcony being petted by Alena. The Cat pretends to purr in \naffection as she clearly tries to snatch a pendant from the \nyoung woman’s neck.\nFirst Reset: If this is the first time he encounters the \nHunters in this Place, Bastian will try to escape. However, \nif the Hunters have already met him here, Bastian will not \nappear again.\nSecond Reset: Same as the First Reset, except that a \ngroup of guards (2 per Hunter) will enter the Scene when \nthe Hunters approach Alena. The leader of the guards will \nsay that by Lord Wagner’s order, no one can enter the garden of the Villa. If the Hunters can get the captain to talk</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641569,"modifiedTime":1781557641569,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"q8hSV9JrLJ6VvD74","name":"Snow of Memory","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"ppMmtHlWyy9NhYBW","name":"Snow of Memory - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Tiny snowflakes that can freeze a person’s \nmemories forever until they forget everything.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 223.","positive":"Tiny snowflakes that can freeze a person’s \nmemories forever until they forget everything.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646114,"modifiedTime":1781557646114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"hUtEj55i5SheCfkl","name":"Gift - Ice Oblivion","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>For each minute a subject is under \nthe snowfall, it is touched by a number of flakes equal to \nthe result of a die roll. The result determines the effect to be \napplied. If the subject does nothing to protect themselves \nfrom the snow, they cannot make a Defense Check against \nthe Threat. The Storyteller must evaluate, based on protective measures and the subject’s clothing, whether they are \nmore exposed to snowflakes (roll 2 dice and choose the \nhigher value) or are more sheltered (roll 2 dice and choose \nthe lower value). \n1-2: A severe headache accompanies a cherished memory \nthat slowly fades, leaving the target with the perception of \nan event lost forever. The target loses 2 Soma. An NPC reduces their OL by 1 for the remainder of the Scenario.\n3-4: The face of a loved one appears fleetingly in the tar -\nget’s mind before disappearing, leaving them with the feeling of having lost the memory of a loved one. The target \nloses the use of one of their Descriptors (except the Dark \nEgo) until the end of the Scenario. An NPC loses their only \nDescriptor and replaces it with this one: I’ve lost my memory and have no idea where I am. \n5-6: The target hears a phrase whispered so quietly it is \nunintelligible, leaving them with the perception that a part \nof themselves is lost forever. The target loses the use of one \nGift for the rest of the Scenario (except Dark Ego). An NPC \nwho has no Gifts to lose reduces their OL by one category. If</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 223.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646114,"modifiedTime":1781557646114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"V9aJY05GLgkOoih7","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: Tiny snowflakes that can freeze a person’s \nmemories forever until they forget everything. \nGift - Ice Oblivion: For each minute a subject is under \nthe snowfall, it is touched by a number of flakes equal to \nthe result of a die roll. The result determines the effect to be \napplied. If the subject does nothing to protect themselves \nfrom the snow, they cannot make a Defense Check against \nthe Threat. The Storyteller must evaluate, based on protective measures and the subject’s clothing, whether they are \nmore exposed to snowflakes (roll 2 dice and choose the \nhigher value) or are more sheltered (roll 2 dice and choose \nthe lower value). \n1-2: A severe headache accompanies a cherished memory \nthat slowly fades, leaving the target with the perception of \nan event lost forever. The target loses 2 Soma. An NPC reduces their OL by 1 for the remainder of the Scenario.\n3-4: The face of a loved one appears fleetingly in the tar -\nget’s mind before disappearing, leaving them with the feeling of having lost the memory of a loved one. The target \nloses the use of one of their Descriptors (except the Dark \nEgo) until the end of the Scenario. An NPC loses their only \nDescriptor and replaces it with this one: I’ve lost my memory and have no idea where I am. \n5-6: The target hears a phrase whispered so quietly it is \nunintelligible, leaving them with the perception that a part \nof themselves is lost forever. The target loses the use of one \nGift for the rest of the Scenario (except Dark Ego). An NPC \nwho has no Gifts to lose reduces their OL by one category. If</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 223."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646114,"modifiedTime":1781557646114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-snow-of-memory-223","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":223,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: Tiny snowflakes that can freeze a person’s \nmemories forever until they forget everything. \nGift - Ice Oblivion: For each minute a subject is under \nthe snowfall, it is touched by a number of flakes equal to \nthe result of a die roll. The result determines the effect to be \napplied. If the subject does nothing to protect themselves \nfrom the snow, they cannot make a Defense Check against \nthe Threat. The Storyteller must evaluate, based on protective measures and the subject’s clothing, whether they are \nmore exposed to snowflakes (roll 2 dice and choose the \nhigher value) or are more sheltered (roll 2 dice and choose \nthe lower value). \n1-2: A severe headache accompanies a cherished memory \nthat slowly fades, leaving the target with the perception of \nan event lost forever. The target loses 2 Soma. An NPC reduces their OL by 1 for the remainder of the Scenario.\n3-4: The face of a loved one appears fleetingly in the tar -\nget’s mind before disappearing, leaving them with the feeling of having lost the memory of a loved one. The target \nloses the use of one of their Descriptors (except the Dark \nEgo) until the end of the Scenario. An NPC loses their only \nDescriptor and replaces it with this one: I’ve lost my memory and have no idea where I am. \n5-6: The target hears a phrase whispered so quietly it is \nunintelligible, leaving them with the perception that a part \nof themselves is lost forever. The target loses the use of one \nGift for the rest of the Scenario (except Dark Ego). An NPC \nwho has no Gifts to lose reduces their OL by one category. If</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646114,"modifiedTime":1781557646114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"q91gTXG8nH7JQ89X","name":"The Guards of Gerard Dubois","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"WBdsDzUEWe0fEKT2","name":"The Guards of Gerard Dubois - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are duty-bound - as long as we get \npaid.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122.","positive":"We are duty-bound - as long as we get \npaid.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4nZAc0IDW2rQ9W3L","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are duty-bound - as long as we get \npaid.\nAgenda: Vincent is the boss. We’ll follow his lead.</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 122."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-the-guards-of-gerard-dubois-122","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":122,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are duty-bound - as long as we get \npaid.\nAgenda: Vincent is the boss. We’ll follow his lead.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Vincent is the boss. We’ll follow his lead.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621314,"modifiedTime":1781557621314,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"qLJlCXxy6Tf8IRVT","name":"Pepe","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"kDnohm4DbStp2Q4U","name":"Pepe - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the leader of the Bats and responsible for the sur -\nvival of my companions. I am brave and skilled with knives, and I like \nto whistle my mother’s lullaby, a happy memory from my childhood.</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 105.","positive":"I am the leader of the Bats and responsible for the sur -\nvival of my companions. I am brave and skilled with knives, and I like \nto whistle my mother’s lullaby, a happy memory from my childhood.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639930,"modifiedTime":1781557639930,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"iLLt1u6QG3HvUXcv","name":"Gift - Big Brother","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Pepe will not allow anyone to harm his comrades. Against a target that threatens a Bat, Pepe inflicts 1 Additional \nWound. All Bats increase their OL by 1 when Pepe is present. \nThe Gang of Bats</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 105.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639930,"modifiedTime":1781557639930,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tnZFvvvkYuZ48tiW","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the leader of the Bats and responsible for the sur -\nvival of my companions. I am brave and skilled with knives, and I like \nto whistle my mother’s lullaby, a happy memory from my childhood.\nAgenda: Robbing the people of Murcia as revenge for their indiffer -\nence to those who have nothing / Taking care of the Bats, whom I consider my new family. \nGift - Big Brother: Pepe will not allow anyone to harm his comrades. Against a target that threatens a Bat, Pepe inflicts 1 Additional \nWound. All Bats increase their OL by 1 when Pepe is present. \nThe Gang of Bats</p>","notes":"A Mother's Heart - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 105."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639930,"modifiedTime":1781557639930,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-mothers-heart-pepe-105","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","adventureTitle":"A Mother's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":105,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Mother's Heart","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the leader of the Bats and responsible for the sur -\nvival of my companions. I am brave and skilled with knives, and I like \nto whistle my mother’s lullaby, a happy memory from my childhood.\nAgenda: Robbing the people of Murcia as revenge for their indiffer -\nence to those who have nothing / Taking care of the Bats, whom I consider my new family. \nGift - Big Brother: Pepe will not allow anyone to harm his comrades. Against a target that threatens a Bat, Pepe inflicts 1 Additional \nWound. All Bats increase their OL by 1 when Pepe is present. \nThe Gang of Bats</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Robbing the people of Murcia as revenge for their indiffer -\nence to those who have nothing / Taking care of the Bats, whom I consider my new family.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557639930,"modifiedTime":1781557639930,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"qmNupbdbncTjr6qY","name":"Gerda the Swindler","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"qwgPyiMjUuShiYqm","name":"Gerda the Swindler - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled trickster, my sharp mind matched \nonly by my nerve. While studying Lady Storm’s books, I discovered that I can also dabble in magic, and I have no qualms \nabout using it to my own advantage.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 224.","positive":"I am a skilled trickster, my sharp mind matched \nonly by my nerve. While studying Lady Storm’s books, I discovered that I can also dabble in magic, and I have no qualms \nabout using it to my own advantage.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646208,"modifiedTime":1781557646208,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"DLJjtuf9kiNGCKyc","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled trickster, my sharp mind matched \nonly by my nerve. While studying Lady Storm’s books, I discovered that I can also dabble in magic, and I have no qualms \nabout using it to my own advantage. \nAgenda: Living in luxury without working and increasing \nmy power to get my hands on more wealth / Supporting Kay \nin his whims, because even though I think he is an idiot, I \nneed a trustworthy sidekick who will always do what I say. \nShard Descriptor: I am a naive girl who struggles \nto express her feelings. Thanks to the magic I have learned, I \ncan help others. \nShard Agenda: Save my beloved Kay from the sad \nfate that befell him / Defeat the Ice Heart.\nGift - Power of the Shard: The Shard of the Mirror of \nthe Other Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the \nperson it injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they \nact in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor \nor Agenda.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 224."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646208,"modifiedTime":1781557646208,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-gerda-the-swindler-224","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":224,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled trickster, my sharp mind matched \nonly by my nerve. While studying Lady Storm’s books, I discovered that I can also dabble in magic, and I have no qualms \nabout using it to my own advantage. \nAgenda: Living in luxury without working and increasing \nmy power to get my hands on more wealth / Supporting Kay \nin his whims, because even though I think he is an idiot, I \nneed a trustworthy sidekick who will always do what I say. \nShard Descriptor: I am a naive girl who struggles \nto express her feelings. Thanks to the magic I have learned, I \ncan help others. \nShard Agenda: Save my beloved Kay from the sad \nfate that befell him / Defeat the Ice Heart.\nGift - Power of the Shard: The Shard of the Mirror of \nthe Other Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the \nperson it injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they \nact in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor \nor Agenda.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Living in luxury without working and increasing \nmy power to get my hands on more wealth / Supporting Kay \nin his whims, because even though I think he is an idiot, I \nneed a trustworthy sidekick who will always do what I say. \nShard Descriptor: I am a naive girl who struggles \nto express her feelings. Thanks to the magic I have learned, I \ncan help others. \nShard Agenda: Save my beloved Kay from the sad \nfate that befell him / Defeat the Ice Heart.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646208,"modifiedTime":1781557646208,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"qqclosrwhT5MHUOz","name":"The Elephant-Eared Giant","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"2TWScGor6cjxO9GQ","name":"The Elephant-Eared Giant - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a huge Giant of herculean strength, I \nhave no natural predators on the island. I consider all creatures smaller than me to be weak, and I am not afraid that \nthey will harm me.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 155.","positive":"I am a huge Giant of herculean strength, I \nhave no natural predators on the island. I consider all creatures smaller than me to be weak, and I am not afraid that \nthey will harm me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642301,"modifiedTime":1781557642301,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3LjYFSCqfTH3Mcs1","name":"Gift - Elephant Ears","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>As a free action, the Giant can use \nits massive ears to create a gust of wind capable of hurling \na human thirty feet. The gust affects 2 targets and can be \navoided with a Defense Check. If someone is pushed back, \nroll 1 die: \n1-2: Loses an Equipment.\n3-4: Suffers 1 Wound.\n5-6: Ends up in impassable terrain, requiring a Check to \nget out. \n5A An Old Bride\nThe story that led us here...\nThe ship lands on a large island that is familiar to Sinbad. \nThe old sailor goes down with some of his crew to resupply, \nbut only one of his men returns. The survivor tells the Hunters that Sinbad once married the daughter of the island’s king, \nbut she died shortly after the wedding. According to local tradition, Sinbad was buried alive with his bride to be united \nwith her forever. The cunning traveler, however, managed to \nescape, and now that more than fifty years had passed, he believed that all had been forgotten by the new ruler. But to his \nastonishment, Sinbad and his people found themselves in the \npresence of a centenarian king who did not hesitate to return \npoor Sinbad to the tomb of his wife. \nPlace: A large pyramid-shaped tomb not far from the \ntown where the island’s ruler resides.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 155.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642301,"modifiedTime":1781557642301,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TrUXn7k3PotzI5hZ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a huge Giant of herculean strength, I \nhave no natural predators on the island. I consider all creatures smaller than me to be weak, and I am not afraid that \nthey will harm me.\nGift - Elephant Ears: As a free action, the Giant can use \nits massive ears to create a gust of wind capable of hurling \na human thirty feet. The gust affects 2 targets and can be \navoided with a Defense Check. If someone is pushed back, \nroll 1 die: \n1-2: Loses an Equipment.\n3-4: Suffers 1 Wound.\n5-6: Ends up in impassable terrain, requiring a Check to \nget out. \n5A An Old Bride\nThe story that led us here...\nThe ship lands on a large island that is familiar to Sinbad. \nThe old sailor goes down with some of his crew to resupply, \nbut only one of his men returns. The survivor tells the Hunters that Sinbad once married the daughter of the island’s king, \nbut she died shortly after the wedding. According to local tradition, Sinbad was buried alive with his bride to be united \nwith her forever. The cunning traveler, however, managed to \nescape, and now that more than fifty years had passed, he believed that all had been forgotten by the new ruler. But to his \nastonishment, Sinbad and his people found themselves in the \npresence of a centenarian king who did not hesitate to return \npoor Sinbad to the tomb of his wife. \nPlace: A large pyramid-shaped tomb not far from the \ntown where the island’s ruler resides. \nInformation: The tomb is protected by a notorious order \nof Guardians who are said to devour intruders alive. \nChallenges: The tomb is patrolled by over a hundred \nGuardians. Entering it requires some sort of distraction. \nOn the east side of the tomb, there is a crack in the wall \nthrough which a person can safely pass. While waiting for \nit to be repaired, a team of six Guardians stands watch by \nthe wall. The king is the only one who insists on enforcing</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 155."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642301,"modifiedTime":1781557642301,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-the-elephant-eared-giant-155","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":155,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a huge Giant of herculean strength, I \nhave no natural predators on the island. I consider all creatures smaller than me to be weak, and I am not afraid that \nthey will harm me.\nGift - Elephant Ears: As a free action, the Giant can use \nits massive ears to create a gust of wind capable of hurling \na human thirty feet. The gust affects 2 targets and can be \navoided with a Defense Check. If someone is pushed back, \nroll 1 die: \n1-2: Loses an Equipment.\n3-4: Suffers 1 Wound.\n5-6: Ends up in impassable terrain, requiring a Check to \nget out. \n5A An Old Bride\nThe story that led us here...\nThe ship lands on a large island that is familiar to Sinbad. \nThe old sailor goes down with some of his crew to resupply, \nbut only one of his men returns. The survivor tells the Hunters that Sinbad once married the daughter of the island’s king, \nbut she died shortly after the wedding. According to local tradition, Sinbad was buried alive with his bride to be united \nwith her forever. The cunning traveler, however, managed to \nescape, and now that more than fifty years had passed, he believed that all had been forgotten by the new ruler. But to his \nastonishment, Sinbad and his people found themselves in the \npresence of a centenarian king who did not hesitate to return \npoor Sinbad to the tomb of his wife. \nPlace: A large pyramid-shaped tomb not far from the \ntown where the island’s ruler resides. \nInformation: The tomb is protected by a notorious order \nof Guardians who are said to devour intruders alive. \nChallenges: The tomb is patrolled by over a hundred \nGuardians. Entering it requires some sort of distraction. \nOn the east side of the tomb, there is a crack in the wall \nthrough which a person can safely pass. While waiting for \nit to be repaired, a team of six Guardians stands watch by \nthe wall. The king is the only one who insists on enforcing</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642301,"modifiedTime":1781557642301,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"rLrvmvHW6gjuzl3J","name":"5: Usko","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"RnjHeodlxGZkLmrP","name":"5: Usko - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a prospector and direct the \nwork of recovering metals from the big river \neast of Rovaniemi.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 119.","positive":"I am a prospector and direct the \nwork of recovering metals from the big river \neast of Rovaniemi.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640550,"modifiedTime":1781557640550,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2DEMuAedX2Y5sKsD","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 \nWounds)\nDescriptor: I am a prospector and direct the \nwork of recovering metals from the big river \neast of Rovaniemi.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 119."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640550,"modifiedTime":1781557640550,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-5-usko-119","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":119,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 \nWounds)\nDescriptor: I am a prospector and direct the \nwork of recovering metals from the big river \neast of Rovaniemi.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640550,"modifiedTime":1781557640550,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"rQHWHqCHebYyHVce","name":"Warden Casket","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"7xpGerZmaKbW8Sum","name":"Warden Casket - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a fierce Warden Casket, ready to bite any \nthief with my sharp teeth. I am very sensitive to bad smells, \nwhich makes me sneeze until I vomit my contents.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 207.","positive":"I am a fierce Warden Casket, ready to bite any \nthief with my sharp teeth. I am very sensitive to bad smells, \nwhich makes me sneeze until I vomit my contents.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645098,"modifiedTime":1781557645098,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"t2KHpykujDVy7gLt","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fierce Warden Casket, ready to bite any \nthief with my sharp teeth. I am very sensitive to bad smells, \nwhich makes me sneeze until I vomit my contents. \nInformation: Flora’s diary describes Gerda and Kay, two \ncriminals who proposed the Frozen Madness scam to Flora. Flora seems to have agreed mainly to take revenge on an \nold rival of hers, a witch named Lady Storm. The contact \nbetween Flora and the two criminals was facilitated by a \nwoman named Lene, who is identified in the diary as Ger -\nda’s mother. Flora reports that she is not too happy about \ninvolving so many innocent people in this plan, but the \nchance to teach the arrogant and haughty Lady Storm a \nlesson was too good to pass up. Flora does not trust Gerda \nand Kay, but she does not believe that the two criminals can \npose any real danger to her. \nStoreroom\nDescriptor: A small room filled with books, gardening \ntools, and strange vials.\nInformation: Hidden among the many stacked objects it \nis possible to find a Treasure of the Order. The Storyteller is \nfree to decide which one.\nThe Greenhouse\nDescriptor: A large greenhouse filled with vegetation. A \nthick mist of pollen chokes those who walk through the rows \nof plants and flowers with its smell. \nInformation: Flora has taken up residence in the Greenhouse, where she repeats the same tasks over and over \nagain. Without her careful oversight, many of the plants \nhave grown beyond control, and the ecosystem of the place \nhas become mixed with the witch’s out-of-control magic. \nMoving inside the Greenhouse activates the Threat - Magic \nGreenhouse. Flora is in the center of it and will not move \nunder any circumstances.\nThreat - Magic Greenhouse</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 207."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645098,"modifiedTime":1781557645098,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-warden-casket-207","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":207,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fierce Warden Casket, ready to bite any \nthief with my sharp teeth. I am very sensitive to bad smells, \nwhich makes me sneeze until I vomit my contents. \nInformation: Flora’s diary describes Gerda and Kay, two \ncriminals who proposed the Frozen Madness scam to Flora. Flora seems to have agreed mainly to take revenge on an \nold rival of hers, a witch named Lady Storm. The contact \nbetween Flora and the two criminals was facilitated by a \nwoman named Lene, who is identified in the diary as Ger -\nda’s mother. Flora reports that she is not too happy about \ninvolving so many innocent people in this plan, but the \nchance to teach the arrogant and haughty Lady Storm a \nlesson was too good to pass up. Flora does not trust Gerda \nand Kay, but she does not believe that the two criminals can \npose any real danger to her. \nStoreroom\nDescriptor: A small room filled with books, gardening \ntools, and strange vials.\nInformation: Hidden among the many stacked objects it \nis possible to find a Treasure of the Order. The Storyteller is \nfree to decide which one.\nThe Greenhouse\nDescriptor: A large greenhouse filled with vegetation. A \nthick mist of pollen chokes those who walk through the rows \nof plants and flowers with its smell. \nInformation: Flora has taken up residence in the Greenhouse, where she repeats the same tasks over and over \nagain. Without her careful oversight, many of the plants \nhave grown beyond control, and the ecosystem of the place \nhas become mixed with the witch’s out-of-control magic. \nMoving inside the Greenhouse activates the Threat - Magic \nGreenhouse. Flora is in the center of it and will not move \nunder any circumstances.\nThreat - Magic Greenhouse</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645098,"modifiedTime":1781557645098,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"rY1ZaY9BaOxbIabI","name":"The Eyes of the Order are men and women of faith who gather useful clues to ferret out hum","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"AyRru6l3n76ZAVfp","name":"The Eyes of the Order are men and women of faith who gather useful clues to ferret out hum - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a skilled spy in the service of the Papacy \nand can assume different identities as needed. I do not like \ndirect action and prefer to support the Hunters from behind \nthe scenes.</p>","notes":"Rome, City of the Order - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 59.","positive":"I am a skilled spy in the service of the Papacy \nand can assume different identities as needed. I do not like \ndirect action and prefer to support the Hunters from behind \nthe scenes.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638197,"modifiedTime":1781557638197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0GokxLz03ibo7g43","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled spy in the service of the Papacy \nand can assume different identities as needed. I do not like \ndirect action and prefer to support the Hunters from behind \nthe scenes.\nAgenda: Gather all possible information about secrets and \ncuriosities to report to the Order.\nGift - Thousand Faces: An Eye of Order can change \ntheir identity by disguising themselves to appear as an ordinary villager or play any other social role. While disguised \nor hidden, an Eye of Order increases their OL by 1 on all \nChecks made to detect them.</p>","notes":"Rome, City of the Order - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 59."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638197,"modifiedTime":1781557638197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-rome-city-of-the-order-the-eyes-of-the-order-are-men-and-women-of-faith-who-gather-useful-clues-to-ferret-out-hum-59","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"rome-city-of-the-order","adventureTitle":"Rome, City of the Order","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":59,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Rome, City of the Order","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a skilled spy in the service of the Papacy \nand can assume different identities as needed. I do not like \ndirect action and prefer to support the Hunters from behind \nthe scenes.\nAgenda: Gather all possible information about secrets and \ncuriosities to report to the Order.\nGift - Thousand Faces: An Eye of Order can change \ntheir identity by disguising themselves to appear as an ordinary villager or play any other social role. While disguised \nor hidden, an Eye of Order increases their OL by 1 on all \nChecks made to detect them.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Gather all possible information about secrets and \ncuriosities to report to the Order.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638197,"modifiedTime":1781557638197,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"rhBwxK3e2jqlz12K","name":"Brigit the Cook","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"1Fvm19dAk6P7H781","name":"Brigit the Cook - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a good cook, the best. I love my tavern \nand can’t stand any argument between my tables. \nThe Old Barracks\nDescriptor: A dirty old building where soldiers on leave \ncan sleep for free.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 141.","positive":"I am a good cook, the best. I love my tavern \nand can’t stand any argument between my tables. \nThe Old Barracks\nDescriptor: A dirty old building where soldiers on leave \ncan sleep for free.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641651,"modifiedTime":1781557641651,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fAkuoLbrxrmUjSJi","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a good cook, the best. I love my tavern \nand can’t stand any argument between my tables. \nThe Old Barracks\nDescriptor: A dirty old building where soldiers on leave \ncan sleep for free.\nInformation: Bastian sleeps in the Old Barracks, but \nhas never told anyone about it because it would damage \nthe image of wealth and prosperity he is trying to build \nin Alena’s eyes. Bastian has joined forces with four other \ndeserters who will help him in his plan to rob Villa Wagner. In the Barracks, many people know Bastian and will \ndescribe him as a blowhard, but too stupid to actually \namount to anything.\nIf Bastian is present: At night, Bastian sleeps in a secret room on the second floor of the building. If discovered, he will try to escape by throwing himself out the \nwindow to cause a Reset.\nAfter any Reset caused in this Place: Bastian will \nnot go back to sleep but will use Ulrich to send messages \nto his co-conspirators.\nBritta’s House\nDescriptor: A small abandoned house near the gra -\nveyard. In the garden, in the middle of a vegetable patch \nand near a well, there is an old hollow tree with no leaves.\nInformation: The Hollow Tree in the garden hides a \nburrow that leads to a series of Caves. Descending into \nthe Caves, Hunters can find Britta’s decapitated body. The \nwitch’s spirit is still bound to the body, but the only way to \ncommunicate with her is with a Gift that allows it. In the \nlittle house, Hunters can find Britta’s diary open on the \nkitchen table. In the diary, the witch describes in detail</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 141."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641651,"modifiedTime":1781557641651,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-brigit-the-cook-141","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":141,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a good cook, the best. I love my tavern \nand can’t stand any argument between my tables. \nThe Old Barracks\nDescriptor: A dirty old building where soldiers on leave \ncan sleep for free.\nInformation: Bastian sleeps in the Old Barracks, but \nhas never told anyone about it because it would damage \nthe image of wealth and prosperity he is trying to build \nin Alena’s eyes. Bastian has joined forces with four other \ndeserters who will help him in his plan to rob Villa Wagner. In the Barracks, many people know Bastian and will \ndescribe him as a blowhard, but too stupid to actually \namount to anything.\nIf Bastian is present: At night, Bastian sleeps in a secret room on the second floor of the building. If discovered, he will try to escape by throwing himself out the \nwindow to cause a Reset.\nAfter any Reset caused in this Place: Bastian will \nnot go back to sleep but will use Ulrich to send messages \nto his co-conspirators.\nBritta’s House\nDescriptor: A small abandoned house near the gra -\nveyard. In the garden, in the middle of a vegetable patch \nand near a well, there is an old hollow tree with no leaves.\nInformation: The Hollow Tree in the garden hides a \nburrow that leads to a series of Caves. Descending into \nthe Caves, Hunters can find Britta’s decapitated body. The \nwitch’s spirit is still bound to the body, but the only way to \ncommunicate with her is with a Gift that allows it. In the \nlittle house, Hunters can find Britta’s diary open on the \nkitchen table. In the diary, the witch describes in detail</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641651,"modifiedTime":1781557641651,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ryp8y4IAJmHJYzmM","name":"Medoro The Old Bear","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"WwsCZFKNtDZegjRg","name":"Medoro The Old Bear - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its \nfur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I am happy to \nserve her. I have retained most of my bestial strength, despite \nmy age.\nThe Villa\nDescriptor: A large manor house, once flamboyant, but \nnow covered in dust and mold.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 138.","positive":"I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its \nfur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I am happy to \nserve her. I have retained most of my bestial strength, despite \nmy age.\nThe Villa\nDescriptor: A large manor house, once flamboyant, but \nnow covered in dust and mold.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621890,"modifiedTime":1781557621890,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"giyc3XeO0t2YNFk8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its \nfur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I am happy to \nserve her. I have retained most of my bestial strength, despite \nmy age.\nThe Villa\nDescriptor: A large manor house, once flamboyant, but \nnow covered in dust and mold. \nInformation: \n ◆ Azzurra is wandering around the Villa and will not \nhesitate to appear and confront intruders.\n ◆ In the dining room, there is a huge painting on the \nnorth wall depicting a whale swallowing an entire \nship. By looking behind the painting, the Hunters can \nactivate the mechanism which opens the secret door to \naccess the Secret Laboratory.\n ◆ The remaining 4 Marionettes covered in human skin \nroam around the Villa, but they only act on Azzurra’s \norders.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 138."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621890,"modifiedTime":1781557621890,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-medoro-the-old-bear-138","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":138,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its \nfur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I am happy to \nserve her. I have retained most of my bestial strength, despite \nmy age.\nThe Villa\nDescriptor: A large manor house, once flamboyant, but \nnow covered in dust and mold. \nInformation: \n ◆ Azzurra is wandering around the Villa and will not \nhesitate to appear and confront intruders.\n ◆ In the dining room, there is a huge painting on the \nnorth wall depicting a whale swallowing an entire \nship. By looking behind the painting, the Hunters can \nactivate the mechanism which opens the secret door to \naccess the Secret Laboratory.\n ◆ The remaining 4 Marionettes covered in human skin \nroam around the Villa, but they only act on Azzurra’s \norders.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621890,"modifiedTime":1781557621890,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"rzds0J3XPXmv4O7p","name":"Alena Wagner","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"7P66f4uE6yLsxE1y","name":"Alena Wagner - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the young scion of the Wagner family. I \nlove adventure and romance novels. I’m cultured and dream \nof becoming a teacher one day.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 139.","positive":"I am the young scion of the Wagner family. I \nlove adventure and romance novels. I’m cultured and dream \nof becoming a teacher one day.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641606,"modifiedTime":1781557641606,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ABsEbcbhGesjWvV5","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young scion of the Wagner family. I \nlove adventure and romance novels. I’m cultured and dream \nof becoming a teacher one day. \nAgenda: To have a good adventure like the ones I read \nabout in novels.\nWagner Treasury\nDescriptor: A small fortified tower connected to \nthe Villa by an underground tunnel. Aside from the \ntunnel, the only way to access the tower is to know \nthe combination of the large metal door that \nblocks the main entrance.\nInformation: The Treasury is permanently \nmanned by 4 Guards who change shifts every \neight hours.\nFirst, Second, and Third Reset: Bastian</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 139."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641606,"modifiedTime":1781557641606,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-alena-wagner-139","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":139,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the young scion of the Wagner family. I \nlove adventure and romance novels. I’m cultured and dream \nof becoming a teacher one day. \nAgenda: To have a good adventure like the ones I read \nabout in novels.\nWagner Treasury\nDescriptor: A small fortified tower connected to \nthe Villa by an underground tunnel. Aside from the \ntunnel, the only way to access the tower is to know \nthe combination of the large metal door that \nblocks the main entrance.\nInformation: The Treasury is permanently \nmanned by 4 Guards who change shifts every \neight hours.\nFirst, Second, and Third Reset: Bastian</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"To have a good adventure like the ones I read \nabout in novels.\nWagner Treasury\nDescriptor: A small fortified tower connected to \nthe Villa by an underground tunnel. Aside from the \ntunnel, the only way to access the tower is to know \nthe combination of the large metal door that \nblocks the main entrance.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641606,"modifiedTime":1781557641606,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"sA8gseJZkSxDxqyt","name":"Guinevere the Fugitive","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"E5yBVYtfOPOWab8u","name":"Guinevere the Fugitive - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the queen of Camelot, and my good heart \nis matched only by my beauty.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 186.","positive":"I am the queen of Camelot, and my good heart \nis matched only by my beauty.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643894,"modifiedTime":1781557643894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9CAc28i1UsQ2X151","name":"Gift - Virtue of Love","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Imbued with the power of the Virtue of Love, Guinevere cannot be killed: when she reaches \n0 Wounds, she will fall into a state of apparent death, waking up fully healed at the end of the Scene. Guinevere will \ngive the power of her Virtue to those who show a sincere \ninterest in stopping Arthur’s madness: when this happens, \nthe Virtue transforms into a heart-shaped pendant. While \nimbued with the power of Virtue, Guinevere cannot be deceived in any way and will see everything for what it really \nis, breaking all magic and deception.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 186.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643894,"modifiedTime":1781557643894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tIprAGp7St9Y9o65","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the queen of Camelot, and my good heart \nis matched only by my beauty.\nAgenda: To find a cure for the madness that has taken hold \nof my beloved Arthur. \nGift - Virtue of Love: Imbued with the power of the Virtue of Love, Guinevere cannot be killed: when she reaches \n0 Wounds, she will fall into a state of apparent death, waking up fully healed at the end of the Scene. Guinevere will \ngive the power of her Virtue to those who show a sincere \ninterest in stopping Arthur’s madness: when this happens, \nthe Virtue transforms into a heart-shaped pendant. While \nimbued with the power of Virtue, Guinevere cannot be deceived in any way and will see everything for what it really \nis, breaking all magic and deception.\nInformation: Guinevere poses as a common Villager, \nthough her noble features are hard to hide. Guinevere is \naware that Arthur has gone mad because he has lost his \nVirtues. Indeed, the woman is seeking help and will not \nhesitate to reveal herself to the Hunters if they prove trustworthy.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 186."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643894,"modifiedTime":1781557643894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-guinevere-the-fugitive-186","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":186,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the queen of Camelot, and my good heart \nis matched only by my beauty.\nAgenda: To find a cure for the madness that has taken hold \nof my beloved Arthur. \nGift - Virtue of Love: Imbued with the power of the Virtue of Love, Guinevere cannot be killed: when she reaches \n0 Wounds, she will fall into a state of apparent death, waking up fully healed at the end of the Scene. Guinevere will \ngive the power of her Virtue to those who show a sincere \ninterest in stopping Arthur’s madness: when this happens, \nthe Virtue transforms into a heart-shaped pendant. While \nimbued with the power of Virtue, Guinevere cannot be deceived in any way and will see everything for what it really \nis, breaking all magic and deception.\nInformation: Guinevere poses as a common Villager, \nthough her noble features are hard to hide. Guinevere is \naware that Arthur has gone mad because he has lost his \nVirtues. Indeed, the woman is seeking help and will not \nhesitate to reveal herself to the Hunters if they prove trustworthy.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To find a cure for the madness that has taken hold \nof my beloved Arthur.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643894,"modifiedTime":1781557643894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"sLUiuETmHESMEZVo","name":"Lowe the Coward Henchman","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"DKyA1asoHpsE0KIP","name":"Lowe the Coward Henchman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I’m an eternal coward \nwho has been given a monstrous aspect \nby fate. I can adapt to any situation \nand am quick to jump to the winning \nside.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 226.","positive":"I’m an eternal coward \nwho has been given a monstrous aspect \nby fate. I can adapt to any situation \nand am quick to jump to the winning \nside.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ZbkukJf8bpnk7gx9","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I’m an eternal coward \nwho has been given a monstrous aspect \nby fate. I can adapt to any situation \nand am quick to jump to the winning \nside.\nAgenda: To help Dorothea in her \nmission, with the hope of recovering \nfrom my condition / Save my life, no \nmatter who I have to betray.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 226."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-lowe-the-coward-henchman-226","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":226,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC \n(2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I’m an eternal coward \nwho has been given a monstrous aspect \nby fate. I can adapt to any situation \nand am quick to jump to the winning \nside.\nAgenda: To help Dorothea in her \nmission, with the hope of recovering \nfrom my condition / Save my life, no \nmatter who I have to betray.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To help Dorothea in her \nmission, with the hope of recovering \nfrom my condition / Save my life, no \nmatter who I have to betray.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624255,"modifiedTime":1781557624255,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"sWEBU01G9L79djoa","name":"The Ice Heart","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"QsxbsHnSYUZaZr47","name":"The Ice Heart - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a fragment of pure power and live only \nto punish all humans guilty of hurting my Lady Storm. I am \nthe castle and within it, all is in my power. I have no human \nmalice and speak my mind without a filter.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 225.","positive":"I am a fragment of pure power and live only \nto punish all humans guilty of hurting my Lady Storm. I am \nthe castle and within it, all is in my power. I have no human \nmalice and speak my mind without a filter.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646239,"modifiedTime":1781557646239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KDsMOW7cAiNhTGHs","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fragment of pure power and live only \nto punish all humans guilty of hurting my Lady Storm. I am \nthe castle and within it, all is in my power. I have no human \nmalice and speak my mind without a filter. \nAgenda: Punish Gerda for what she did to Lady Storm / \nPunish humanity and freeze it in eternal ice. \nGift - I Am Winter: The Ice Heart is a manifestation of \npower and can manipulate anything within the castle. As \nan action, the Heart can inflict 1Wound from cold on any \nsubject in the castle without the ability to make a Defense \nCheck. The only safe place in the castle is the Library, where \nthe Heart’s power cannot reach because of the seal Gerda \ncreated. A sincere expression of love or friendship in the \npresence of the Ice Heart can immediately shatter and destroy it.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 225."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646239,"modifiedTime":1781557646239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-the-ice-heart-225","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":225,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fragment of pure power and live only \nto punish all humans guilty of hurting my Lady Storm. I am \nthe castle and within it, all is in my power. I have no human \nmalice and speak my mind without a filter. \nAgenda: Punish Gerda for what she did to Lady Storm / \nPunish humanity and freeze it in eternal ice. \nGift - I Am Winter: The Ice Heart is a manifestation of \npower and can manipulate anything within the castle. As \nan action, the Heart can inflict 1Wound from cold on any \nsubject in the castle without the ability to make a Defense \nCheck. The only safe place in the castle is the Library, where \nthe Heart’s power cannot reach because of the seal Gerda \ncreated. A sincere expression of love or friendship in the \npresence of the Ice Heart can immediately shatter and destroy it.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Punish Gerda for what she did to Lady Storm / \nPunish humanity and freeze it in eternal ice.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557646239,"modifiedTime":1781557646239,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"snbKEa22mAGkuDRa","name":"OZena (Dorothea)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"VdPPhUVHR3e10BP9","name":"OZena (Dorothea) - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young girl who wants to return to \nher world. The disease that afflicts me has ruined my face \nand with it all the hopes of a normal life. I am willing to do \nanything to heal, which is why I became a witch killer.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 229.","positive":"I am a young girl who wants to return to \nher world. The disease that afflicts me has ruined my face \nand with it all the hopes of a normal life. I am willing to do \nanything to heal, which is why I became a witch killer.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624341,"modifiedTime":1781557624341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7JaUZZBiI7hHNaY9","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young girl who wants to return to \nher world. The disease that afflicts me has ruined my face \nand with it all the hopes of a normal life. I am willing to do \nanything to heal, which is why I became a witch killer.\nAgenda: Kill every witch Henkle points out to me and \nretrieve all four pieces of the Compass Rose.\nGift - The Silver Slippers: The wearer of this magical \nartifact can move through folds in space, disappearing and \nreappearing in a flash. Dorothea can move freely up to a \nmaximum distance of thirty feet without anyone preventing \nher, but she must be able to see the point of arrival. Once \nper Scene, Dorothea can take a longer journey and reappear \nin any place she has seen at least once.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 229."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624341,"modifiedTime":1781557624341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-ozena-dorothea-229","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":229,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young girl who wants to return to \nher world. The disease that afflicts me has ruined my face \nand with it all the hopes of a normal life. I am willing to do \nanything to heal, which is why I became a witch killer.\nAgenda: Kill every witch Henkle points out to me and \nretrieve all four pieces of the Compass Rose.\nGift - The Silver Slippers: The wearer of this magical \nartifact can move through folds in space, disappearing and \nreappearing in a flash. Dorothea can move freely up to a \nmaximum distance of thirty feet without anyone preventing \nher, but she must be able to see the point of arrival. Once \nper Scene, Dorothea can take a longer journey and reappear \nin any place she has seen at least once.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Kill every witch Henkle points out to me and \nretrieve all four pieces of the Compass Rose.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624341,"modifiedTime":1781557624341,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"sox8SkLT6YEavjmR","name":"Aladdin the Mad Sultan","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"n9xDarZyyXcJ4c6O","name":"Aladdin the Mad Sultan - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am drunk with the power the lamp gives me \nand I demand that the whole world do as I command. I have \na background as a street thief and know all the tricks of the \ntrade.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 160.","positive":"I am drunk with the power the lamp gives me \nand I demand that the whole world do as I command. I have \na background as a street thief and know all the tricks of the \ntrade.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642505,"modifiedTime":1781557642505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"JoETxcBKeeEhEaqy","name":"Gift - Wishing Lamp","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Whatever Aladdin wishes for will \nbe granted by the Djinn who lives in the lamp. As an action, \nAladdin can rub the lamp and ask for the following wishes:\n1. Eliminate: (as an action) The target is somehow \nknocked out and suffers all the remaining Wounds, or is \nteleported to a place where they cannot harm Aladdin. The \ntarget can make a Defense Check to avoid the effect of the \nwish, but will still take 1 Wound even if it succeeds.\n2. Create: (1 time per Scene) Aladdin creates up to 4 \nMonsters to do his bidding.\n3. Block: (as an action) Aladdin will remove the effect of \na spell or mind control from a subject. Alternatively, he can \nprevent the use of a Gift that he has already seen in action \nin the Scene.\nAladdin has already made some wishes to make himself \nmore powerful, so he can act up to 3 times in an Exchange \n(but not back-to-back).\nCity Guards</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 160.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642505,"modifiedTime":1781557642505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"L4XRSVeqEWWOoBhL","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am drunk with the power the lamp gives me \nand I demand that the whole world do as I command. I have \na background as a street thief and know all the tricks of the \ntrade. \nAgenda: To find something to kill my terrible boredom.\nGift - Wishing Lamp: Whatever Aladdin wishes for will \nbe granted by the Djinn who lives in the lamp. As an action, \nAladdin can rub the lamp and ask for the following wishes:\n1. Eliminate: (as an action) The target is somehow \nknocked out and suffers all the remaining Wounds, or is \nteleported to a place where they cannot harm Aladdin. The \ntarget can make a Defense Check to avoid the effect of the \nwish, but will still take 1 Wound even if it succeeds.\n2. Create: (1 time per Scene) Aladdin creates up to 4 \nMonsters to do his bidding.\n3. Block: (as an action) Aladdin will remove the effect of \na spell or mind control from a subject. Alternatively, he can \nprevent the use of a Gift that he has already seen in action \nin the Scene.\nAladdin has already made some wishes to make himself \nmore powerful, so he can act up to 3 times in an Exchange \n(but not back-to-back).\nCity Guards</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 160."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642505,"modifiedTime":1781557642505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-aladdin-the-mad-sultan-160","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":160,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am drunk with the power the lamp gives me \nand I demand that the whole world do as I command. I have \na background as a street thief and know all the tricks of the \ntrade. \nAgenda: To find something to kill my terrible boredom.\nGift - Wishing Lamp: Whatever Aladdin wishes for will \nbe granted by the Djinn who lives in the lamp. As an action, \nAladdin can rub the lamp and ask for the following wishes:\n1. Eliminate: (as an action) The target is somehow \nknocked out and suffers all the remaining Wounds, or is \nteleported to a place where they cannot harm Aladdin. The \ntarget can make a Defense Check to avoid the effect of the \nwish, but will still take 1 Wound even if it succeeds.\n2. Create: (1 time per Scene) Aladdin creates up to 4 \nMonsters to do his bidding.\n3. Block: (as an action) Aladdin will remove the effect of \na spell or mind control from a subject. Alternatively, he can \nprevent the use of a Gift that he has already seen in action \nin the Scene.\nAladdin has already made some wishes to make himself \nmore powerful, so he can act up to 3 times in an Exchange \n(but not back-to-back).\nCity Guards</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To find something to kill my terrible boredom.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642505,"modifiedTime":1781557642505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"t6XKWn7xYmosypDY","name":"Nicholas the Huntsman","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"UCRMs9eq30HszBuM","name":"Nicholas the Huntsman - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to \nshow off in front of Baron Gerard.\n3 Genevieve the Chemist</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","positive":"I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to \nshow off in front of Baron Gerard.\n3 Genevieve the Chemist","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dx2t3KLKYynEx2d6","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to \nshow off in front of Baron Gerard.\n3 Genevieve the Chemist</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-nicholas-the-huntsman-123","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":123,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to \nshow off in front of Baron Gerard.\n3 Genevieve the Chemist</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"tNqHtihrJCAJp5xF","name":"Aleksander Okland","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"abbDQ7s4Q9Uxs0Pp","name":"Aleksander Okland - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I use my position to help \nall unfortunate people. I can’t stand the bullying of the weak by the powerful, \nand I strive to change society so that everything is more equal.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 205.","positive":"I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I use my position to help \nall unfortunate people. I can’t stand the bullying of the weak by the powerful, \nand I strive to change society so that everything is more equal.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645007,"modifiedTime":1781557645007,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QdncmmGzx7SAtgsK","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I use my position to help \nall unfortunate people. I can’t stand the bullying of the weak by the powerful, \nand I strive to change society so that everything is more equal. \nAgenda: Helping others find their way and realize their plans. \nShard Descriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I use my \nposition to bend everyone to my command. I can’t stand to be told no, and I \nabuse all the people I consider inferior.\nShard Agenda: Satisfying my thirst for power by crushing those who are \nweaker. \nGift - Power of the Shard: The Shard of the Mirror of the Other Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the person it injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they act in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor or Agenda. \nEnd of Scene: The Hunters must decide whether to contact Flora or the \nBlack Feathers through Lene. Go to SECOND SCENE OPTION A - Flora’s \nGreenhouse or SECOND SCENE OPTION B - Lene’s House.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 205."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645007,"modifiedTime":1781557645007,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-aleksander-okland-205","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":205,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I use my position to help \nall unfortunate people. I can’t stand the bullying of the weak by the powerful, \nand I strive to change society so that everything is more equal. \nAgenda: Helping others find their way and realize their plans. \nShard Descriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I use my \nposition to bend everyone to my command. I can’t stand to be told no, and I \nabuse all the people I consider inferior.\nShard Agenda: Satisfying my thirst for power by crushing those who are \nweaker. \nGift - Power of the Shard: The Shard of the Mirror of the Other Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the person it injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they act in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor or Agenda. \nEnd of Scene: The Hunters must decide whether to contact Flora or the \nBlack Feathers through Lene. Go to SECOND SCENE OPTION A - Flora’s \nGreenhouse or SECOND SCENE OPTION B - Lene’s House.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"Helping others find their way and realize their plans. \nShard Descriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I use my \nposition to bend everyone to my command. I can’t stand to be told no, and I \nabuse all the people I consider inferior.\nShard Agenda: Satisfying my thirst for power by crushing those who are \nweaker.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645007,"modifiedTime":1781557645007,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"tdLgvr1dRa7rO0Nz","name":"The Furious Djinn","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"q3ayrswfjUh1cCny","name":"The Furious Djinn - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a powerful Djinn, skilled with a scimitar. \nI hate lies and those who break agreements.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 153.","positive":"I am a powerful Djinn, skilled with a scimitar. \nI hate lies and those who break agreements.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642170,"modifiedTime":1781557642170,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"v6Zp5EnJIFw2dbKr","name":"Gift - Frenzied","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>When the Djinn suffers 1 Wound, it can \nimmediately attack with its giant scimitar to strike the one \nwho did the damage. \n2A The Island Fish\nThe story that led us here...\nSinbad’s ship has docked at a large island dense with plants \nthat bear delicious fruits. The entire crew has gone ashore to \nresupply, but what no one can imagine is that this lush land is \nactually resting on the back of a giant, sleeping fish. While the \nsailors are busy harvesting fruit, the island begins to tremble \nand the land cracks. Sinbad begs the Hunters to save his men, \nor no one will be able to sail the ship to continue the journey. \n \nPlace: A large natural island filled with plants and fruits.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 153.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642170,"modifiedTime":1781557642170,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2NZpvgrfy4ZCdDOs","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful Djinn, skilled with a scimitar. \nI hate lies and those who break agreements.\nAgenda: To avenge my son’s death by punishing the Mer -\nchant who caused it. \nGift - Frenzied: When the Djinn suffers 1 Wound, it can \nimmediately attack with its giant scimitar to strike the one \nwho did the damage. \n2A The Island Fish\nThe story that led us here...\nSinbad’s ship has docked at a large island dense with plants \nthat bear delicious fruits. The entire crew has gone ashore to \nresupply, but what no one can imagine is that this lush land is \nactually resting on the back of a giant, sleeping fish. While the \nsailors are busy harvesting fruit, the island begins to tremble \nand the land cracks. Sinbad begs the Hunters to save his men, \nor no one will be able to sail the ship to continue the journey. \n \nPlace: A large natural island filled with plants and fruits. \nInformation: Sailors are divided into six groups, each in a \ndifferent part of the island. \nChallenges: Traveling by land is very dangerous due to the \nconstant movements of the Island Fish. When a group of \nsailors is rescued, roll 1 die: if you roll a 6, the sailors are \ncarrying a strange barrel found in the vegetation. If a 6 is \nnever rolled, the barrel is automatically in the hands of the \nsixth party.\nHow to get the Tarì: Found inside the barrel.\nThreat – The Island Fish</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 153."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642170,"modifiedTime":1781557642170,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-the-furious-djinn-153","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":153,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful Djinn, skilled with a scimitar. \nI hate lies and those who break agreements.\nAgenda: To avenge my son’s death by punishing the Mer -\nchant who caused it. \nGift - Frenzied: When the Djinn suffers 1 Wound, it can \nimmediately attack with its giant scimitar to strike the one \nwho did the damage. \n2A The Island Fish\nThe story that led us here...\nSinbad’s ship has docked at a large island dense with plants \nthat bear delicious fruits. The entire crew has gone ashore to \nresupply, but what no one can imagine is that this lush land is \nactually resting on the back of a giant, sleeping fish. While the \nsailors are busy harvesting fruit, the island begins to tremble \nand the land cracks. Sinbad begs the Hunters to save his men, \nor no one will be able to sail the ship to continue the journey. \n \nPlace: A large natural island filled with plants and fruits. \nInformation: Sailors are divided into six groups, each in a \ndifferent part of the island. \nChallenges: Traveling by land is very dangerous due to the \nconstant movements of the Island Fish. When a group of \nsailors is rescued, roll 1 die: if you roll a 6, the sailors are \ncarrying a strange barrel found in the vegetation. If a 6 is \nnever rolled, the barrel is automatically in the hands of the \nsixth party.\nHow to get the Tarì: Found inside the barrel.\nThreat – The Island Fish</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To avenge my son’s death by punishing the Mer -\nchant who caused it.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642170,"modifiedTime":1781557642170,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"twWKKGCHHiBdBoMn","name":"Head in the Clouds","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"i5peEw3n7cnaKMGv","name":"Head in the Clouds - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A dreamy spirit who cannot keep his attention on the living for more than a few seconds.\nIf the Hunters can get the spirit’s attention, he will tell them \nabout the strange, inky-handed figure who bought his \nmansion for far more than it was worth. After his death \n(which occurred when he fell out of the tree where he had \nmoved to live), the Baron wandered around the mansion \nand learned part of the magic formula to open the door. He \nwill also know the name of the alchemist who worked on \nthe door and who should know the rest of the formula. To \nget these two pieces of information, the Baron will ask the \nHunters to perform two missions for him.\nTo reveal the part of the formula he knows: He will \nask the Hunters to make sure one of his descendants is okay. \nThe Storyteller will describe a Minor NPC from a Scenario \nyet to be played, and create a problem about them that is \nrelated to the Hunters’ main antagonist in that context. If \nthe Hunters return the Baron’s relative safely to Rome, the \nspirit will reveal the first part of the formula: A Fairytale. \nTo know the identity of the creator of the door: The \nBaron will only make this request after the Hunters have \ncompleted the first task. The spirit will describe a Main \nNPC of a yet-to-be-played Scenario as the one who created the door. The Storyteller must edit the NPC’s profile to \ngive him a Descriptor or Gift that makes them a de facto \nalchemist capable of creating the door. The NPC in question, if convinced, will reveal the second part of the formula: Turned Upside Down.\nA note on the Baron’s spirit: Discovering the formula \nto open the Alchemical Door opens a direct route for the \nHunters to track down the One Who Plots in the Shadows. \nFor this reason, obtaining the two parts of the formula is \nvery important and has been tied to two playable Scenarios \nthat the Storyteller may propose as they see fit during the \ncourse of the Campaign, thus affecting the duration of the \nCampaign itself. \nIf Silvan is present: If the guide has already been to the \nAlchemical Door with the Hunters, he will recognize the \nspirit of the Baron and allow you to meet and talk to him \nwithout any Checks.</p>","notes":"Rome, City of the Order - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 68.","positive":"A dreamy spirit who cannot keep his attention on the living for more than a few seconds.\nIf the Hunters can get the spirit’s attention, he will tell them \nabout the strange, inky-handed figure who bought his \nmansion for far more than it was worth. After his death \n(which occurred when he fell out of the tree where he had \nmoved to live), the Baron wandered around the mansion \nand learned part of the magic formula to open the door. He \nwill also know the name of the alchemist who worked on \nthe door and who should know the rest of the formula. To \nget these two pieces of information, the Baron will ask the \nHunters to perform two missions for him.\nTo reveal the part of the formula he knows: He will \nask the Hunters to make sure one of his descendants is okay. \nThe Storyteller will describe a Minor NPC from a Scenario \nyet to be played, and create a problem about them that is \nrelated to the Hunters’ main antagonist in that context. If \nthe Hunters return the Baron’s relative safely to Rome, the \nspirit will reveal the first part of the formula: A Fairytale. \nTo know the identity of the creator of the door: The \nBaron will only make this request after the Hunters have \ncompleted the first task. The spirit will describe a Main \nNPC of a yet-to-be-played Scenario as the one who created the door. The Storyteller must edit the NPC’s profile to \ngive him a Descriptor or Gift that makes them a de facto \nalchemist capable of creating the door. The NPC in question, if convinced, will reveal the second part of the formula: Turned Upside Down.\nA note on the Baron’s spirit: Discovering the formula \nto open the Alchemical Door opens a direct route for the \nHunters to track down the One Who Plots in the Shadows. \nFor this reason, obtaining the two parts of the formula is \nvery important and has been tied to two playable Scenarios \nthat the Storyteller may propose as they see fit during the \ncourse of the Campaign, thus affecting the duration of the \nCampaign itself. \nIf Silvan is present: If the guide has already been to the \nAlchemical Door with the Hunters, he will recognize the \nspirit of the Baron and allow you to meet and talk to him \nwithout any Checks.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638487,"modifiedTime":1781557638487,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tkMgIalIPHqdlYqZ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A dreamy spirit who cannot keep his attention on the living for more than a few seconds.\nIf the Hunters can get the spirit’s attention, he will tell them \nabout the strange, inky-handed figure who bought his \nmansion for far more than it was worth. After his death \n(which occurred when he fell out of the tree where he had \nmoved to live), the Baron wandered around the mansion \nand learned part of the magic formula to open the door. He \nwill also know the name of the alchemist who worked on \nthe door and who should know the rest of the formula. To \nget these two pieces of information, the Baron will ask the \nHunters to perform two missions for him.\nTo reveal the part of the formula he knows: He will \nask the Hunters to make sure one of his descendants is okay. \nThe Storyteller will describe a Minor NPC from a Scenario \nyet to be played, and create a problem about them that is \nrelated to the Hunters’ main antagonist in that context. If \nthe Hunters return the Baron’s relative safely to Rome, the \nspirit will reveal the first part of the formula: A Fairytale. \nTo know the identity of the creator of the door: The \nBaron will only make this request after the Hunters have \ncompleted the first task. The spirit will describe a Main \nNPC of a yet-to-be-played Scenario as the one who created the door. The Storyteller must edit the NPC’s profile to \ngive him a Descriptor or Gift that makes them a de facto \nalchemist capable of creating the door. The NPC in question, if convinced, will reveal the second part of the formula: Turned Upside Down.\nA note on the Baron’s spirit: Discovering the formula \nto open the Alchemical Door opens a direct route for the \nHunters to track down the One Who Plots in the Shadows. \nFor this reason, obtaining the two parts of the formula is \nvery important and has been tied to two playable Scenarios \nthat the Storyteller may propose as they see fit during the \ncourse of the Campaign, thus affecting the duration of the \nCampaign itself. \nIf Silvan is present: If the guide has already been to the \nAlchemical Door with the Hunters, he will recognize the \nspirit of the Baron and allow you to meet and talk to him \nwithout any Checks.</p>","notes":"Rome, City of the Order - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 68."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638487,"modifiedTime":1781557638487,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-rome-city-of-the-order-head-in-the-clouds-68","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"rome-city-of-the-order","adventureTitle":"Rome, City of the Order","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":68,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Rome, City of the Order","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A dreamy spirit who cannot keep his attention on the living for more than a few seconds.\nIf the Hunters can get the spirit’s attention, he will tell them \nabout the strange, inky-handed figure who bought his \nmansion for far more than it was worth. After his death \n(which occurred when he fell out of the tree where he had \nmoved to live), the Baron wandered around the mansion \nand learned part of the magic formula to open the door. He \nwill also know the name of the alchemist who worked on \nthe door and who should know the rest of the formula. To \nget these two pieces of information, the Baron will ask the \nHunters to perform two missions for him.\nTo reveal the part of the formula he knows: He will \nask the Hunters to make sure one of his descendants is okay. \nThe Storyteller will describe a Minor NPC from a Scenario \nyet to be played, and create a problem about them that is \nrelated to the Hunters’ main antagonist in that context. If \nthe Hunters return the Baron’s relative safely to Rome, the \nspirit will reveal the first part of the formula: A Fairytale. \nTo know the identity of the creator of the door: The \nBaron will only make this request after the Hunters have \ncompleted the first task. The spirit will describe a Main \nNPC of a yet-to-be-played Scenario as the one who created the door. The Storyteller must edit the NPC’s profile to \ngive him a Descriptor or Gift that makes them a de facto \nalchemist capable of creating the door. The NPC in question, if convinced, will reveal the second part of the formula: Turned Upside Down.\nA note on the Baron’s spirit: Discovering the formula \nto open the Alchemical Door opens a direct route for the \nHunters to track down the One Who Plots in the Shadows. \nFor this reason, obtaining the two parts of the formula is \nvery important and has been tied to two playable Scenarios \nthat the Storyteller may propose as they see fit during the \ncourse of the Campaign, thus affecting the duration of the \nCampaign itself. \nIf Silvan is present: If the guide has already been to the \nAlchemical Door with the Hunters, he will recognize the \nspirit of the Baron and allow you to meet and talk to him \nwithout any Checks.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557638487,"modifiedTime":1781557638487,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"tyxiOi2mO1T1X5aY","name":"Dirana the Faithful Slave","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"9dTqBdlB0SZjMRcD","name":"Dirana the Faithful Slave - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a fighting slave and fear nothing and no \none. My kicks can even cut through metal as if it were plain \npaper.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 162.","positive":"I am a fighting slave and fear nothing and no \none. My kicks can even cut through metal as if it were plain \npaper.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642567,"modifiedTime":1781557642567,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"stnUxJ7aVLvDsLYy","name":"Gift - Death Machine","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>As deadly as she is agile, Dirana \ncan act 2 times during an Exchange. \nThe Thieves</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 162.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642567,"modifiedTime":1781557642567,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ImG5I9ZSVxOSH5OQ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fighting slave and fear nothing and no \none. My kicks can even cut through metal as if it were plain \npaper.\nAgenda: Baba saved my life and now I will do the same to \nrepay him. \nGift - Death Machine: As deadly as she is agile, Dirana \ncan act 2 times during an Exchange. \nThe Thieves</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 162."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642567,"modifiedTime":1781557642567,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-dirana-the-faithful-slave-162","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":162,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a fighting slave and fear nothing and no \none. My kicks can even cut through metal as if it were plain \npaper.\nAgenda: Baba saved my life and now I will do the same to \nrepay him. \nGift - Death Machine: As deadly as she is agile, Dirana \ncan act 2 times during an Exchange. \nThe Thieves</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Baba saved my life and now I will do the same to \nrepay him.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642567,"modifiedTime":1781557642567,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uAa26FLFmPmES1H8","name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"HoBp42ZvW280Sopa","name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Everyone thinks I’m crazy and maybe they’re \nright. I don’t feel any fear and I can see beneath the surface of \nthose who pretend they are normal.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 228.","positive":"Everyone thinks I’m crazy and maybe they’re \nright. I don’t feel any fear and I can see beneath the surface of \nthose who pretend they are normal.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624309,"modifiedTime":1781557624309,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"nxx7sIfMR9VU5rC4","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: Everyone thinks I’m crazy and maybe they’re \nright. I don’t feel any fear and I can see beneath the surface of \nthose who pretend they are normal.\nAgenda: I follow OZena because I can see past her pain. \nThere is another world, the one where she comes from and \nwhere I want to go too.\nEnd of Scene: Margareta asks the Hunters to save little \nKlaus, offering to reveal all her secrets in exchange for the \nlittle one’s safety. If the Hunters set out to save Klaus go \nto SCENE THREE - In the Swamp . If, on the other hand, \nthey decide to stay in the village or split up, for those who \nremain, go to the FOURTH SCENE - OZena’s Attack.\nTHIRD SCENE – In the Swamp\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You don’t have to go too \nfar into the swamp before you hear little Klaus scream. You \nrun to a small clearing where Hirnloser puts a sickle to the \nchild’s throat. He is near an old, abandoned shed from which \nsuddenly emerges a huge figure covered in grotesque armor \nmade of debris. Hirnloser stares at you, his eyes pools of pure \nmadness. “ And while we dance here in our little puppet show, \nthe real performance unfolds in the village, ” the madman \ncries and smiles maliciously, as you realize that you have \nbeen lured into a trap.\nPlace: A clearing in the swamp twenty minutes’ walk from \nGelb.\nTime: It is late morning and the sun filters through the \ntrees.\nInformation: Hirnloser and Dose want to engage the \nHunters to give Dorothea time to kill Margareta. \n ◆ Hirnloser is insane but he doesn’t really want to kill \nKlaus. It will soon become clear that he uses the child \nas a shield and lever to keep the Hunters busy.\n ◆ If Lowe is present, he will try to surprise the Hunters \nfrom behind but will flee at the slightest sign of danger.\nDose The Tin Man</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 228."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624325,"modifiedTime":1781557624325,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-hirnloser-the-scarecrow-228","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":228,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: Everyone thinks I’m crazy and maybe they’re \nright. I don’t feel any fear and I can see beneath the surface of \nthose who pretend they are normal.\nAgenda: I follow OZena because I can see past her pain. \nThere is another world, the one where she comes from and \nwhere I want to go too.\nEnd of Scene: Margareta asks the Hunters to save little \nKlaus, offering to reveal all her secrets in exchange for the \nlittle one’s safety. If the Hunters set out to save Klaus go \nto SCENE THREE - In the Swamp . If, on the other hand, \nthey decide to stay in the village or split up, for those who \nremain, go to the FOURTH SCENE - OZena’s Attack.\nTHIRD SCENE – In the Swamp\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You don’t have to go too \nfar into the swamp before you hear little Klaus scream. You \nrun to a small clearing where Hirnloser puts a sickle to the \nchild’s throat. He is near an old, abandoned shed from which \nsuddenly emerges a huge figure covered in grotesque armor \nmade of debris. Hirnloser stares at you, his eyes pools of pure \nmadness. “ And while we dance here in our little puppet show, \nthe real performance unfolds in the village, ” the madman \ncries and smiles maliciously, as you realize that you have \nbeen lured into a trap.\nPlace: A clearing in the swamp twenty minutes’ walk from \nGelb.\nTime: It is late morning and the sun filters through the \ntrees.\nInformation: Hirnloser and Dose want to engage the \nHunters to give Dorothea time to kill Margareta. \n ◆ Hirnloser is insane but he doesn’t really want to kill \nKlaus. It will soon become clear that he uses the child \nas a shield and lever to keep the Hunters busy.\n ◆ If Lowe is present, he will try to surprise the Hunters \nfrom behind but will flee at the slightest sign of danger.\nDose The Tin Man</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I follow OZena because I can see past her pain. \nThere is another world, the one where she comes from and \nwhere I want to go too.\nEnd of Scene: Margareta asks the Hunters to save little \nKlaus, offering to reveal all her secrets in exchange for the \nlittle one’s safety. If the Hunters set out to save Klaus go \nto SCENE THREE - In the Swamp . If, on the other hand, \nthey decide to stay in the village or split up, for those who \nremain, go to the FOURTH SCENE - OZena’s Attack.\nTHIRD SCENE – In the Swamp\nRead aloud to the Hunters: You don’t have to go too \nfar into the swamp before you hear little Klaus scream. You \nrun to a small clearing where Hirnloser puts a sickle to the \nchild’s throat. He is near an old, abandoned shed from which \nsuddenly emerges a huge figure covered in grotesque armor \nmade of debris. Hirnloser stares at you, his eyes pools of pure \nmadness. “ And while we dance here in our little puppet show, \nthe real performance unfolds in the village, ” the madman \ncries and smiles maliciously, as you realize that you have \nbeen lured into a trap.\nPlace: A clearing in the swamp twenty minutes’ walk from \nGelb.\nTime: It is late morning and the sun filters through the \ntrees.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624325,"modifiedTime":1781557624325,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uJq1AyRkyjQNIM9D","name":"The Villagers of Emerald","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"y1Oknpk77XGUWQdO","name":"The Villagers of Emerald - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are poor villagers changed by a wish we \nmade.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 243.","positive":"We are poor villagers changed by a wish we \nmade.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624772,"modifiedTime":1781557624772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WxpFgsh2PnLeCFBO","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are poor villagers changed by a wish we \nmade. \nAgenda: We hate Henkle for what he did to us, but we serve \nhim in the hope that we can make another wish.\nGift - Careful What you Wish For: Each Villager has \nmade a wish, but it has not had the desired effects. Roll 1 die \nto see what mutation has developed: 1. Wish for Wealth: \nThe NPC spits out gold coins mixed with bile. With a single \naction, they can hit up to 3 targets at a distance of 15 feet; \n2. Wish for Beauty: The NPC warps their body so as \nalways to look beautiful in the eyes of the beholder. When \nthere is more than one subject in view, their body changes \nconstantly. Whoever witnesses the show receives 1 Penalty \non their Checks out of disgust; 3. Wish for Health: The \nNPC’s body regenerates as their hair and body hair grow \nout of proportion. The NPC recovers 1 Wound as soon as it \nloses 1, making them effectively immortal. The effect of the \nWound suffered is applied, so the NPC can be defeated, but \nwill regenerate on its turn to act; 4. Wish for Skill: The \nNPC raises their OL to Medium; 5. The NPC can no longer \nsleep because they are obsessed with the idea of working, \nand will constantly be chattering nonsense; 5. Wish to \nGrow Up: The NPC is a child with a body of a giant while \ntheir head has remained the same as before. They can take \n2 extra Wounds and inflict 1 additional Wound when they \nunleash their strength; 6. Wish for Love: The NPC has \nmerged with the one they love, literally obtaining the desire \nto “become one. ” As a double body the NPC can act twice.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are two Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nWhen Henkle realizes that Dorothea does not have \nthe missing pieces of the Compass Rose with her: \nhe will take off on the balloon as soon as it is ready, and \nthen activate the power of the incomplete Rose.\nIf Dorothea realizes that Henkle is willing to \nabandon her to return to the future: she will do \nanything to reach the man, begging him not to abandon \nher.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 243."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624772,"modifiedTime":1781557624772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-the-villagers-of-emerald-243","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":243,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are poor villagers changed by a wish we \nmade. \nAgenda: We hate Henkle for what he did to us, but we serve \nhim in the hope that we can make another wish.\nGift - Careful What you Wish For: Each Villager has \nmade a wish, but it has not had the desired effects. Roll 1 die \nto see what mutation has developed: 1. Wish for Wealth: \nThe NPC spits out gold coins mixed with bile. With a single \naction, they can hit up to 3 targets at a distance of 15 feet; \n2. Wish for Beauty: The NPC warps their body so as \nalways to look beautiful in the eyes of the beholder. When \nthere is more than one subject in view, their body changes \nconstantly. Whoever witnesses the show receives 1 Penalty \non their Checks out of disgust; 3. Wish for Health: The \nNPC’s body regenerates as their hair and body hair grow \nout of proportion. The NPC recovers 1 Wound as soon as it \nloses 1, making them effectively immortal. The effect of the \nWound suffered is applied, so the NPC can be defeated, but \nwill regenerate on its turn to act; 4. Wish for Skill: The \nNPC raises their OL to Medium; 5. The NPC can no longer \nsleep because they are obsessed with the idea of working, \nand will constantly be chattering nonsense; 5. Wish to \nGrow Up: The NPC is a child with a body of a giant while \ntheir head has remained the same as before. They can take \n2 extra Wounds and inflict 1 additional Wound when they \nunleash their strength; 6. Wish for Love: The NPC has \nmerged with the one they love, literally obtaining the desire \nto “become one. ” As a double body the NPC can act twice.\nScenario Events\nIn this Scenario, there are two Events. As a Storyteller, feel \nfree to create new ones in response to the actions of the \nHunters.\nWhen Henkle realizes that Dorothea does not have \nthe missing pieces of the Compass Rose with her: \nhe will take off on the balloon as soon as it is ready, and \nthen activate the power of the incomplete Rose.\nIf Dorothea realizes that Henkle is willing to \nabandon her to return to the future: she will do \nanything to reach the man, begging him not to abandon \nher.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"We hate Henkle for what he did to us, but we serve \nhim in the hope that we can make another wish.","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624772,"modifiedTime":1781557624772,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uKoNmMOCpocsPmyb","name":"The Porcelain Princess","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"bz7efcagQ1FGzXX3","name":"The Porcelain Princess - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young noble who has fallen from grace. \nMy disfigured face is covered in a beautiful doll mask, and I \nsadistically manage the cult of the Crimson Kiss on behalf of \nmy lady Helga.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 235.","positive":"I am a young noble who has fallen from grace. \nMy disfigured face is covered in a beautiful doll mask, and I \nsadistically manage the cult of the Crimson Kiss on behalf of \nmy lady Helga.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5pwWmXbBpoman4dg","name":"Gift - Vials","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The Princess always has five or six vials of \nHelga’s blood with her for newcomers to drink. She also has \n1 vial of the Infusion of Purity.\nPorcelain Dolls</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 235.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7Q5DPhxBZfsycQ7M","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young noble who has fallen from grace. \nMy disfigured face is covered in a beautiful doll mask, and I \nsadistically manage the cult of the Crimson Kiss on behalf of \nmy lady Helga.\nAgenda: Carry out every order of Helga in the hope that she \nwill heal my face / I would do anything to get my face back.\nGift - Vials: The Princess always has five or six vials of \nHelga’s blood with her for newcomers to drink. She also has \n1 vial of the Infusion of Purity.\nPorcelain Dolls</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 235."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-the-porcelain-princess-235","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":235,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young noble who has fallen from grace. \nMy disfigured face is covered in a beautiful doll mask, and I \nsadistically manage the cult of the Crimson Kiss on behalf of \nmy lady Helga.\nAgenda: Carry out every order of Helga in the hope that she \nwill heal my face / I would do anything to get my face back.\nGift - Vials: The Princess always has five or six vials of \nHelga’s blood with her for newcomers to drink. She also has \n1 vial of the Infusion of Purity.\nPorcelain Dolls</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Carry out every order of Helga in the hope that she \nwill heal my face / I would do anything to get my face back.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624498,"modifiedTime":1781557624498,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uUr0pwy6QtN1ETZh","name":"Illusory Labyrinth","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"lbMgKJu1UreTeYkl","name":"Illusory Labyrinth - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A maze of trees and houses that change every \nminute, making it impossible to find your way around.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters arrive at the center of the \nvillage. Go to the THIRD SCENE - The Magician’s Fake \nCastle.\nTHIRD SCENE – The \nMagician’s Fake Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Finally in the center of the \nvillage, you find yourself in front of a huge oak that has been \nmolded into the shape of a grotesque castle. Inside the tree, \nyou can see a hot-air balloon made of patched fabric that is \nslowly inflating. You have never seen anything like it, but you \nunderstand it will not be good.\nPlace: Henkle’s workshop house in the center of the \nvillage, where the hot-air balloon is set up.\nTime: The morning sun is high in a cloudless sky.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 240.","positive":"A maze of trees and houses that change every \nminute, making it impossible to find your way around.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters arrive at the center of the \nvillage. Go to the THIRD SCENE - The Magician’s Fake \nCastle.\nTHIRD SCENE – The \nMagician’s Fake Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Finally in the center of the \nvillage, you find yourself in front of a huge oak that has been \nmolded into the shape of a grotesque castle. Inside the tree, \nyou can see a hot-air balloon made of patched fabric that is \nslowly inflating. You have never seen anything like it, but you \nunderstand it will not be good.\nPlace: Henkle’s workshop house in the center of the \nvillage, where the hot-air balloon is set up.\nTime: The morning sun is high in a cloudless sky.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624654,"modifiedTime":1781557624654,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MUxcwX44pBQw8VFS","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A maze of trees and houses that change every \nminute, making it impossible to find your way around.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters arrive at the center of the \nvillage. Go to the THIRD SCENE - The Magician’s Fake \nCastle.\nTHIRD SCENE – The \nMagician’s Fake Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Finally in the center of the \nvillage, you find yourself in front of a huge oak that has been \nmolded into the shape of a grotesque castle. Inside the tree, \nyou can see a hot-air balloon made of patched fabric that is \nslowly inflating. You have never seen anything like it, but you \nunderstand it will not be good.\nPlace: Henkle’s workshop house in the center of the \nvillage, where the hot-air balloon is set up.\nTime: The morning sun is high in a cloudless sky.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 240."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624654,"modifiedTime":1781557624654,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-illusory-labyrinth-240","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":240,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A maze of trees and houses that change every \nminute, making it impossible to find your way around.\nEnd of Scene: The Hunters arrive at the center of the \nvillage. Go to the THIRD SCENE - The Magician’s Fake \nCastle.\nTHIRD SCENE – The \nMagician’s Fake Castle\nRead aloud to the Hunters: Finally in the center of the \nvillage, you find yourself in front of a huge oak that has been \nmolded into the shape of a grotesque castle. Inside the tree, \nyou can see a hot-air balloon made of patched fabric that is \nslowly inflating. You have never seen anything like it, but you \nunderstand it will not be good.\nPlace: Henkle’s workshop house in the center of the \nvillage, where the hot-air balloon is set up.\nTime: The morning sun is high in a cloudless sky.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624654,"modifiedTime":1781557624654,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uVrZcTV7fbEvnMXB","name":"Shadows of Sherazade (Dark Presence Opponent)","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"7R4EBkn3kkjVCW2T","name":"Shadows of Sherazade (Dark Presence Opponent) - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We disguise ourselves as helpless citizens, but \nin reality, we are ready to strike with our shadow sabers.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 166.","positive":"We disguise ourselves as helpless citizens, but \nin reality, we are ready to strike with our shadow sabers.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642795,"modifiedTime":1781557642795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4IfIxHVXgC6YaHIv","name":"Gift - Shadow Body","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A Shadow is a darker, sadder ver -\nsion of the original. They can speak and behave like the \ncharacter they are modelled after, but on a careful inspection they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per Scene, \na Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness by \nmoving through walls and other solid obstacles. When it \nspawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element of \nsurprise. When it suffers the Wound that would kill it, the \nShadow dissipates until its turn in the Exchange. At that \npoint, it will emerge from the darkness as if nothing had \nhappened. The Shadow will not reappear if the area the \nHunters are in is fully illuminated with light sources or \nmagic. The only way to truly destroy the Shadow is to expose it to sunlight.\nSultan’s Guards</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 166.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642795,"modifiedTime":1781557642795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Fap0HWVGlVUll8oX","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We disguise ourselves as helpless citizens, but \nin reality, we are ready to strike with our shadow sabers. \nAgenda: Interfere with and complicate the lives of the Or -\nder’s Hunters, preventing them from fulfilling their mission.\nGift - Shadow Body: A Shadow is a darker, sadder ver -\nsion of the original. They can speak and behave like the \ncharacter they are modelled after, but on a careful inspection they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per Scene, \na Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness by \nmoving through walls and other solid obstacles. When it \nspawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element of \nsurprise. When it suffers the Wound that would kill it, the \nShadow dissipates until its turn in the Exchange. At that \npoint, it will emerge from the darkness as if nothing had \nhappened. The Shadow will not reappear if the area the \nHunters are in is fully illuminated with light sources or \nmagic. The only way to truly destroy the Shadow is to expose it to sunlight.\nSultan’s Guards</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 166."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642795,"modifiedTime":1781557642795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-shadows-of-sherazade-dark-presence-opponent-166","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":166,"role":"Scenario Actor"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Scenario Actor","notes":"<p>- (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We disguise ourselves as helpless citizens, but \nin reality, we are ready to strike with our shadow sabers. \nAgenda: Interfere with and complicate the lives of the Or -\nder’s Hunters, preventing them from fulfilling their mission.\nGift - Shadow Body: A Shadow is a darker, sadder ver -\nsion of the original. They can speak and behave like the \ncharacter they are modelled after, but on a careful inspection they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per Scene, \na Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness by \nmoving through walls and other solid obstacles. When it \nspawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element of \nsurprise. When it suffers the Wound that would kill it, the \nShadow dissipates until its turn in the Exchange. At that \npoint, it will emerge from the darkness as if nothing had \nhappened. The Shadow will not reappear if the area the \nHunters are in is fully illuminated with light sources or \nmagic. The only way to truly destroy the Shadow is to expose it to sunlight.\nSultan’s Guards</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Interfere with and complicate the lives of the Or -\nder’s Hunters, preventing them from fulfilling their mission.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642795,"modifiedTime":1781557642795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uWsXjWJVk529gk7o","name":"Corinne the Housekeeper","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"aW34FjL9kiAFveR9","name":"Corinne the Housekeeper - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I know all rumors in the village, partly because \nI start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love \nreceiving gifts.\n6 Didier the Grumpy Old Man</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123.","positive":"I know all rumors in the village, partly because \nI start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love \nreceiving gifts.\n6 Didier the Grumpy Old Man","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HshPJkFExHuCS3QM","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I know all rumors in the village, partly because \nI start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love \nreceiving gifts.\n6 Didier the Grumpy Old Man</p>","notes":"Red-hood / Iskra - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 123."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-red-hood-iskra-corinne-the-housekeeper-123","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","adventureTitle":"Red-hood / Iskra","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":123,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Red-hood / Iskra","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I know all rumors in the village, partly because \nI start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love \nreceiving gifts.\n6 Didier the Grumpy Old Man</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621329,"modifiedTime":1781557621329,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uXiM3h3PQA4Ao1oD","name":"Karl and Elsa Karenmann","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"Gw3FR42K16bZ0SFH","name":"Karl and Elsa Karenmann - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are two loving parents who only want what’s \nbest for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout \nLohr.</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 111.","positive":"We are two loving parents who only want what’s \nbest for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout \nLohr.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628470,"modifiedTime":1781557628470,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UKvi5szDeR5KnvGg","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two loving parents who only want what’s \nbest for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout \nLohr.\nAgenda: To have Ottone’s death case closed as soon as possible, \nplacing the blame on Bruna / Protect Bianca from a world that \ncould not accept her for what she is.\nKarenmann Palace\nDescriptor: A large and magnificent palace that contrasts \nwith the humble appearance of the rest of Lohr’s dwellings.\nDuring the interview, the Hunters will realize that the palace \nis full of paintings depicting the Karenmann family. In many \npaintings, a beautiful girl with long black hair, snow-white \nskin, and a pure and innocent look can be seen. From the \npaintings the great love that unites Elsa and Karl to their \ndaughter Bianca is clear.\nThe Village of Lohr\nDescriptor: A small village that is experiencing new prosperity \nthanks to the Karenmann family.\nThe Hunters may hear some rumors while exploring the \nvillage. Choose or roll 1 die:</p>","notes":"Bloodwhite's Heart - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 111."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628470,"modifiedTime":1781557628470,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-bloodwhites-heart-karl-and-elsa-karenmann-111","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","adventureTitle":"Bloodwhite's Heart","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":111,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Bloodwhite's Heart","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are two loving parents who only want what’s \nbest for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout \nLohr.\nAgenda: To have Ottone’s death case closed as soon as possible, \nplacing the blame on Bruna / Protect Bianca from a world that \ncould not accept her for what she is.\nKarenmann Palace\nDescriptor: A large and magnificent palace that contrasts \nwith the humble appearance of the rest of Lohr’s dwellings.\nDuring the interview, the Hunters will realize that the palace \nis full of paintings depicting the Karenmann family. In many \npaintings, a beautiful girl with long black hair, snow-white \nskin, and a pure and innocent look can be seen. From the \npaintings the great love that unites Elsa and Karl to their \ndaughter Bianca is clear.\nThe Village of Lohr\nDescriptor: A small village that is experiencing new prosperity \nthanks to the Karenmann family.\nThe Hunters may hear some rumors while exploring the \nvillage. Choose or roll 1 die:</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"To have Ottone’s death case closed as soon as possible, \nplacing the blame on Bruna / Protect Bianca from a world that \ncould not accept her for what she is.\nKarenmann Palace\nDescriptor: A large and magnificent palace that contrasts \nwith the humble appearance of the rest of Lohr’s dwellings.\nDuring the interview, the Hunters will realize that the palace \nis full of paintings depicting the Karenmann family. In many \npaintings, a beautiful girl with long black hair, snow-white \nskin, and a pure and innocent look can be seen. From the \npaintings the great love that unites Elsa and Karl to their \ndaughter Bianca is clear.\nThe Village of Lohr\nDescriptor: A small village that is experiencing new prosperity \nthanks to the Karenmann family.\nThe Hunters may hear some rumors while exploring the \nvillage. Choose or roll 1 die:","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557628470,"modifiedTime":1781557628470,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"vEvyW2Sp40nYEwbT","name":"Cutthroat","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"A2uouUsfRDP780ZT","name":"Cutthroat - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are ruthless killers who will do anything to \nmake a profit. We eliminate the target with chilling efficiency.</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136.","positive":"We are ruthless killers who will do anything to \nmake a profit. We eliminate the target with chilling efficiency.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"D5hX5rk3z8Vl3hnk","name":"Gift - Assassin","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>If they act to kill, they are considered to</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9Ov5zWRhBUWahG6q","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are ruthless killers who will do anything to \nmake a profit. We eliminate the target with chilling efficiency. \nGift - Assassin: If they act to kill, they are considered to</p>","notes":"The Last Wish - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 136."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-last-wish-cutthroat-136","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","adventureTitle":"The Last Wish","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":136,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The Last Wish","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: We are ruthless killers who will do anything to \nmake a profit. We eliminate the target with chilling efficiency. \nGift - Assassin: If they act to kill, they are considered to</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557641427,"modifiedTime":1781557641427,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"vfzGiuaPLCPBMaGd","name":"Glatisant","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"YxG9t8M7gQP3HIls","name":"Glatisant - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a giant snake-headed monster with a deformed body, the result of the union of more than ten different \nanimals. I have an insatiable appetite for flesh.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 190.","positive":"I am a giant snake-headed monster with a deformed body, the result of the union of more than ten different \nanimals. I have an insatiable appetite for flesh.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644083,"modifiedTime":1781557644083,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wqvFsjuA0SDqn9yn","name":"Gift - Monstrous Abomination","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Glatisant can act 2 \ntimes during an Exchange, but not back to back. Its long \nneck allows it to snatch prey up to thirty feet away, and \nwhen it moves, it can make great leaps, ignoring enemies \nand terrain in its path. Glatisant is obsessed with the flesh of \nthe Twrch Trwyth and, if given the opportunity, will spend \nthe entire Exchange devouring it, ignoring even potential \nenemies.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 190.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644083,"modifiedTime":1781557644083,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ZxAijHHJRlp1xfQ7","name":"Gift - Virtue of Courage","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Glatisant unknowingly carries \nthe Virtue of Courage, encased in a sword embedded in his \nright side. Defeating the beast will allow the Hunters to recover the power of Courage. \nZone 4 – Village of \nCorrinton \nDescription: A fishing village buzzing with activity. The \npeople are friendly and hospitable, though it is clear from \ntheir faces that something is troubling the community.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 190.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644083,"modifiedTime":1781557644083,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sMvqAHweLaMHeccX","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a giant snake-headed monster with a deformed body, the result of the union of more than ten different \nanimals. I have an insatiable appetite for flesh.\nAgenda: I devour every delicious human I meet, though my \nfavorite prey is the tasty Twrch Trwyth.\nGift - Monstrous Abomination: Glatisant can act 2 \ntimes during an Exchange, but not back to back. Its long \nneck allows it to snatch prey up to thirty feet away, and \nwhen it moves, it can make great leaps, ignoring enemies \nand terrain in its path. Glatisant is obsessed with the flesh of \nthe Twrch Trwyth and, if given the opportunity, will spend \nthe entire Exchange devouring it, ignoring even potential \nenemies.\nGift - Virtue of Courage: Glatisant unknowingly carries \nthe Virtue of Courage, encased in a sword embedded in his \nright side. Defeating the beast will allow the Hunters to recover the power of Courage. \nZone 4 – Village of \nCorrinton \nDescription: A fishing village buzzing with activity. The \npeople are friendly and hospitable, though it is clear from \ntheir faces that something is troubling the community. \nInformation: Chatting with the locals is another way to \nget the information revealed in the Encounter with the Villagers (page 181). At the explicit request of the Hunters, \nsome fishermen will take them by boat along the coast but \nwill ask for payment. This arrangement allows the Hunters \nto choose any coastal Zone as their destination (i.e., all except 7, 8, and 9). Unless special arrangements are made, the \nfishermen are in a hurry to return to their activities, and \nonce they have unloaded the Hunters, they will not wait for \nthem to return.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 190."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644083,"modifiedTime":1781557644083,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-glatisant-190","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":190,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a giant snake-headed monster with a deformed body, the result of the union of more than ten different \nanimals. I have an insatiable appetite for flesh.\nAgenda: I devour every delicious human I meet, though my \nfavorite prey is the tasty Twrch Trwyth.\nGift - Monstrous Abomination: Glatisant can act 2 \ntimes during an Exchange, but not back to back. Its long \nneck allows it to snatch prey up to thirty feet away, and \nwhen it moves, it can make great leaps, ignoring enemies \nand terrain in its path. Glatisant is obsessed with the flesh of \nthe Twrch Trwyth and, if given the opportunity, will spend \nthe entire Exchange devouring it, ignoring even potential \nenemies.\nGift - Virtue of Courage: Glatisant unknowingly carries \nthe Virtue of Courage, encased in a sword embedded in his \nright side. Defeating the beast will allow the Hunters to recover the power of Courage. \nZone 4 – Village of \nCorrinton \nDescription: A fishing village buzzing with activity. The \npeople are friendly and hospitable, though it is clear from \ntheir faces that something is troubling the community. \nInformation: Chatting with the locals is another way to \nget the information revealed in the Encounter with the Villagers (page 181). At the explicit request of the Hunters, \nsome fishermen will take them by boat along the coast but \nwill ask for payment. This arrangement allows the Hunters \nto choose any coastal Zone as their destination (i.e., all except 7, 8, and 9). Unless special arrangements are made, the \nfishermen are in a hurry to return to their activities, and \nonce they have unloaded the Hunters, they will not wait for \nthem to return.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I devour every delicious human I meet, though my \nfavorite prey is the tasty Twrch Trwyth.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644083,"modifiedTime":1781557644083,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"vprTm5CXkSSA4aHd","name":"The Island Fish","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"zRF6qLuO5OTjpQPQ","name":"The Island Fish - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>The earth cracks and trees fall on those unlucky \nenough to be nearby. Seawater slowly submerges everything.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 153.","positive":"The earth cracks and trees fall on those unlucky \nenough to be nearby. Seawater slowly submerges everything.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642170,"modifiedTime":1781557642170,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7OhyFgpQaz4AUM5R","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: The earth cracks and trees fall on those unlucky \nenough to be nearby. Seawater slowly submerges everything. \nGift - The Island Moves!: Moving around the island is \nvery dangerous, rescuing a group of sailors requires at least \n2 Checks against this Threat, one to get to the group and one \nto return to the ship. The Check can only be made by the \nHunter leading the search party. For each failed Check, roll \n1 die and apply the result to one of the Hunters.\n1: Suffers 1 Wound caused by falling trees and rocks.\n2: Receives 1 Penalty at the next Check due to mud. \n3: Loses 1 Soma due to fatigue. \n4: Loses 1 Equipment in the waves of the sea.\n5: Loses more time than expected. Increase the OL of this \nThreat by 1 for those performing the next Check.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 153."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642170,"modifiedTime":1781557642170,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-the-island-fish-153","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":153,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: The earth cracks and trees fall on those unlucky \nenough to be nearby. Seawater slowly submerges everything. \nGift - The Island Moves!: Moving around the island is \nvery dangerous, rescuing a group of sailors requires at least \n2 Checks against this Threat, one to get to the group and one \nto return to the ship. The Check can only be made by the \nHunter leading the search party. For each failed Check, roll \n1 die and apply the result to one of the Hunters.\n1: Suffers 1 Wound caused by falling trees and rocks.\n2: Receives 1 Penalty at the next Check due to mud. \n3: Loses 1 Soma due to fatigue. \n4: Loses 1 Equipment in the waves of the sea.\n5: Loses more time than expected. Increase the OL of this \nThreat by 1 for those performing the next Check.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642170,"modifiedTime":1781557642170,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"wMm2moqCTKwmbLPy","name":"Lucino - The Good Friend","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"zuRqzvDGhHFyOOeZ","name":"Lucino - The Good Friend - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a dutiful and studious child \nwho can’t wait to learn a trade to help my family.</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137.","positive":"I am a dutiful and studious child \nwho can’t wait to learn a trade to help my family.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lWdcK9hDimFJzTX8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a dutiful and studious child \nwho can’t wait to learn a trade to help my family.\nAgenda: Help Carlo become a responsible \nchild / Work to help adults who behave well \nand follow the law.\nVilla Balocchi\nDescriptor: A beautiful and sumptuous inn, recently \nrefurbished.\nInformation: \n ◆ Amabile hosts little Carlo, making him sleep in a small \nback room. \n ◆ The Puppet pays the greedy innkeeper with stones \nwhich he temporarily turns into gold coins with his \npowers. Throwing the coins into a safe in his room, the \ninnkeeper hasn’t yet noticed the Puppet’s trick. \n ◆ During the afternoon and evening, Carlo is at Villa \nBalocchi and can be found playing with Lucino or \npretending to study.\nAmabile Burromo</p>","notes":"Of Flesh and Wood - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 137."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-of-flesh-and-wood-lucino-the-good-friend-137","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","adventureTitle":"Of Flesh and Wood","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":137,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Of Flesh and Wood","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a dutiful and studious child \nwho can’t wait to learn a trade to help my family.\nAgenda: Help Carlo become a responsible \nchild / Work to help adults who behave well \nand follow the law.\nVilla Balocchi\nDescriptor: A beautiful and sumptuous inn, recently \nrefurbished.\nInformation: \n ◆ Amabile hosts little Carlo, making him sleep in a small \nback room. \n ◆ The Puppet pays the greedy innkeeper with stones \nwhich he temporarily turns into gold coins with his \npowers. Throwing the coins into a safe in his room, the \ninnkeeper hasn’t yet noticed the Puppet’s trick. \n ◆ During the afternoon and evening, Carlo is at Villa \nBalocchi and can be found playing with Lucino or \npretending to study.\nAmabile Burromo</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Help Carlo become a responsible \nchild / Work to help adults who behave well \nand follow the law.\nVilla Balocchi\nDescriptor: A beautiful and sumptuous inn, recently \nrefurbished.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557621874,"modifiedTime":1781557621874,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"wsPcP3W2amjkzEoX","name":"4: Katri","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"EGgeryLfGojF6vpC","name":"4: Katri - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a good hunter, but now my venerable age \nkeeps me from hunting. I know the area around Rovaniemi \nvery well.</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 119.","positive":"I am a good hunter, but now my venerable age \nkeeps me from hunting. I know the area around Rovaniemi \nvery well.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640550,"modifiedTime":1781557640550,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9LyZvv4p3M22N6aW","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a good hunter, but now my venerable age \nkeeps me from hunting. I know the area around Rovaniemi \nvery well.\nAgenda: Defend the village of Rovaniemi from any possible \nthreat from the wilderness. \nInformation: Katri leads the hunters in the Village, and \nlately she has been told that the presence of animals has \ndecreased dramatically. There are several hunting lodges \nin the forest around the Village, where one \ncan find shelter. The area where Nikola Lupei’s mansion was built is full of ravines and \nnatural caves. \n5: Usko</p>","notes":"Nikola's Pledge - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 119."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640550,"modifiedTime":1781557640550,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-nikolas-pledge-4-katri-119","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","adventureTitle":"Nikola's Pledge","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":119,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Nikola's Pledge","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a good hunter, but now my venerable age \nkeeps me from hunting. I know the area around Rovaniemi \nvery well.\nAgenda: Defend the village of Rovaniemi from any possible \nthreat from the wilderness. \nInformation: Katri leads the hunters in the Village, and \nlately she has been told that the presence of animals has \ndecreased dramatically. There are several hunting lodges \nin the forest around the Village, where one \ncan find shelter. The area where Nikola Lupei’s mansion was built is full of ravines and \nnatural caves. \n5: Usko</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Defend the village of Rovaniemi from any possible \nthreat from the wilderness.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557640550,"modifiedTime":1781557640550,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"wwkTNF2FxgMuKbsp","name":"The Red Knight","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"l5IGhYIVRWT4niHB","name":"The Red Knight - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an immortal spirit in a knight’s armor, \nand with my skeletal steed I travel all over Avalon in search \nof the one who killed me.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 184.","positive":"I am an immortal spirit in a knight’s armor, \nand with my skeletal steed I travel all over Avalon in search \nof the one who killed me.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643831,"modifiedTime":1781557643831,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"gFg0x5sMXo3FGSrR","name":"Gift - Eternal Vengeance","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>When Percival the Seeker \nappears on the Scene, if he is present, the Red Knight will \nattack, ignoring all other risks. If Percival is not present, \nthe Red Knight will see the face of the hated opponent in \nthe most skilled subject in combat among those present, \nactivating this Gift as well. As long as the Red Knight has \nhis target in sight, no effect can block or prevent him from \nattacking. In the heat of vengeance, the Red Knight ignores \nall other enemies and reduces his OL against them to Easy \n3.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 184.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643831,"modifiedTime":1781557643831,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8O3t0RK8ZReXerZ8","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an immortal spirit in a knight’s armor, \nand with my skeletal steed I travel all over Avalon in search \nof the one who killed me.\nAgenda: Death has clouded my consciousness, and in every \nperson I meet I see my hated enemy, Percival. \nGift - Eternal Vengeance: When Percival the Seeker \nappears on the Scene, if he is present, the Red Knight will \nattack, ignoring all other risks. If Percival is not present, \nthe Red Knight will see the face of the hated opponent in \nthe most skilled subject in combat among those present, \nactivating this Gift as well. As long as the Red Knight has \nhis target in sight, no effect can block or prevent him from \nattacking. In the heat of vengeance, the Red Knight ignores \nall other enemies and reduces his OL against them to Easy \n3. \nInformation: The Red Knight is unable to communicate, \nand the only words he utters are vengeful epithets directed at Percival the Seeker. If the Hunters eliminate the Red \nKnight, he will not appear in Zone 12 - Cliff (page 197).</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 184."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643831,"modifiedTime":1781557643831,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-the-red-knight-184","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":184,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an immortal spirit in a knight’s armor, \nand with my skeletal steed I travel all over Avalon in search \nof the one who killed me.\nAgenda: Death has clouded my consciousness, and in every \nperson I meet I see my hated enemy, Percival. \nGift - Eternal Vengeance: When Percival the Seeker \nappears on the Scene, if he is present, the Red Knight will \nattack, ignoring all other risks. If Percival is not present, \nthe Red Knight will see the face of the hated opponent in \nthe most skilled subject in combat among those present, \nactivating this Gift as well. As long as the Red Knight has \nhis target in sight, no effect can block or prevent him from \nattacking. In the heat of vengeance, the Red Knight ignores \nall other enemies and reduces his OL against them to Easy \n3. \nInformation: The Red Knight is unable to communicate, \nand the only words he utters are vengeful epithets directed at Percival the Seeker. If the Hunters eliminate the Red \nKnight, he will not appear in Zone 12 - Cliff (page 197).</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":7,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Hard 7","impulse":"Death has clouded my consciousness, and in every \nperson I meet I see my hated enemy, Percival.","oppositionLevel":7}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557643831,"modifiedTime":1781557643831,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xCQWGWtOYFrX7YkP","name":"Andersen","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"lnriWGDSrLdXRmPi","name":"Andersen - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills. \nIn addition to being a good leader, I am also a capable fighter.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 161.","positive":"I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills. \nIn addition to being a good leader, I am also a capable fighter.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622594,"modifiedTime":1781557622594,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UP9On97FThkWXgoQ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills. \nIn addition to being a good leader, I am also a capable fighter.\nAgenda: Defend my new family from the danger that Enar \nrepresents / Redeem myself in the eyes of Satu and make her \nunderstand that I am now a different man / Prevent anyone \nfrom discovering what I have done.\nGift - Commander: Andersen is skilled at giving orders \nand managing a battle. Up to 3 times per Scene, Andersen \ncan issue an order to an ally who will receive 1 Additional \nSuccess (+1 to OL in the case of an NPC) while executing it.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 161."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622594,"modifiedTime":1781557622594,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-andersen-161","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":161,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills. \nIn addition to being a good leader, I am also a capable fighter.\nAgenda: Defend my new family from the danger that Enar \nrepresents / Redeem myself in the eyes of Satu and make her \nunderstand that I am now a different man / Prevent anyone \nfrom discovering what I have done.\nGift - Commander: Andersen is skilled at giving orders \nand managing a battle. Up to 3 times per Scene, Andersen \ncan issue an order to an ally who will receive 1 Additional \nSuccess (+1 to OL in the case of an NPC) while executing it.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Defend my new family from the danger that Enar \nrepresents / Redeem myself in the eyes of Satu and make her \nunderstand that I am now a different man / Prevent anyone \nfrom discovering what I have done.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622594,"modifiedTime":1781557622594,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xLx3Qoav0DOMjvGg","name":"Murder of Crows","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"cRbNVzF0YI46VRJs","name":"Murder of Crows - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We are a great murder of crows and watch over \nour beloved human brothers Ravn and Kråke.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 211.","positive":"We are a great murder of crows and watch over \nour beloved human brothers Ravn and Kråke.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645350,"modifiedTime":1781557645350,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ng3dEOT331SskCdw","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: We are a great murder of crows and watch over \nour beloved human brothers Ravn and Kråke.\nGift - The Three Feathers: The Murder of Crows acts in \nthe service of Kråke and Ravn to protect them and treat them \nas if they were a Crow. Once per Exchange, both Kråke and \nRavn can enjoy one of the following effects:\n1. Coat of Feathers: The Murder shields a Black Feather, \nwhich increases their OL to Hard 7 against an attack.\n2. Flight of the Crow: The Murder lifts the Black Feather \noff the ground and allows it to run over their feathery bodies. \nThe Black Feather can move anywhere within a thirty-foot \nradius, and no one can block them. If they make an attack \nafter moving, the Black Feather increases their OL by 1.\n3. Feather Storm: The Murder encircles a target while it \nperforms an action that is not a physical attack. This effect \ncan be activated when an opponent acts, but it still counts \nagainst the limit of one effect per Exchange. The target must \npass a Defense Check or lose the action.\nEpilogue\nIt takes two days of sailing to get to the White Hospital.\nIf a Black Feather is captured, they will not agree to talk, but \nthe Hunters can use magic or other means to force them to \nreveal the following information:\n ◆ The mission of the Black Feathers is to take the wealthiest \npatients to Os, where the famous White Hospital is located, but even that is a cover-up by Gerda and Kay. The \nreal goal is to get the patients into the hands of a certain \nReinsdyr, who will then lead them through the forest to \nbe robbed by a group of bandits.\n ◆ The Black Feathers do not know how to get to the castle where Gerda and Kay live, but they have heard more \nthan once from the two fraudsters about witches who \nhelp them. \nStoryteller’s Note: The Hunters’ journey continues in \nPART TWO - Towards Lady Storm’s Castle. Keep track of the \nfate of the Black Feathers, for they will be recurring enemies \nin the next parts. \nScenario Events\nThere are 3 Events in this Scenario, though the Storyteller \nshould feel free to create new ones in response to the Hunter’s \nactions.\nIf the Hunters use violence to stop Aleksander: his \ndaughter will stand up for him, going so far as to beg the \nHunters to spare him. If the situation is not resolved, Fredrika will send the Hunters away with less information to end \nthe dinner quickly. \nIf the Hunters try to destroy Flora’s Greenhouse to \nforce her out: the old witch will use her magic to call for \nhelp, causing many townspeople to rush to her defense. \nIf  the  Hunters  inflict  at  least  one  Wound  on  both \nBlack Feathers or corner them: the two will attempt to \nescape by transforming into a rook and a raven and mingling \nwith the Murder.</p>","notes":"A Frozen Reflection - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 211."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645350,"modifiedTime":1781557645350,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-a-frozen-reflection-murder-of-crows-211","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","adventureTitle":"A Frozen Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":211,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Frozen Reflection","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: We are a great murder of crows and watch over \nour beloved human brothers Ravn and Kråke.\nGift - The Three Feathers: The Murder of Crows acts in \nthe service of Kråke and Ravn to protect them and treat them \nas if they were a Crow. Once per Exchange, both Kråke and \nRavn can enjoy one of the following effects:\n1. Coat of Feathers: The Murder shields a Black Feather, \nwhich increases their OL to Hard 7 against an attack.\n2. Flight of the Crow: The Murder lifts the Black Feather \noff the ground and allows it to run over their feathery bodies. \nThe Black Feather can move anywhere within a thirty-foot \nradius, and no one can block them. If they make an attack \nafter moving, the Black Feather increases their OL by 1.\n3. Feather Storm: The Murder encircles a target while it \nperforms an action that is not a physical attack. This effect \ncan be activated when an opponent acts, but it still counts \nagainst the limit of one effect per Exchange. The target must \npass a Defense Check or lose the action.\nEpilogue\nIt takes two days of sailing to get to the White Hospital.\nIf a Black Feather is captured, they will not agree to talk, but \nthe Hunters can use magic or other means to force them to \nreveal the following information:\n ◆ The mission of the Black Feathers is to take the wealthiest \npatients to Os, where the famous White Hospital is located, but even that is a cover-up by Gerda and Kay. The \nreal goal is to get the patients into the hands of a certain \nReinsdyr, who will then lead them through the forest to \nbe robbed by a group of bandits.\n ◆ The Black Feathers do not know how to get to the castle where Gerda and Kay live, but they have heard more \nthan once from the two fraudsters about witches who \nhelp them. \nStoryteller’s Note: The Hunters’ journey continues in \nPART TWO - Towards Lady Storm’s Castle. Keep track of the \nfate of the Black Feathers, for they will be recurring enemies \nin the next parts. \nScenario Events\nThere are 3 Events in this Scenario, though the Storyteller \nshould feel free to create new ones in response to the Hunter’s \nactions.\nIf the Hunters use violence to stop Aleksander: his \ndaughter will stand up for him, going so far as to beg the \nHunters to spare him. If the situation is not resolved, Fredrika will send the Hunters away with less information to end \nthe dinner quickly. \nIf the Hunters try to destroy Flora’s Greenhouse to \nforce her out: the old witch will use her magic to call for \nhelp, causing many townspeople to rush to her defense. \nIf  the  Hunters  inflict  at  least  one  Wound  on  both \nBlack Feathers or corner them: the two will attempt to \nescape by transforming into a rook and a raven and mingling \nwith the Murder.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557645350,"modifiedTime":1781557645350,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xlTE50GrkIiwUuH8","name":"Makes Wishes Come True","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ukPIIvgZ3XFN4sth","name":"Makes Wishes Come True - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a powerful wizard and what I desire \nbecomes reality. My skill as a barker always charms everyone \nto my side.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242.","positive":"I am a powerful wizard and what I desire \nbecomes reality. My skill as a barker always charms everyone \nto my side.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"n7mCVcZyFMEepShH","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful wizard and what I desire \nbecomes reality. My skill as a barker always charms everyone \nto my side.\nAgenda: I want to go back to my time alone and become a \ncelebrity thanks to the power of magic.\nGift - Hot-Air Balloon: As soon as it is ready, Henkle will \nboard and release his hot-air balloon into the air to activate \nthe Compass Rose. As indicated by the Scenario, based on \nthe actions of the Hunters this Gift will accumulate Time \nTokens. When the third Time Token is placed, the hot-air \nballoon is ready to go.</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 242."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-makes-wishes-come-true-242","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":242,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (2 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful wizard and what I desire \nbecomes reality. My skill as a barker always charms everyone \nto my side.\nAgenda: I want to go back to my time alone and become a \ncelebrity thanks to the power of magic.\nGift - Hot-Air Balloon: As soon as it is ready, Henkle will \nboard and release his hot-air balloon into the air to activate \nthe Compass Rose. As indicated by the Scenario, based on \nthe actions of the Hunters this Gift will accumulate Time \nTokens. When the third Time Token is placed, the hot-air \nballoon is ready to go.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":2},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I want to go back to my time alone and become a \ncelebrity thanks to the power of magic.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624756,"modifiedTime":1781557624756,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xnCRudOgdBeBRbtu","name":"Frank Browne the Middle Brother","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"0ncUzyadqpKjZRB6","name":"Frank Browne the Middle Brother - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act \nas the strongarm of the gang. I have control over all cultists, \nand the power of The God Under the Mine has given me \nstrength and endurance equal to that of five men.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 210.","positive":"I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act \nas the strongarm of the gang. I have control over all cultists, \nand the power of The God Under the Mine has given me \nstrength and endurance equal to that of five men.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623894,"modifiedTime":1781557623894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"926KjsL5I9hkA9mL","name":"Gift - The Pincer","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Frank replaced his left arm with a \nhome-made mechanical arm with many functions. During \na Scene, Frank can use each of the following one time: \n1. Crush, a hit with the pincer inflicts 1 additional Wound; \n2. Pulley, the pincer can launch from the arm and raise \nor lower Frank about thirty feet. Frank can carry 2 other \nsubjects with him.</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 210.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623894,"modifiedTime":1781557623894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"f3KEPeAT4GiRuz2V","name":"Gift - Gang Leader","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a \nsecond time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. \nOnce per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a \nsingle action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe Mine</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 210.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623894,"modifiedTime":1781557623894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3f4isSb4QBcvckLm","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act \nas the strongarm of the gang. I have control over all cultists, \nand the power of The God Under the Mine has given me \nstrength and endurance equal to that of five men.\nAgenda: Take revenge on Bardolf for what he did to me and \nfind a remedy for the wounds that have marred me since the \nday of the accident / Mix the flesh of The God Under the Mine \nwith beef from the slaughterhouse and feed it to the miners to \nadd to the ranks of the gang.\nGift - The Pincer: Frank replaced his left arm with a \nhome-made mechanical arm with many functions. During \na Scene, Frank can use each of the following one time: \n1. Crush, a hit with the pincer inflicts 1 additional Wound; \n2. Pulley, the pincer can launch from the arm and raise \nor lower Frank about thirty feet. Frank can carry 2 other \nsubjects with him. \nGift - Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a \nsecond time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. \nOnce per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a \nsingle action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe Mine\nDescriptor: A gigantic coal mine where miners work day \nand night. Many areas are abandoned in favor of more \nprofitable veins. \nGift - Maze of Galleries: Whitehaven’s Mine is gigantic \nand without a guide it’s not easy to get to a specific location. \nWith each exploration roll, you can get 1 or more Map \nTokens which represent progress in learning the layout of \nthe mine. Upon reaching 3 Map Tokens, you can go directly \nto the Special result.\nWhen the Hunters explore the mine, roll 1 die or choose \ndirectly based on the narrative.\n1-2 Work zone A: Threading through the tunnels, \ndeafened by the sound of steam engines and digging, the \nHunters encounter a group of miners (2d6 + 6 Minor \nNPCs). If the Hunters do something weird, one of the \nworkers will alert Edward. Exploration will yield 1 Map \nToken.\n3-4 Work zone B: Threading through the tunnels, \ndeafened by the sound of steam engines and digging, the \nHunters encounter a group of miners (2d6 + 6 Minor \nNPCs). If the Hunters do something weird, 1d6 + 6 miners \nwill reveal themselves as Pig Heads and attack. Exploration \nwill yield 2 Map Tokens.\n5-6 Abandoned lodging: In an area close to the collapse, \nrecent traces of passage can be found. The Hunters meet \nFrank and 5 Pig Heads who are going to the well to meet up \nwith Arthur. Exploration will yield 2 Map Tokens.\nSpecial (3 Map Tokens): By moving a heavy stone, \nthe Hunters will find the mouth of the well that leads to \nArthur’s chamber. The shaft is narrow and thirty feet deep,</p>","notes":"The City of Pigs - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 210."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623894,"modifiedTime":1781557623894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-city-of-pigs-frank-browne-the-middle-brother-210","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","adventureTitle":"The City of Pigs","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":210,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The City of Pigs","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act \nas the strongarm of the gang. I have control over all cultists, \nand the power of The God Under the Mine has given me \nstrength and endurance equal to that of five men.\nAgenda: Take revenge on Bardolf for what he did to me and \nfind a remedy for the wounds that have marred me since the \nday of the accident / Mix the flesh of The God Under the Mine \nwith beef from the slaughterhouse and feed it to the miners to \nadd to the ranks of the gang.\nGift - The Pincer: Frank replaced his left arm with a \nhome-made mechanical arm with many functions. During \na Scene, Frank can use each of the following one time: \n1. Crush, a hit with the pincer inflicts 1 additional Wound; \n2. Pulley, the pincer can launch from the arm and raise \nor lower Frank about thirty feet. Frank can carry 2 other \nsubjects with him. \nGift - Gang Leader: Eating the flesh of The God Under \nthe Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform \ninto monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can \nmutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound \nonce they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will \nrevive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a \nsecond time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. \nOnce per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a \nsingle action where they can harness their superhuman \nstrength.\nThe Mine\nDescriptor: A gigantic coal mine where miners work day \nand night. Many areas are abandoned in favor of more \nprofitable veins. \nGift - Maze of Galleries: Whitehaven’s Mine is gigantic \nand without a guide it’s not easy to get to a specific location. \nWith each exploration roll, you can get 1 or more Map \nTokens which represent progress in learning the layout of \nthe mine. Upon reaching 3 Map Tokens, you can go directly \nto the Special result.\nWhen the Hunters explore the mine, roll 1 die or choose \ndirectly based on the narrative.\n1-2 Work zone A: Threading through the tunnels, \ndeafened by the sound of steam engines and digging, the \nHunters encounter a group of miners (2d6 + 6 Minor \nNPCs). If the Hunters do something weird, one of the \nworkers will alert Edward. Exploration will yield 1 Map \nToken.\n3-4 Work zone B: Threading through the tunnels, \ndeafened by the sound of steam engines and digging, the \nHunters encounter a group of miners (2d6 + 6 Minor \nNPCs). If the Hunters do something weird, 1d6 + 6 miners \nwill reveal themselves as Pig Heads and attack. Exploration \nwill yield 2 Map Tokens.\n5-6 Abandoned lodging: In an area close to the collapse, \nrecent traces of passage can be found. The Hunters meet \nFrank and 5 Pig Heads who are going to the well to meet up \nwith Arthur. Exploration will yield 2 Map Tokens.\nSpecial (3 Map Tokens): By moving a heavy stone, \nthe Hunters will find the mouth of the well that leads to \nArthur’s chamber. The shaft is narrow and thirty feet deep,</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Take revenge on Bardolf for what he did to me and \nfind a remedy for the wounds that have marred me since the \nday of the accident / Mix the flesh of The God Under the Mine \nwith beef from the slaughterhouse and feed it to the miners to \nadd to the ranks of the gang.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623894,"modifiedTime":1781557623894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xtzu803xWEfppZjH","name":"Alicia The Young Girl in Love","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"2bgOJRdXDSUj3zF3","name":"Alicia The Young Girl in Love - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a young rebel from the slums who knows \nhow to get by on her own. Thanks to my tenacity, I can \novercome every obstacle.</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 173.","positive":"I am a young rebel from the slums who knows \nhow to get by on her own. Thanks to my tenacity, I can \novercome every obstacle.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622907,"modifiedTime":1781557622907,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yCcek5tomPpaWA1L","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young rebel from the slums who knows \nhow to get by on her own. Thanks to my tenacity, I can \novercome every obstacle.\nAgenda: I want to save Alissa from this cursed place and run \naway with her to live out our love in peace.\nThreat - The White Rabbit</p>","notes":"Wonderbedlam - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 173."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622907,"modifiedTime":1781557622907,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-wonderbedlam-alicia-the-young-girl-in-love-173","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","adventureTitle":"Wonderbedlam","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":173,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Wonderbedlam","origin":"Core Book","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>– Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a young rebel from the slums who knows \nhow to get by on her own. Thanks to my tenacity, I can \novercome every obstacle.\nAgenda: I want to save Alissa from this cursed place and run \naway with her to live out our love in peace.\nThreat - The White Rabbit</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"I want to save Alissa from this cursed place and run \naway with her to live out our love in peace.\nThreat - The White Rabbit","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622907,"modifiedTime":1781557622907,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"y6AcALXGWGxXaCVN","name":"Mordred the Peaceless","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"ZE0pA1SMhmzGSgej","name":"Mordred the Peaceless - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am an undead knight in the service of the evil \nMerlin. I do whatever my master tells me to do, though I only \nwish to return to the grave from which I was torn. \nAgenda (if Merlin is present): Obey my master’s orders.\nAgenda (if Merlin is not present): Eliminate anyone \nwho approaches the waters of the lake, as ordered by my master / Be destroyed and return to death, receiving a farewell \nprayer.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 199.","positive":"I am an undead knight in the service of the evil \nMerlin. I do whatever my master tells me to do, though I only \nwish to return to the grave from which I was torn. \nAgenda (if Merlin is present): Obey my master’s orders.\nAgenda (if Merlin is not present): Eliminate anyone \nwho approaches the waters of the lake, as ordered by my master / Be destroyed and return to death, receiving a farewell \nprayer.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644521,"modifiedTime":1781557644521,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"VTzTwwadu5zFlgXh","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an undead knight in the service of the evil \nMerlin. I do whatever my master tells me to do, though I only \nwish to return to the grave from which I was torn. \nAgenda (if Merlin is present): Obey my master’s orders.\nAgenda (if Merlin is not present): Eliminate anyone \nwho approaches the waters of the lake, as ordered by my master / Be destroyed and return to death, receiving a farewell \nprayer. \nInformation: Mordred can be persuaded to surrender in \nexchange for the promise of a burial that will bring peace \nto his soul. If peace is granted, Mordred will reveal Merlin’s \nplans for why he wants the Virtue of Wisdom and the Secret Landing.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 199."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644521,"modifiedTime":1781557644521,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-mordred-the-peaceless-199","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":199,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am an undead knight in the service of the evil \nMerlin. I do whatever my master tells me to do, though I only \nwish to return to the grave from which I was torn. \nAgenda (if Merlin is present): Obey my master’s orders.\nAgenda (if Merlin is not present): Eliminate anyone \nwho approaches the waters of the lake, as ordered by my master / Be destroyed and return to death, receiving a farewell \nprayer. \nInformation: Mordred can be persuaded to surrender in \nexchange for the promise of a burial that will bring peace \nto his soul. If peace is granted, Mordred will reveal Merlin’s \nplans for why he wants the Virtue of Wisdom and the Secret Landing.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":4},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644521,"modifiedTime":1781557644521,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"yBzgI0MrrROY3PFe","name":"The Animated Forest","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"Qh85MQ9iFUTAZI5y","name":"The Animated Forest - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>We grab and capture all intruders through the \nmagic that animates our branches and roots.\nWolfgang the “druid”</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 233.","positive":"We grab and capture all intruders through the \nmagic that animates our branches and roots.\nWolfgang the “druid”","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624451,"modifiedTime":1781557624451,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mL1lh2jL2nTpCFpQ","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: We grab and capture all intruders through the \nmagic that animates our branches and roots.\nWolfgang the “druid”</p>","notes":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 233."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624451,"modifiedTime":1781557624451,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-the-animated-forest-233","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","adventureTitle":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":233,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: We grab and capture all intruders through the \nmagic that animates our branches and roots.\nWolfgang the “druid”</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557624451,"modifiedTime":1781557624451,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"yNbD7Z7ieBOlL4vf","name":"The Sacred Cup Among the Rocks","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"66QzFi6jcW7smEw2","name":"The Sacred Cup Among the Rocks - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A steep cliff overlooking the sea that hides the \ncup of the Holy Grail in its rocks. \nNote: Getting to the cup requires moving along the slippery, pointy rocks as the sea crashes relentlessly. Retrieving the embedded cup requires breaking the rock or finding a way to slide it out.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 198.","positive":"A steep cliff overlooking the sea that hides the \ncup of the Holy Grail in its rocks. \nNote: Getting to the cup requires moving along the slippery, pointy rocks as the sea crashes relentlessly. Retrieving the embedded cup requires breaking the rock or finding a way to slide it out.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644505,"modifiedTime":1781557644505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LrvPJ1SCtFYb0HGM","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A steep cliff overlooking the sea that hides the \ncup of the Holy Grail in its rocks. \nNote: Getting to the cup requires moving along the slippery, pointy rocks as the sea crashes relentlessly. Retrieving the embedded cup requires breaking the rock or finding a way to slide it out.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 198."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644505,"modifiedTime":1781557644505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-the-sacred-cup-among-the-rocks-198","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":198,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A steep cliff overlooking the sea that hides the \ncup of the Holy Grail in its rocks. \nNote: Getting to the cup requires moving along the slippery, pointy rocks as the sea crashes relentlessly. Retrieving the embedded cup requires breaking the rock or finding a way to slide it out.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644505,"modifiedTime":1781557644505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"yQx3IMSoVhEMUMbc","name":"Dead Pirates","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"G9A0yi4fgyHjCGOD","name":"Dead Pirates - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a lost soul who only \nwishes for revenge on those who are still \nalive. My body is a heap of swollen and \nrotten flesh that moves slowly.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 163.","positive":"I am a lost soul who only \nwishes for revenge on those who are still \nalive. My body is a heap of swollen and \nrotten flesh that moves slowly.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622641,"modifiedTime":1781557622641,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"GqKhbnhOLHrf2UPu","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a lost soul who only \nwishes for revenge on those who are still \nalive. My body is a heap of swollen and \nrotten flesh that moves slowly.\nSpecial agenda (James the \nSwordsman): We recognize James \nas the one who killed our captain in \na duel! It is his fault that our ship was \nwrecked, and we will taste his flesh \nfirst!\nGift - Walking Dead: The body \nof the Dead Pirate is rotten and \nputrescent, but it does not stop even if \ndismembered. After suffering his only \nWound, a Dead Pirate can still take his \naction before being eliminated, if he \nhas not already done so in the course \nof the Exchange. If a Dead Pirate acts \nagainst an outnumbered enemy, his \nOpposition Level is increased by 1.</p>","notes":"A Soldier's Duty - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 163."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622641,"modifiedTime":1781557622641,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-a-soldiers-duty-dead-pirates-163","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","adventureTitle":"A Soldier's Duty","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":163,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"A Soldier's Duty","origin":"Core Book","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am a lost soul who only \nwishes for revenge on those who are still \nalive. My body is a heap of swollen and \nrotten flesh that moves slowly.\nSpecial agenda (James the \nSwordsman): We recognize James \nas the one who killed our captain in \na duel! It is his fault that our ship was \nwrecked, and we will taste his flesh \nfirst!\nGift - Walking Dead: The body \nof the Dead Pirate is rotten and \nputrescent, but it does not stop even if \ndismembered. After suffering his only \nWound, a Dead Pirate can still take his \naction before being eliminated, if he \nhas not already done so in the course \nof the Exchange. If a Dead Pirate acts \nagainst an outnumbered enemy, his \nOpposition Level is increased by 1.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":3,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Easy 3","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":3}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557622641,"modifiedTime":1781557622641,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"zS1jWu2uamVNfp9k","name":"The swamp where the fairies have","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/cowled.svg","items":[{"_id":"1NJb2BJ9qoIClw6c","name":"The swamp where the fairies have - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>A marshy swamp with a stone \ntrack as its only path.\nThe water is black, cold, and deep enough to slow a \nHunter who falls into it.\nNote: During this Scene, the Hunters may encounter \nSkutt.\n ◆ The Fairies are corrupted by the splendor of the crown \nand will not allow anyone to touch it. It is possible to \ncommunicate with them by interrupting their dance. \nThe Fairies will tell the story of a human princess who \ngifted them with the crown, as bright as a small sun, \nin order to cross the swamp. It is difficult to maintain \na conversation with dreamlike entities, and in a short \ntime they will slip back into their dreams and start \ndancing again.\n ◆ If the Hunters attempt to take the crown, the Fairies \nwill awaken from their trance. Screaming in pain, they \nwill attack the culprits without hesitation. Around the \ncrown there are always twelve fairies.\n ◆ Somehow blocking the light emanating from the \ncrown will awaken the Fairies from the spell. They will \nlook at the cracked moon, screaming in agony as they \nrealize how much the lands around \nthem have been corrupted. Some will \nsuffer so much that they will become \ndew in the grass or a pale reflection in \nthe pond. Others will ask the Hunters \nto do something to save their lands.\nFairies</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 189.","positive":"A marshy swamp with a stone \ntrack as its only path.\nThe water is black, cold, and deep enough to slow a \nHunter who falls into it.\nNote: During this Scene, the Hunters may encounter \nSkutt.\n ◆ The Fairies are corrupted by the splendor of the crown \nand will not allow anyone to touch it. It is possible to \ncommunicate with them by interrupting their dance. \nThe Fairies will tell the story of a human princess who \ngifted them with the crown, as bright as a small sun, \nin order to cross the swamp. It is difficult to maintain \na conversation with dreamlike entities, and in a short \ntime they will slip back into their dreams and start \ndancing again.\n ◆ If the Hunters attempt to take the crown, the Fairies \nwill awaken from their trance. Screaming in pain, they \nwill attack the culprits without hesitation. Around the \ncrown there are always twelve fairies.\n ◆ Somehow blocking the light emanating from the \ncrown will awaken the Fairies from the spell. They will \nlook at the cracked moon, screaming in agony as they \nrealize how much the lands around \nthem have been corrupted. Some will \nsuffer so much that they will become \ndew in the grass or a pale reflection in \nthe pond. Others will ask the Hunters \nto do something to save their lands.\nFairies","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Bnjm7M4kzqtQTlmV","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Descriptor: A marshy swamp with a stone \ntrack as its only path.\nThe water is black, cold, and deep enough to slow a \nHunter who falls into it.\nNote: During this Scene, the Hunters may encounter \nSkutt.\n ◆ The Fairies are corrupted by the splendor of the crown \nand will not allow anyone to touch it. It is possible to \ncommunicate with them by interrupting their dance. \nThe Fairies will tell the story of a human princess who \ngifted them with the crown, as bright as a small sun, \nin order to cross the swamp. It is difficult to maintain \na conversation with dreamlike entities, and in a short \ntime they will slip back into their dreams and start \ndancing again.\n ◆ If the Hunters attempt to take the crown, the Fairies \nwill awaken from their trance. Screaming in pain, they \nwill attack the culprits without hesitation. Around the \ncrown there are always twelve fairies.\n ◆ Somehow blocking the light emanating from the \ncrown will awaken the Fairies from the spell. They will \nlook at the cracked moon, screaming in agony as they \nrealize how much the lands around \nthem have been corrupted. Some will \nsuffer so much that they will become \ndew in the grass or a pale reflection in \nthe pond. Others will ask the Hunters \nto do something to save their lands.\nFairies</p>","notes":"Tuvstarr's Reflection - bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, page 189."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"core-book-tuvstarrs-reflection-the-swamp-where-the-fairies-have-189","collection":"Core Book","adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","adventureTitle":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","page":189,"role":"Threat"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","origin":"Core Book","role":"Threat","notes":"<p>Descriptor: A marshy swamp with a stone \ntrack as its only path.\nThe water is black, cold, and deep enough to slow a \nHunter who falls into it.\nNote: During this Scene, the Hunters may encounter \nSkutt.\n ◆ The Fairies are corrupted by the splendor of the crown \nand will not allow anyone to touch it. It is possible to \ncommunicate with them by interrupting their dance. \nThe Fairies will tell the story of a human princess who \ngifted them with the crown, as bright as a small sun, \nin order to cross the swamp. It is difficult to maintain \na conversation with dreamlike entities, and in a short \ntime they will slip back into their dreams and start \ndancing again.\n ◆ If the Hunters attempt to take the crown, the Fairies \nwill awaken from their trance. Screaming in pain, they \nwill attack the culprits without hesitation. Around the \ncrown there are always twelve fairies.\n ◆ Somehow blocking the light emanating from the \ncrown will awaken the Fairies from the spell. They will \nlook at the cracked moon, screaming in agony as they \nrealize how much the lands around \nthem have been corrupted. Some will \nsuffer so much that they will become \ndew in the grass or a pale reflection in \nthe pond. Others will ask the Hunters \nto do something to save their lands.\nFairies</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557623373,"modifiedTime":1781557623373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"zb47g8daygvAoOYo","name":"Djinn of the Dream Gate","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"8HHgHO6oubrdWQSZ","name":"Djinn of the Dream Gate - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a powerful Djinn, my body is pure magic \nand my strength transcends that of wretched humans. I pay \nrespect to those who show purity of spirit and courage.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 167.","positive":"I am a powerful Djinn, my body is pure magic \nand my strength transcends that of wretched humans. I pay \nrespect to those who show purity of spirit and courage.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642827,"modifiedTime":1781557642827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xnNDKYb2d5s03vkq","name":"Gift - Duty","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Each Djinn is immune to any effect of mind \ncontrol, deception, or magic that would influence them to \nrelinquish their duty.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 167.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642827,"modifiedTime":1781557642827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KVYdcTM7pSYjBkZP","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC \n(3 Wounds - the Guardian and the Servant) \n(1 Wound - All other Djinn) \n(1 Djinn for each undelivered Tarì)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful Djinn, my body is pure magic \nand my strength transcends that of wretched humans. I pay \nrespect to those who show purity of spirit and courage. \nGift - Duty: Each Djinn is immune to any effect of mind \ncontrol, deception, or magic that would influence them to \nrelinquish their duty.\nGift - Power of the Djinn: Each Djinn has a different \npower:\nFirst - The Guardian: If the Djinn receives 1 Wound, \nroll a die; on a roll of 5 or 6, the person who inflicted the \nWound receives 1 in turn. \nSecond - The Warrior: Once per Scene, even if a Defense Check to avoid a Djinn attack succeeds, the target still \nsuffers 1 Wound.\nThird - The Mage: If an enemy uses a magic-related Gift \nin the presence of the Djinn, they must spend 1 Soma or see \ntheir spell dissolve without effect.\nFourth - The Servant: If a Djinn takes 1 Wound, it can \ntransfer it to the Servant who takes it instead.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 167."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642827,"modifiedTime":1781557642827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-djinn-of-the-dream-gate-167","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":167,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC \n(3 Wounds - the Guardian and the Servant) \n(1 Wound - All other Djinn) \n(1 Djinn for each undelivered Tarì)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful Djinn, my body is pure magic \nand my strength transcends that of wretched humans. I pay \nrespect to those who show purity of spirit and courage. \nGift - Duty: Each Djinn is immune to any effect of mind \ncontrol, deception, or magic that would influence them to \nrelinquish their duty.\nGift - Power of the Djinn: Each Djinn has a different \npower:\nFirst - The Guardian: If the Djinn receives 1 Wound, \nroll a die; on a roll of 5 or 6, the person who inflicted the \nWound receives 1 in turn. \nSecond - The Warrior: Once per Scene, even if a Defense Check to avoid a Djinn attack succeeds, the target still \nsuffers 1 Wound.\nThird - The Mage: If an enemy uses a magic-related Gift \nin the presence of the Djinn, they must spend 1 Soma or see \ntheir spell dissolve without effect.\nFourth - The Servant: If a Djinn takes 1 Wound, it can \ntransfer it to the Servant who takes it instead.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642827,"modifiedTime":1781557642827,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"zbiXkgU65H5k2dlS","name":"Jasmina the Brave","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"PhGOs1F3SbGgLTOj","name":"Jasmina the Brave - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am the true ruler of the island and would \ngive my life for my people. I am charismatic and skilled with \na scimitar.</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 160.","positive":"I am the true ruler of the island and would \ngive my life for my people. I am charismatic and skilled with \na scimitar.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642505,"modifiedTime":1781557642505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"p37vRmvbwMgP7fUs","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the true ruler of the island and would \ngive my life for my people. I am charismatic and skilled with \na scimitar. \nAgenda: Defeat Aladdin and restore the island’s fortunes. \nMonsters Summoned by Aladdin</p>","notes":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 160."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642505,"modifiedTime":1781557642505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-jasmina-the-brave-160","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","adventureTitle":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":160,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>- Minor NPC (1 Wound)\nDescriptor: I am the true ruler of the island and would \ngive my life for my people. I am charismatic and skilled with \na scimitar. \nAgenda: Defeat Aladdin and restore the island’s fortunes. \nMonsters Summoned by Aladdin</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":1},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Defeat Aladdin and restore the island’s fortunes. \nMonsters Summoned by Aladdin","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557642505,"modifiedTime":1781557642505,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"zdfOXbmT8p4Femcw","name":"The Prince","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"g7qnLrczUCVHVcSO","name":"The Prince - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a Golem of blood \nand flesh. There is only hatred in my \nbroken heart.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 172.","positive":"I am a Golem of blood \nand flesh. There is only hatred in my \nbroken heart.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637842,"modifiedTime":1781557637842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KeYGTGNdtjOLEUv9","name":"Gift - Broken Heart","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Once per Scene, the Prince can \nemit a freezing scream of pain that affects all living beings \nin the area, causing 1 Penalty to any action against him.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 172.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637842,"modifiedTime":1781557637842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"op3EcTxHv05yMVMf","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a Golem of blood \nand flesh. There is only hatred in my \nbroken heart. \nAgenda: Killing and tearing apart the ungrateful \npeople of Prague / I prefer to take my revenge on the \nrich and powerful above all others. \nGift – Broken Heart: Once per Scene, the Prince can \nemit a freezing scream of pain that affects all living beings \nin the area, causing 1 Penalty to any action against him. \nGift – Tornado of Blades: The Prince’s body is \ncomposed of arms, legs, and heads held together by a \nmetal structure. Any limb that can hold a blade \ndoes. The Prince can start spinning, hitting \neach opponent on his way in a single \nattack, inflicting 1 Wound on anyone \nwho fails a Defense Check.</p>","notes":"I Will Stay with You Always - bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, page 172."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637842,"modifiedTime":1781557637842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"the-broken-ones-i-will-stay-with-you-always-the-prince-172","collection":"The Broken Ones","adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","adventureTitle":"I Will Stay with You Always","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","page":172,"role":"Minor NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"I Will Stay with You Always","origin":"The Broken Ones","role":"Minor NPC","notes":"<p>– Minor NPC \n(6 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a Golem of blood \nand flesh. There is only hatred in my \nbroken heart. \nAgenda: Killing and tearing apart the ungrateful \npeople of Prague / I prefer to take my revenge on the \nrich and powerful above all others. \nGift – Broken Heart: Once per Scene, the Prince can \nemit a freezing scream of pain that affects all living beings \nin the area, causing 1 Penalty to any action against him. \nGift – Tornado of Blades: The Prince’s body is \ncomposed of arms, legs, and heads held together by a \nmetal structure. Any limb that can hold a blade \ndoes. The Prince can start spinning, hitting \neach opponent on his way in a single \nattack, inflicting 1 Wound on anyone \nwho fails a Defense Check.</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":6},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Killing and tearing apart the ungrateful \npeople of Prague / I prefer to take my revenge on the \nrich and powerful above all others.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557637842,"modifiedTime":1781557637842,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"zz0bzgwmQMIPNTHb","name":"Percival the Seeker","type":"threat","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","items":[{"_id":"SEcJ8wBRqBlfOofZ","name":"Percival the Seeker - Descriptor","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>I am a disgraced knight. My body is immortal, \nbut my mind has lost bits of memory over the centuries.</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 187.","positive":"I am a disgraced knight. My body is immortal, \nbut my mind has lost bits of memory over the centuries.","negative":"","exhausted":false,"xpMarked":false,"specialization":false,"sceneUsed":false},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644040,"modifiedTime":1781557644040,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0585e3LaedRvTTXO","name":"Gift - Virtue of Faith","type":"gift","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>Imbued with the power of the Virtue of Faith, Percival cannot be killed. When he reaches 0 \nWounds, he will fall into a state of apparent death and will \nawake at the end of the Scene fully healed. Percival’s Virtue \ncannot be granted because it is inside the Grail chalice that \nthe Knight remembers throwing between the rocks and \nshoals in Zone 12 - Cliff (page 197).</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 187.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644041,"modifiedTime":1781557644041,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"QSmt1q1vtZzMovEs","name":"Source Text","type":"storyElement","img":"icons/svg/scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{},"system":{"description":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a disgraced knight. My body is immortal, \nbut my mind has lost bits of memory over the centuries. \nAgenda: Remember why I am on this strange island. \nGift - Virtue of Faith: Imbued with the power of the Virtue of Faith, Percival cannot be killed. When he reaches 0 \nWounds, he will fall into a state of apparent death and will \nawake at the end of the Scene fully healed. Percival’s Virtue \ncannot be granted because it is inside the Grail chalice that \nthe Knight remembers throwing between the rocks and \nshoals in Zone 12 - Cliff (page 197).\nInformation: Percival only remembers things when he \nis in his little house on the Cliff: he cycles back to Camelot, \nbut on the way he loses his memory and remembers only \nthe place he left from. Upon his return, Percival remembers \nhis mission and the cycle begins again.\n \nThe Map of Camelot\nZone 1 - Landing Zone 2 - Beach Zone 3 - Glatisant's \nLair \nZone 4 - Village of \nCorrinton\nZone 5 -Merlin’s \nTower\nZone 6 - Forest Zone 7 - Battlefield Zone 8 - Camelot \nCastle Zone 9 - Fairy Falls Zone 10 - Circle of \nStones\nZone 11 - Town of \nStow Zone 12 - Cliff Zone 13 - Lake Zone 14 - Abandoned House\nZone 15 - Secret \nLanding</p>","notes":"The King's Awakening - bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, page 187."},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644041,"modifiedTime":1781557644041,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"scenarioActorSlug":"lost-stories-the-kings-awakening-percival-the-seeker-187","collection":"Lost Stories","adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","adventureTitle":"The King's Awakening","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","page":187,"role":"Main NPC"}},"system":{"details":{"concept":"The King's Awakening","origin":"Lost Stories","role":"Main NPC","notes":"<p>- Main NPC (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a disgraced knight. My body is immortal, \nbut my mind has lost bits of memory over the centuries. \nAgenda: Remember why I am on this strange island. \nGift - Virtue of Faith: Imbued with the power of the Virtue of Faith, Percival cannot be killed. When he reaches 0 \nWounds, he will fall into a state of apparent death and will \nawake at the end of the Scene fully healed. Percival’s Virtue \ncannot be granted because it is inside the Grail chalice that \nthe Knight remembers throwing between the rocks and \nshoals in Zone 12 - Cliff (page 197).\nInformation: Percival only remembers things when he \nis in his little house on the Cliff: he cycles back to Camelot, \nbut on the way he loses his memory and remembers only \nthe place he left from. Upon his return, Percival remembers \nhis mission and the cycle begins again.\n \nThe Map of Camelot\nZone 1 - Landing Zone 2 - Beach Zone 3 - Glatisant's \nLair \nZone 4 - Village of \nCorrinton\nZone 5 -Merlin’s \nTower\nZone 6 - Forest Zone 7 - Battlefield Zone 8 - Camelot \nCastle Zone 9 - Fairy Falls Zone 10 - Circle of \nStones\nZone 11 - Town of \nStow Zone 12 - Cliff Zone 13 - Lake Zone 14 - Abandoned House\nZone 15 - Secret \nLanding</p>"},"resources":{"soma":{"value":0,"max":0},"xp":0,"wounds":{"value":0,"max":3},"darkness":{"value":0,"max":6}},"opposition":{"defaultLevel":5,"modifier":0},"bookmark":{"wound1":"","wound2":"","wound3":"","extraWound":""},"threat":{"rank":"Medium 5","impulse":"Remember why I am on this strange island.","oppositionLevel":5}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781557644041,"modifiedTime":1781557644041,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
